caption:
Why I love my muscles 🫶

What you see:
✅ A girl who loves exercise - possibly even obsessed 
✅ A person who is motivated
✅ A physically strong female
✅ Someone who eats really well
✅ Not a big partier 
✅ Has time to train 6 times a week

What I see:
✅ A rock solid mindset 
✅ Someone who is disciplined 
✅ A physically and mentally strong female
✅ Someone who nourishes and fuels her body
✅ The most extrovert, social butterfly you’ll ever meet - but doesn’t prioritise partying
✅ Commits to training 6 times a week

Mindset - one of the most important elements to any health and fitness journey. Perspective changes based on the person - we all know the glass half empty/half full example.

If you’re eating well and doing physical exercise but not prioritising your mental exercise - I can promise you what you’re doing is not sustainable in the long term! 

Work on your mindset and the game changes…

caption:
𝐂𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐞
Creatine is one of the most vastly researched supplements and has been promoted in the fitness industry in the last few years. According to research, supplementation with creatine monohydrate has been shown to increase Skeletal muscle mass, lean body mass and muscle fibre size. Research also suggests past this and it may encourage healthy aging and benefit brain health. 

𝐃𝐨 𝐈 𝐧𝐞𝐞𝐝 𝐂𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐞?
Creatine supplementation can be hugely beneficial for athletic performance and studies have also showed it can have an impact on body composition (prolonged creatine ingestion inducing an increase in fat free mass). 

𝐃𝐨 𝐈 𝐧𝐞𝐞𝐝 𝐭𝐨 𝐥𝐨𝐚𝐝 𝐂𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐞?
Nope. 5g daily will suffice. (The idea to saturate the muscle is just to experience benefits sooner).
Increase water consumption when you start taking creatine.

𝐖𝐡𝐞𝐧 𝐬𝐡𝐨𝐮𝐥𝐝 𝐈 𝐭𝐚𝐤𝐞 𝐢𝐭?
Evidence does suggest post workout is superior to pre workout. 

𝐀𝐫𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐞 𝐚𝐧𝐲 𝐬𝐢𝐝𝐞 𝐞𝐟𝐟𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐬?
- Bloating - This is due to the muscles absorbing the water with the Creatine. Very common and usually subsides when the muscles are saturated.
- Stomach discomfort - May cause stomach sensitivity like bloating.

#creatine #supplements #nutritioncoach #realnutrition #realresults #fitness #fitliving #strengthtraining

7 things I wish I knew in my early 20s. I dont want you to make the same mistakes I made.

1. Being consistently good is better than being occasionally perfect.

2. The weekend makes up a large part of the week. If you think you’re being good during the week and not making progress - take a look at your weekends.

3. Sleep is one of the most underestimated tools to help you achieve ANY goal. If you’re sleep is shit and you’re sacrificing it ‘to seize the morning’ and train at 6am - you may be doing more harm than good.

4. Water consumption is the simplest way to becoming a healthier version of yourself. Stop looking at fad diets, detox teas, apple cider vinegar and look at your hydration status. Dehydration affects every system in our body and can lead to lack of energy, low mood, injury and brain fog (to mention afew).

5. Human connection, vitamin D and exercise are some of the most under utilised mental health prescriptions. Try increase all of these on the daily to see an instant mood shift 🙏

6. Stop trying to be a people pleaser and learn to say no - you are your own most important asset. 

7. Live every day like it’s your last ❤️ Do what makes you happy! 

Would you add anything to the list?

caption:
Wanna know the key to a high metabolism? 

Would you be shocked to know it’s NOT a supplement? Or a food?

It’s actually an accumulatory effect of the decisions you make on a day to day basis 🙏

I’ve actually done a Free Webinar on this topic. Comment ‘me’ below if you’d like a copy ⬇️⬇️⬇️

People make fat loss complicated. I’m not saying for a second it’s easy. But it is so much more simple than we make it 🫣🙊

👉 Instead of spending hours watching the ‘calories you’re burning’ why not swap for getting stronger instead 💪

👉 Instead of a meal plan why not become totally equipped to make better food choices for yourself

👉 Instead of trying to ‘eat clean’ why not find an 80/20 balance and count calories 

👉 Instead of trying to exercise more - sleep more

👉Instead of trying to use detox teas, shakes and ACV - drink more water 

❌And stop being so impatient and inconsistent. 

I’m a big believer in being inclusive rather than exclusive - add things in to your life like water, sleep, movement and vegetables rather than always looking for things to exclude 🙌🙏

If you’re looking for a lifestyle change - Dm me ‘Lifestyle’

caption:
We’re almost 2 weeks into January 😱

How are your New Years Resolutions coming along? 

Are you struggling? 

Is it sustainable? 

My clients are thriving 🙌

Why? 
 - Because I make it easy for them ✅

But how?
- Well instead of giving them 7 million tasks in week one. I have a much slower, more sustainable approach! I use healthy habits to help them adjust to a long term lifestyle change. 

❌It’s not pretty. 
❌It’s not fancy. 
❌It doesn’t sell well.

✅ But it works. You see if you commit to the long term, you can do it slower. If you’re only commiting to 6 weeks - you have to change immediately. But we all know nothing changes that quick. Nothing sustainable anyway. It takes time. It takes effort. But we’re here for the long term so who’s rushing? 🤷‍♀️

✅ My ethos is you only have ONE BODY - ONE PLACE to call home! You need to look after it. You need to mind and care for it. 

- If your house was falling apart around you or your car was dangerous to drive you’d pay any amount to fix it. How come when it comes to our body - OUR HOME - an investment is too expensive or not worth it? 🤔

Anyway - I’ll be over here sipping the odd Margarita educating my clients on the importance of overall health and balance…. While you do YET ANOTHER 6 week challenge 🫣 (oops did I just say that)

Training on holidays ☀️

Yay or Nay? 🧐

I put up a poll on my Instagram before Christmas to see who would be training over the holidays and 90% of you said you would. 

Sometimes, we have really high expectations of ourselves that when we don’t meet those expectations - we become disappointed 😔 While having high expectations is not necessarily a bad thing, being realistic is important 🙏

Going on holidays this Christmas I recognised that training was not going to be a priority to me. I said I’d train 2-3 times a week because I love it - not because I HAD to. 

There is NO NECESSITY for you to train during holidays. If you want to - do it! If you don’t - don’t! One thing I will say is 1. Do it for the right reasons - maybe that’s to get back into a routine, or for your mental health - but NOT to ‘burn off calories’

2. Whatever decision you make - own it! Don’t go winging and complaining after 3 weeks off that ‘you wish you did a bit’ or ‘how sore you are’. Get over it and get on with it.

Ok, thanks for listening to my ted talk - I’m off to the gym 👋

caption:
Struggle with protein 🧐

Here’s my TOP TIP - Build your meals around the protein source🙃

My first thought at any meal is what is the protein? And then I build my meal from there! 

People will blame time for their poor food choices but I can assure you, you don’t have to be super organised to make better choices! (The last 2 days I’ve been eating Turkey burgers, microwave rice and microwave cauliflower rice)

When I go shopping I like to have a rough guide done of what I’ll eat during the week so all the options are in my house - that way I’ve no excuses to eat out or make poor food choices! And if you do eat out, there’s NUMEROUS options to align with your goals!

So I don’t want to hear any more excuses 😛 Hitting protein targets has never been easier 🙏

caption:
I think my CrossFit journey has been a little like your weight loss journey and here’s why 👂

I was asked to do my first CrossFit competition late 2018.

I first started to dabble in Crossfit in 2019. 

I would just do random workouts with random exercises and to be fair - it was enough to win competitions at a scaled level.

In 2020, I joined a CrossFit gym and this is where I say my journey began.

I can honestly say the most progress I’ve made was in the last 6 months of 2022. 

Let me tell you why? 

I started a programme that was tailored to my goals. A structured progressive overload programme that was in accordance with my goals.

Ok let me relate this back to your weight loss journey. 

My first year of CrossFit I was essentially pissing in the wind. Random workouts with no structure. But I still made progress. Does that relate to the start of your journey? You were doing it alone but you still lost weight because you made some small changes?

The next year and a half - I programme hopped - I think I did 3 different programmes in the space of 1.5 years with none of them aligning with my goals. Although the process of programme hopping in itself is the problem - not sticking with something long enough to see the results 🫣

The last 6 months I feel like Goldilocks, I’ve got it just right. This programme is geared towards my goals. It allows for progression and I’ve reaped the rewards!

You see this could be you. 

Maybe you’ve had the same journey as me?

Maybe you’ve tried it alone?

You’ve tried many diets or coaches or programmes that didn’t work?

But take it from me - when you find the right one - you’ll never look back 💪

caption:
There are a few circumstances where people ‘don’t have time’ but more often than not - It’s just not a priority! 

Health and fitness should not be difficult. It should be something that fits into your lifestyle and not something you have to force. But we over complicate it. 

Some of the things you DON’T need to do to become healthier, fitter and happier:

❌ Cut out carbs
❌Cut out sugar
❌ Exercise 7 days a week 
❌ Drink detox juices/teas
❌ Eat 1000 Calories or less 
❌ Train twice a day
❌ Train longer than an hour in the gym

I can promise you - I can make health and fitness part of your lifestyle. I will offer a money back guarantee I’m so sure of myself 💪🙌 DM me ‘PRIORITY’ if you’re ready to make health and fitness a priority 🥰

Keep it super simple 💯

✅ Drink 2L Water

✅ Get back to sleep routine 

✅ Prioritise protein and colour 

✅ Move your body 

DO NOT:

❌Cut calories like crazy 

❌ Give into ‘detoxs’

❌ Start a fad diet 

❌ Sign up to a quick fix 

Make 2023 the year your prioritise yourself ♥️ Your body will thank you for it 🙏

caption:
How was my Christmas? 🎄

In one word - ‘Perfect’ ♥️

I caught up with old friends. Spent quality time with family. Ate loads and drank more than usual 💃 

It was a great Christmas and it reminded me of how far I’ve come with regards my feelings towards my body and my mind 🙏 

✅Gone be the days of guilt associated with over indulging.

✅Gone be the days of feeling guilty for exercising less

✅ Gone be the days of exercising to ‘burn off’ calories

And what will I do this week? 
I will get back into normality and routine! No crazy restricting food or extra cardio! I’ll get back to extra movement, no alcohol and lots of protein and fibre 🥰

If you have any sense - you’ll do the same! Don’t give into dads! You don’t need to ‘detox’. You don’t need to ‘burn off’ extra calories. Just simply get back to:
✅ Movement 
✅ Protein, colour & fibre
✅ Water
✅ Sleep

caption:
Yesterday I told you about time being a problem for women trying to change their body shape. They feel they can't give full commitment to a programme because they are too busy. 

They feel they have no time to go to the gym because they are too busy. Or they don’t have time to be making seperate dinners for their family.

Thankfully a lot of my clients train from home 3 times a week with minimal equipment. And I NEVER ask them to make seperate dinners.

You see the thing is - you don't actually need hours in the gym to achieve your goals - especially if you're crazy busy. I also encourage women to make better, more simple choices if they are too busy to cook. And instead of scrolling on Social media - I set step targets for them (even if they scroll while they walk). 

You see - it's pretty simple. Try this out and let me know how it goes. 

P.s I'm looking for 5 more women who want to drop body fat and become their most confident selves. If that's you, DM me the word 'ME'

I’d say it’s a bit obvious my highlight of 2022 🥰

Here’s to making me laugh for many more years ♥️

Another common problem I see most women have when they are trying to change their body shape is time to commit to a programme. 

We all lead such busy lifestyles these days. We give time to our families, our friends, and work and we are left with little to no time. 

It's so frustrating because you're trying to be a good friend, mother, daughter, sister, colleague, or employee. But what's left for you? Or maybe there is time? 

I've found that most people usually can find time. Maybe instead of an hour of Netflix we could swap it for a workout? Maybe instead of scrolling we could be walking? Or instead of picking up a takeaway on the way home from work, we could pick up a ready meal in a supermarket? The problem lies in trying to do too much.

Are you interested in learning about how you could commit to a programme even WITH limited time? 

Comment 'me' below and I'll tag you tomorrow when it's up.

Hey there aspiring fit, strong, confident lady...

Yep I'm talking to you....

How many times have you stopped and started your health and fitness journey?

How many times have you got bored and quit?

How many times have you tried your hardest but not seen the results you've worked for?

Listen I get it. I've been there too. It's so frustrating when you've been putting in all this effort to no avail.

Thankfully for you I have the solution - my Strong and Sassy programme starts next month and I'm opening up 4 spots 🎉

If you're looking to:
- See incredible results internally and externally 
- Feel the fittest and strongest you've ever felt
- Rock a bikini or feel good in your favourite dress

Then THIS is the programme for you. 

If you're finally ready to stop with fad diets and find a lifestyle that works for you - Dm me 'READY' today ❤️

This isn’t your typical transformation post ❌❌❌

To be totally honest, I love both pictures. I’m proud of my body in both pictures. 🙏 

These pictures respresent 2 points in time. The one on the left I was socialising a lot more while the one on the right was sacrificing a lot more. 

Both pictures, I trained. Both pictures I ate well and slept lots. 

The two main differences are: 
1. A lot more structured training programme 
2. A lot less social events 

Some times I’ll be leaner. Other times I’ll retain a little more water. But honestly, I don’t train for aesthetics - I train and eat well for how my body feels. When I train hard and eat nutritiously - my body is energised and thanks me 🙏 i want every woman to feel good no matter what they’re body fat percentage or scale weight shows ❤️

And that's why I created my Strong and Sassy Programme to help women become bikini confident year round without restrictions. Comment 'CHANGE' below if you'd like for me to personally message you today and see if I can help you!

Yesterday, I mentioned a common problem i see in women trying to drop body fat.

Women lack education and understanding around nutrition which causes serial yo yo dieting. 

To fix this problem, you need more nutrition education on how you can eat the foods you love and still get the results you deserve. 

Here's how it works: 

As a qualified nutritionist, I educate females on how to make good food choices to achieve their goals. I don't focus on short term quick fixes but long term sustainable results. I genuinely believe if you hand someone a diet plan you will only help them so far,  but if you educate them on a balanced lifestyle - this is invaluable. 

P.s I'm looking for 5 MORE females who want to be bikini confident in the next 12 weeks. If that's you DM me 'HELP'.

A huge issue I see amongst women is their lack of knowledge and understanding of nutrition. They have no clue what to do to achieve that body confidence they desire 😢 

Are you constantly fad dieting because you're afraid if you're not dieting you will gain weight. You're afraid that if you don't stick to that deficit you'll never be happy in your clothes. 

I feel terrible for you, because you're genuinely trying. You know no different. We've grown up with fad dieting, our mothers  yo yo dieted. It's all we've known - we only know strict calorie deficits and exercise to burn calories 😢 

But I've found the solution to your problems. I believe in education. Have you ever heard the saying “If you give a man a fish, you feed him for a day. If you teach a man to fish, you feed him for a lifetime.” I want you to understand you CAN ACHIEVE results and ENJOY the food you love 😍 

Are you interested in learning more about nutrition? Do you want to drop body fat while enjoying a balanced diet? I'm going to explain all tomorrow. 

Comment ME below and I'll tag you tomorrow when its up!

I'm looking for 4 fabulous females who want to drop body fat and be bikini confident year round without restriction in the next 12 weeks. 

Take a look at how some of my Strong and Sassy females did: 

- Simone’s (working mum) habits are now as engrained as brushing her teeth

- Aine came to me in preparation for her wedding day 😍

- Teresa (busy professional) is the fittest and strongest she’s ever been.

I'm looking for a few specific things from my ladies. So if you: 

- Are committed to finally changing your habits.
- Are able to train 3 times a week
- Consider yourself to be coachable
- And are ready to get pushed out of your comfort zone. 

Then just comment below with the words 'I'M IN' and I'll be choosing people today. 

(Check your DMs and/or message requests regularly 😁 If you don't want to miss a message from me)

caption:
Dust off the cobwebs and come work out with me after Christmas for this fun charity event in @fullbodyworkhouse on 7th January at 10am. 

All levels welcome and all proceeds will go to The Craig Connolly Memorial Fund! 

If you’re interested in attending please contact myself or @fullbodyworkhouse so we have an idea of numbers 🙏💪

This January the Strong and Sassy Programme is going to be better and more educational than EVER!!!! 

Did you know along with nutrition and accountability calls every week, nutrition guidelines, and calories calculated for you - the training programmes are all tailored to you.

That means if you train from home with limited equipment, if you have an injury, if you play sport, if you’re a beginner or if you’re a seasoned gym goer - I adapt the programme to you! I’m going to be using my Strong and Sassy programme while I’m at home (here’s some of the movements I did last week)

If you’re sick of cookie cutter programmes or asking for changes because youve injuries or adaptations. 
Dm me ‘SAS’.

Life Update:

November was hectic (my Dad's Anniversary and Birthday, moving house, sorting visas and multiple competitions). It was a bit of a whirlwind. 

I'm looking forward to spending Christmas with friends and family at home ❤🙏 I'm very lucky that work doesn't much feel like work and although I will have some downtime I will be working most of Christmas 🧑‍🎄 

This is my first time home in 3 years, It's definitely different to Christmas in Austrailia, I’ll have a lot more clothes on this Christmas Day 😅 

This year - I’ll be focusing on my little black dress rather than a bikini. Some of my clients are already sending me pictures of their Christmas clothes and are excited to be buying them in sizes smaller or tighter fit 🙏🙌

Anyway I'm going to keep this short as I spend quality time with my family💃 If you're interested in feeling amazing in your clothes as my clients.  DM me 👗

3 years later and it literally feels like yesterday we were home ♥️🙏

Feeling very grateful 🥹♥️

Now onto the next leg. See you soon Midlands 🙏

caption:
‘Ah you’re so lucky you can work your own hours’

Let me tell you as with EVERYTHING in life - there are pros and cons to everything. 

What I am doing now is LITERALLY my dream job ❤️🔥 And I wouldn’t change it for the world. But nothing good in life comes without sacrifice.

While most people take a trip home and enjoy a month off. I will be working. (I’ll take the holidays off) But my job doesn’t stop ✋ 

Goals require sacrifice. Achievements require sacrifice. Nothing is handed to anyone.

The same goes for fat loss or weight loss.

Effort determines the result! 

So next time you think - someone is ‘so lucky’ - think of what they did to achieve that. No matter what area of life - jobs, fitness, weight loss, relationships - I can assure you - that person has sacrificed something somewhere 🔥

caption:
Christmas is well and truely on its way. While this is an exciting time and a time where people are socialising more and enjoying themselves more. I’ve actually found it can be a hugely anxious time for people too.🥹

I’ve witnessed women who are hugely self conscious and unhappy in their body struggle to pick an outfit for a Christmas dinner.

I’ve seen women change about 10 times before throwing on the baggiest option they can find.

Up until this year - that was Teresa. Teresa hid behind bigger clothes in an effort to feel better.

I remember once upon a time - myself - holding onto clothes ‘that would fit again’.

Ladies this has to stop 🛑 

I am telling you now - it’s not about weight loss. It’s not about a clothes size. It’s not about number on the weighing scales.

It’s about feeling good internally.

It’s about having a balanced lifestyle. Nourishing your body but never feeling guilty about food. It’s about exercising because you enjoy it. Not using it as punishment. ❌

Until you can find that internal happiness - it doesn’t matter what diet you’re doing, what calories you’re eating, what exercise you’re doing - you won’t be comfortable and confident.

But the good news is - I have the solution🙋‍♀️

My Strong and Sassy programme was designed specifically to help women become the healthiest, happiest and most confident versions of themselves.

If you want to become like Sarah - who is now ROCKING tight, figure hugging clothes. Or Jennifer who is wearing bikinis and crop tops. Dm me ‘Sas’
Out on a Sunday 🥂

caption:
Nutrition and Training Workshop 💪

My ethos is to help women become the strongest, healthiest most confident versions of themselves WITHOUT restricting the foods you love and enjoy ❤️

What better time to sign up to a seminar than early January. Take this as you’re sign that 2024 is going to be the year where achieve the biggest and brightest goals ⭐️

Location: Fullbody Workhouse Roscommon

Date: Saturday 7th January 

Cost: €99 (including lunch)

What to expect:
- An educated filled day 
- A more thorough understanding of recovery
- Learn compound movements 
- Enjoy a sweaty metcon 
- All with a like minded community 

Please let me know if you’d like to attend and I’ll send you over the payment link!

10 minutes to prepare and cook ✅

Serving serves 3-4 portions.

High protein and nutritious ✅

#healthyrecipes #highprotein #quickandeasy #simplerecipes #onlinecoach #nutritionist

Mission accomplished ✅🎉

To say I’m proud would be an understatement here and be prepared for a long post 😂

Going into my first individual event my expectations were to keep within the Top 6. So winning this event was truely special 🥰

With 3 event wins, I can honestly say my proudest moment was 3rd in the last event 😂 I went to one of the darkest places I’ve ever been in my training and I would not have got through it without my ultimate cheer squad @lillie704 @lift__with__laura @misssophieelizabeth @col_ryaner @renners9 @o_boyce 

I feel so thankful and grateful to be ABLE to push my body to these limits and how fun is it doing it with the best crew. Even more special was podiuming with @brian_fannon 🙌🙏

As always with every competition, there’s things to learn and FUCK these girls are STRONG 💪 So there’s still lots to be done 🙏

Thank you to @battleofbenton for an incredible event. Ran impeccably from start to finish. 

And the biggest thank you to @jaydenazza @crossfitbotany who had me in this condition going into this competition. The future is looking bright 💃

That’s it for the competitions for 2022 (never again will I do 3 in a row 😂). Social Amanda is ready to go 💃🥂

I have never ever done a deal on my coaching so I’m so excited to give you the opportunity to work with me at a discounted rate 💃

If you’re looking to:
✨ Become the healthiest, happiest, most confident version of yourself

✨ Be the strongest, fittest you’ve ever been

✨ Be educated on nutrition to a level you’ve never understood before

✨ Gain a new lifestyle - not a short term quick fix 

✨ Improve your daily habits 

✨ Lose weight 

✨ Be part of a global female community 

If you’ve answered yes to any or all of the above.

My coaching is for you. 

And my yearly subscription is 50% OFF!!!!!!
My 6 month package is 33% OFF!!!!!

Offer Ends Midnight Monday! 

Dm me ‘Black Friday’ to hear more 👂

Does age affect weight loss? Yes.

Does that mean you shouldn’t try? Absolutely not!

Hear me out 👂

Travel is not easy. You’ve to travel to an airport. Have a passport to board. Pack all your clothes and items you’ll need. Board a plane. Travel hours depending on where you go. Set up in another part of the world. Find new places and set yourself up.

But you don’t NOT do it. It has a few requirements and pre requisites but if you want it - you’ll tick all of the boxes. 

Age is like the distance to the destination. Some flights take longer, some countries are further away. But that DOES not mean we can’t make it to our destination! 

What makes the journey easier? 
- Nutrition Habits that create long term sustainable change - rather than quick fix 6 week challenges (comparing a first class Quantas flight to a RyanAir flight here incase you missed it)
- Resistance based training that supports healthy hormones, bone mass density and reducing muscle mass decrease (airbus a380 versus a Boeing 737)
- Accountability and support. (We all know how good an attentive cabin crew is 🙏)
- Yes there are more considerations to consider here but that’s the beauty of having a coach. You can discuss these topics and work on them.

- I’ve helped 100s of women achieve their goals all ages. All shapes and sizes. Nothing is a ‘too difficult’. If you’re interested in finally shifting your mindset from a can’t to a CAN. get in touch today!

Your health. 

Your GREATEST asset.

Yet you neglect it.

You don’t prioritise it.

You look after everyone else. 

Everything else.

What if one day - your health was GONE? 

What would happen? 

You’d be gone! 

Your kids, husband, partner, employer, friends would be without their mother, wife, partner, employee and friend.

I can’t emphasis it enough. 

Invest in your health.

If you think being healthy is expensive. Try illness!

caption:
‘Why most women will NEVER have visible abs’

And that’s ok! 

Firstly, we need to understand some biology here. Women have approximately DOUBLE the amount of essential body fat that a man has. What does essential mean? We need it. It’s necessary for our overall health. 

Secondly, understand when a female has visible abs - they are usually on the threshold of that healthy/unhealthy body fat percentage. 
If they are super active or athletes and consuming adequate calories and have a higher lean muscle mass - often they’re body fat percentage is healthy for their level. On the other hand, someone who has <18% Body Fat from extreme dieting with low lean muscle mass is mostly considered an unhealthy body composition.

Lastly and MOST importantly, the main reason why most women will never have visible abs is because they are simply not willing to make the sacrifices to achieve them. And that’s PERFECTLY alright. In a lot of instances women would have to give up social occassions, wine & chocolate. And have to engage in a lot more activity than their time schedules allow! 🙏

So if you have that as a goal - have a little think about the above points. Is it REALLY worth having abs to you? 🤔

caption:
‘It’s easy for you’ 

‘Sure you’ve never had weight to lose’

‘You wouldn’t understand’

I’ll be the first to put my hand up and say I’ve never had a physical transformation. I’ve never lost an excessive amount of weight. I’ve never ‘struggled’ with my weight! 

But that doesn’t mean I haven’t changed, improved, or grown ❌

Like everyone I have my own story ❤️

And it goes a little like this…

Once upon a time I was a skinny, scrawny, self conscious teenager who decided to become a nutritionist. Not because I was healthy and loved the idea of nourishing food but because I was a geek and loved science 🥰 Said geek went to college with a poorer than average diet. Young Amanda, started learning more and with more knowledge came more power 😍 Knowledge helped improve my nutrition choices! All of a sudden, with better nutrition choices, I’m feeling more energetic, I’m not constantly sick, I’m starting to gain a little muscle and I’m sleeping better 🥰

Fast forward - 7 years later - and you have the Coach Mc Loone you see today. But that person did not always exsist. You see through knowledge I gained power. I now KNOW how to nourish my body, how to become strong, how to feel energised.

And guess what - I can help you too ❤️ Dm me ‘energy’.

caption:
We all have the same 24 hours in the day 💁‍♀️

I actually hate this statement. Although TECHNICALLY correct - people’s priorities are very different.

Let me give you an example. Comparing my 24 hours with a 40 year old working mother of 4 is just INCOMPARABLE!!!!

It’s not that the 40 year old mother of 4 doesn’t WANT to look after her health and fitness (I literally have women with these credentials doing the Strong and Sassy Programme).

I have the luxury of working from home. Because of time differences with clients - the bulk of my work is done mornings and evenings so my free time is during the day. I’ve no kids. No mortgages. Life is EASIER for me! So my 24 hours are very different to my clients.

Like Mandi who is a mother of 5 and runs her own business. She prioritises her workouts when her kids are gone to school💃

Or Elaine who is a doctor - has to get her workouts done on her lunch break 💪

Jacqui is doing tennis as her exercise - she gets to socialise and exercise 🎾 

Gillian who doesn’t want to make different meals for her family - controls portions and adds extra veg.

Lucy who is commuting 2hours a day - has her meals and snacks prepared! 

We all have the same 24 hours in a day. But we all have different priorities. What are your priorities? 🤔

Want results that seem unimaginable right now? 🧐

Did you know it’s 💯 within your reach? 🎉💃

We all have to start somewhere - had you told my 21 year old self who started on ring rows - 10 years later I’d be doing ring muscle ups - I’d be pretty pissed off that it took 10 years 😂😞 But you know what - the time passed anyway! 

I could lie to you and tell you the Strong and Sassy programme is the best strength programme around. But truth is all programmes can work - if you can be consistent with them. How can we stay consistent with them?

I spoke with a friend yesterday who used to do classes in the gym and has recently started an online programme. She said ‘it actually keeps her more accountable- because if she misses a day of the programme - it messes up the rest of her programme. Plus she has someone checking in with her each week’. The accountability of her programme is MAKING her be more consistent. With classes, if she missed a day - no one checked in to see why? It didn’t have an impact on the rest of her programme, she just picked up where she left off?

Online programmes allow you to have more flexibility and freedom. But also, regular check ins mean you’ve always someone holding you accountable.

Want to finally be consistent with your health and fitness? Find a way that works for you 💪

Picture of a happy girl who just got her period 🎉🎉🎉

As a woman, one of the greatest signs of health is a regular, monthly cycle. 🙏❤️

I know it’s a nuisance. I know it can be painful. I know it can cause us to be a bottomless pit 🐷 (p.s out BMR actually increases the week before our period - so we actually NEED extra calories 😍)

But if overall health is your goal - a regular monthly cycle is the pinnacle of health. If for some reason, you’re not getting a monthly cycle (unknown reason) - please reach out to your doctor.

I’m particularly happy to see mine this time around. Why?

Because mine arrived 7 days LATE! We knew we weren’t expecting any baby Boyce’s- I knew EXACTLY why my period was late and I actually anticipated it.

I’m SUPER in tune with my body. I know what’ll put it out of whack. I know that travel causes disruptions to my cycle. I know that alcohol has an effect on it and I know the impact stress has on my body too.

As I’ve harped on about the last few weeks have been super stressful for me. You could join the dots with all spots on my neck and chest and I knew something had to give.

Do NOT underestimate the affect of stress on your body. It affects our health in more ways than people could even imagine. Accumulation of stress can lead to much greater health risks than a delayed period - so do something about it today ❤️🙏

Hopefully some menstrual gains today - for yet another comp 💪🎉

caption: Check out these high protein breakfast ideas and hit save ☝️ #nutrition #nutritionist #breakfastideas #breakfastoptions #breakfasttime #highprotein #proteinbased #onlinecoach #onlinecoaching #strongandsassyprogramme

Do you fail? 🤔

If you don’t fail. Are you even really trying? 🤔

When it comes to strength training and a structured programme we work a lot of percentages. Some days the weights feel great - and like you could actually add a little extra. Other days 10kg feels like 100 😬🥹

When you’ve been strength training for as long as I have pbs don’t come that often either. (If you’re in the shiny new year of strength training and still hitting pbs all the time - enjoy this 😂)

Failing is part of life - if we fail - at least we know we tried. The thing about failing is though. At SOME point - you will succeed. If you KEEP CONSISTENT and follow a plan - you WILL achieve that number or target or goal.

The same goes for a diet! With nutrition, even if you’ve failed 100 times - you’ve can STILL achieve that goal. You just need to be consistent 🙏

caption:
Hazel

45 

Lecturer 

Hazel is super active. She actually just completed an Iron Man at the weekend 💪

There were 3 main reason Hazel wanted to join the Strong and Sassy programme

1. Get a home based strength programme to accomodate her training goals

2. Work on her nutrition - she’s always been active but knows she needs to work more on her nutrition (not just for weight loss but also to match her activity)

3. As she’s getting older, she wants to support her overall health. Prepare her body as best as possible for the next stage of her life 🙏

She’s already reaping the rewards as she completed her Ironman at the weekend.

I’m so proud of this lady and the commitment she makes even with a super busy schedule 🔥

If you’re looking to make a change, why not dm me today?! 📞

Moving house has been listed as one of the most stressful events in your life. Up there with loss of a loved one and divorce.

Unfortunately, I’ve experienced 2 of the 3.

I can honestly say the strain it puts on your physical and mental health is difficult but the most notable stress was the one I experienced with Owen. 

I was moody, complaining constantly and actually quite aggressive. But thankfully, it was short term and I’m back to my normal happy, bubbly self 🙏

This reminded me of a client (a couple of them actually) who was constantly agitated and barking at her partner. The poor fella couldn’t do anything right. 

Why? Why was she constantly cranky to her partner? We soon realised two things that were causing these mood disturbances.
1. She was on crazy low calories - constantly hungry and lacking in energy (anyone who has been HANGRY understands 🙈)
2. She was desperately unhappy in how she viewed herself. This unhappiness in herself projected into her moody outbursts and they were becoming too frequent.

She was GENUINELY worried these feelings were going to have a long term impact on her relationship.

So what did we do?
1. The first one was easy - increasing calories to a normal level while still allowing her to achieve her goals. Her energy levels sky rocketed and her mood instantly improved.
2. Working on self confidence and self esteem was a little trickier. We started to focus on her health from an internal perspective and not just what her body looked like on the outside. We started to do resistance based training and she started to appreciate what her body could do instead of just ‘burning calories’.

Within weeks, her mood improved dramatically, and the cranky outbursts declined steadily. She is now happier in herself than ever before and her partner is also reaping the rewards!!!

Sound familiar? You’re not alone! But you CAN change - with the right guidance and support anything is possible 🙏

Let’s talk mindset 🤯

I stand out of my comfort zone pretty regularly. But twice this year, I stood out of my comfort zone big time.

First, was a novice Weightlifitng competition. Second, a half marathon. 

Why take on these challenges?

Because guess what - it’s not your body that’s saying no. It’s your mind. Your body is capable of a lot more than you think.

It’s not easy going to competitions knowing you won’t win. It’s not easy being 20kg behind other peoples lifts. It’s not easy running 21km. 

But it helps you learn. It builds character. Everytime you step outside that comfort zone you build a little more resilience, a little more confidence. 

I spoke to a client last week and she talked about how increasing calories was mentally challenging. I get it I do, comfort zones are easier.

It’s easy to continue training and exercising while ignoring the biggest problem that’s not allowing you achieve your goals (nutrition 🙈). It’s easy to do 6 week challenges every quarter - lose weight and regain it because you couldn’t sustain it.

What’s not easy? 
Committing to a 6 month programme to improve your habits and make LONG TERM sustainable change.

We want results yesterday. Believe me. I get it. But unfortunately, that’s not how the cookie crumbles.

And the longer you waste on short term, quick fixes. The longer it takes to actually get to your final destination 🙌🙏

ℍ𝕠𝕨 𝕨𝕖𝕝𝕝 𝕒𝕣𝕖 𝕪𝕠𝕦 𝕣𝕖𝕔𝕠𝕧𝕖𝕣𝕚𝕟𝕘?
.
.
Quite often people think you need to do more to achieve your goals. And in a lot of cases that is true - more exercise, more water, better nutrition. But for some actually less is more. 
.
.
Everyone has their problem areas. 

👉Some people nail nutrition and exercise and can’t understand why they can’t lose weight - while their bodies are in chronic sleep deprivation 🤦‍♀️ 

👉Others weigh in the week before their period and can’t understand why their weight fluctuates. 

👉Others would rather take a supplement than eat real food 🙈

👉 No ice baths will not mask the fact that you’ve been boozing Friday, Saturday and Sunday.
.
.
These are some of the elements to think about when it comes to your goals - in no particular order 👊
.
.
Nutrition and exercise are not the only 2 elements you can control. If you have those nailed why not look at other areas? 🤔
.
.
Save this one for later ⬇️

Meet Elaine 🔦

Age: 41

Occupation: Doctor

I don’t say this lightly when I say Elaine has overcame more obstacles in the last year than most people do in their lifetime.

✅ Covid

✅ Pneumonia 

✅ Moved Continent

✅ Living in a country that their first language isn’t English

✅ Works in a different country to the one she lives in

✅ Kids with autism 

And she STILL MANAGES to prioritise her health ❤️

Half the time she’s working out with kids hanging out of her. The other half she’s squeezing a lunchtime session in. 

It’s NOT easy but she makes it work.

You see the problem we have is we are waiting for these PERFECT circumstances to start. Truth is there’s never a perfect time. Life is ALWAYS going to get in the way. But something is ALWAYS better than NOTHING! 

I could not be prouder of the effort this lady has put in. The habits she has implemented and the lifestyle she has changed - all for the better. 

🔥And she topped it all off with running a 10km at the weekend. Elaine - you are a rockstar 🎉

caption:
We all want results yesterday.

I’m no different. I’m impatient too. 

We opt for the path of least resistance. 

We opt for the easier option.

We give into instant gratification constantly. 

We’d rather take drugs to make us happy than get out in nature or exercise.

We choose supplements over real food. 

We choose the latest toys or gadgets before doing the work.

We have become a lazy society.

But I’m calling out to your future selves. Your future self who is begging you to make better food choices. Your future self who is determined by what you do now. The mother you want to be. The grandmother you want to be. She is counting on you to make the right decisions NOW! 

So what are you going to do?

November doors are open 🫵

Have you been on the fence for awhile and still not sure if online coaching is for you?

Do any of these scenarios sound familiar?🤔🤔🤔

👉 You’ve been eating really healthy Monday to Friday - weekend comes and all hell breaks loose. Chocolate, wine, crisps, chips - everything! 🥹

👉 You’ve LITERALLY tried EVERYTHING. Every diet. Every exercise known to man and NOTHING WORKS 😭

👉 You’re a working mother and gym class times don’t suit your busy schedule. 🤯

👉 You’re hiding in clothes that are oversized and baggy but you secretly keep the smaller clothes that used to fit you - just incase! 😢

👉 You avoid photos being taken of you or hide behind people because you’re embarrassed or ashamed 😔

👉 You get ready to go out for dinner with your partner and try on everything in your wardrobe - and settle for the jeans and top because nothing feels comfortable 😦

👉 You’re exercising relentlessly but never achieving the physique you’re aspiring to. 

I know there are people out there who not only relate to one of the above but maybe even multiple 😭 And it’s not for the lack of trying. You feel like you’ve been trying your whole life and nothing ever works.

What if I told you - I have the solution! To every single one of the above scenarios? 😱

Because I do! 

And I know this because I have helped women overcome every single one of the above situations. 

🔥 Look at Simone (mother) - who completed ALL of her training from home. 

🔥 Check out Ciara (nurse) - who is finally seeing progress in the gym with her own personalised programme.

🔥 Teresa (mother) - who is the fittest she’s been in years and feeling incredible in a dress

🔥 Elaine (doctor) - who ran 10km for the first time.

🔥 Jennifer (nurse) - who has finally found the right nutrition balance and no longer worries about scale weight.

This is just a handful of the women I’ve helped become healthier, fitter, stronger and happier ❤️ 

If you can relate to any of the scenarios I’ve mentioned and you FINALLY want to DITCH yo yo dieting for good. Dm me ‘I’m in’

caption:
Proud of this team ❤️ Proud to be representing @crossfitbotany 🙏 @thewesterngames 🔥

Every competition is a learning curve📈

How amazing is it to be a strong woman 💪22.5kg Dumbbell feels light to me. When I started in the gym, I wasn’t lifting above a 5kg over my head 🤌

I’ll be honest, I learned ALOT. Although we finished in an INCREDIBLE fourth position with all top 5 finishes and I’m BEYOND proud of our efforts - My focus will be on my weaknesses 🏋️‍♀️ 

I’ve been strength training for 10 years and football fitness means I have a decent cardio background. But I’ve only been doing CrossFit for 2.5 years so the skills side of it is still a major weakness. My gymnastics capacity and barbell cycling is NOT where I want it to be. That’s ok - I have high expectations and I’m willing to put in the work ⛏

I want to ask you something- do you reflect on situations and circumstances? For example - if you’re not where you want to be - do you blame other people and other things? Or do you take responsibility? 🧐

If you are not where you want to be. That’s down to you 🫵 YOU have the control. YOU can change your circumstances. What are you gonna do about it?🤔

caption:
‘I was too stubborn to admit I couldn’t do it on my own’

From my experience, most women are control freaks (I’m one too 🙊😂). We think we need to know everything. We are strong independent women afraid to rely on others for help ☹️

We think we should ‘know what to do’ in all areas of life. But from my experience - those who delegate work to other people in different areas of their life - often have the most success.

Why?
Because it’s one less thing for YOU to do.

Having a coach to help you with your health and fitness is actually a shortcut! 

Why? Because the expertise, accountability and the right plan allows you to HAVE MORE TIME! 

Not only that - you’re not WASTING your time trailing methods that may or may not work for you! 

Sarah just wishes she started sooner. 

Don’t make that mistake. Start today and finish 2022 strong 💪

Did you know that every choice you make now - your future self is paying the consequence.

I’ll give you an example. 
Were you that slim 20 year old that could eat whatever she wanted without ever gaining weight. So you ate takeaways and never exercised? Your 40 year old self may not feel the same way. 

I try to educate to my clients that every action you take has a consequence. You may not be able to see it in the short term, but long term your body is thanking you 🙏❤️

Another example - last week I was talking to my clients about menopause. Now majority of my clients are a long way away from menopause - so why talk to them about it?
Every action they choose between now and then can have an impact on their symptoms. For example - if you start resistance training in your 20s - your menopausal body will thank you 🙏 

Every action has a consequence. If you constantly rely on short term gratification- there will be long term consequences. If you decide to play the long game - stop sweating the small stuff, and be patient - your future self WILL thank you 🙏

caption:
Toning up 🚨⚠️

Not going to lie - this is a trigger for me. I absolutely HATE the term. I hate it a little bit less than ‘I don’t want to get bulky’ 😂

Anyway here’s what you need to do to ‘tone up’

1. Understand what it is you’re saying 😂 you want to change your body composition which is reducing your body fat mass and increasing your lean muscle mass. 

2. Lift weights - a body building style progressive overload programme is best for this if aesthetic goals are what you’re looking for

3. Control your food intake - easiest achieved by a calorie deficit

4. Be consistent - it doesn’t happen overnight so you may aswell enjoy the process. 

Ps think of all the other amazing goals you’re achieving in the meantime (increasing bone mass density, increased BMR, reducing risk sarcopenia)

caption:
Everyone in your life needs you to take care of you..

You’re a daughter, an employee, a friend, maybe a sister or a mother…

The ONLY way you can become the best version of you is by attending to your own oxygen mask first.

Running yourself into the ground is the exact opposite–and it’s taking you further away from being that person. 

Self-Care is a selfless act. 

When YOU are at your best, in shape, full of energy and confidence… you can serve everyone around you at the highest level and feel AMAZING doing it. 

People around you will recognize your work and follow your example. 

When you aren’t at your best, you simply can’t do that. It’s impossible.

Just ask my client Teresa who has found her ‘me time’ and continues to find it every week. She trains from home in the morning and has just completed a half marathon and done breathwork for the first time in her life.

Or my clients who do shift work. And even though it’s difficult to find a good routine - they manage to smash it every week. 

Or what about Elaine who moved continent, works abroad, has 2 kids with special needs AND IS A DOCTOR! 

You see all these ladies realise how important their own health is. If they don’t look after themselves - they can’t be the best mothers, employees, friends or family members.

So they prioritise their health and fitness 🙏
It’s not selfish - it’s necessary!

caption:
As I strolled around Aldi on Saturday. I had a little moment of gratitude.

I had two thoughts -
1. My picky eating habits have come a long way in the last 10 years 
2. I’m so grateful to eat food with 0 guilt, no working off calories or depriving myself of the foods I love.

When I wanted to become a nutritionist - my family were astounded - ‘but you don’t eat anything’ . I had a diet full of beige foods and very little protein. They were right 😂 but I loved science and I wanted to understand how nutrition affects the body.

The pickiness was something that weaned it’s way out as I aged and was more open to food suggestions.

The guilt and binging was a whole different kettle of fish…

This one took me years and a whole lots of self development to find! 

It’s one of the many reasons I love my job so much. I know personally how hard it is to form a good relationship with food - so when I help my clients achieve that - I feel that happiness deep in my soul! 

You see the Strong and Sassy programme is so much more than a training programme and diet plan…

caption:
I have high expectations. 

I give off good energy and I need people to match the effort I give off.

I don’t expect people to match my energy (because let’s be honest that would be hard 😅).

But I don’t appreciate negative energy!

There have be instances and situations in my life that I had to let of due to this negative energy! But every time I have - I’ve found another level of me 🙏❤️

Anyway - point of this post?

Don’t settle. EVER! For anything in life - jobs, relationships, friends, houses etc. Don’t lose yourself trying to be someone you’re not ✌️

I’ll be honest. Pictures don’t do this programme justice.

But comments and quotes like this - these are what makes my job the best job in the world.

I am one of those annoying people who wakes up with no snooze button.

My alarm goes off Monday and I’m buzzing to see the check ins from all over the world.

I am so truely blessed with the women who venture on this programme.

There’s not 100s of women on this course but a small select few. Women who are sick of fad dieting. Women who are sick of starting again EVERY week. Women who are taking control of their health and fitness, one step at a time! 

These women are making long term sustainable change and their future selves are already thanking them ❤️

How lucky am I that I get to work with these women to help them achieve their healthiest and happiest selves? 🙏

I started a new sport at 29.

For anyone who knows my background, you’ll know I played Gaelic football almost my whole life. 

I know 29 is NOT old. I’m well aware of this. But when you’re competing against people who started in their early teens it’s pretty late to the party.

I have clients who never consistently exercised until 40.

I have clients who only started becoming knowledgeable on nutrition at 50.

You see the thing is. 

We tell ourselves a story in our head.

I’ll wait until Monday.

I’ll wait until next month.

I’ll start in the New Year.

It’s easy to say we’ll start - when we’re ready. Or until we have time to commit to it.

You see the thing is. We’re actually not guaranteed time. My Dad died at 55. Him dying at such a young age, made me truely value time! 

If you want something, you have to start now. Not when you’re ready or when the perfect circumstances arise. You have to be willing to start now.

I’ve 3 competitions coming up over the next few months and I am BUZZING! You see I decided I want to become the healthiest, fittest and strongest version of myself and that’s the commitment I’ve made to myself.

There’s 11 weeks left in 2022. 11 weeks could get you started to becoming the healthiest and happiest version of yourself. If you’re sick of waiting for the right time and want to make a change NOW. Dm me ‘CHANGE’.

Let’s talk sacrifice.

There’s no doubt about it. In order to achieve our goals - we need to make sacrifice.

I do believe however, our sacrifices have to be less extreme and a lot more sustainable.
For example: People who embark on diets of no sugar, no carbs and no alcohol would be much better off just reducing the frequency and quantity of these foods or drinks in their diet.

My client Jennifer has dramatically reduced her alcohol consumption. She’s not taking extreme measures or going off it forever but she doesn’t prioritise it anymore.

Personally, I have a lot of competitions coming up over the next few weeks so I will definitely have to make sacrifices. Socialising takes a back seat during these busy periods.

Sacrifice is inevitable. But what you sacrifice is up to you. Stop with the extremes of 0 or 100%. Find the right balance and enjoy a life where you can achieve your results and NOT give up everything you like and enjoy 🙏

How many times have you had an idea of what you were going to wear only to try it on, take it off and change about 7 million times after that? 

How many items of clothes are you ‘saving’ or waiting to fit back into them? 🤔

How many times have you looked in the mirror and picked at every imperfection you have? 🥹

This has to change ❌❌❌

And you my darling have the power to change this 🙏

You see my Strong and Sassy programme has helped people with this exact problem 🙏

How?
✅ Building self confidence and self esteem
✅ Building a bullet proof mindset 
✅ Working on yourself - inside and out 

I want you to feel incredible in any clothes you wear whether it be a ball gown or a bikini.

And you CAN achieve this! But you have to be willing to put in the work ❤️

Successful testing week ✅

The last 4 months I have not been focusing on strength so I wasn’t expecting any significant strength gains. And that’s ok, my training is periodised and I have other fish to fry so goals change.

The reason this testing week was so successful was I’ve been hugely focusing on technique and being pain free 🙌

For me personally, this is key. It’s all well and good clocking up big numbers but if your technique sucks - it will catch up on you in one way or another.

Personal wins for me this week:

✅ My beautiful snatch 🥰 Because I am FINALLY squat snatching my numbers actually went up to but honestly if my numbers remained the same and I improved my technique I would have been happy.

✅ I’m also finally squat cleaning - my body is still in a little bit of shock (if you’re a power clean person you’ll know what I mean) but slowly but surely I’m getting more confident and comfortable under that bar.

✅ PB Split Jerk - again due to technique improvement 🙌

✅ Shoulder Pressing - pain free. For a LONG time I’ve had pain while shoulder pressing and it made me shy away from the movement. How good is it to move a weight without pain 🙏

✅ Gymnastics - my obvious downfall when it comes to CF but with INCREDIBLE guidance and coaching - this weakness is starting to become much better. And again, doing it with a structured programme has allowed for pain free movement.

I’ve realised with the right programme and mentoring anything is possible. 

So please no matter what your goals are there is a roadmap for you to achieve them. You may not have found it in the past, but that doesn’t mean you can’t find it in the future. Remember your goals. Remember not everyone’s are the same and what works for someone else - may not work for you. But don’t give up trying 🙏

caption:
I knew that taking more time to work on kicking and shooting would mean that I would improve at scoring. It’s a known fact. Work on your skill. Drill that skill. You become better.

But I never did it. And thus, I NEVER became better at scoring 🤷‍♀️

Information is NOT transformation.

You see I get this all the time.

‘I know what to do. I need to eat better and move more.’

But information is NOT transformation.

Just because you know it - doesn’t mean you’ll do it!

During my whole football career, I wanted to be a forward. But I didn’t apply my knowledge. 

This story reminds me of most peoples health and fitness journey. Most people know what to do - but don’t apply it!

Maybe if I had someone keeping me accountable - Amanda to achieve x, you need to do extra shooting drills 3 times a week. Honestly, I think I would have done it! Or if I had some encouragement to try and achieve it!

Maybe all you’re missing is that encouragement to go and achieve your health and fitness goals. Maybe you need someone to be accountable to you - to do the work for you.  You need to eat x,y & z and train Monday, Wednesday, Friday.

Information is NOT transformation!

Who knows if I had used my information more wisely - maybe I’d still be playing today 😂

caption:
Real women. Real results.

There’s no criteria to becoming a Strong and Sassy female. There’s no age limit or fitness level required.

What I do expect - 
🔥 Commitment
🔥 To show up 
🔥 Enjoy the person you are about to become

✨Aoibheann has been with me for quite awhile. She originally started during lockdown and had fantastic physical results. She came back to me recently to strike a balance between socialising and commiting to her health and fitness. Having turned 30 at the weekend - she is feeling the best

✨ Simone is a working momma who initially signed up for 6 months but ended up staying a year 😍 She honestly had every excuse to NOT prioritise herself but she didn’t let the excuses get in her way. 8kg later - she’s the healthiest fittest version of herself and everyone is noticing.

✨ Teresa had been consistently training before coming to me. Once she had that nailed she wanted to dial in on her nutrition. While she worked immensely hard on her nutrition we also educated her on the importance of sleep and stress management and her coffee intake DRAMATICALLY decreased.

✨ Laura (teacher) wanted to find a balance and get back into a good exercise regime. Not only did she lose weight on the scales but her confidence grew exponentially.

These are just the physical results you can achieve from doing my Strong and Sassy programme. In my opinion, the mental changes are what makes this different!

I almost cried when I woke up Monday morning…

Teresa had sent me this photo -beaming from ear to ear with pride.

She had just completed a half marathon in 2hours 18mins.

Let me tell you a little bit about Teresa’s journey.

Firstly, and probably most importantly - she thought Online Coaching was a scam 😅

She didn’t know what she had signed up to with her initial call with Brian but she went for it anyway 🙈

After realising it wasn’t a scam and after a great consultation call - she actually realised this was the perfect programme for her lifestyle (she’s a working mother).

She initially signed up to 12 weeks and had an initial goal of running a 10km.

6 months later - she has signed up for ANOTHER 3 Months AND completed a half marathon.

This isn’t a fluke.

This is what you get when you surround yourself with a great like minded community and a coach who supports and educated you.

Teresa now describes the programme as ‘her time’ and the best investment she’s ever made in herself.

If you’re a working mum like Teresa, and gyms don’t work for you, you need guidance and education or even just a little bit of ‘you time’ get in contact today 🙌

I had a conversation in my DMs at the weekend that really made me smile so I thought I’d share.

I put up a question box asking ‘why people like following me’ and a lovely lady responded ‘Confident, go getter’.

Wow 🤩 

That is EXACTLY how I’d like to be described.

This absolutely warmed my heart because honestly that has not always been the case.

When I was younger I conformed to societal norms. I REALLY REALLY wanted to be liked. I craved attention so badly. To the naked eye - I probably appeared Uber confident. I was loud and always trying to be the centre of attention. 

I defined my worth on how many friends I had. How much money I had. Having the latest brands and caking my face in make up. I genuinely believed ‘that is what confident is’.

But I couldn’t have been more wrong.

I was young and immature. 

I don’t regret it. Because I truely believe these things mould you into the person you become.

I now realise confidence is not walking into a room expecting and hoping people will like me. Confidence is walking into a room and not caring if they do!

Confidence is wearing a bikini or dress at any time of the year and not worrying about what anyone else thinks.

Confidence is belief in yourself and your own abilities but never belittling someone else for your gain.

Confidence is NOT something you’re born with. Confidence is something you have to work on -  day in day out. It’s something you have to talk to yourself about. Something that needs reassurance from time to time. 

But confidence will make you happier than any scale weight, any dress size or any weight lifted.

And guess what - it’s my speciality.

So if you’re looking to gain some confidence - hit me up 🤙

How can I eat up to 3,000 Calories a day ⬇️

1. My lean muscle mass means that my BMR is higher. More muscle = more calories

2. Resistance training - lifting weights supports an increased BMR. Lifting weights does not need to be in a gym - remember half my clients train from home and achieve incredible results.

3. I’ve been training at a high level - both cardio and strength for 10+ years - time frame matters

4. The type of food I consume - NOT JUST CALORIES - I support a balanced lifestyle but most of my nutrition comes from wholefoods

5. I sleep 7.5-8 hours a night

6. Alcohol is not a priority. It doesn’t mean I don’t drink. It means I’d rather train on a Saturday morning than drink on a Friday night. 

If you want to stop fad dieting and you don’t want to spend your life on 1,200 calorie diets, miserable and hungry - come to the dark side 👹

caption:
I need you to understand something…

My goals are different to yours.

Your goals are different to your friends.

Everyone in this picture has different goals.

See what I’m getting at…

So why would we all do the same thing 🤔

This is something that I get in my dms or with clients regularly -
‘But my friend Mary did paleo and she lost a stone in a month’

Yes Sarah - but you’re 5 years older than her, have 2 kids more than her and she has been training for 10 years’

Truth is - even if Sarah didn’t have 2 kids, was 5 years younger and trained for 10 years she may STILL never get the same results as Mary 🤷‍♀️

Because EVERYONE is different 😣

I’m sorry if that’s not the answer you wanted to hear but it’s the truth 🙈

So next time - you try to compare - please don’t!

Every single person I deal with has different goals and how I coach them varies from person to person.

Sometimes I have clients who come to me thinking they need to dial in on their nutrition - when they actually need to stress less and sleep more 💤

Other ladies think they need to be training 7 days a week when they actually need to do less and walk more.

Don’t settle for cookie cutter. 

Don’t settle for anything less than what you want and need.

I promise you it’s worth it. Every second of it and every cent you invest in it.

Because when you achieve those goals. It’s life changing ❤️🥰

caption:
‘Look Amanda, I know what to do’ 

Truth is. We all have a good idea what to do. But that doesn’t mean - we’re doing it! 

I remember before I became a PT spending HOURS in the gym - on a threadmill or stair master followed by ab work. 

This was consistently 3-5 days a week.

But I was also drinking almost every night and my portion sizes were above what I needed!

I was bloated, tired and fed up.

I bought some fat loss supplements and asked a PT for some good tummy exercises. 

The result?

Zero. Zilch. Nada.

Nothing changed. 

I THOUGHT I knew what I was doing. I was exercising consistently. I was a nutritionist. I didn’t need anyones help! 

And I stayed the same.

Bloated. Tired. And fed up.

And I had knowledge. I had experience with exercise. 

I can’t imagine how hard it is for a newbie trying to achieve results! 😫 

But all is not lost. I can help 🙋‍♀️

I can save you the time, energy and money I wasted.

I can help you achieve that bikini body without restriction 🥰 Dm me ‘bikini’ today 🔥

caption:
Helen has been a client with me since February. 

She has been training on and off for years. Her main goal was to get into a good routine and be accountable. She was looking for a long term sustainable change - without restriction. 

Before we started working together Helen did programmes and trained - but as soon as she had a bad week or didn’t see the scales moving - she gave up. She found herself unhappy in her clothes and she was sick of stopping and starting. 

She hesitated in starting because of pride ‘She thought she could and should do it alone’. And if she's honest, she thought ‘I know what to do’. But she realised she needed direction, accountability and a community - which drove her to take action.
(P.s Helen is a trainer and has a background in Health promotion - but even coaches need coaches)

'I knew others who did Amanda’s programme and I knew it had a personal approach' ‘I knew there was a community environment to it and I liked that’

In the last few weeks, I have seen another level to Helen’s commitment. We set up some goals to achieve before the end of the year and her training has been upped another level 💪 A good head and good routine has meant her nutrition is looking better than ever.

I am so proud and privileged to have Helen on my team ❤️🔥

My world turned upside down in 2015. 

For those of you who don’t already know, I lost my Dad to pancreatic cancer.

I can tell you right now - it was without a doubt one of the hardest times in my entire life. 

I can tell you another thing - one of the biggest things that got me through it was training! 

I would hope it’s obvious that I was not motivated to eat healthy when my Dad was terminally ill. The easy option was to eat takeaways - but instead I brought my tupperware to Tullamore hospital! I also think it’s obvious that when he eventually passed away - I wasn’t waking up BUZZING to get to the gym.

But I still went…

I still showed up.

Even when my Dad was dying. Even when he died. I SHOWED up! I didn’t eat rubbish or crap or convenience! 

Why? 
- Because I said I would. I am committed to myself - not only when it’s easy and I’m positive and I’m motivated. I’m committed to my health even more on the tough days - on the days I barely feel like getting out of bed. 

And I will continue to commit to myself. I will continue to show up for myself.

So please, next time you think of the word ‘motivated’ think of this story ❤️🙏

And if it’s support you need - which is more often the case. People need support - not motivation!

Remember, I can help you with that 🙏💪

caption:
What does a day in the life of me entail? 

5am alarm clock…

Whether I’m doing coaching calls or the odd outdoor training session, my 5am alarm is a constant. I’m without a doubt a morning lark and get all my most productive work done in the morning! 

I’ll usually get a little walk in mid morning or afternoon. My job is actually quite sedentary but my 10,000 steps is a non negotiable.

I train either early afternoon or 4pm. I train  days - sometimes twice a day. 
(P.s for anyone thinking you need to do this it is ABSOLUTELY UNNECESSARY unless you have a sporting goal - which I do)

My bedtime is 8.30pm sharp and I honestly think I have the sleep requirements of a newborn baby 😂

I went to a life coach a few years ago and he asked me my dream job. I couldn’t give him an answer but I could say this -
✅ choose my working hours 
✅ have my own business
✅ help as many people as possible in the world
✅ be an educator 

Turns out I’ve pretty much nailed that job down 😂 

This lifestyle works for me. I’m so happy that I have this career and it allows me to train the way I would like to also. But for majority of people - training that much is unnecessary and honestly, does not fit into many people’s time schedule.

Be smarter and wiser with your time. So find what works for you and your lifestyle. And whatever it is - make sure it’s sustainable 💪👊

@marceauphotography 
@thewodlife

Just back from a lovely weekend away with my friends 😍🙏

I’m super tired after the four hour drive home today.

Easy to let excuses slip in for not having my food prepared or not train tomorrow.

But see the thing is - my health and fitness is a priority to me. I could have EASILY opted for Uber Eats but having good nutritious food in my fridge is essential for me. 

I’ll be in bed super early so training doesn’t suffer also. Again, training is a priority. I don’t allow excuses especially not choices I’ve made myself 👊

You see these small boring habits are the habits that work.

These are the difference between you seeing results and staying the same.

It may seem boring and monotonous. But that is what works 🙏

Looking forward to getting back to my routine as always after a few days out of routine 🙏 but as always non negotiables always hit 💪🔥

caption:
It’s hard to believe that once upon a time I couldn’t do chin ups.

Because guess what - that’s the reality.

Once upon a time, I was EXACTLY where you are now. 

I couldn’t do an inverted row - let alone a chin up - and that was when I was training to be a Personal trainer 🫣

So what changed? 🤔
✨I started training consistently 
✨I designed a progressive overload programme (I’ve recently delegated my programming and coaching to others)
✨I started eating to fuel my body 
✨I showed up - even when I didn’t want to

And 10 years later - here we are. Not just doing chin ups but repping an extra 20kg to Bodyweight (which isn’t light btw 😅)

So why are you struggling so much to see progress?

Ok ask yourself -
☄️ Are you just doing random classes that achieve random results? Or are you doing a programme that works TOWARDS your goal? 
🤓P.s Doing chin ups once a week is NOT enough

☄️ Do you even have a goal?

☄️ Are you eating enough to fuel performance? 

☄️ Are you eating the correct types of foods?
🤓P.s contrary to what every other PT on the internet says this MOST CERTAINLY does matter

☄️ And finally and most importantly - Are you showing up?

You could have the best programme in the world, a million dollar nutrition coach and if you’re not applying it - you’re going NOWHERE! 

I know how hard it is. I know how frustrating it is. I know how impatient you are.

I HAVE BEEN THERE!!!!

But the time is going to pass anyway - may aswell spend it getting strong AF 💪

caption:
I get a lot of comments about my fitness levels and my physique. Mainly off people I train with or perhaps people who follow me on social media.

⚡️HOW do I get abs like you? 

⚡️HOW do I do a pull up?

⚡️HOW do I get stronger? 

So I’m about to let the cat out of the bag.

All of your goals can be achieved - if you just do ONE thing - BE CONSISTENT! 

I have been strength training for 10 years. That’s why I can do a pull up with ease. Not because of a programme or any gym. Because for 10 years I showed up. 

I have been taking my nutrition serious for a similar amount of time. So when someone comes to me looking for quick fix, or expecting miracles in a few months - that is my response.

You see consistency trumps EVERY diet or programme on the planet. 

So instead of trying to follow the next trend - why not show up - every week - no excuses, no complaints! 

If you find this difficult (like MANY people do) invest in some accountability, invest in someone who will HELP you when things get tough (because they will), invest in someone who pushes you on the days you don’t want to show up (because it will happen).

If you want to REALLY be like me - why not get coached by me 🥰 I’ve spaces opening up over the next few days! Dm me ‘RESULTS’

I was stuck in a rut too…

I wanted to give it more time…

I hoped and wished and prayed it would work for me…

But time and time again, I realised I was not achieving the results I wanted.

I’m a competitive athlete. Programme, coaching, nutrition, sleep, hydration and environment all have to be aligned for me to make progress. For the last few months, I was staying in an environment that I was comfortable in. I wasn’t seeing results and I wasn’t making progress. 

BUT it was all a choice. I was CHOOSING to stay the same. I was CHOOSING to not make progress – because I was CHOOSING to stay in the same environment. 

Have you ever been in that situation? 

💫 Maybe you’ve been with a coach for so long that you’re no longer getting the service you initially received. 

💫 Maybe you’ve been in a cycle of doing 6 week challenges with people – you don’t know how to do anything long term.

💫Maybe you’ve been with the same gym for years and you’re no longer pushed.

💫 Maybe you’ve been blaming your husband and kids for your lack of time? 

💫 Maybe you’ve used the excuse of - ‘I can’t or I’ll never be…’ 

Just remember, you HAVE the choice. You CHOOSE to remain the same. 

If you’re sick of your old habits and want to make a life long change – why not jump on a call today? 📞 

Changing your whole life is just a phone call away ☄️

🚀 How I became stronger, happier and more confident and how you can too. 

❌When I started in the fitness industry I was a little lost. I was focused on how I looked. I was obsessed with having abs. I only ate ‘clean’ food mid week which led to weekend binges. My relationship with nutrition and fitness definitely was not a healthy one. 

🚨I wasn’t happy. Not in my body. Not in my mind. I genuinely couldn’t imagine continuing my life with this level of restriction and I began to resent the gym 😢 I was tired and cranky and was constantly sick. I distinctly remember a time in final year college where I could not get rid of bronchitis - I was zapped constantly and I lost my place on the college football team! 

✅ Then I stopped focusing so much on HOW I looked. I stopped looking for abs every time I walked by the mirror. I started to appreciate resistance training and I began focusing on how much stronger I was becoming. My goals changed. Performance based goals replaced the quest for abs and I found my love for exercise again. I found a balanced approach to nutrition. I still eat very healthy and nutritious but I no longer restrict myself. 

🔥 I no longer focus on HOW I look but WHAT my body can do. I wear bikinis now without dieting to get in them. I’m stronger and fitter than I’ve ever been and clothes sizes no longer dictate my life. I’m happier and healthier. I love the skin I’m in ❤ Looking back on these pictures actually makes me incredibly sad. I see someone totally different to the person I’ve become! 🙏

🎯 And that’s why I created my Strong and Sassy Programme to help women become bikini confident year round without restrictions. Comment ‘CHANGE’ below if you’d like for me to personally message you today and see if I can help you!

caption:
Yesterday, I told you about a common problem that most women experience when trying to change their body shape. 

No matter what diet they do, they can't stick to it at weekends.... 

To fix this problem I get my clients to find their non negotiables. 

What are non negotiables?
They are habits you can stick to NO MATTER WHAT the circumstances are. 

I usually recommend 3 of them.. 

3 things you can stick to every weekend.
For example - Drink 2 litres of water, walk 10,000 steps daily and 1 piece of fruit. 

It's pretty simple. Try this out and let me know how it goes. 

P.s I'm looking for 5 MORE ladies who want to be bikini confident year round without giving up the foods they enjoy. If that's you DM me 'Bikini'.

A common problem I see most women have when they are trying to change their body shape is their struggle to stay on track at weekends 🐒🐷 

You may notice yourself cutting calories during the week and then all hell breaks lose at weekends and you're afraid that if you continue this way you'll never achieve that bikini body 😢 

It's so frustrating because you're really trying to make a change. What's actually causing this is a binge restrict cycle that you've developed over the years. We only know and understand nutrition at 2 levels - 'really good' or 'really bad' 

I've found the best solution to fix this is to SAY NO to the all or nothing approach - but this will require help. Accountability to someone who knows what they're talking about can definitely help with this. I've also found having non negotiables proves very helpful.

As much as my Dad would be so proud looking down on me today. I am not a runner 😂 But challenge ✅

caption:
Why is it - in a world where dieting and fat loss can actually be so simple - we over complicate it? 🫣

Honestly, the vast majority of people are willing to cut out sugar and alcohol for 6 weeks cold Turkey - but tell them to reduce these things in the long term and all hell breaks lose 😑

I still cannot fathom why we all stick to the hard options? The difficult scenarios? The all or nothing approach? Do we hate ourselves so much that we’re willing to put ourselves through that much torture to drop a dress size 😰

If you’re sick of the fad dieting. If you’re sick of yo-yo ing. If you finally want to start seeing long term results - get in contact today!

If you think with coeliac disease - you can only shop in the expensive, health food, Gluten free section - you could not be more wrong.

Did you know a diet in whole foods - fruit, veg, meat, fish, eggs, rice, potatoes (all 1 ingredient foods) are gluten free 🤷‍♀️

I know choice and convenience is taken away from you but nutrition quality certainly isn’t. Opt for more of these foods and less of those expensive packaged foods 🙏

#glutenfree #coeliac #nutrition #nutritiontips #nutritioncoach

Top tips for hitting protein targets 🎯

People really struggle initially with increasing protein in their diet. But with these simple tricks - I think it’ll get a whole lots easier ✅

caption:
Check out this reel to see why you’re not making progress this season 🤔

Here are some common problems I see -

1. When I started spending more time in the gym than on the pitch - I realised - the pitch was not for me anymore 🥲 (this probably won’t apply to an injured athlete)

2. Stop with all the volume - you SHOULDN’T have dead legs going to play your match if you have a sports specific programme. You are either doing too much volume (following a generic programme) or not recovering well enough.

3. Females in particular tend to have a tendency to underestimate when it comes to sports. If you’re not fuelling adequately - you’re putting your performance at major risk!

4. Sleep and hydration are the two most important factors for recovery. Worry about ice baths, massages and sleep when you have these nailed!
