caption:
Good things come to those who wait.

We are all impatient beings (myself included). We want results yesterday 🙊

I’m here to tell you when it comes to your health and fitness goals putting a timeframe on it makes it significantly harder 🤦‍♀️

That’s not to say you can’t set yourself some realistic goals and targets 🎯 

But when it comes to our health - I always say ‘does this affect your future self in a positive manner’ or ‘does this support the person you want to become’. 

If your future self will thank you for it - do it! ✅ Be patient. 😉 and enjoy the ride 🤘

🚨Struggling to see results in the gym🚨

Here’s so of my top tips

1. Find a programme that aligns with your goals. Progressively overload. Amen 🙏 
Random classes = random results.

2. Be consistent. You could have the best programme in the world but unless you’re actually being consistent with it - it’s useless. Don’t be disappointed with the results you didn’t achieve from the work you didn’t put in! 

3. Do the boring exercises. Squat, Hinge, Push, Pull, Lunge and Carry every week - and you’re onto a winner.

4. For consistency, enjoyment and fulfilment to happen - you need to have something you really enjoy in there too - for me that’s a metcon 😍

If you’re struggling to see results in the gym - there’s a number of reasons it may not be working for you. But make sure you’re putting in the work in the gym and in the kitchen before blaming the programme 🙊 I see this one very often. 🙊 And if you’re not happy or satisfied - there are always other options.

If you want help on training and nutrition - Dm me ‘HELP’ 🙏🚨

caption:
Almost half of the world's population are not consuming enough fruit and vegetables 🤯
.
.
Bare in mind that a large majority of low to middle income families actually don't have access to or can't afford these luxuries.
.
.
I'm sure I wasn't the only one who grew up with 'Eat that up, the poor starving children in Africa would do anything for that'. And while I may not agree with my mother's force feeding tactics, she is right about this 🤔
.
.
We need to reframe our minds. We should be so grateful and privileged we CAN eat such whole nutritious food. 
.
.
Do yourself a favour this week - Increase your vegetable consumption. Even if its only by one portion a week. Maybe try something different for dinner? Maybe order a side salad if you're out for dinner?! Maybe add some spinach to your morning smoothie?! Your body and gut will thank you for it ❤🙏
.
.

How many of you have went on holidays feeling unhappy and uncomfortable in your own skin? 

How many of you have not wore that bikini because you felt you ‘didn’t have a bikini body?’

How many of you hide under swimsuits or shorts or even a towel?

How many of you wear floaty dresses and baggy tshirts to hide your tummy? 

If you have answered yes to any of the above - listen up! 

What if I told you - I can help you change this? ⬆️

How do I know? BECAUSE I HAVE BEEN THERE. I am walking, talking living proof that my Strong and Sassy programme helps you achieve happiness and comfort in your own skin 🙏

caption:
And it may cost you more than just money 😢

#yourhealthmatters #yourhealthisyourwealth

If you’re not doing some form of strength training - I’m afraid you’re getting left behind 🙊🥹👋

Strength training is NOT just about here and now - your future self is actually thanking you 🙏 

Why?

Because as we age our muscle mass and bone mass density declines, resistance training helps offset this otherwise dramatic loss of muscle and bone mineral density.

Evidence suggest resistance based training in cancer survivors is not only well-tolerated in cancer patients, but also a tool to counteract adverse effects of cancer and its treatment. 

Resistance training in youths is not only safe but is also a great way to prepare their bodies for the physical demands of sport.

Resistance training in athletes is a pivotal part of every sport.

So if resistance or strength training is so important to everyone - young, old, sick, or sporty - why isn’t everyone doing it? 🤔

I’ll leave that question with you 🤔

What a bloody gorge weekend 🫶

From CrossFit comps to Bingo Loco to City2Surf and finished off with some footy 😜

Feeling very appreciative of my lovely Oz Fam this weekend ❤️

Trip Down Memory Lane 🫶

Once upon a time, I based my worth on how I looked.  I restricted. I binged. I did every crunch known to man. I did hours of endless cardio. I punished myself with exercise. I acted like the most confident person in the world to hide how I really felt about myself 😭

Fast forward 8 years, I know that confidence means - it’s not trying to make people like you but being absolutely fine if they don’t 🙏 I’m happier, healthier, fitter and stronger than I’ve ever been ❤️ I’m so proud of my journey and how far I’ve come 💪

My new obsession is sharing - not only my knowledge, but my journey. It’s been a long road, but it’s a path best not walked alone ❤️🙏 If you want to become they healthiest, happiest, most confident version of yourself - I CAN HELP 🙋‍♀️

I have one coaching space left for August. Dm me - COACH 🫶

caption:
Is protein really that important? 🤔
.
.
1. Amino Acids are proteins building blocks and we NEED these for recovery. Remember recovery is not only essential if you train, our bodies recover every single day.

2. Satiety - every sit down to eat 3 chicken breasts? Doubtful because protein rich foods are so filling. They also help stabilise our blood sugars and reduce cravings. So get your protein in 👊

3. Thermic Effect from Food (TEF) - Did you know that TEF has the same effect on our TDEE as purposeful exercise? 🤔 Did you know protein actually requires more energy to break down than fats or carbohydrates? 🤔 So double whammy here 👊
.
.
Long story short - eat yo protein 🤤
.
.
 How much?
💫 Gold Standard = 2g/kg BW/day 
(But anything between 1.5-2 is very good)
.
.
Save this post and drop any questions below⬇️⬇️⬇️

caption:
5 Reasons you’re not achieving your results 🚨🚨

1. Lack of consistency - this is usually the main problem. Working hard Monday to Friday to blow it all at weekends. Strict rigid dieting for 6 weeks to blow it all for the 6 months afterwards. Consistency is KEY to achieving your results.

2. You are impatient - we want results yesterday 😖 As opposed to playing the long game with our health, we put a time line on it and expect our results to reflect that time line.

3. Your goals are totally unrealistic - Having abs as a female (for majority of females) requires two things.
A. An unhealthy body fat percentage 
B. Sacrifices most people are NOT willing to make to achieve it. 
So lower your expectations 🙏

4. What is your why? 
I want to lose weight is not enough. When the motivation is low - ‘I want to lose weight won’t cut it’. 

‘I want to feel amazing on my wedding day’ 
‘I want enough energy to play with my kids’
‘I want to feel comfortable in a bikini’ 
👆these will 👆

5. No roadmap to your goals - this is a very common one. A lot of people set off on their health and fitness journeys alone with no support or help. A majority fail - why? They have absolutely no guidance, no help and no clear cut roadmap to HOW they achieve their results. 

If you want to finally get results and stop failing. I’m looking for 2 new clients. Dm me ‘HELP’ today 💪

caption:
Overnight weight gain is NOT fat!!!!!

Stop. With. The. Nonsense ✋

Just because a scale weight fluctuates this is not an excuse for you to throw in the towel.

Anyone who has ever played sport - if the other team scores do you just quit? No you continue playing until the end.

Unlike sport, your health and fitness should not have an end date or time. You should always be playing the long game and finding a sustainable approach to the person you want to become. 

And that person is NOT determined by a number on a scales.

So next time you want to have a breakdown that you’ve GAINED fat overnight - refer back to this post, hell throw out that scales if it has that much of an impact on your head. And remember, daily flucuations happen. It is not a reflection of your progress! 

Keep going 💪

caption:
Protein Snacks 🍴🤤

An area I know a lot of people struggle with is increasing protein in their diet. Based on the poll I put up yesterday - those who wanted more help - I’ve tagged you 🙋‍♀️

Main meals seem to be easier to get protein in but there's definitely a disconnect when it comes to protein snacks. Although keep an eye for protein in main meals too. 

While most people would have protein bars etc. Included in here - a lot of these options are highly processed and the protein quality is poor (I am NOT saying don't eat them. I would just not be relying heavily on them for protein sources). 

Hope this helps. Save for later 👇

caption:

I have been there. I have been the girl trying to be the smallest version of myself, wishing and hoping it would make me happier. 

I’ve restricted too 🙋‍♀️So much so that weekends would come and I’d binge like there was no tomorrow.

But now here I am, trying to save you from the person I once was.

You can be the happiest, healthiest, fittest, strongest version of yourself - and you can actually enjoy the process 🥰

You want to hear more? Dm me ‘HAPPY’ and I’ll tell you!

caption:
Protein Squares

Ingredients: (makes 6)
Tbsp maple syrup
3 tbsp coconut oil
4 heaped tbsp peanut butter 
2 scoops protein powder
4 Corncakes
50g Dark Chocolate 

Heat coconut oil, syrup and peanut butter. Add 2 scoops protein and stir. Crush corncakes and add to mixture. Stir and coat corncakes. Place in baking tray and spoon melted dark chocolate over. Place in fridge for 2 hours.

Save for later.

caption:
There are a few circumstances where people ‘don’t have time’ but more often than not - It’s just not a priority! 

Health and fitness should not be difficult. It should be something that fits into your lifestyle and not something you have to force. But we over complicate it. 

Some of the things you DON’T need to do to become healthier, fitter and happier:

❌ Cut out carbs
❌Cut out sugar
❌ Exercise 7 days a week 
❌ Drink detox juices/teas
❌ Eat 1000 Calories or less 
❌ Train twice a day
❌ Train longer than an hour in the gym

I can promise you - I can make health and fitness part of your lifestyle. I will offer a money back guarantee I’m so sure of myself 💪🙌 DM me ‘PRIORITY’ if you’re ready to make health and fitness a priority 🥰

caption:
Throwback to one of my last trips away. Next on the agenda is Fiji 🇫🇯❤️ 

A parcel arrived yesterday with some holiday and summer pieces and it got me thinking 🤔 

Things have changed so much in the last few years…

A few years ago, 4 weeks out from a holiday I would be cutting carbs and doing crunches for that bikini 👙 

Now, the bikini takes me as I am. ❤️

There is nothing WRONG with wanting to look and feel good in a bikini. Actually the total contrary I think it is VITALLY important for us. 

But contrary to what people think, being smaller DOES NOT equal happier 😱

If you are not happy in a bikini, you need to find out why 🤔 When you get to the root of it, more often than not you’ll realise the bikini was never the problem! 

I strived to be smaller and leaner. And at my smallest and leanest, I was still direly uncomfortable in a bikini 😱🥹

Now, I’m happy, healthy and strong. I’m at least a dress size bigger and sometimes I chaf 🙊 But, now putting on a bikini does not bother me.

I want to help women realise your dress size has nothing to do with your happiness. That scale weight is just one representation of progress. I want women to put on a bikini and stop worrying about how they look and focus more on how they feel ❤️

This is my mission. I’m already on the road to success. Who wants to join me? 🥂

2 months muscle up progress 🙌💪

Lost some chicken wings 🍗
Gained some hips to bar ✅

And the journey to gymnast continues…

#whendoesgymnasticsgeteasier

caption:
Read what some of my current clients are saying about my Strong and Sassy programme 👂👂👂

I asked some ladies to tell their success stories. Success is different to everyone. Goals are individual. But when I read things like this it sets my heart alight ❤️‍🔥

If you want to share a similar success story. Why not get in contact today 💪

Are you ‘eating healthy’ but not seeing a shift on the scales? 

Eating healthy, not eating junk, not eating chocolate ≠ Fat Loss 

It is a very common problem I see and it is VERY possible to over consume healthy foods. 

What we are looking for is overall energy balance. 

If you are ‘eating healthy’ but not seeing results - DM me 😇

There are things in life that give us energy and we need more of in our life. Obvious ones including exercise and good wholesome foods - but the list is much longer than that 🙌🙏
Do you do these things on a daily basis? 

And then there are things we do that zap the energy from us - these are things we need to discourage or reduce in life 🙏

Make sure you’re tipping the scales in the right direction 🙌

What a bloody day ❤️🙏

Thank you so so much to everyone who came to my first workshop yesterday 🙏🙌 I feel so grateful to be able to help educate women about how to work with their bodies, and how important nutrition, movement and sleep are for your overall health.

The group of ladies were absolutely fabulous from start to finish were fantastic and made the day the success it was with their willingness to learn ❤️

Thanks @niamhmulvey who started the day with a lovely meditation and set us up for the day 🙏 To my incredible colleagues @chris.strengthandmovementlab @d_rigknee who put the women through some movement and educated them on the importance of movement and training 💪 @strengthandmovementlab was the perfect facility for the workshop and I feel very grateful to work in a space that have the same ethos as me 🙏

caption:
I’m an over thinker 🙋‍♀️

Yep I overthink everything. I’ve a situation made up in my head, I have the whole story told to myself and it has about 10 endings - all of them negative 🙊😱 I’m working on this.

Do you overthink?

Do you write your own story. Do you tell yourself 
- I’m not good enough
- I’ll never be able
- I’m too old
- I’m not fit enough
- I could never look like that

If you DIDN’T overthink - what would be the outcome? What could the best possible case scenario be? 

Because let me tell you - YOU AND YOUR MIND are the ONLY things holding you back.

If you don’t try - that is the ONLY time you will fail. 

Quick story - once upon a time I studied to become a fitness instructor. I felt so far out of my depth at the gym with everyone that was there. We had to strength test. One of the tests was chin ups (I was no where NEAR being able to do a chin up) so the alternative was an inverted row. I couldn’t even do 1 inverted row. Last week, I did a workout with 15 Inverted Rows which I did WITH EASE!!!! 8 years later, the effort I have been putting in is coming to fruition. 

It may take time but you CAN achieve whatever it is you want - but your mind needs to play ball ⚽️

Every week I’m trying to be a Big Strong Girl and a Gymnast 🤸‍♀️ 💪

And each week I get rudely reminded - I’m a cardio bunny 🐰

#godlovesatrier #roadtobeingagymnast #crossfit

I’ve always been a little different.
I’ve never been a party animal 🤷‍♀️3 nights of drinking was never ‘the norm’. I’m always the first in bed 😂

That’s not to say I don’t drink. I love a good night out. I love to dance and if I make it to a sing song it’s my favourite part of the night 🥰

But I’d much rather a Saturday morning gym session to a Friday night drink session.

I’d pick waking up for sunrise over staying up till sunrise.

I’d rather spend my money on food and supplements than alcohol and drugs. 

I’ve more gym gear than I do ‘normal’ clothes.

It’s ok to be different. And it’s ok to change 🙏

As long as it aligns with your goals and values ❤️ don’t try to be someone you’re not. Don’t try and do something you’re not comfortable with - to fit in. Don’t lose sight of your morals ❤️ 

Be unapologetically you ❤️

caption:
It’s not always about nutrition and exercise 🤷‍♀️ Controversial I know 🙊

I believe the 4 pillars of a healthy lifestyle are:
1. Nutrition
2. Exercise
3. Sleep
4. Stress Management 

❌Stop trying so hard to exercise more and learn to go to bed earlier 

❌Stop stressing over the ‘perfect’ diet

Look after these 4 elements and the results will follow….

How to get better at Bench Press and Pull Ups

1. Most important is frequency and volume 
✅ Pull Ups - Slow eccentrics, change grip, use Rings/Trx 
✅ Bench Press - Dumbbell Press, Floor Press, Push Ups, Inclince Press

You need to be hitting some form of these movements AT LEAST twice a week to progress.

2. Assistance Exercises 
It’s not all about doing more and more volume. Are you doing other back exercises to build a strong back? Do you neglect isolation exercises? 
A good programme will incorporate all of the above.

3. Nutrition for performance
If you are not eating enough, of course performance will suffer. Eat to fuel your body 🥦🍏🍉🥑🍚

Drop questions below.

Hot Momma Alert 🚨 🚨 🚨

Emily is a new Mum who came to me ‘get back to her pre pregnancy shape’. She wanted to be ‘less flabby’ and stronger.

She started the programme at 68kg and has dropped a whopping 10kg since the 21st March 🎉Now the calories are at maintenance and we are full steam ahead to become the strongest, healthiest Mum we can get 💪❤️🙏

In her own words - 
‘Incredibly happy doesn’t even cut it tbh Amanda, I’m in better shape then I was before I had Eva/EVER, you always say it and it’s so true, why wouldn’t you ask for help with something as life changing as this.
I asked for help and look at my results 💪’

👉 Are you post partum looking to get back to ‘feeling yourself’?

👉 Do you feel like you have ‘no time’? 

👉 Do you think you can never get back to pre pregnancy you? 

If you’re feeling ‘stuck’ please reach out 🙌❤️

The easiest way to change your habits? 

Change your environment 🫵🫵🫵

That could be connecting with more like minded people, it could be changing job, moving house or having a colder bedroom. 

 But remember- nothing changes if nothing changes!!!!

You want to see change? 
Make a change 🫵

Grainne (physio and mother) was looking to get back on the pitch post partum. 

She surpassed all expectations of her body and was back flying fit with the aid of a post partum training programme and nutrition education.

If you are looking to get back to exercise after having a baby, why not Dm me? I’m a pre and post natal coach. Currently, I am working with a lot of post natal clients who are achieving amazing results and feeling the best they have felt in years!

Want that to be you?

Happy Birthday to my best friend ❤️ @lift__with__laura 

Thank you for being you 😘 Love you to the moon and back 🌙❤️

Meet Michelle 

Michelle (31) is a busy dog mom who came to me in January and needed accountability. She also wanted education and a long term solution to health and fitness.

Michelle was very sporty when she was younger and when she gets into a good routine she feels great. She is competitive so exercise is not a problem for her.

Her goals included fat loss and body confidence and feeling pride in what she’s doing.

Well I guess you could say she’s achieving her goals 💪 Thankfully, she has a great training environment with incredible programming. Last week she hit PBs in all her lifts - this lady is STRONG 💪💪💪

She is getting strong AF (110kg 3 RM Deadlift, 90kg 3RM Squat, 42.5kg 3 RM bench) but her body shape is changing 👉

Now here is the mind blowing fact 🤯 Michelle has not changed on the scales - this is the EXACT reason why we should NOT use scales as our only measure of progress.

6 months in and she is achieving BIG things 💪💪💪

Would you like results like Michelle? Dm me!

𝐃𝐨𝐧'𝐭 𝐧𝐞𝐠𝐥𝐞𝐜𝐭 𝐟𝐚𝐭𝐬
.
.
Fat gets a bad rep. 
Sure it is 9Kcal per gram but it is an essential part of a balanced fat. 
.
.
Fats provide us with energy, makes up our cell membranes of our brain and nervous system. Fats are necessary to transport vitamins A,D,E and K and make and balance certain hormones.
.
.
Dietary Fat can be found in 2 forms:
Saturated – mainly found in animal products like meat, dairy, eggs, coconut
Unsaturated – found in marine sources like fish oils, as well as nuts, seeds and vegetable oils
.
. 
For years saturated fat was thought to be associated with higher risk of Cardiovascular Disease and so it was deemed as ‘unhealthy’ or ‘bad for you’. The problem with saturated fat was not the actual fat itself but rather the increased consumption of processed food or the large quantities of saturated fat products. Saturated fat helps increase the cholesterol production in the body which is an essential part of metabolism and in the production of steroid hormones. So saturated fat should feature in our diet, just maybe don’t latter every meal in butter.
.
. 
Unsaturated fats are made up of mono and polyunsaturated fats.  These contain our omega 3 and omega 6 fatty acids. Omega 3 fatty acids open our airways and blood vessels. They reduce our blood lipids and cholesterol and lower inflammation and pain. Omega 6 fatty acids do the opposite. Both are needed in the body, without both we wouldn’t heal or recover from exercise. The problem with Western diets is that we don’t have the proper ratios. We are at about 10:1 where we should be at 2:1 (omega 6/omega 3).
.
. 
Low fat diets were a fad a few years ago. While people reduced calories, they increased their intake of processed foods. Diets lacked fats and fat soluble vitamins so instead of being healthier people were losing weight but were not healthier.
.
. 
Fats are an essential part of any healthy diet. Be aware that they are very calorie dense so portion control may be important and don’t opt for processed versions. Enjoy them as part of a balanced lifestyle.

caption:
By saying yes to something - you are ultimately saying no to something else.

I’ll give you a little example - at the weekend I had a CrossFit competition - it meant I had to say no to a friends birthday on Saturday.

For years and years, I gave up all my social Occassions to say yes to playing football.

I used to be a yes person. I would say yes to everything - I’d help everyone.
At one stage when I lived at home I was:
Managing a gym, looking after my mother who was in hospital, playing football with Roscommon and Garrycastle, helping train Roscommon u14 girls AND Garrycastle Minor girls 😵‍💫🥴 That’s not to mention trying to spend time with my partner and friends.

I learned how to say no from working with a life coach and it was one of the best things I’ve ever learned to do. I encourage and promote saying no to things with my clients too.

Saying no has added benefits - not only are you NOT doing what you don’t WANT to do but you end up saying yes to what you do want.

An example of saying no. Last bank holiday weekend I refused to make plans - I wanted to just go with the flow - see what happened, I ultimately wanted to chill. I said no to making plans and in turn I had a lovely chilled, relaxed weekend 🫶

Are you a yes or a no person?

caption:
Coffee - Yay or nay 

Here are some of my top tips:
❌ Stop using coffee as an appetite suppressant 
🚫 Does having a little milk in your coffee break your fast? Who cares 🙊
❌ Stop abusing it - do you need 17 cups a day - highly unlikely
🚫 More coffee ≠ more energy (quite often over consumption of coffee will lead to you feeling burnt out and tired)
❌ Stop drinking it in the afternoon - I don’t care if you say ‘it doesn’t affect me’ - it most likely DOES affect your sleep quality

✅ Enjoy in moderation 
✅ If you have a sensitive stomach - perhaps eat before your morning coffee 
✅ Have the coffee you enjoy - Although long black is king 👑 

Who’s not a coffee fan?

caption:
Greens for Breakfast 🍌🥭🍍🌱

I know some people struggle to get colour into their breakfast so here’s a super simple and quick way.

- Frozen Fruit 
- Mint 
- Green Powder 
- Water 

I have this along side a substantial breakfast off eggs and toast. If you were rushed for time - why not simply add protein powder - voila you have a balanced smoothie for breakfast 🌱

Someone asked me recently if I miss football…

I have Sundays free…
I don’t feel like I have 2 jobs…
I actually get to see my boyfriend…

So honestly, no I don’t miss the sport.

That’s not to say I don’t miss the people ❤️

But I still get the team training environment. I still eat, sleep and train like an athlete.
And I have so much more free time and control of what I do.

I don’t regret playing football. It was some of the best years of my life. And some of the life skills I’ve learned - I owe to football. But for me, the fire quenched a long time before quitting. 

If there is a part of your life, you’re not happy with. You have full control of changing it.

I didn’t quit football out of fear of not being ‘Amanda the footballer’ anymore. It was actually such an engrained part of my character. And now, the people I’ve met in Australia have never even met that person 😅

Don’t let fear dictate your choices. Do what sets your heart on fire ❤️‍🔥

What am I trying to promote?

I want women to become thier healthiest, strongest, most confident selves 🙏

I encourage women to ‘attend to their own oxygen masks first’. 🫶

I want women to realise being confident in a bikini has very little to do with how you look and everything to do with how you feel. ❤️

I’m just out here trying to practice what I preach and make all queens realise how incredible they are 👑

caption:
If you are still using scales as your only measure of progress? 

If so, check out Blaithin’s progress!

We treat our phones and cars better than we treat our bodies 🥹😫

❌ You wouldn’t put the wrong fuel into your car? Why? It’d damage the engine? 

❌ You wouldn’t let your battery go dead on your phone? Why? Because you need your phone!

By choosing to make poor food choices, drink too much alcohol and not drink enough water - we are choosing to fill our bodies with the ‘wrong fuel’. By choosing to not prioritise sleep and be sedentary, we have no energy. 

The choices you make daily shape and align the person you become. 

Do me a favour - from today - stop prioritising your phone and car more than you prioritise yourself 🙌

caption:
I've always been very open minded.
.
.
I pride myself on it actually. I've alway been a pro choice kinda girl in all aspects of life (not just health and fitness related). You'll never hear me boast about one type of diet or slate any either. You won't hear me downgrade any form of exercise, although I do openly talk about the huge benefits of resistance training 💪 I'll never tell any of my client's 'you cannot eat this for weight loss'. If someone who loves yoga comes to me, I'm not going to force them to lift weights. And if someone who is vegan comes to me, I would not force them to eat animal products. My problem with any of these things lies in the misinformation. 
.
.
Did you know that vegan fast food production has sky rocketed in recent years? 🤔 Similarly, a few years ago, gluten free products were a huge trend? And before that, sugar free was the hype? This I have a problem with.
.
.
Veganism is a lifestyle choice. I have huge respect for anyone's lifestyle choices, whether they conform to my own is irrelevant. What actually annoys me is actual vegans are getting a terrible name due to all these people jumping on the bandwagon, thinking veganism is the healthiest lifestyle going. People are going into this lifestyle, uneducated and naive. 😒 It was the same a few years ago when gluten free was the buzzword. Did you know you can have a totally adequate, balanced, healthy diet without adding one gluten free product? And thats for ACTUAL coeliacs out there, because they are the ONLY people that need to be eating gluten free toast 😂
.
.
What my very long winded post is trying to say is stop jumping on bandwagons. If you are and always have been vegan, that's fine. Continue with your choices. If you are coeliac, continue with your gluten free bread 🙈 
.
For the rest of you, stop following trends by the latest celebrity diet.
❎ Stop conforming to social norms ✊ 
❎Stop basing your beliefs on a bloody stupid documentary 😒 
✅Get some advice from a professional. 🙏
✅ Follow said advice 🌈 
✅ And unfollow anyone giving terrible, uneducated advice 
.
.

caption:
7 things I wish I knew in my early 20s. I dont want you to make the same mistakes I made.

1. Being consistently good is better than being occasionally perfect.

2. The weekend makes up a large part of the week. If you think you’re being good during the week and not making progress - take a look at your weekends.

3. Sleep is one of the most underestimated tools to help you achieve ANY goal. If you’re sleep is shit and you’re sacrificing it ‘to seize the morning’ and train at 6am - you may be doing more harm than good.

4. Water consumption is the simplest way to becoming a healthier version of yourself. Stop looking at fad diets, detox teas, apple cider vinegar and look at your hydration status. Dehydration affects every system in our body and can lead to lack of energy, low mood, injury and brain fog (to mention afew).

5. Human connection, vitamin D and exercise are some of the most under utilised mental health prescriptions. Try increase all of these on the daily to see an instant mood shift 🙏

6. Stop trying to be a people pleaser and learn to say no - you are your own most important asset. 

7. Live every day like it’s your last ❤️ Do what makes you happy! 

Would you add anything to the list?

caption:
You are not weak if you ask for help ❌❌❌
In Fact if anything I think you're a little more courageous 
🤩🤩🤩
.
.
You are not expected to know everything. That's why people have occupations with the relevant knowledge and skills to help 👌
.
.
💥 If you are a student, unsure of your path. Please talk to a career guidance teacher.
💥 If you are unsure of your career and thinking about changing everything for a different route. Maybe you could see a life coach.
💥 If you are sick. See a doctor.
💥 If you are having mental health issues, a counsellor may be an option
💥 If you're having car troubles, go to a mechanic.
💥 If your phone isn't working, bring it to a phone shop.
.
.
See the trend???
.
.
Once upon a time I thought I was totally independent. I didn't want to ask for help from anyone!!! But then I realised, I can't do it all alone and actually support and guidance is the best thing I could get. NOW, I ask for help all the time. From family, friends, and colleagues. I have a coach. If my mental health is affecting me I call someone for help. One of the best things I ever did was see a life coach ❤
.
.

.

caption:
How Eibhlin decided she no longer needs permission to do things for herself and how she is the master of her own destiny.

Eibhlin is a 42 year old busy mum of 3. She wanted to do my Strong and Sassy programme as has a big holiday coming up in June and ‘wanted to feel stronger and more confident’.

Before we started working together, Eibhlin had been through a few lockdowns, had developed some bad nutrition habits and had lost a lot of fitness. With her holiday looming, she wanted to gain structure as well as get fitter and stronger. 

She delayed a little in reaching out to me as she wasn’t 100% ready but as soon as she did - she signed up straight away - knowing this was the right programmme for her. 

‘The app is great and I realise I actually love working out on my own! I can do it in my time and the programme is tailored to me’

Fast forward 2 months and Eibhlin cannot believe the change in her progress photos. She had no originally joined for weight loss but is pleasantly surprised by the secondary effects of an overall healthy lifestyle. 

'I recommend this programme for mothers’

If you're like Eibhlin, you’re a mom with limited time looking to drop a dress size or get stronger and more confident, I'd love to help you get there. 

Comment 'STRONG' below and I'll directly reach out to you and determine if I can help.

A huge issue I see amongst women is their lack of knowledge and understanding of nutrition. They have no clue what to do to achieve that body confidence they desire 😢 

Are you constantly fad dieting because you're afraid if you're not dieting you will gain weight. You're afraid that if you don't stick to that deficit you'll never be happy in your clothes. 

I feel terrible for you, because you're genuinely trying. You know no different. We've grown up with fad dieting, our mothers  yo yo dieted. It's all we've known - we only know strict calorie deficits and exercise to burn calories 😢 

But I've found the solution to your problems. I believe in education. Have you ever heard the saying “If you give a man a fish, you feed him for a day. If you teach a man to fish, you feed him for a lifetime.” I want you to understand you CAN ACHIEVE results and ENJOY the food you love 😍 

Are you interested in learning more about nutrition? Do you want to achieve bikini confidence and enjoy a balanced diet? I'm going to explain all tomorrow. 

Comment ME below and I'll tag you tomorrow when its up!

Yesterday I told you about time being a problem for women trying to change their body shape. They feel they can't give full commitment to a programme because they are too busy. 

They feel they have no time to go to the gym because they are too busy. 

Thankfully a lot of my clients train from home 3 times a week with minimal equipment. 

You see the thing is - you don't actually need hours in the gym to achieve your goals - especially if you're crazy busy. I also encourage women to make better choices if they are too busy to cook. And instead of scrolling on Social media - I set step targets for them (even if they scroll while they walk). 

You see - it's pretty simple. Try this out and let me know how it goes. 

P.s I'm looking for 5 more women who want to become bikini confident with restriction in the next 12 weeks. If that's you, DM me the word 'ME'

Another common problem I see most women have when they are trying to change their body shape is time to commit to a programme. 

We all lead such busy lifestyles these days. We give time to our families, our friends, and work and we are left with little to no time. 

It's so frustrating because you're trying to be a good friend, mother, daughter, sister, colleague, or employee. But what's left for you? Or maybe there is time? 

I've found that most people usually can find time. Maybe instead of an hour of Netflix we could swap it for a workout? Maybe instead of scrolling we could be walking? Or instead of picking up a takeaway on the way home from work, we could pick up a ready meal in a supermarket? The problem lies in trying to do too much.

Are you interested in learning about how you could commit to a programme even WITH limited time? 

Comment 'me' below and I'll tag you tomorrow when it's up.

How Helen changed her habits and became more confident over 12 weeks. 

Helen has been training on and off for years. Her main goal was to get into a good routine and be accountable. She was looking for a long term sustainable change - without restriction. 

Before we started working together Helen did programmes and trained - but as soon as she had a bad week or didn’t see the scales moving - she gave up. She found herself unhappy in her clothes and she was sick of stopping and starting. 

She hesitated in starting because of pride ‘She thought she could and should do it alone’. And if she's honest, she thought ‘I know what to do’. But she realised she needed direction, accountability and a community - which drove her to take action.

'I knew others who did Amanda’s programme and I knew it had a personal approach' ‘I knew there was a community environment to it and I liked that’

Fast forward 12 weeks and she feels so much happier and more confident.

'This programme is for anyone who is lacking direction’

If you want results like Helen - Dm me 'Helen’

How I became stronger, happier and more confident and how you can too. 

When I started in the fitness industry I was a little lost. I was focused on how I looked. I was obsessed with having abs. I only ate 'clean' food mid week which led to weekend binges. My relationship with nutrition and fitness definitely was not a healthy one. 

I wasn't happy. Not in my body. Not in my mind. I genuinely couldn't imagine continuing my life with this level of restriction and I began to resent the gym 😢 

Then I stopped focusing so much on HOW I looked. I stopped looking for abs every time I walked by the mirror. I started to appreciate resistance training and I began focusing on how much stronger I was becoming. My goals changed. Performance based goals replaced the quest for abs and I found my love for exercise again. I found a balanced approach to nutrition. I still eat very healthy and nutritious but I no longer restrict myself. 

I no longer focus on HOW I look but WHAT my body can do. I wear bikinis now without dieting to get in them. I'm stronger and fitter than I've ever been and clothes sizes no longer dictate my life. I'm happier and healthier. I love the skin I'm in ❤ 

And that's why I created my Strong and Sassy Programme to help women become bikini confident year round without restrictions. Comment 'CHANGE' below if you'd like for me to personally message you today and see if I can help you!

Yesterday, I told you about a common problem that most women experience when trying to change their body shape. 

No matter what diet they do, they can't stick to it at weekends.... 

To fix this problem I get my clients to find their non negotiables. 

What are non negotiables?
They are habits you can stick to NO MATTER WHAT the circumstances are. 

I usually recommend 3 of them.. 

3 things you can stick to every weekend.
For example - Drink 2 litres of water, walk 10,000 steps daily and 1 piece of fruit. 

It's pretty simple. Try this out and let me know how it goes. 

P.s I'm looking for 5 MORE ladies who want to be bikini confident year round without giving up the foods they enjoy. If that's you DM me 'Bikini'.

caption:
A common problem I see most women have when they are trying to change their body shape is their struggle to stay on track at weekends 🐒🐷 

You may notice yourself cutting calories during the week and then all hell breaks lose at weekends and you're afraid that if you continue this way you'll never achieve that bikini body 😢 

It's so frustrating because you're really trying to make a change. What's actually causing this is a binge restrict cycle that you've developed over the years. We only know and understand nutrition at 2 levels - 'really good' or 'really bad' 

I've found the best solution to fix this is to SAY NO to the all or nothing approach - but this will require help. Accountability to someone who knows what they're talking about can definitely help with this. I've also found having non negotiables proves very helpful.

caption:
Let’s get one thing clear - there is no ‘good alcohol’ 🙈

But there are lower calorie options - check this out. 

Be aware that actions around alcohol are usually more detrimental to your goals than alcohol alone. The dehydration, poor sleep quality and numerous Uber ears are certainly not helping towards your goals 🙈

The sooner you start finding a better balance with socialising, alcohol and your overall health the better ❤️

#lowercalorieoptions #alcohol #alcoholoptions #under150calories

caption:
I can’t believe I still have to explain this but here I go again 💁‍♀️
.
.
When people said to Arnold Schwarzenegger 
'Oh but I don't want to look like you.'

He replied:
'Don't worry. You never will.'
.
.
Let me tell you. Building muscle is BLOODY HARD. You don't just wake up one day and 'are bulky' 😅😅😅
.
.
I've spent YEARS improving myself and getting stronger, fitter and healthier. That is my goal. So don't think after lifting afew weights you're going to gain 10kg of muscle and look 'bulky'. And honestly, most people will NEVER EVER train as hard as I train 😅 
.
.
But let me also tell you. Majority of the photos I take are mid or post training when I have a serious pump. In normal clothes, I'm a normal size 8-10 female. I don't have jacked quads or a shoulder vein 😅 (Even though I'd be happy to walk around like that)
.
.
Moral of the story: most people will never train hard enough to get bulky. Most people don't walk round jacked 😅 The 'toned' look you want is actually muscle - so if you say you want to be 'toned' and don't want muscle you're actually contradicting yourself 😅

Oh and if it wasn't already obvious - lift weights 🏋‍♀️

caption:
Do you have PCOS or a hormonal imbalance and have been told ‘you’ll always struggle with weight? 🤔

❌Don’t accept it❌

Grace came to me frustrated. She was doing HIIT style training and in a calorie deficit and couldn’t understand why she wasn’t achieving results 🙊

After introducing her to resistance training and increasing her calories and fat intake - she started seeing results 🙌

The key was her consistency. Months after finishing the programme she is still continuing with her new lifestyle and is repairing the rewards 🙌The scales haven’t changed too much but her body composition is totally different 🙋‍♀️

If this sounds like you - DM me and we’ll set up a call 📞

I see it so often, people working out or trying to train and exercise more but being sedentary for the other 23 hours of the day. 

If that sounds like you - Listen up 👂

Happiest when… with you ❤️🙏

I’m not going to start trying to give relationship advice 😅 But one thing I will say and encourage is try to give and take a little 🙏

I got these tickets for Owen back in December to celebrate his birthday month and I had 0 interest in coming (turns out now I actually really like it 😅).

Owen comes to my CF comps and watches competitions with me even though he hates burpees 😅

caption:
Stop comparing foods as like with like 🤦‍♀️
.
.
✅€30 = $44.12 AUD. But they are 2 totally different currencies.
✅1000 Tonnes Feathers = 1000 Tonnes Coal. But they are 2 totally different components. 
.
.
The same goes for food. 
.
.
100 Calories Apple = 100 Calorie Chocolate Bar (as a measure of calories). But you cannot compare them in composition. The lack of micronutrients, the high sugar and fat content in the chocolate bar cannot be easily compared to the vitamins, mineral, water and phytonutrients in the apple 🤦‍♀️
.
.
Since when was Maths ever that simple 😅 I am not saying Calories in versus calories out is non sense, because it isn't. It makes sense and is very important. All I'm saying is, it's not the ONLY thing that is important. Food quality matters for long term health benefits and body composition 🙌
.
.
Questions? 🤔

caption:
Just because something didn’t work for you before - doesn’t mean something can’t work? 🤷‍♀️

If you had a bad experience with an old banger of a car - do you quit driving? No you get another car. Maybe even upgrade to a better version 😜

There IS something out there that works for everyone. Just because you’ve tried 10 different things that haven’t worked doesn’t mean the next one can’t! 

If you’ve tried:
👉 Gyms
👉 Weight Watchers/Slimming World
👉 Personal training 
👉 Online Coach 
And none of them led to long term sustainable results. DM me. I’m happy to talk about your goals and if my coaching could work for you 🙏🙌

Why are you so anti weight loss? 🤔

LET’S GET ONE THING STRAIGHT. I am NOT anti weight loss. I am pro health. If weight loss is going to make you healthier - I am ALL for it 🙋‍♀️

But let’s get one thing straight. Weight loss ≠ happiness. 

Let me tell you something personal - that not many people know/realise.

When I was younger, I dressed to impress. Not myself but others. I craved attention so much, I wore clothes to reflect the amount of attention I knew I’d receive. I made out that I was this confident queen when inside I was falling apart 😢

Fast forward to now - I dress for me 💃 I feel like the belle of the ball when I wear something that shows off my strong, healthy body ❤️ 

My point - I don’t look much different from then until now. But my mindset - poles apart. 🙏

So I will reiterate - Health is and always will be my number 1 priority - physical and mental. Being happy, comfortable and confident is a really difficult place to get to and no scale weight or clothes size will measure that. 

Everyday I am changing people’s lives - scales drop as a bi product of a healthier lifestyle. But their happiness, confidence and self worth is the goal 🦋🙌

If you’re interested in becoming the healthiest, happiest, most confident version of yourself. Dm me ‘Coach’

caption:
Is protein really that important? 🤔
.
.
1. Amino Acids are proteins building blocks and we NEED these for recovery. Remember recovery is not only essential if you train, our bodies recover every single day.

2. Satiety - every sit down to eat 3 chicken breasts? Doubtful because protein rich foods are so filling. They also help stabilise our blood sugars and reduce cravings. So get your protein in 👊

3. Thermic Effect from Food (TEF) - Did you know that TEF has the same effect on our TDEE as purposeful exercise? 🤔 Did you know protein actually requires more energy to break down than fats or carbohydrates? 🤔 So double whammy here 👊
.
.
Long story short - eat yo protein 🤤
.
.
 How much?
💫 Gold Standard = 2g/kg BW/day 
(But anything between 1.5-2 is very good)
.
.
Save this post and drop any questions below⬇️⬇️⬇️

caption:
Health and Happiness 🙏

These are the two most important things to me. And I try to preach this believe to my clients 🙋‍♀️

⛔️If you are looking for a quick fix, I’m not your girl.
⛔️If you are looking for an 8 week challenge, I’m not your girl.

But if you want to become the healthiest and happiest version of yourself - Dm me ‘Health’.

READ THE CAPTION! 

This one is important.

For those of you who don’t know - my Dad died of pancreatic cancer aged 50 (5 days before his 51st birthday).

Since his death, two things have been hugely prominent in my life - 
1. Your health is your wealth 
2. I was put on this Earth to help people 

Yesterday I paid almost $600 on blood tests. The receptionist asked me ‘Are you sure you want this one? It’s the most expensive’ (the blood test in Question was related to my Dads condition which I want to do any test for that I can). 
I actually couldn’t believe she asked me that 🤔 But I realised people have probably declined to pay that price. I’m not gonna lie the price came as a shock to me, and I had to fiddle between bank accounts to hand it over. But never ONCE did it cross my mind to not pay. You see to me, my health is priceless. I am willing to invest or hand over WHATEVER I need to, to ensure I am as healthy as I possibly can be. And to me, that money was a NECESSITY! 

I cannot believe people put a price on their health 😱 Your health literally is your wealth! 

That brings me to my second realisation. I need to help as many women as possible in this world to realise your health is your wealth. Not just physical, but mental too. 
⛔️Hating your body is not healthy
⛔️ Constant dieting is not healthy
⛔️ Exercising to burn calories is not healthy
⛔️ Trying to look like someone else is not healthy

I want to educate women about nutrition without restriction. I want to help women become the healthiest, happiest, most confident versions of themselves ❤️🙏
If you want to make a change to your health, Dm me ‘Health’ today 🙌

caption:
𝙀𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙣𝙜 𝙤𝙣 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙜𝙤 🚗
.
.
These days we are busy. Sometimes maybe even too busy to food prep 🙈
.
.
I've been there 🙋‍♀️ I used to eat on the go ALL THE TIME. If I didn't have Tupperware I had to make do with what I could get in the shops 🙌 I can promise you though, you do NOT have to revert to delis and unhealthy options just because you're not prepared 👊
.
.
Here are some examples of meals I used to eat on the go. (P.S I still eat a lot of these types of meals because convenience is key for me 😜) but luckily now I get @hunger_gains_ - convenience and amazing tasting healthy food. Win win 🥳🙋‍♀️
.
All of these require minimal time and effort. And you knit pick and say 'Packet bought chicken isn't the healthiest?' Well Susan... it's better than that sausage roll you reached for last week 🙈😅
.
.
💢 You can have excuses or results 👊 You can't have both 💢

I’m no gymnast 🤸‍♀️

But I have been trying 🙈

Not that it made ANY difference for the Open 😅

My promise to you all - to get a reel to show you some beautiful muscle ups ❌🍗

caption:
𝐈 𝐡𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐛𝐞𝐞𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐞...
.
.
That God damn comparison bubble again.
.
.
Oh if only I had her legs 🤔
.
.
Why does she have a washboard stomach and I don't 😭
.
.
Omg would she ever cover up. Who does she think she is 🙀
.
.
I was so obsessed with comparing myself to other women. I was so certain if I looked like other people I would be happier in my own body. I was indoctrinated. I used to look up Owen's exes for Christ sake and compare myself 😅 (Just so you know if any of you follow me 😅). 
.
.
So how did I get to present day Amanda? My God it took time and a lot of effort. Took some counselling too 🤟 Becoming happy comfortable and confident in my body took gratitude, talking to myself and listening to a lot of positive self help books. 
.
.
I started to appreciate how incredible my body is. Not for what it looks like but what it can do. And after that changed, so did my whole outlook.
.
.
I still get a little envious (of a good tan 😍😍😍) but I'm pretty darn happy with my body. I no longer compare it to smaller waist sizes. I'm not upset any more that I have a little pouch (that's my happiness pouch). 
.
.
I'm proud of my body. And you should be too ❤
.
.
P.s Appreciating a rocking body is different 😍 I'm allllllll about that
👊 But I'm happy in my own 👊

#happyinmyownskin

caption:
Sarah’s Story

Sarah is a busy mum to Edie who came to me with the goals:
1. Keep up with her daughter - have more energy
2. Weight loss
3. Get healthier and feel better
4. Wear a swimsuit

Now it was not all plain sailing for this lady. She spent over 3 months in a moon boot. Anyone else would throw the towel in. But not Sarah 💪

She used this as an opportunity to perfect her nutrition and work on her upper body strength 🙌 

If you would like to get healthier, feel better and wear a swimsuit with confidence. Dm me ‘Sarah’.

I used to be the pickiest eater ever…

I changed and you can too!

It’s very easy for me to spout on about how great my coaching is…

I genuinely believe I am changing people’s lives on a daily basis.

But don’t take my word for it, take Elaine’s.

Elaine came to me as a footballer with goals to prevent injury and get stronger.

One of my fondest memories of Elaine during my programme was her epiphany of taking progress photos.
‘I don’t want to take them every 2 weeks because I know if I don’t see results I’ll get disheartened. I’m happy with how I’m doing and I don’t need justification through photos’.

Yes girl 🙌

If you’re like Elaine - want to get stronger, learn long lasting nutrition habits and get that all important accountability. 

Dm me ‘Elaine’ and I’ll get back to you ASAP.

Good Karma 💫💥☄️

⭐️ When a person does something good and that individual’s positive actions seems to lead to positive consequences ⭐️

Also I can confirm the burpees were NOT a torture but a rest 😅

#ifyouknowyouknow

caption:
We are all creatures of habit 🐈‍⬛
.
.
And while those habits can be very beneficial, they can also hinder us from reaching our full potential 🚀
.
.
Same things goes for nutrition. Eat the same foods. Get the same nutrients. See the same results 👌
.
.
Eat more variety. Get more nutrients. See more benefits 🥳
.
.
That's the simplest way I can put it 🤷‍♀️
.
.
You don't have to overhaul change your diet. It could be as simple as adding a new fruit every week?
Or swapping chicken breasts for chicken thighs? What about adding quinoa instead of cous cous? Or swapping a stir fry for raw veggies? 
.
.
💥 Small changes = better results 💥

#nutritioncoach #nutritionist #onlinecoach #onlinecommunity #nutritioneducation

This is NOT fitness...
.
.
Surely I'm not the only person sick of seeing people pulling their upper abs up revealing a six pack and hashtagging it Fitness?? 
.
.
I'm pretty sure abs are not all that representative of fitness. And since when did one body shape become associated with fitness. 
.
.
My interpretation of fitness must be very different. I don't see fitness as a visual
I see fitness as an active representation. 

Fitness is NOT an influencer posing in her sponsored underwear or cute matching outfits. Fitness is red faces, strange facial expressions, a sense of achievement and accomplishment, the sweat. 

Let’s start making our expectations a little more realistic 🙏

Give this post a little share if you agree ❤

caption:
Let me talk about a bi product of feeling confident, feeling beautiful, sexy etc

This has an impact on the people around us. 

If we are happier, more confident, feel better it HAS an impact on husbands, partners and children.

Here are some of the implications that have happened because of my coaching:

‘Nicole felt great in a dress she wore at the weekend. Her boyfriend thought it was lovely to not hear her give out about herself for once’. 

‘Colleen’s husband was so proud of her for throwing out her weighing scales’

‘Karen’s daughter does her stretching and burpees with her’

This CAN be you too ❤️🙌Just DM me ‘Bikini’ if you’d like to feel bikini confident year round 🥰 

📸 @marceauphotography

Proud is an understatement ❤️🥰

Every coaching call I have been on since I started this journey…

Every individual call I do…

Every accountability message I send…

Every time I get to meet these fabulous females in person…

I know I am making a difference 🙏 They say you attract who you are. And these women are all successful, kind, caring, empathetic women looking to better themselves ❤️🙏 So if that describes me - I am beyond happy 💃

This community of strong and sassy women is just getting started 💪

‘Your busy doubting yourself, while others are intimidated by your full potential’

Reminder to myself and everyone else. Self doubt is normal. But don’t let it overtake you - you are enough ❤️🙏

My top tip: Immerse yourself with the people that uplift you, push you, encourage you and genuinely care for you ❤️ 

Self doubt is soon eliminated 😂

caption:
If your coach is not celebrating your daily/weekly/monthly/annual wins… 

Find yourself a new coach 👊

One of the saddest things I hear from females is past experiences with old coaches 😢 I’ve had numerous women who had been made feel like a failure because ‘They weren’t losing enough/expected amount of weight on scale each week’. ‘They were made to feel like they failed’

Ok coaches look I get it - a woman comes to you with one goal you want to help her achieve said goal. 

My approach with women is a little less hardcore. I’ve developed a soft spot. I think it’s important that if a female has not achieved her desired result you educate her on why this possibly occurred. Then, focus on what did happen over that time period - all the positives they achieved 🙏

My approach is ‘yes weight loss can and will occur but let’s focus on enjoying exercise, educating ourselves on nutrition and finding a lifestyle we can sustain forever. Bi product of that - weight loss 🤷‍♀️

𝙄𝙢𝙖𝙜𝙞𝙣𝙚 𝙉𝙊𝙏 𝙛𝙚𝙖𝙧𝙞𝙣𝙜 𝙖 𝙗𝙞𝙠𝙞𝙣𝙞 👙 ✖
.
.
𝐈𝐦𝐚𝐠𝐢𝐧𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐟𝐫𝐞𝐞𝐝𝐨𝐦 𝐨𝐟 𝐛𝐞𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐡𝐚𝐩𝐩𝐲 𝐢𝐧 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐛𝐨𝐝𝐲 𝐧𝐨 𝐌𝐀𝐓𝐓𝐄𝐑 𝐖𝐇𝐄𝐍 🙋‍♀️
.
.
𝙄𝙢𝙖𝙜𝙞𝙣𝙚 𝙉𝙊𝙏 𝙙𝙞𝙚𝙩𝙞𝙣𝙜 𝙗𝙚𝙛𝙤𝙧𝙚 𝙀𝙑𝙀𝙍𝙔 𝙝𝙤𝙡𝙞𝙙𝙖𝙮 🍔🥦
.
.
It is GENUINELY THE MOST EMPOWERING FEELING ❤ 😍
.
.
OK, I know what you're going to say back.....
.
.
That's easy for you to say. 
'Sure you've nothing to feel embarrassed about' (not my words - obviously)
.
.
Would you believe all of the above actually have VERY little to do with how actually look to other people and 100 percent have to do with how you feel about yourself on the inside 🙏
.
.
𝙸 𝚑𝚊𝚟𝚎 𝚋𝚎𝚎𝚗 𝚠𝚊𝚢 𝚕𝚎𝚊𝚗𝚎𝚛.
That does not mean I was happier. 
.
.

𝐌𝐲 𝐛𝐨𝐝𝐲 𝐢𝐬 𝐚 𝐛𝐢 𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐝𝐮𝐜𝐭 𝐨𝐟 𝐦𝐲 𝐥𝐢𝐟𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐲𝐥𝐞. 
I eat very well. I train regularly. And I generally look after my body. When Summer comes I'll probably gain a little extra body fat as my social life ramps up. 
.
.
But honestly, I don't view my body how most people view there's. I don't view it for what it looks like. I view it for what it can do. 
.
.

.
.

caption:
𝐏𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐨𝐝 𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐛𝐮𝐭 𝐤𝐧𝐨𝐰 𝐲𝐨𝐮'𝐫𝐞 𝐧𝐨𝐭 𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐠𝐧𝐚𝐧𝐭? 𝐑𝐞𝐚𝐝 𝐨𝐧... 🔴🔴🔴
.
.
Firstly, do you track your period? Do you even know when your period is due? If not, why not?
Cycles are a very important part of a woman's life and a lot of elements can be affected at different phases of our cycle and not just our hormones 🙀 💥Have you ever noticed you're more productive at certain times? 
💥 Noticed you're stronger at certain times?
💥 Is your sleep affected at certain times? 
What gets measured gets managed 👊👊👊
.
.
OK, so you've started tracking...
And you notice, ok my cycle length is a lot longer than normal (21-35 days). You know you're not pregnant (immaculate conception 😇). So what could it be?
.
.
There are many factors that may contribute to your irregular cycle. 
.
🔴𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐯𝐞𝐥
🔴𝐈𝐥𝐥𝐧𝐞𝐬𝐬
🔴𝐒𝐭𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐬
🔴𝐎𝐯𝐞𝐫 𝐞𝐱𝐞𝐫𝐜𝐢𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐠 
🔴𝐔𝐧𝐝𝐞𝐫 𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠
🔴𝐇𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐨𝐧𝐚𝐥 𝐈𝐦𝐛𝐚𝐥𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐞
🔴𝐀𝐥𝐜𝐨𝐡𝐨𝐥
.
.
Tracking will help you realise what your irregular cycle may be linked to.
I personally know travel and alcohol really disrupt mine but I never would have realised if I didn't track 👊
.
.
Ladies start getting to know and understand your body 🙌

#irregularcycles

There is not a lack of online coaches out there.

There is a lack of online coaches who deliver life changing results.

Know the difference!

Today I almost quit…

Comfort zones are great. Spending ‘most’ of your time there is fine - normal if you will. But if you want to grow you need to get out of that comfort zone.

Today I did just that. For a girl that is afraid to rock climb with a harness on, I was on clawing my way up a mountain today 😱

Ever heard the sayings -
 ‘Nothing changes if nothing changes 🤷‍♀️’

Or

‘If you want a different result - make a different choice’

When was the last time you ventured outside that comfort zone!?

❇️Maybe it was quitting a job you hate without having another opportunity lined up?
❇️Maybe it starting a new sport
❇️Maybe it was having a cold shower
❇️Maybe it was trying a new food
❇️Maybe it was speaking on instagram stories
❇️Maybe it was travelling

The list goes on…

I encourage you all to do it. It’s something I try to do multiple times a week (I’d like to say daily but I don’t think I do it that often). 
Adrenaline is an important hormone in our body and it is encouraged to release it (nobody is saying you have to sign up for an ultra marathon or live in the Antarctic).

Let me know some things you’ve done recently that were totally outside your comfort zone? 
⬇️⬇️⬇️

These results are going to be sustainable. Why? Because this lady has learned habits that will last her a lifetime 🔆

She is now back loving them gym and has a better relationship with food 🤙

If you are looking for a 6 week challenge. I’m not your gal. But if you’re looking for long term sustainable changes that are going to change you from the inside out - DM me 🤗

Aoife

28

Occupation
Farm Sustainability Manager

Original Goal when you started with me?

- Improve relationship with food, feel better in myself, lose weight

Largest Obstacle/ Problem separating you from achieving that goal?

-Lack of understanding with nutrition, exercise

How do you feel I helped you overcome the problem?

-Education with nutrition, even though I struggled with exercise due to factors out of my control, my relationship with food and the improvements I made still resulted in a weight loss but more importantly improved mood, improved skin, more energy and overall mental health is much better.

❌I don't believe in quick fixes.... 

❌I don't believe in short term, unsustainable results 

Sure you may go through short periods where you diet briefly and want short term results a little faster 🤷‍♀️ A little 'cut' or 'shred' here and there is fine. But if you are CONSTANTLY 'on' or 'off' a diet - I can promise you your results will not be as good as someone who has committed to long term sustainable changes 🤦‍♀️ 

✅ I'm here to help women realise you CAN have your cake and eat it. 

✅ I want to promote long term sustainable change. 

IT IS POSSIBLE. Even if you think you've 'tried everything' and 'nothing has worked'. But you need to be willing to trust the process. Oh and did I mention become the strongest, healthiest, most confident version of yourself in the meantime 😍 

If you're interested in working with me. Dm me 'Coach' for more details.

caption:
💫💫💫Client Wins 💫💫💫

I celebrate client wins every single week. I now even do a coaching call every month dedicated to client wins 🥳 Why? Because I need to celebrate how God damn incredible my clients are AND they need to realise how amazing they are too 🥰💃

Unfortunately, especially as females we tend to focus heavily on what we CAN'T do or all the WRONG we do. We never give ourselves a pat on the back or celebrate all we CAN do 🥳💪 So I want to change that ✅

Wins are not always MASSIVE. Although shout out to Aine who will be completing a half marathon at the weekend 🏃‍♀️

Take a look through some of my clients wins this week.

- Picture 1 - Hitting calories and Protein through a Vegan diet ✅

- Picture 2 - I don't TELL my clients what to do when it comes to nutrition. I educate them and let them make their own decisions. Helen decided to be disciplined and chose just to have water at the cinema. Juliet opted for salads to chips. These are all DECISIONS made by clients. 

- Picture 3 - My coaching is MORE than just nutrition and training. Being organised has a knock on effect on your mental health. I try to encompass and encourage a Hollistic approach to health 🙏 Rest and Recovery are absolutely vital for our body. As I have a lot of athletes, it is so important not only their nutrition and training is on point but that they know how to recovery properly ✅

Do you celebrate your weekly wins? 🤔

💥 If you are unsure of your career and thinking about changing everything for a different route. Maybe you could see a life coach.
💥 If you are sick. See a doctor.
💥 If you are having mental health issues, a counsellor may be an option
💥 If you're having car troubles, go to a mechanic.
💥 If your phone isn't working, bring it to a phone shop.
.
.
See the trend???
.
.
Once upon a time I thought I was totally independent. I didn't want to ask for help from anyone!!! But then I realised, I can't do it all alone and actually support and guidance is the best thing I could get. NOW, I ask for help all the time. From family, friends, and colleagues. I have a coach. If my mental health is affecting me I call someone for help. One of the best things I ever did was see a life coach ❤
.
.
Why is it so hard for people to see the same applies to training and nutrition? 🥴🥴🥴 You could be spending weeks, months or even years trying to do it alone? 🙈 Wasting your time and money in the process. If you aren't qualified in the area. YOU CAN ALWAYS ASK FOR HELP 🙏 Please please stop making poor nutrition choices based on what Google told you. Stop wasting time trying to 'shred belly fat' based on a free workout Susan gave you.
.
Ask for help. Stop wasting your time. I'm literally just a phone call away. 
.
.
Pm me with 'Get Started' to organise a phonecall 😁

caption:
Progress is so much more than weight loss ✅

Progress is so much more than pictures ✅

I focus every week on wins - something we don't do as females half enough. Progress is a win. No matter what form 🙌

For some clients:
✔ Doing less is a win
✔ Being guilt free is a win
✔ Sleeping for more than 5 hours is a win

Progress looks different on everyone 🙏 Maybe stop focusing so much on the scales and your body composition and start looking at all the smallsustainable changes you're making 🙌🙏

Allie

Occupation
Engineer 

Original Goal
Lose fat and build a better relationship with food and exercise 

How do you think I've helped you
With the knowledge and understanding I’ve learned from Amanda I can make the same (yummy and exciting) meals as pre-coaching but within my daily macros. My habits or non negotiables are drilled into me (and those close to me) 🤣 ie STEPS!! water, fruit and veg etc… basics but make such a difference once they are a must EVERYDAY and not just when you feel like it. I’m also subconsciously so much more aware of the different weekly habits I learned like getting enough protein, varied protein sources, eating colour, reading food labels if they have 10’s of ingredients etc etc 

Why you chose to work with me over someone else?
Your Passion and enthusiasm! Also so helpful if having a bad week: never judgey, always give relatable advice and very kind. So good at giving us perspective when being hard on ourselves. 

If you want to be like Allie and eat the food you enjoy while still getting results - DM me 'Coach'

Take a look at how Teresa has done: 

- Teresa has lost 30kg over 12 months (7kg between these pictures)

- Teresa is EXTREMELY busy but 'prioritises' her nutrition and training 

- Teresa turned up to a coaching call EVERY week, responded to every accountability message but DIDN'T give up the foods she enjoys or alcohol. She enjoyed her Christmas and STILL GOT RESULTS!!!!! 

I'm looking for a few specific things from my ladies. So if you:

- And are ready to get pushed out of your comfort zone.

caption:
It's the last day of January.... 

How are your new year resolutions going? 

How's dry January going? 

Did you get Covid over the holidays? How have you recovered? 

I'm intrigued... 

I find January a funny time of year. 

People tend to do exactly the OPPOSITE of what I preach 🤣 I don't believe in the ALL OR NOTHING approach and that's exactly what people tend to do 🙈 

So come February 1st: 
✅ People have let go of their 'resolutions'
✅ Feel like they've failed because they can't sustain 6 days of exercise a week and 1200 cals daily 🤦‍♀️
✅ Back drinking every 2nd night. 

In my camp, since January 1st: 

- Aine O had a big trip away and 'felt great in her clothes'
- Aine L has dropped 4kg and is back running again
- Anna has got her first EVER push ups
- Post partum Colleen is back bossing her training 
- Helen is feeling the 'happiest she has been in a long time'
- Maeve's work uniform is feeling looser
- Raychel's nutrition is improving daily
- Susan is already feeling stronger physically and mentally.
- Zac weighed in at an all time low 

NO CRAZY RESTRICITIONS 

NO ALCOHOL BANS
NO FOOD IS OFF LIMITS
NO TRAINING 6 DAYS A WEEK 

Small sustainable changes which leads to long lasting results. And do you want to know the best part? 

They are only getting started 💪 This week we up our game when we get MJ Nutrition in to talk to the ladies (I get guest speakers in every 4-6 weeks). 

If you are interested in achieving results like the people above (in just one month 😵). Dm me 'Ready'

Warm up done for next weekend ✅

I still cannot believe I am doing my first Rx Competition with @lillie704 next week 😵

When I did scaled competitions at home I would look at the weights the rx people were lifting and it literally felt IMPOSSIBLE to EVER get there. I literally could not even snatch a barbell - yesterday I did 7 TNG reps at 40kg 😈 

22 months of consistent training later (with a dislocated knee to mess up my training and some covid) and I am PUMPED to do this next week 🏋‍♀️ 

I'm baaaaaaack 💪🙋‍♀️

Get practising your pull ups ladies 😜
.
.
And if this is a goal you'd like to achieve - why not work with me to help you achieve it 💪 Dm me 'Pull Ups'

caption:
It's not just about WHAT you eat, but HOW and WHY you eat 🙌
.
.
What I've learned over the last 8 years in the fitness industry:
.
.
People THINK eating better, exercising  more and losing weight will make them feel better. 
.
.
What ACTUALLY makes people feel better is healing their relationships with food and exercise. And absolutely no shape, size or weight will make you feel better unless you're happy and content within yourself 🙏
.
.
I've developed an ebook that will help with your mindset towards nutrition and health in general. If you're interested in a copy - comment 'ME' below 👇

𝕊𝕒𝕞𝕖 𝕤𝕒𝕞𝕖 💁‍♀️
.
.
When people said to Arnold Schwarzenegger 
'Oh but I don't want to look like you.'

He replied:
'Don't worry. You never will.'
.
.
Let me tell you. Building muscle is BLOODY HARD. You don't just wake up one day and 'are bulky' 😅😅😅
.
.
I've spent YEARS improving myself and getting stronger, fitter and healthier. That is my goal. So don't think after lifting afew weights you're going to gain 10kg of muscle and look 'bulky'. And honestly, most people will NEVER EVER train as hard as I train 😅 
.
.
But let me also tell you. Majority of the photos I take are mid or post training when I have a serious pump. In normal clothes, I'm a normal size 8-10 female. I don't have jacked quads or a shoulder vein 😅 (Even though I'd be happy to walk around like that)
.
.
Moral of the story: most people will never train hard enough to get bulky. Most people don't walk round jacked 😅 The 'toned' look you want is actually muscle - so if you say you want to be 'toned' and don't want muscle you're actually contradicting yourself 😅

Oh and if it wasn't already obvious - lift weights 🏋‍♀️

P.s Those tan lines though 😅

caption:
Keep looking at the bigger picture 📸

If you are still looking at your health and fitness in a short term Window - 6, 8, 12 week challenges, you already have the wrong attitude 🤦‍♀️

It still baffles me that people think they are going to change habits of a lifetime in 6 weeks. 

Take things slow, build important habits, improve your mindset and your attitude towards yourself and enjoy the process - Health and Fitness is for life ❤🙏

Would you believe us if we said we didn't do this in tune to the song 🤔😅

caption:
Protein Snacks 🍴🤤

An area I know a lot of people struggle with is increasing protein in their diet. Main meals seem to be easier to get protein in but there's definitely a disconnect when it comes to protein snacks.

While most people would have protein bars etc. Included in here - a lot of these options are highly processed and the protein quality is poor (I am NOT saying don't eat them. I would just not be relying heavily on them for protein sources). 

Hope this helps. Save for later 👇

caption:
𝕀 𝕘𝕖𝕥 𝕓𝕠𝕣𝕖𝕕...
.
.
Sick of chicken and broccoli? 🤔
.
.
You will quickly run out of ideas if you try to change whole meals so why not change up the sides 💁‍♀️
.
.
From my experience, people tend to like certain foods. If you stick with the foods you like, you're more likely to stick with it 🙏 
.
.
So my advice:
- Change the vegetables - not just the type but how you cook them - stir fry, boil, steam, roast. 

- Change the carb source - sick of brown rice? Add quinoa or cous cous! Sick of potato, try sweet potato.

- Rotate Week 1 - Chicken and pork based meals. Week 2 - Tofu and tuna based meals. Week 3 - Turkey & Salmon based meals. Week 4 - Prawn & Beef based meals. And start the cycle again 🙌
.
.
Save this post for later 🙋‍♀️

✴ My 𝙬𝙝𝙮? 
.
.
If you haven't already noticed I feel very passionate about helping people. 
.
.
I too, disliked my body image, under fuelled and exercised to burn calories. I too did endless amounts of cardio and crunches in a bid to find abs. And guess what, nothing changed. How I felt about myself didn't change one single bit. Even when I was a size 6 and probably <18% BF with visible abs, I still wasn't happy. 
.
.
And you won't be either, unless you deal with what's going on in your head and understand the 
Importance of your why. 
.
.
My 𝙬𝙝𝙮 is to be a role model 🙋‍♀️ I want younger girls to look up to me. I want peers to understand the message I am preaching. I want older women to see that fad diets and restriction is NOT the answer. I want Dad's to say 'You should listen to that Mc Loone one' (if you know you know 😅).
.
.
My 𝙬𝙝𝙮 is to help as many women as I can become the best versions of themselves. 
💥I want to educate women that you can still enjoy the food you like and be happy. 
💥I want women to see how empowering it is to become physically stronger. 
💥I want to help women see how incredible they are and stop focusing so much on how they look on the outside and see what they have to offer from the inside. 
💥I want to see confidence radiating from the women I work with. 
.
.
I truely believe I was put on this planet for 3 reasons:
1. To help as many people as physically possible.
2. To become the fittest and healthiest version of myself
3. To have loads of animals 
.
.
If you want my help - Reach out and Dm me 'Help'. 🙏

caption:
Christmas is over 💥 
.
.
Now from my experience, during lockdowns or home isolation, one of the biggest habits people are  developing is daily alcohol drinking. And openly admitted when working from home, the time would get earlier and earlier 🙈
.
.
I am not anti alcohol. Actually I am the polar opposite. I encourage clients to have a glass of wine at weekends if that is what truely makes them happy. It's important to have balance in your life 🙏
.
.
I do believe though that alcohol is a little too readily available and can be 'too easy' to use as an escape. 
.
.
I implore people to find other things to pass their time. Exercise, walk, bake, knit, zoom call, cook, spring clean, learn a new skill ... the list goes on. But please don't let alcohol be the ONLY thing you look forward to daily 🙏🙏🙏

caption:
We over complicate EVERYTHING 🙈
.
.
Instead of breaking it down to basics and nailing the basics - every year people start off all guns blazing on January 1st with a list of 7 million things to do:
- Drink Detox juices
- Hiit training daily 
- 10,000 Steps
- 1200 Calories
- High Protein foods
- No Carbs
-No sugar
- No alcohol

Would you believe it if I said from that list I only encourage 2 of those with clients?

Would you believe if you don't want to - you never have to do a burpee for the rest of your life?

What if I told you I had a client who lost 30.7kg (yes you heard me right) in 1 year from nailing the basics:
✔ 3 resistance sessions a week
✔ Drink 2L water 
✔ Sleep adequately (this is still her Achilles heel but it's a heck of a lot better)
✔ 10,000 Steps
✔ Focus on food quality 
While still:
✅ Eating the foods she enjoys
✅ Drinking Alcohol
✅ Enjoying the exercise she does 

I am beyond excited to get my new crew up and running tomorrow 🥳🥳If you're interested in making a change this January DM me 🤙

caption:
Spot the difference 🔍
.
.
When people say to me they 'want to lose weight', more often than not - it's fat loss they are actually seeking. And there is a difference 👆
.
.
Weight loss is a combination of fat, muscle and water. When people go on very restrictive diets they often see a huge scale shift on week 1 due to a reduction in total body water - as opposed to fat loss. 
.
.
If people focus solely on scale loss unfortunately there is likely to be muscle mass loss - which is what we don't want. As far as I'm aware some diet clubs actually discourage resistance training as it will lead to muscle gain (and essentially an increase on the scales) 🙈
.
.
Ladies, please please understand smaller ≠ happier 🚫
.
.
If someone is overweight/obese, weight loss should be the goal to a healthier overall body composition 🙏
.
.
Anyone else - Fat Loss is what you should be seeking 👆
.
.

caption:
The meaning behind my Lotus Flower Tattoo 🌺
.
.
I went through a really hard period of my life after my Dad died. As the oldest of his daughters I felt a responsibility to keep my shit together, look after my mother and sister and keep up appearances. It was a struggle. I tried to do this while managing a gym, commuting, playing with 2 football teams, studying, trying to maintain friendships and a relationship. I felt like I was just surviving as opposed to living 😢
.
.
And then I took control of my life. I started to look after myself first and everybody else's needs and wants came second. 
.
.
The meaning of the tattoo is that even the most beautiful things can come from the ugliest of places. 🙏
.
.
I'm not alone. I know we've all had struggles and strifes in our lives. I'm not saying mine has been harder than anyone else's. But I decided to take control of mine. I asked for help. I seeked the help I needed. And I made life changing decisions 💔❤
.
.
