caption:
Yesterday, I mentioned a common problem i see in women trying to become bikini confident. 

Women lack education and understanding around nutrition which causes serial yo yo dieting. 

To fix this problem, you need more nutrition education on how you can eat the foods you love and still get the results you deserve. 

Here's how it works: 

As a qualified nutritionist, I educate females on how to make good food choices to achieve their goals. I don't focus on short term quick fixes but long term sustainable results. I genuinely believe if you hand someone a diet plan you will only help them so far,  but if you educate them on a balanced lifestyle - this is invaluable. 

P.s I'm looking for 5 MORE females who want to be bikini confident in the next 12 weeks. If that's you DM me 'HELP'.

How Eimear got fitter, stronger and more confident while avoiding injury. 

Eimear is a GAA footballer in Sydney who was looking to get fitter, stronger and more confident on the pitch. She wanted to do my Strong and Sassy programme as she felt 'she never reached her full potential'. 

Before we started working together, Eimear had been doing her farm work in Austrailia and had developed some bad nutrition habits and had lost a lot of fitness. With her football season looming, she wanted to gain structure as well as get fitter and stronger. 

She has always worked in a face to face setting so she almost didn't reach out to me because she thought the online method 'wouldn't work for her'. She decided to give it a go as she really wanted to make a change. 

'The app was great because it logged all the stats and I wanted to see improvements and log into that'. The programme worked around me, football and my injuries. 

Fast forward 12 weeks and Eimear cannot believe the change it has made not only to her physically but mentally too. Her confidence is through the roof on and off the pitch. 

'If you want a coach who trains you for life. If you want someone who will let you off in to the world to be the best version of yourself' then choose Amanda.' 

If you're like Eimear and want to get fitter, stronger and more confident, I'd love to help you get there. 

Comment 'STRONG' below and I'll directly reach out to you and determine if I can help.

A huge issue I see amongst women is their lack of knowledge and understanding of nutrition. They have no clue what to do to achieve that body confidence they desire 😢 

Are you constantly fad dieting because you're afraid if you're not dieting you will gain weight. You're afraid that if you don't stick to that deficit you'll never be happy in your clothes. 

I feel terrible for you, because you're genuinely trying. You know no different. We've grown up with fad dieting, our mothers  yo yo dieted. It's all we've known - we only know strict calorie deficits and exercise to burn calories 😢 

But I've found the solution to your problems. I believe in education. Have you ever heard the saying “If you give a man a fish, you feed him for a day. If you teach a man to fish, you feed him for a lifetime.” I want you to understand you CAN ACHIEVE results and ENJOY the food you love 😍 

Are you interested in learning more about nutrition? Do you want to achieve bikini confidence and enjoy a balanced diet? I'm going to explain all tomorrow. 

Comment ME below and I'll tag you tomorrow when its up!

caption:
Yesterday I told you about time being a problem for women trying to change their body shape. They feel they can't give full commitment to a programme because they are too busy. 

They feel they have no time to go to the gym because they are too busy. 

Thankfully a lot of my clients train from home 3 times a week with minimal equipment. 

You see the thing is - you don't actually need hours in the gym to achieve your goals - especially if you're crazy busy. I also encourage women to make better choices if they are too busy to cook. And instead of scrolling on Social media - I set step targets for them (even if they scroll while they walk). 

You see - it's pretty simple. Try this out and let me know how it goes. 

P.s I'm looking for 5 more women who want to become bikini confident with restriction in the next 12 weeks. If that's you, DM me the word 'ME'

Another common problem I see most women have when they are trying to change their body shape is time to commit to a programme. 

We all lead such busy lifestyles these days. We give time to our families, our friends, and work and we are left with little to no time. 

It's so frustrating because you're trying to be a good friend, mother, daughter, sister, colleague, or employee. But what's left for you? Or maybe there is time? 

I've found that most people usually can find time. Maybe instead of an hour of Netflix we could swap it for a workout? Maybe instead of scrolling we could be walking? Or instead of picking up a takeaway on the way home from work, we could pick up a ready meal in a supermarket? The problem lies in trying to do too much.

Are you interested in learning about how you could commit to a programme even WITH limited time? 

Comment 'me' below and I'll tag you tomorrow when it's up.

caption:
How Kelly changed her habits and became more confident over 12 weeks. 

Kelly has been training approximately 5 years now. Her main goal was to feel better in herself. She was looking for a long term sustainable change - without restriction. 

Before we started working together Kelly had tried every 4 and 6 week challenge going and had achieved incredible results - that she couldn't sustain. She found herself unhappy in her clothes and she was sick of stopping and starting. 

She hesitated in starting because of the slow approach we use. And if she's honest, she thought it would be another failed attempt. But her unhappiness drove her to take action. 

'The new habits and coaching calls thought me how to increase my calories healthily'. She found a balance between training, nutrition and socialising. 'It was great' 

Fast forward 12 weeks and she feels so much happier and more confident.
'It made me feel 1 million times better knowing I was looking after myself' 

'Everyone should put themselves first and think about in the long run, this is going to make you feel better. The 12 weeks goes so fast.'

If you want results like Kelly - Dm me 'Kelly'.

caption:
How I became stronger, happier and more confident and how you can too. 

When I started in the fitness industry I was a little lost. I was focused on how I looked. I was obsessed with having abs. I only ate 'clean' food mid week which led to weekend binges. My relationship with nutrition and fitness definitely was not a healthy one. 

I wasn't happy. Not in my body. Not in my mind. I genuinely couldn't imagine continuing my life with this level of restriction and I began to resent the gym 😢 

Then I stopped focusing so much on HOW I looked. I stopped looking for abs every time I walked by the mirror. I started to appreciate resistance training and I began focusing on how much stronger I was becoming. My goals changed. Performance based goals replaced the quest for abs and I found my love for exercise again. I found a balanced approach to nutrition. I still eat very healthy and nutritious but I no longer restrict myself. 

I no longer focus on HOW I look but WHAT my body can do. I wear bikinis now without dieting to get in them. I'm stronger and fitter than I've ever been and clothes sizes no longer dictate my life. I'm happier and healthier. I love the skin I'm in ❤ 

And that's why I created my Strong and Sassy Programme to help women become bikini confident year round without restrictions. Comment 'CHANGE' below if you'd like for me to personally message you today and see if I can help you!

Yesterday, I told you about a common problem that most women experience when trying to change their body shape. 

No matter what diet they do, they can't stick to it at weekends.... 

To fix this problem I get my clients to find their non negotiables. 

What are non negotiables?
They are habits you can stick to NO MATTER WHAT the circumstances are. 

I usually recommend 3 of them.. 

3 things you can stick to every weekend.
For example - Drink 2 litres of water, walk 10,000 steps daily and 1 piece of fruit. 

It's pretty simple. Try this out and let me know how it goes. 

P.s I'm looking for 5 MORE ladies who want to be bikini confident year round without giving up the foods they enjoy. If that's you DM me 'Bikini'.

A common problem I see most women have when they are trying to change their body shape is their struggle to stay on track at weekends 🐒🐷 

You may notice yourself cutting calories during the week and then all hell breaks lose at weekends and you're afraid that if you continue this way you'll never achieve that bikini body 😢 

It's so frustrating because you're really trying to make a change. What's actually causing this is a binge restrict cycle that you've developed over the years. We only know and understand nutrition at 2 levels - 'really good' or 'really bad' 

I've found the best solution to fix this is to SAY NO to the all or nothing approach - but this will require help. Accountability to someone who knows what they're talking about can definitely help with this. I've also found having non negotiables proves very helpful. 

Are you interested in learning about non negotiables? I'm going to teach it to you tomorrow. 

Comment 'me' below and I'll tag you tomorrow when it's up.

caption:
Life Update 

I went through a tough time in November (my Dad's Anniversary and Birthday, my friend at home got married late October, trials and tribulations of working for yourself). It was a bit of a whirlwind. But I'm 2 counselling sessions in and I can safely say I'm feeling a lot better ❤ 

I'm looking forward to spending Christmas with friends and family in Nelson Bay ❤🙏 I'm very lucky that work doesn't much feel like work and although I will have some downtime I will be working most of Christmas 🧑‍🎄 

It's my second 'summer' in Austrailia and it still feels weird wearing a bikini on Christmas Day 😅 I must say it does feel good to be bikini ready year round. And I love that my clients will be wearing a bikini with confidence this year. Some of them for 'THE FIRST TIME EVER'!!!!!! Mind blowing 🥳🤯 

Anyway I'm going to keep this short as I pack for holidays 💃 If you're interested in feeling as bikini confident as my clients.  DM me 👙

(P.s This is last years pic).

caption:
Progress over perfection every single day 👊👊👊

(Although these looking perfect would be pretty sweet 🤣)

Anyone want a mobility challenge - give this exercise a go 😲 I've went from a very unstable 5kg to a much improved 15kg SA OH Squat - still needs work but we're definitely seeing improvements 💪

I'm a HUGE believer in mobility and movement and honestly believe it's one of the main contributors to injury. 

🚨Fun Fact: I used to be really anti CrossFit - because I was young and naive.  But also because I believe in training pain free. If you have problems/niggles/issues don't wait until you're broken to be fixed. Look after your body, mind your body, continue to train 🙋‍♀️ From doing Crossfit for the last 2 years I understand my body, know my weak areas and work to make sure I can train as regularly as I want to. That means going to a physio once every 6 weeks - not because I'm injured but because I want to be injury free 🙌

caption:
This post may cause a little controversy... 

I'm normally very empathetic but here we go...

You can come up with every excuse under the sun...

⏰ Time 
💰 Money 
🎓 Study
🦺Work 
👩‍👧‍👧 Kids
🦿 Injuries 
🫁 Illness 

And for every excuse I've heard. I've worked with someone who worked through hardship.

✔I've worked with women in pregnancy.

✔ I've worked with people on the dole. 

✔I've worked with people who can only commit 20 mins to exercise because that is literally all they have. 

✔I've worked with mothers who get up at 5am because that's the only time they can train.

✔ I've coached NUMEROUS people with injuries.

✔ I've worked with people with MS to Cancer.

But at the end of the day they all made the choice to PUT THEMSELVES FIRST. They all decided they were sick of where they were and needed to make a change. They didn't make the excuses you are making to yourself. Instead they took action 👊

Tell me again what's your excuse? 🤔

Had you told me 7 years ago it would take 5 years for chin ups to become comfortable I'd have been pissed off...

Had you told me I'd break a wrist, dislocate fingers and my knee I'd laugh at you...

I already knew I was losing my Dad 😢

7 years is a long time and a lot can happen but you know what...
The time passes anyway.

7 years of getting stronger. Bring on the next 7 💪💪💪

caption:
Grocery List Essnials 🙌
.
.
If these were the only items on your grocery list, you'd actually have a super balanced, nutritious diet 🙏
.
.
𝐏𝐫𝐨𝐭𝐞𝐢𝐧
Eggs, tuna, Basa and chicken are all great sources of protein. Protein is essential for repair and recovery. Protein keeps us fuller for longer and has the highest TEF (thermic effect from food). 

𝐂𝐚𝐫𝐛𝐨𝐡𝐲𝐝𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐬
Rice and Oats are complex carbohydrates and give us a slow release in energy. Meanwhile, fruit are simple sugars and give us a quicker release. Carbohydrates is the body's main fuel for energy.

𝐅𝐚𝐭𝐬
Avocado, cheese and eggs all contain fats. Good Fats are essential in the diet and can affect our ability to absorb fat soluble vitamins. We also need them for hormone function.

𝐌𝐢𝐜𝐫𝐨𝐧𝐮𝐭𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬
Colourful food is jam packed with vitamins, minerals and antioxidants. Make sure you're getting enough in your diet 🙏

Hit save on this post for your next shopping day 👇

Can't believe it's been a week since our Catch up ❤🙏
.
.
The only con to being an online Coach is not getting to see these incredible ladies in person every day. But some of us finally got to meet up last weekend ❤
.
.
The biggest pro is that I've had groups like this catch up in Ireland and I am working with people in numerous different countries and time zones 🙏
.
.
Online coaching has the benefit of:
✅ Being able to train in your own time
✅ High level of accountability 
✅ Nutrition education as opposed to a meal plan
✅ Like minded community - who catch up weekly on coaching calls, guest speakers, organised online events and in person events 🙏🙌
.
.
If this sounds like something you need. Dm me 'Coach' for more details.

𝐂𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐞
Creatine is one of the most vastly researched supplements and has been promoted in the fitness industry in the last few years. According to research, supplementation with creatine monohydrate has been shown to increase Skeletal muscle mass, lean body mass and muscle fibre size. Research also suggests past this and it may encourage healthy aging and benefit brain health. 

𝐃𝐨 𝐈 𝐧𝐞𝐞𝐝 𝐂𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐞?
Creatine supplementation can be hugely beneficial for athletic performance and studies have also showed it can have an impact on body composition (prolonged creatine ingestion inducing an increase in fat free mass). 

𝐃𝐨 𝐈 𝐧𝐞𝐞𝐝 𝐭𝐨 𝐥𝐨𝐚𝐝 𝐂𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐞?
Nope. 5g daily will suffice. (The idea to saturate the muscle is just to experience benefits sooner).
Increase water consumption when you start taking creatine.

𝐖𝐡𝐞𝐧 𝐬𝐡𝐨𝐮𝐥𝐝 𝐈 𝐭𝐚𝐤𝐞 𝐢𝐭?
Evidence does suggest post workout is superior to pre workout. 

𝐀𝐫𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐞 𝐚𝐧𝐲 𝐬𝐢𝐝𝐞 𝐞𝐟𝐟𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐬?
- Bloating - This is due to the muscles absorbing the water with the Creatine. Very common and usually subsides when the muscles are saturated.
- Stomach discomfort - May cause stomach sensitivity like bloating.

#creatine #supplements #nutritioncoach #realnutrition #realresults #fitness #fitliving #strengthtraining

caption:
It's still possible to progress...

But you may just need some help...

1. One of the most common mistakes I see people make is their lack of structure when it comes to training. Having a 'toned' goal or a strength/performance based goal is very difficult if you're participating in random spin classes or copying what other people do in the gym. If you're looking to change shape or get stronger - follow a progressive plan.

2. Consistency in EVERYTHING is 🔑 to success. Ask yourself - Can you see yourself doing this in a years time? If the answer is no, chances are you need to change something.

3. Unrealistic goals is a huge problem. Let's give the example of 'Having Abs' for a female. 
Most women have to sacrifice too much to achieve this goal. This leaves them A. Frustrated at not achieving it or B. Achieving it but hating life.
(Notice I said most females - some won't find this difficult at all but they are a minority).

4. Nutrition habits have changed. Again, ask yourself can you see yourself eating this way a year from now - if the answer is no - it's not going to be sustainable.

5. Stress is one of the most overlooked barriers to success. Just like you can't out exercise a bad diet. You can't achieve goals in an utterly stress fried body.

If any of the above sounds like you, I am getting my Strong and Sassy programme ready for the new year 🥳 DM me 'SAS' if you'd like more information 🏋‍♀️

caption:
I used to struggle....
.
.
I use struggle with the fact that I don't conform to certain standards and expectations of a woman....
For example:
✔ I hate cleaning 
✔ I'm not an exceptional cook
✔ I don't bake
.
.
✔ I always wanted to wear comfy sportswear rather than dress up
✔ I didn't like being told what to do - by anyone 😅
.
.
✔ I prefer going to the gym rather than getting my hair done
✔ I'd rather a new pair of metcons over an expensive braclet 
✔ I'd pick a new tatoo over hair extensions
.
.
I struggled with this for years because  this is what I thought women did. I felt I was different. Possibly even there was something wrong with me 🙊
.
.
Now, I'm happy, confident and comfortable in myself - I realise I am who I am. I won't ever be a typical housewife (and @o_boyce is still with me 😅). I'd still rather have calluses than soft hands. And I WILL have a cleaner as I get older 😅 There is ABSOLUTELY nothing wrong with me. Maybe I am a little different but if we were all the same, the world would be a boring place 😅🙏

Anyone else ever have these feelings? 🤔

#iamwhoiam #iamastrongwoman

caption:
Deirdre is back 🙌
.
.
Coaching with me that is 🥳 This time Deirdre's goals are different. She's actually kept such great habits going since she finished up with me. But she wants a level of accountability again 🙏 So what better time than over the Christmas period 🤶🧑‍🎄 
.
.
If you think you can't make some progress over the month of December - you are so wrong 🚨 It's a full month. 
Some of the reasons people think its a bad time to start:
✅ I've Christmas parties 💃
✅ I want to enjoy Christmas 🐷
✅ I'll be drinking more 🥂
✅ I won't have as much time for training 🏋‍♀️
.
.
I can assure you my clients and I will all be doing the same over Christmas. But difference is come January, we won't be starting from scratch. My clients understand its ok to enjoy Christmas and eat and drink a little too much. But they also understand how important protein is and why they should drink at least 2 litres water daily. 🙌
.
.
So what are you waiting for? Use the next 3 weeks as your starting point. Dont wait until January AGAIN this year 🙈 Dm me 'Get Started' for more information.

Would you believe me if I said we weren't always this close 🙊
.
.
Well it's true. Our first 16/18 years on this earth were turbulent 🤣
.
.
Every day I am grateful for the relationship I have with my sister. Theres not many people who can take crazy Amanda during WODs or my need to micro manage every single part of a trip 🤣
.
.
Our passion to not only better ourselves but to help and encourage everyone around us is something I am so proud of and I know there's a man looking down just as proud of us 😇
.
.
P.s Did I mention she's a beast 💪

P.p.s Did I mention we're much better at fitness than drinking 🤣

caption:
𝐏𝐞𝐫𝐬𝐨𝐧𝐚𝐥 𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐢𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐨𝐫 𝐎𝐧𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐞 𝐂𝐨𝐚𝐜𝐡𝐢𝐧𝐠?
.
.
(Firstly, just note - the PT pros and cons are based on a general PT. I know and work with PTs who offer so much more. Secondly, the online coaching is based on MY online coaching. I know online coaches who provide a LOT less - but you pay peanuts, you get monkeys).
.
.
Here is my two cents. 
My Online coaching works best for people who:
✅ Need a high level of accountability-  which PT will rarely give you.
✅ Need nutrition education rather than another diet plan 🤦‍♀️
✅ Are busy and can't commit to Class times or can't even commit to joining a gym and need to train from home
✅ Need help working on their mindset 
.
.
PT works best for people who:
✅ Need that face to face interaction
✅ Have injuries and need in person training 
.
.
I would love to know people's experiences of both 🤔

𝐈'𝐦 𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐡𝐞𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐡𝐲 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐈'𝐦 𝐬𝐭𝐢𝐥𝐥 𝐧𝐨𝐭 𝐬𝐞𝐞𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐮𝐥𝐭𝐬 🤷‍♀️
.
.
I want to state very strongly I am not recommending A vs B in any of the above. I just want to educate you all that sometimes health and fat loss goals can be different 🤷‍♀️ So while you may be eating 'Healthy' you may not actually be eating less and be in that negative energy balance you need to be in for fat loss to occur.
.
.
Also worth noting - my definition of health being less processed whole foods as opposed to lower calorie options 💫
.
.
Remember, the best 'diet' out there is the one you can stick to consistently. The one you don't feel deprived and can find a good balance 🙏 So find what works for you ❤🙏

Save for later ✅

caption:
Almost half of the world's population are not consuming enough fruit and vegetables 🤯
.
.
Bare in mind that a large majority of low to middle income families actually don't have access to or can't afford these luxuries.
.
.
I'm sure I wasn't the only one who grew up with 'Eat that up, the poor starving children in Africa would do anything for that'. And while I may not agree with my mother's force feeding tactics, she is right about this 🤔
.
.
We need to reframe our minds. We should be so grateful and privileged we CAN eat such whole nutritious food. 
.
.
Do yourself a favour this week - Increase your vegetable consumption. Even if its only by one portion a week. Maybe try something different for dinner? Maybe order a side salad if you're out for dinner?! Maybe add some spinach to your morning smoothie?! Your body and gut will thank you for it ❤🙏
.
.
Hit save for later. Maybe tag someone who this would help x

Last chance to sign up for my webinar tomorrow 🥳🥳🥳
.
.
We will be discussing all things Resistance Training and the habits based approach to nutrition.
.
.
There is literally nothing to lose from attending this webinar.

It is not you signing up to work with me.

It is simply free information and guidance. Who doesn't love that? 🤔

P.s there is no catch. You sign up via the link in my link tree and I'll send you a calendar invite. The reason I emphasise the free is because a lot of people charge for these webinars. 🙏

See you tomorrow 👋👋👋

- You will miss workouts

- You will have bad workouts

- You will slip up on your diet

- You will lose motivation

- You will have to adjust

And that's ok. Nobody is expecting perfection. Failure, challenges and adversity are an important part of the process of changing your life and habits.

Forget about ALL OR NOTHING. And start accepting failure 🙏 And if you're worried if you're doing the right thing to achieve your goals, reach out ❤

caption:
Is protein really that important? 🤔
.
.
1. Amino Acids are proteins building blocks and we NEED these for recovery. Remember recovery is not only essential if you train, our bodies recover every single day.

2. Satiety - every sit down to eat 3 chicken breasts? Doubtful because protein rich foods are so filling. They also help stabilise our blood sugars and reduce cravings. So get your protein in 👊

3. Thermic Effect from Food (TEF) - Did you know that TEF has the same effect on our TDEE as purposeful exercise? 🤔 Did you know protein actually requires more energy to break down than fats or carbohydrates? 🤔 So double whammy here 👊
.
.
Long story short - eat yo protein 🤤
.
.
 How much?
💫 Gold Standard = 2g/kg BW/day 
(But anything between 1.5-2 is very good)
.
.
Save this post and drop any questions below⬇️⬇️⬇️

" 𝐘𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐛𝐨𝐝𝐲 𝐝𝐨𝐞𝐬𝐧'𝐭 𝐞𝐱𝐬𝐢𝐬𝐭 𝐭𝐨 𝐛𝐞 𝐥𝐨𝐨𝐤𝐞𝐝 𝐚𝐭, 𝐬𝐨 𝐡𝐞𝐚𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐛𝐨𝐝𝐲 𝐢𝐦𝐚𝐠𝐞 𝐢𝐬𝐧'𝐭 𝐣𝐮𝐬𝐭 𝐚𝐛𝐨𝐮𝐭 𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐧𝐠𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐡𝐨𝐰 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐯𝐢𝐞𝐰 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐛𝐨𝐝𝐲. 𝐈𝐭'𝐬 𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐧𝐠𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐡𝐨𝐰 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐯𝐚𝐥𝐮𝐞 𝐢𝐭. "
.
.
Sport always helped me value my body. But unfortunately as a young girl, sport wasn't enough. I cared deeply about how I looked and I constantly tried to change it. I was always slim but I had such a distorted idea of what I looked like in my head. I always wanted to be leaner. And I was willing to get there in very unhealthy manners.
.
.
Fast forward 10 years 👋
Lifting weights and Crossfit has changed my whole view on my body. I am no longer obsessed with how I look. Like everyone I've days where I feel amazing and days where I feel like a bag of 💩. But HOW I look doesn't hugely affect me. 
.
.
I am so damn proud of what my body can do. I am so proud that I have been so consistent. I am so proud that I have encouraged so many others to live a similar lifestyle. None of that can be found when fixating on a scale number 🤔
.
.
𝐉𝐮𝐬𝐭 𝐫𝐞𝐦𝐞𝐦𝐛𝐞𝐫, 𝐰𝐡𝐞𝐧 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐨𝐧𝐥𝐲 𝐥𝐨𝐯𝐞 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐛𝐨𝐝𝐲 𝐰𝐡𝐞𝐧 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐥𝐨𝐯𝐞 𝐡𝐨𝐰 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐥𝐨𝐨𝐤 - 𝐭𝐡𝐚𝐭'𝐬 𝐧𝐨𝐭 𝐥𝐨𝐯𝐞, 𝐭𝐡𝐚𝐭'𝐬 𝐨𝐛𝐣𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐟𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧.

Gimme a 💪 if you agree ❤

ℍ𝕠𝕨 𝕨𝕖𝕝𝕝 𝕒𝕣𝕖 𝕪𝕠𝕦 𝕣𝕖𝕔𝕠𝕧𝕖𝕣𝕚𝕟𝕘?
.
.
Quite often people think you need to do more to achieve your goals. And in a lot of cases that is true - more exercise, more water, better nutrition. But for some actually less is more. 
.
.
Everyone has their problem areas. Some people nail nutrition and exercise and can't understand why they can't lose weight - while their bodies are in chronic sleep deprivation 🤦‍♀️ Others weigh in the week before their period and can't understand why their weight fluctuates. Others would rather take a supplement than eat real food 🙈
.
.
These are some of the elements to think about when it comes to your goals - in no particular order 👊
.
.
My own Experience 
- I'm excellent with training and drinking water, I'm very good with nutrition and my sleep is decent. Performance is my goal. But my social life is also heightening so I can't push my training as hard as I was during lockdown. I'm also very cautious and work with my body as opposed to against it 🙏🙌
.
.
Nutrition and exercise are not the only 2 elements you can control. If you have those nailed why not look at other areas? 🤔
.
.
Save this one for later ⬇️

Why are you waiting? 🤔
.
.
In the next 7 weeks you could be getting closer to your goal?

Say hello to Trish, 38 year old mum from Dublin. Trish initially started the programme to lose body fat. 

What she gained?
An understanding of tracking food and importance of protein (educating me more) and still enjoying treats and not restricting any food type☺️
.
.
Your Objections:

'𝐓𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐞'𝐬 𝐧𝐨 𝐩𝐨𝐢𝐧𝐭 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐛𝐞𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐞 𝐂𝐡𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐦𝐚𝐬?'

Why not? 7 weeks is a long time? A lot of habit based changes can be made over 7 week.

'𝐈 𝐰𝐚𝐧𝐭 𝐭𝐨 𝐞𝐧𝐣𝐨𝐲 𝐦𝐲 𝐂𝐡𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐦𝐚𝐬'

I also want you to enjoy your Christmas. This programme is not like your normal 6 week shred. I teach you habits that you can use over the Christmas period 🙌

'𝐈 𝐰𝐢𝐥𝐥 𝐛𝐞 𝐝𝐫𝐢𝐧𝐤𝐢𝐧𝐠'

Me too 🙋‍♀️ Nothing is OFF LIMITS with my programme!

'𝐈 𝐜𝐚𝐧'𝐭 𝐜𝐨𝐦𝐦𝐢𝐭 𝐭𝐨 𝟓 𝐝𝐚𝐲𝐬 𝐚 𝐰𝐞𝐞𝐤 𝐭𝐫𝐚𝐢𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐠'

That's ok because only 10% of my clients train 5 times a week throughout the year 🤣

This programme works around you NOT you work around it. The results are slower but they are so much more sustainable. I want to help more and more women become the healthiest, most confident versions of themselves.

caption:
I still can't believe people still ask me is fruit bad 🤯
.
.
Honestly, if fruit is your biggest problem re nutrition you're doing pretty darn well 🤣 
.
.
Unless you are diabetic, have issues with glucose levels or insulin or are preparing for a body building competition- fruit is not going to be something you need to worry about 🤦‍♀️
.
.
Not only are they an abundant source of vitamins and minerals but some can even add to our hydration status 👌 As well as that they contain fibre and help add to a healthy gut 💩
Try vary your fruit as much as possible to get an array of healthy benefits 🤗
.
.

caption:
Sometimes it's not enough to just eat healthily or eat in a calorie deficit 🤷‍♀️
.
.
Here's another addition to the never ending list of ways to be a healthier version of yourself 🙌
.
.
Mindful = Not Mindless
.
.
1. Eat with intent - savour food.

2. Chew your food - did you know you should be chewing your food about 32 times before swallowing? 🙈

3. Eat at a table if possible - avoid eating of your knees in poor posture, avoid standing 

4. Give yourself time - 5 minutes is RARELY enough. Give yourself the time you deserve to take a lunch break

5. Limit distractions - no phones or tvs while eating.
.
.
A lot of the time when we experience stomach discomfort - cramping, bloating etc we put it down to certain foods. Unfortunately our environment and our focus can quite often be a factor and one that is totally overlooked 🥴
.
.
Hit save on this one for later 🙌

caption:
ℍ𝕖𝕒𝕝𝕥𝕙 ℙ𝕪𝕣𝕒𝕞𝕚𝕕 🔺️
.
.
The fitness industry is becoming saturated. There is so much conflicting information it's overwhelming to even know where to start. I want to stand out and not fade into the same mould.
.
.
I'm pretty safe though because:

❎ I won't be that 'hot' fitness model - although leave some 🔥 if you love the posts of my sweaty red head
❎ I won't be posing in lingerie to get thousands followers - although I do look good in Lingerie 😜
❎ I won't be putting videos up of myself doing 10 variations of crunches or booty band workouts.
.
.
I actually struggle to find time to put up educational content these days because I am so busy with my clients. All my time, effort and education goes into helping everyone of them. They have invested their time and money in me and I'm so proud of the work we do together ❤
.
.
Anyway, I'm going to be different to a lot of other fitness accounts - I'm not going to say its just as simple as 'Eat Less, Move More✌'. 
Sorry unfortunately I just don't think it is.
.
.
My hierarchy begins with stress reduction - why?
.
.
Well because stress in all shapes and sizes leads to incredible problems in the body. 
Example: Stress of too little calories - Can lead to hormonal disruptions which can lead to amenorrhoea which can lead to infertility. Too little calories and poor food quality can lead to micronutrient deficiencies and injury. 
Stress can be as simple as drinking too much caffeine or as severe as overwhelm. Add up all the daily stresses in your life and see how many there are😱
.
.
Sleep should be AS IMPORTANT as exercise and nutrition combined - end of story😴
.
.
Nutrition and food quality come next.🥦
.
.
Exercise in general should technically come next but this is my pyramid so I'm going to do what I believe is most important - irrespective of goals 🏋‍♀️
.
Lastly, individual variance. Have a condition or a goal? Follow all the below first and foremost and the individuality should come last 
.
.
Interested to see your views 🤔

.
.

💫 Unhappy in your body?
💥 Toxic relationship? 
💫 Lacking confidence?
💥 Single?
💫 Poor relationship with food?
.
.

𝐘𝐨𝐮 𝐧𝐞𝐞𝐝 𝐭𝐨 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐭 𝐥𝐨𝐨𝐤𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐭𝐨𝐰𝐚𝐫𝐝𝐬 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐟𝐮𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞 🔮

.

𝘋𝘪𝘥 𝘺𝘰𝘶 𝘬𝘯𝘰𝘸?
🎯 Extreme dieting can affect your fertility
🎯 Hormonal imbalances can have an affect on bone density
🎯 Too much exercise causes stress on the body
🎯 Nutrient deficiencies can have detrimental consequences on people's health
🎯 The knock on affect of dieting or exercise obsession can have an impact on social occassions
🎯 Obsession with food can lead to disordered eating
.
.

.

caption:
𝕀 𝕘𝕖𝕥 𝕓𝕠𝕣𝕖𝕕...
.
.
Sick of chicken and broccoli? 🤔
.
.
You will quickly run out of ideas if you try to change whole meals so why not change up the sides 💁‍♀️
.
.
From my experience, people tend to like certain foods. If you stick with the foods you like, you're more likely to stick with it 🙏 
.
.
So my advice:
- Change the vegetables - not just the type but how you cook them - stir fry, boil, steam, roast. 

- Change the carb source - sick of brown rice? Add quinoa or cous cous! Sick of potato, try sweet potato.

- Rotate Week 1 - Chicken and pork based meals. Week 2 - Tofu and tuna based meals. Week 3 - Turkey & Salmon based meals. Week 4 - Prawn & Beef based meals. And start the cycle again 🙌
.
.
Save this post for later 🙋‍♀️

𝐄𝐱𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐥𝐲 𝐰𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐝𝐨𝐜𝐭𝐨𝐫 𝐨𝐫𝐝𝐞𝐫𝐞𝐝 🙏
.
.
I am beyond blessed that I love my job and honestly I'm so grateful for all the people I help on a daily basis ❤ 
.
.
I used to say 'Find a job you love and you'll never work a day in your life'. I now know this is NOT the case. Although I thoroughly enjoy my job, being switched on 7 days a week is hard. Holidays and time away have always helped me to unwind 🙏
.
.
All it takes is a night away, a break from technology and a cocktail in hand 🤣
.
.
But in all seriousness, especially to those in business for themselves - never feel guilty for needing a little down time 🙏 The way I see it, our clients will thank us for it ❤
.
.
Ready to smash Monday after a beautiful break with @o_boyce ❤

caption:
Training with an injury?
.
.
Lets be totally clear on the context. It was training WITH an injury. Not training THROUGH an injury. Very different. 
.
.
However, it is not uncommon to train through an injury either. I want to be clear here. I am NOT telling you to train with an injury. This is very individual dependent and requires advice from a professional I.e Doctor, physio etc.
.
.
✅Training with an injury 

👉 Anyone who knows me, knows how much of an advocate I am of this. When I injure lower body, upper body is still very much manageable, however, I am careful not to put too much pressure on affected area 

👉 Mental Health - I don't know about the rest of you but mental health is one of my main reasons for training so if I had to sit still I'd cry 😩 

👉 Socialising - It can be a tough time going through an injury. If you are a sports player it can be so isolating 😢 Being able to do something in th gym, in a class or with your team can have a huge impact on your mindframe ❤ 

➡️ Training through an injury 

🚫 Only do under advice from your healthcare professional (But a little bit of important info is there actually is evidence to suggest you can) 

✅ Nutrition with an injury
⛔ Most overlooked aspect of recovery in my opinion 

👉 Fats are anti inflammatory and a vital part of the healing process 

👉 Protein as ALWAYS is King 🤴 

👉 Calories will need to be adjusted for activity levels - But do NOT dramatically cut calories. This is where a lot of people go wrong. The body needs food and fuel to repair and recover so while you may not be as active don't underestimate the importance of fuel. 

➡️Remember Recovery does not just mean 'rest' 

Would love to hear your experiences?

People who are insecure in themselves are uncomfortable or intimated by how confident I am 🤷‍♀️
.
.
That is not a reflection of me, that is their problem, I have no control of that 🤨🤷‍♀️
.
.
I used to be that person. I judged confident people. Said they were cocky 🙄 I didn't understand because I just wasn't happy in myself 😲😠
.
.
🎯What's wrong with being self assured?
🎯What's wrong with knowing your worth?
🎯Whats wrong with being super confident?
.
.
Honestly, if you are someone who has been victimised or undermined by another person, try brush it off. You can't control it and it's actually not a reflection of you but the person saying the hurtful things 🤦‍♀️
.
.
'Confident women - may we know them, may we be them, may we raise them' ❤

caption:
Sometimes I think to myself...
.
.
'Ah it definitely is so much easier for me...'
.
.
Then I think back 🤔
.
.
👉 I was the PICKIEST eater you can ever imagine. Eating healthily did NOT come easy to me. It took years and years. Then I went through periods of super strict clean eating which lead to binging. To have found such a good balance and relationship with food was not easy at all. But we've got there 🙌

👉 It's very easy to see I love exercise. Its not a struggle for me. But that doesn't mean I haven't put in work. Serious work. Not just in the last few years but since I was a teenager. 12 years of training - with injuries, and through adversity. So while the intention of training is easy for me, the work I have put in hasn't been.

👉 It's clear I have never struggled with my weight. I haven't had your typical 'transformation'. I still put that one down to my consistency over the years. But just because I've never carried weight doesn't mean I've never struggled with body image & self confidence. I've done a lot of work on my relationship with my self esteem 🙏And I'm finally in a place where I am happy no matter what I look like ❤

caption:
NOT A TRANSFORMATION POST 👆
.
.
Pregnancy was once considered a reason to stop all exercise and eat for two. Which often led to excessive weight gain, gestational diabetes, pre eclampsia, difficult births and difficulty with weight loss post partum. Now, obviously pregnancy is massively different for everyone. Unfortunately there is no one size fits all. But the information I'm giving is general recommendations. If you have any further questions. It is probably worth talking it over with your doctor or other medical professional ☺️
.
.
Exercise:
-Studies have shown that exercise during pregnancy can actually lead to easier birthing and healthy weight gain during pregnancy.
-It is also thought to be beneficial for post partum weight loss.
-Guidelines for exercise encourage women to stick with similar exercises prior to pregnancy. Light Resistance based training is highly recommended.
- Adaptations may be needed through different trimesters such as: Not lying on your back for too long or overhead extension exercises may need to be removed. This is very dependent on individuals
- Hiit training may not be recommended after trimester 1 - again very dependent on the individual and their training history but it will become a lot harder
- Light exercise like walking can possibly be done the whole way up until due date
- The main take home point from this is: Exercise during pregnancy is encouraged. Everyone's levels, capabilities and pregnancies are different so go with how you're feeling. Don't over exert yourself. And talk with your coach and doctor 🙏
.
.
Nutrition
- This idea of eating double for two is non sense 🙈
- Calories shouldn't even be increased in first trimester. Daily calories should be increased by about 300Cals in 2nd trimester and 500Cals in 3rd Trimester.
- There may be food aversions or food cravings during pregnancy - this is totally normal.
- Try to stick with whole nutritious foods
- Supplements include: Folic Acid, Vitamin D, Iron and Omega 3 Fatty acids. But talk to your doctor or health are consultant before taking any of these.
.
.
Something to be very aware of during pregnancy is labelling. Continued below👇

caption:
Spot the difference 🔍
.
.
When people say to me they 'want to lose weight', more often than not - it's fat loss they are actually seeking. And there is a difference 👆
.
.
Weight loss is a combination of fat, muscle and water. When people go on very restrictive diets they often see a huge scale shift on week 1 due to a reduction in total body water - as opposed to fat loss. 
.
.
If people focus solely on scale loss unfortunately there is likely to be muscle mass loss - which is what we don't want. As far as I'm aware some diet clubs actually discourage resistance training as it will lead to muscle gain (and essentially an increase on the scales) 🙈
.
.
Ladies, please please understand smaller ≠ happier 🚫
.
.
If someone is overweight/obese, weight loss should be the goal to a healthier overall body composition 🙏
.
.
Anyone else - Fat Loss is what you should be seeking 👆
.
.
Save for someone who you think needs to see this x

caption:
𝐃𝐨𝐧'𝐭 𝐧𝐞𝐠𝐥𝐞𝐜𝐭 𝐟𝐚𝐭𝐬
.
.
Fat gets a bad rep. 
Sure it is 9Kcal per gram but it is an essential part of a balanced fat. 
.
.
Fats provide us with energy, makes up our cell membranes of our brain and nervous system. Fats are necessary to transport vitamins A,D,E and K and make and balance certain hormones.
.
.
Dietary Fat can be found in 2 forms:
Saturated – mainly found in animal products like meat, dairy, eggs, coconut
Unsaturated – found in marine sources like fish oils, as well as nuts, seeds and vegetable oils
.
. 
For years saturated fat was thought to be associated with higher risk of Cardiovascular Disease and so it was deemed as ‘unhealthy’ or ‘bad for you’. The problem with saturated fat was not the actual fat itself but rather the increased consumption of processed food or the large quantities of saturated fat products. Saturated fat helps increase the cholesterol production in the body which is an essential part of metabolism and in the production of steroid hormones. So saturated fat should feature in our diet, just maybe don’t latter every meal in butter.
.
. 
Unsaturated fats are made up of mono and polyunsaturated fats.  These contain our omega 3 and omega 6 fatty acids. Omega 3 fatty acids open our airways and blood vessels. They reduce our blood lipids and cholesterol and lower inflammation and pain. Omega 6 fatty acids do the opposite. Both are needed in the body, without both we wouldn’t heal or recover from exercise. The problem with Western diets is that we don’t have the proper ratios. We are at about 10:1 where we should be at 2:1 (omega 6/omega 3).
.
. 
Low fat diets were a fad a few years ago. While people reduced calories, they increased their intake of processed foods. Diets lacked fats and fat soluble vitamins so instead of being healthier people were losing weight but were not healthier.
.
. 
Fats are an essential part of any healthy diet. Be aware that they are very calorie dense so portion control may be important and don’t opt for processed versions. Enjoy them as part of a balanced lifestyle.

.

caption:
✅We like comfort.

✖But nothing exciting happens in our comfort zone.

✅We enjoy winning. 

✖ But if you don't fail - you're not even trying.

❓Why do successful people achieve their goals❓

1. They are willing to work at it. That's means winning but it also means failing.

2. They are willing to do what other people don't. Are you part of the majority or minority?

3. Bulletproof mindset - work on yourself every single day, inside and out.

'𝐘𝐨𝐮 𝐜𝐚𝐧 𝐡𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐮𝐥𝐭𝐬 𝐨𝐫 𝐞𝐱𝐜𝐮𝐬𝐞𝐬 - 𝐧𝐨𝐭 𝐛𝐨𝐭𝐡'

𝘚𝘰 𝘸𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘢𝘳𝘦 𝘺𝘰𝘶 𝘨𝘰𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘵𝘰 𝘤𝘩𝘰𝘴𝘦?

𝐒𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐥𝐞 𝐒𝐧𝐚𝐜𝐤𝐬 🍿
.
.
Roasted Chickpeas 👩‍🍳
.
.
Makes 4 Servings:
✅ Tin Chickpeas
✅ Teaspoons Olive Oil 
✅ Chilli Powder
✅ Garlic Powder
✅ Sea Salt
.
.
Drain chickpeas. Drizzle oil, salt and spices. Bake in oven for 20-30 mins at 180 degrees. Enjoy 😁
.
.
P.s they are higher in protein than your average fruit as a snack but I wouldn't necessarily call these a 'high protein' snack.

#simplesnacks #healthyoptions #healthyfood #nutritioncoach #realresults

caption:
Things I would have told my younger self:
.
.
1. Health is so much more important than weight

2. Stop trying to be perfect. Perfection doesn't exsist

3. Relax a little. Don't stress so much. Good things come to people who work but remember there's a thing called life that needs to be enjoyed

4. Problems aren't solved at the bottom of a vodka bottle

5. Fitness is NOT about being skinny. Fitness is not about abs.

6. Eat your bloody vegetables and stop being so damn picky. It feels so much better on your body and you'd have so much more energy

7. Make up isn't life. You are beautiful, stop hiding yourself with layers of foundation and baggy hoodies.

8.Appreciate everyone in your life. You think they will always be around. Unfortunately that's not the case 💔 

Although these are visual pictures this is not a physical transformation. I love my body not for how it looks but what it can do.

#liveyourbestlife

caption:
𝟐𝟖 𝐃𝐚𝐲 𝐊𝐢𝐜𝐤𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐞𝐫 

‼️I'm looking for 5 ladies who want to become strong and confident while eating the foods they enjoy‼️
.
.
Feel like you've tried everything and still see no results? Here's 3 reasons my coaching programme could work for you: 

1. I educate women on nutrition. I don't give meal plans but actually teach you the importance of nutrient dense food. I help you calculate calories and understand the foods you need to fuel your body. I'm also a big advocate of including foods you actually enjoy! 

2. Want to be able to lift your suitcase with ease when lockdown finishes? Want to perform a push up? Want to become a strong, independent female?
I focus on resistance training and encourage women to become the strongest they can be. 

3. I help women become the best versions of themselves. Confidence comes from the inside out and I help women find that sassy female that's hiding inside. 

I know sometimes people are afraid to make a long term commitment so this kickstarter may be exactly what you need to start your health and fitness journey with me. Did I also mention the incredible community that comes with it? 

𝐖𝐡𝐞𝐧 𝐝𝐨𝐞𝐬 𝐢𝐭 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐭?
𝐌𝐨𝐧𝐝𝐚𝐲 𝟔𝐭𝐡 𝐒𝐞𝐩𝐭𝐞𝐦𝐛𝐞𝐫 

𝘈𝘱𝘱𝘭𝘪𝘤𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯𝘴 𝘤𝘭𝘰𝘴𝘦: 
𝘍𝘳𝘪𝘥𝘢𝘺 3𝘳𝘥

If you're ready to become the strongest, most confident version of yourself - Dm Me 'Kickstart' to hear more.

🎯 Nutrition - Hierarchy of Importance 🎯
.
.
Here's is my nutrition triangle. This is not a standard pyramid, it's mostly just my opinion 😁
.
.
Diet is defined as the kinds of food a person habitually eats. No diet will ever be successful if someone cannot successfully stick to it and be consistent with it. And for this reason, it is my bread and butter. It is the most important element when it comes to nutrition.
.
.
I am a nutritionist so Food Quality is my next most important element. I know in terms of energy balance it is as simple as calories in versus calories out but I just cannot educate people and say that
Food quality doesn't matter. If I didn't care about my clients and I just cared about transformation photos I could give someone a calorie calculator and say 'Here once it's within your calories it doesn't matter what the meals include'. Maybe not for body composition (questionable) but certainly for long term health 🤦‍♀️
.
.
Then, I put calories. Calories do matter but to me food quality matters more. As I've said, this is opinion. At the end of the day, it is an energy balance equation so I can't disregard them but just be aware of how inaccurate logging and tracking can be. Just be informed 👊
.
.
Technically that should be macronutrients but I'm putting protein as the king 🤴 Although I do feel very strongly about good balance so please don't disregard carbs and fats 😬
.
.
Lastly, comes supplements. Supplements should always be an addition.
.
.
Did I miss anything 🤔
.
.
Interested in opinions too 😇

caption:
If scales is the only measure of progress you're using, you are are going down a slippery slope. ⛰
.
.
What happens if you don't lose weight one week? Does it undo all the hard work you've done? All the consistent effort you've made. All the new habits you've built. Or what if your weight plateaus? Does this mean you quit and give up? 🤷‍♀️
.
.
We are all impatient humans. And we want to be rewarded for our hard work. And that's fair. But success does not happen over night in any industry so why would weight loss be different. 🚫
.
.
Consistency is key. Finding a method that works for your goals but that you also enjoy - making it sustainable. And don't forget about all the good habits you are making. If you made one good habits each week for a year, that'd be 52 good habits. ✅ Keep up the great work 🥳

#slowprogressisbetterthannoprogress

caption:
Tomorrow is a luxury we won't always have so please stop wishing your life away 🙏
.
.
Life is here and now 🙏 Not in the past. Not in the future. Believe me, I'm making all the plans for when Lockdown is over and I'm so excited to do it 👊 But I have not wished my life away.
.
.
I've been grateful that it's given me more time with Owen. It's given me time to save some extra money. I will have completed a new course. And I plan on coming out of Lockdown fitter and stronger than I've ever been 👊
.
.
It's not a productivity challenge. I know people are struggling - myself included. I went through my hardest week in Austrailia last week. So I am empathetic 🙏 But I truely try to live in the here and now. And allow myself have bad days and bad weeks 🙏
.
.
But do yourself a favour and stop telling yourself:
❓ You'll be happier when....
❓ You'll start exercising when...
❓ You'll stop drinking when...
❓ You'll eat healthier when...
.
.
I'm here to say that day may NEVER come. I don't want to be morbid or unsupportive but it's the truth.
.
.
So do yourself a favour. And take this as a sign to start living. Not just for When lockdown is over. Not just for the weekends. For the here and now 👊🙌
.
.

caption:
𝕊𝕒𝕞𝕖 𝕤𝕒𝕞𝕖 💁‍♀️
.
.
When people said to Arnold Schwarzenegger 
'Oh but I don't want to look like you.'

He replied:
'Don't worry. You never will.'
.
.
Let me tell you. Building muscle is BLOODY HARD. You don't just wake up one day and 'are bulky' 😅😅😅
.
.
I've spent YEARS improving myself and getting stronger, fitter and healthier. That is my goal. So don't think after lifting afew weights you're going to gain 10kg of muscle and look 'bulky'. And honestly, most people will NEVER EVER train as hard as I train 😅 
.
.
But let me also tell you. Majority of the photos I take are mid or post training when I have a serious pump. In normal clothes, I'm a normal size 8-10 female. I don't have jacked quads or a shoulder vein 😅 (Even though I'd be happy to walk around like that)
.
.
Moral of the story: most people will never train hard enough to get bulky. Most people don't walk round jacked 😅 The 'toned' look you want is actually muscle - so if you say you want to be 'toned' and don't want muscle you're actually contradicting yourself 😅

#onlinecommunity #onlinefitnesscoach #health #strongerfromtheinsideout #strongwomen #strength #strengthtraining

caption:
𝐌𝐲 𝐜𝐥𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬 𝐚𝐜𝐡𝐢𝐞𝐯𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐢𝐫 𝐠𝐨𝐚𝐥𝐬...
𝐇𝐞𝐫𝐞'𝐬 𝐰𝐡𝐲 🤔
.
.
1. Consistency - I make sure every single one of my clients can be consistent with their goals. How? Because each of their programmes and habits are tailored to them.
Eileen mother of 3 barely has enough time to do 2 sessions a week when the kids are off school so why would I give her 5 sessions a week like Mary (a student)? Consistency is key. Each individual is different. Consistency looks different to everyone, but it is the key to every successful fitness journey.
.
.
2. Why? - I told you my why last week. My why is to be a role model. Everyone else has their own why - but unless you know yours and REALLY REALLY care about it, you're probably going no where.
.
.
3. Unrealistic Goals - 
Abs is the perfect example. 
Apart from the tiny minority of genetically gifted people - Abs are not that easy to achieve. Firstly, people don't want to sacrifice what it takes to achieve them. Secondly, being at that low body fat (especially for a woman) is very difficult and unsustainable. So set yourself more realistic, attainable goals.
.
.
4. Impatient - Look I'm impatient too. I get it. But honestly, if you're putting a time frame on your health and fitness journey - you're probably already off to a bad start. You should be looking at the long term - in a few months, a few years etc. It can be good to do a little kick-starter but your fitness journey should never have an end date 👊
.
.
5. You don't have a road map to your goals - This one is easily the most fixable one. Why do you keep trying to do it alone? There are people out there who can help. 

✅People like me who have cared about health and fitness their whole lives. 
✅People like me who have helped 100s of women already.
✅ People like me who have the qualifications to back it up.
.
.
If you:
- want to stop using excuses and start seeing results 
- are sick of stopping and starting 
- are serious about changing
.
.
DM me ' Coach'.

Happy Anniversary to the most beautiful human to roam this planet ❤
.
.
Every day I think of how grateful I am to have you. 10 years on and I'm still the luckiest girl in the world ❤
.
.
It's not always been plain sailing but honestly it's all worked out exactly as it should have ❤
.
.
Thank you for being my rock ❤

caption:
✴ My 𝙬𝙝𝙮? 
.
.
If you haven't already noticed I feel very passionate about helping people. 
.
.
I too, disliked my body image, under fuelled and exercised to burn calories. I too did endless amounts of cardio and crunches in a bid to find abs. And guess what, nothing changed. How I felt about myself didn't change one single bit. Even when I was a size 6 and probably <18% BF with visible abs, I still wasn't happy. 
.
.
And you won't be either, unless you deal with what's going on in your head and understand the 
Importance of your why. 
.
.
My 𝙬𝙝𝙮 is to be a role model 🙋‍♀️ I want younger girls to look up to me. I want peers to understand the message I am preaching. I want older women to see that fad diets and restriction is NOT the answer. I want Dad's to say 'You should listen to that Mc Loone one' (if you know you know 😅).
.
.
My 𝙬𝙝𝙮 is to help as many women as I can become the best versions of themselves. 
💥I want to educate women that you can still enjoy the food you like and be happy. 
💥I want women to see how empowering it is to become physically stronger. 
💥I want to help women see how incredible they are and stop focusing so much on how they look on the outside and see what they have to offer from the inside. 
💥I want to see confidence radiating from the women I work with. 
.
.
I truely believe I was put on this planet for 3 reasons:
1. To help as many people as physically possible.
2. To become the fittest and healthiest version of myself
3. To have loads of animals 
.
.
If this sounds like you. Reach out and Dm me 'Help'. 🙏

caption:
When I started my journey with Amanda 6 months ago, I was stuck in a rut. I was definitely a good during the week, rubbish at the weekend eater.  

Amanda is also such an amazing role model for women with her own fitness goals. 
I’m looking forward to continuing my journey with nutrition and fitness now and I feel Amanda has given me the tools and guidance to continue in confidence. 

Thanks Amanda, you’ve been the influence I needed in my life these past few months 🥰

If this sounds like something you need in your life. Dm me 'Coach'.

You are not weak if you ask for help ❌❌❌
In Fact if anything I think you're a little more courageous 
🤩🤩🤩
.
.
You are not expected to know everything. That's why people have occupations with the relevant knowledge and skills to help 👌
.
.
💥 If you are a student, unsure of your path. Please talk to a career guidance teacher.
💥 If you are unsure of your career and thinking about changing everything for a different route. Maybe you could see a life coach.
💥 If you are sick. See a doctor.
💥 If you are having mental health issues, a counsellor may be an option
💥 If you're having car troubles, go to a mechanic.
💥 If your phone isn't working, bring it to a phone shop.
.
.
See the trend???
.
.
Once upon a time I thought I was totally independent. I didn't want to ask for help from anyone!!! But then I realised, I can't do it all alone and actually support and guidance is the best thing I could get. NOW, I ask for help all the time. From family, friends, and colleagues. I have a coach. If my mental health is affecting me I call someone for help. One of the best things I ever did was see a life coach ❤
.
.
Why is it so hard for people to see the same applies to training and nutrition? 🥴🥴🥴 You could be spending weeks, months or even years trying to do it alone? 🙈 Wasting your time and money in the process. If you aren't qualified in the area. YOU CAN ALWAYS ASK FOR HELP 🙏 Please please stop making poor nutrition choices based on what Google told you. Stop wasting time trying to 'shred belly fat' based on a free workout Susan gave you.
.
Ask for help. Stop wasting your time. I'm literally just a phone call away. 
.
.
Pm me with 'Get Started' to organise a phonecall 😁

Remember it's not all exercise and healthy eating 🤔
.
.
Mental Health and what you do to improve it is just as important. 
.
.
And don't forget health (both physical and mental) is about consistent effort. Attack it with intent. Be grateful and savor each element. Remember, it's about the long term ❤👵
.
.
How many of the above do you do daily? 🙏

caption:
𝙄𝙛 𝙮𝙤𝙪 𝙬𝙚𝙧𝙚 𝙩𝙤 𝙙𝙞𝙚 𝙩𝙤𝙢𝙤𝙧𝙧𝙤𝙬 𝙬𝙤𝙪𝙡𝙙 𝙮𝙤𝙪 𝙝𝙤𝙣𝙚𝙨𝙩𝙡𝙮 𝙗𝙚 𝙝𝙖𝙥𝙥𝙮 𝙬𝙞𝙩𝙝 𝙮𝙤𝙪𝙧 𝙡𝙞𝙛𝙚, 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙘𝙝𝙤𝙞𝙘𝙚𝙨 𝙮𝙤𝙪 𝙝𝙖𝙫𝙚 𝙢𝙖𝙙𝙚 🤔
.
.
I got this tattoo just before moving to Austrailia. I certainly would never say I had a bad life - but I wasn't FULLY happy. I had to make changes. 
💥The first and best thing I did was quit football. This is not a stab at anyone playing or all the amazing people I know through GAA. But it was no longer bringing me joy. If anything, it was an added stress to my life. 
💥The second thing I had to do which was a hell of a lot harder was to try and heal a very strained relationship. 
💥And the third choice I made was Austrailia. 
.
.
Let me tell you we all have these tough decisions to make. Yours won't be the same as mine, but honestly if something is not adding to your life and is bringing you so much misery - YOU HAVE THE POWER TO DO SOMETHING ABOUT IT!!!!
.
.
✴Maybe it's the job you dread going into every day
✴ For some it's a relationship going nowhere 
✴ Countless people are unhappy in their body and doing absolutely NOTHING about it 😭 
.
.
YOU HAVE CONTROL OF YOUR LIFE. THESE ARE CHOICES YOU ARE MAKING EVERY DAY. 
.
.
Honestly, I can happily say, if I died tomorrow. I would be dying with memories. I would be leaving behind a life I am PROUD of 🙏

Could you say the same? 🤔

caption:
I remember 7 years ago when I started strength training. 

I remember saying I wish I'd started sooner... 

7 years on and other people now say that same thing to me. 

It's never too late to start. I know people who start it in their teens and I also know people who start it in their 40s. 

Never use it's too late as an excuse. The time passes anyway.

It is never too late to make an improvement to your health. 

Stop waiting. There will never be a good time. Just do it! 

Not sure what to do? Why not use the next 90 days to make that long awaited start? 🙋‍♀️ 

I am releasing 5 spaces in my Strong and Sassy Programme. Dm me 'Coach' if you're interested.
🔥🔥🔥

.

.
.
I've been there 🙋‍♀️ I used to eat on the go ALL THE TIME. If I didn't have Tupperware I had to make do with what I could get in the shops 🙌 I can promise you though, you do NOT have to revert to delis and unhealthy options just because you're not prepared 👊
.
.
Here are some examples of meals I used to eat on the go. (P.S I still eat a lot of these types of meals because convenience is key for me 😜) but luckily now I get @hunger_gains_ - convenience and amazing tasting healthy food. Win win 🥳🙋‍♀️
.
All of these require minimal time and effort. And you knit pick and say 'Packet bought chicken isn't the healthiest?' Well Susan... it's better than that sausage roll you reached for last week 🙈😅
.
.
💢 You can have excuses or results 👊 You can't have both 💢

caption:
Have you ever heard of the phrase – ‘You're the average of the five people who you spend the most time with’
 
🧪Let’s do a little experiment and see how you go:
 
🤔Are your friends and social network fit and healthy? Or are your meet ups all limited to the takeaways/pub/eating out? 🥡🍷

👨‍👩‍👧‍👦Does your family live a fit and healthy lifestyle?

👴🏼👵Are your parents fit and healthy?

If your parents and/or partner is overweight or unhealthy the research shows that you’re much more likely to also be so.

Does your work 📉encourage or facilitate a healthy atmosphere – healthy food options and/or end of trip facilities/gym access?
Are your colleagues in great shape?🏋️‍♀️
 
⭕️Your environment is EVERYTHING. Within your environment you will have conscious and unconscious biases and make assumptions about life in general based on what’s happening closest to you.
 
🧩If you’re in a circle of friends/family and work where health isn’t a key cornerstone… is it any wonder that you have No Motivation, No Plan and No Consistency?
 
If you would like to take my fitness lifestyle scorecard to see how you score- comment ‘SCORECARD’ below and I’ll shoot you the link 👊

caption:
𝕀𝕤 𝕙𝕒𝕡𝕡𝕚𝕟𝕖𝕤𝕤 𝕒𝕟 𝕠𝕡𝕥𝕚𝕠𝕟? 🤔
.
.
Well that depends...
Are you focusing on what you THINK will make you happy?
.
.
Or are you working on things that ACTUALLY make you happy? 
.
.
𝐖𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐝𝐨𝐞𝐬 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐬𝐜𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞 𝐬𝐚𝐲?
✅ Kindness has been shown to increase happiness - Not just acts of kindness but actually thinking about being kinder.

✅ Spending money on other people - check out the book 'Happy Money'. 

✅ Having more time - studies have shown that people who have more free time and less money are happier than those who have more money and less time

✅ Social connection increases happiness - What I miss most in Lockdown 😢

✅ Meditation causes increased positive emotions. Not just at the time of meditation but it has lasting effects afterwards. Meditation changes and strengthens the brain!

✅ Exercise - a study done by Babayak et al concluded that exercise alone was more effective in reducing depression rates than medication

✅ Sleep - Enough said 😴
.
.
Is it obvious I'm currently studying the Science of Well Being? 😃
.
.
Anyway I get a lot of people asking me how am I always so positive and happy. Well honestly I have nailed A LOT of the above 👆👆👆
.
.
Obviously we know exercise is not something I struggle with. Sleep is just as important and I meditate every night before bed. I have always been an extrovert and I thrive off social connections. I truly believe I'm a very kind person and I get a genuine kick off 'spending money on people'. I have NOT always had time. But since moving to Austrailia things have changed. That's not to say I'm not busy. It just means I spend my time wisely and have time for the things I enjoy in life ❤🙏 I've never been money driven so enjoying my job and having time to travel and do the things  I want to do are what makes me happy 🥰
.
.
𝘿𝙞𝙙 𝙖𝙣𝙮 𝙤𝙛 𝙩𝙝𝙞𝙨 𝙨𝙪𝙥𝙧𝙞𝙨𝙚 𝙮𝙤𝙪? 🤔

We are all creatures of habit 🐈‍⬛
.
.
And while those habits can be very beneficial, they can also hinder us from reaching our full potential 🚀
.
.
Same things goes for nutrition. Eat the same foods. Get the same nutrients. See the same results 👌
.
.
Eat more variety. Get more nutrients. See more benefits 🥳
.
.
That's the simplest way I can put it 🤷‍♀️
.
.
You don't have to overhaul change your diet. It could be as simple as adding a new fruit every week?
Or swapping chicken breasts for chicken thighs? What about adding quinoa instead of cous cous? Or swapping a stir fry for raw veggies? 
.
.
💥 Small changes = better results 💥

#nutritioncoach #nutritionist #onlinecoach #onlinecommunity #nutritioneducation

𝐈 𝐜𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐝 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐦𝐨𝐫𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐠...
.
.
Actually that's an understatement. I bawled 😭🤣
.
.
Why?
If anyone watched the CrossFit games at the weekend you'll know how @anniethorisdottir came 3rd. Not only had she a baby less than a year
ago, she self confessed had Post Natal Depression AND her Grandma died last Friday. 
.
.
Every single obstacle that could be thrown at her had been - physical and mental. And she still managed to pursue. Not only that but she did it with a smile on her face her entire time ❤
.
.
Before the final event, she said the end result didn't matter, she was so proud of herself regardless 😭
.
.
How many of you out there would say that to yourselves? 🤔
.
.
I have never been more proud to be involved in a sport where: 
1. Women SUPPORT Women - even their competitors 
2. Women believe in themselves and know their capabilities 
3. Women can describe themelseves as 'Proud'
4.  A sport that focuses on what you can do as opposed to how you look
🙏🙏🙏
.
.
P.s The above is Pre Covid Lockdown
.
P.p.s Can you guess how proud I was of myself? 🙋‍♀️

caption:
‼️I'm looking for 5 ladies who want to become strong and confident while eating the foods they enjoy. I've had a few spaces become available for my 90 Day Strong and Sassy Programme in August‼️
.
.
Feel like you've tried everything and still see no results? Here's 3 reasons my coaching programme could work for you: 

1. I educate women on nutrition. I don't give meal plans but actually teach you the importance of nutrient dense food. I help you calculate calories and understand the foods you need to fuel your body. I'm also a big advocate of including foods you actually enjoy! 

2. Want to be able to lift your suitcase with ease when lockdown finishes? Want to perform a push up? Want to become a strong, independent female?
I focus on resistance training and encourage women to become the strongest they can be. 

3. I help women become the best versions of themselves. Confidence comes from the inside out and I help women find that sassy female that's hiding inside. 

These are just a few of the amazing elements to my Strong and Sassy programme, not to mention the incredible community that comes with it. 

If you're ready to become the strongest, most confident version of yourself - Dm Me 'Coach' to hear more.

I know some of you love the comfort of a warm meal this time of year (yes it's cold in Austrailia). 

This pumpkin soup is a good source of carbs and colour 🙋‍♀️ But unfortunately lacks protein. Here's a quick and simple way to add protein to your soups 👨‍🍳

ℂ𝕠𝕒𝕔𝕙𝕚𝕟𝕘 𝕚𝕤 𝕗𝕠𝕣 𝕒𝕟𝕪𝕠𝕟𝕖 𝕨𝕙𝕠 𝕚𝕤 𝕨𝕚𝕝𝕝𝕚𝕟𝕘 𝕥𝕠 𝕝𝕖𝕒𝕣𝕟, 𝕦𝕟𝕕𝕖𝕣𝕤𝕥𝕒𝕟𝕕 𝕒𝕟𝕕 𝕓𝕖 𝕖𝕕𝕦𝕔𝕒𝕥𝕖𝕕 👊
.
.
In recent days:

1.I've spoken to one woman and she has had people say to her 'Sure why do you need a coach?'. 
Why the hell not? 🤔 We are so quick to promote counselling for our mental health but you promote coaching and it can only be used for someone overweight? 🤔 
Well I'm here to say I don't discriminate. I don't believe coaching is only for people looking to lose weight. 

2. I spoke to two women struggling with their change in appearance. Gaining weight is sometimes optimal for health. But you know what, it can be hard. And sometimes you need support ❤ A coach can help with that.
.
.
Coaching is not a fitness programme or a diet plan. It's a lifestyle change.

#onlinecoach #onlinecommunity #coaching

I'm not that religious but I am a little spiritual 🙏
.
.
I believe in signs and signals.
.
.
I believe what's for you won't pass you.
.
.
I believe every time I see a white feather my Dad is near ❤
.
.
I think this morning's sky was a sign to us all in Sydney. Appreciate what we have. Find gratitude in every single day ❤
.
.
Remember, even after the darkest night, the sun will rise 🌅 

#mindyourmentalhealth 
#lockdown

caption:
𝐈 𝐡𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐛𝐞𝐞𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐞...
.
.
That God damn comparison bubble again.
.
.
Oh if only I had her legs 🤔
.
.
Why does she have a washboard stomach and I don't 😭
.
.
Omg would she ever cover up. Who does she think she is 🙀
.
.
I was so obsessed with comparing myself to other women. I was so certain if I looked like other people I would be happier in my own body. I was indoctrinated. I used to look up Owen's exes for Christ sake and compare myself 😅 (Just so you know if any of you follow me 😅). 
.
.
So how did I get to present day Amanda? My God it took time and a lot of effort. Took some counselling too 🤟 Becoming happy comfortable and confident in my body took gratitude, talking to myself and listening to a lot of positive self help books. 
.
.
I started to appreciate how incredible my body is. Not for what it looks like but what it can do. And after that changed, so did my whole outlook.
.
.
I still get a little envious (of a good tan 😍😍😍) but I'm pretty darn happy with my body. I no longer compare it to smaller waist sizes. I'm not upset any more that I have a little pouch (that's my happiness pouch). 
.
.
I'm proud of my body. And you should be too ❤
.
.
P.s Appreciating a rocking body is different 😍 I'm allllllll about that
👊 But I'm happy in my own 👊

#happyinmyownskin

caption:
What you think you want and what you need are not always the same thing 🙀
.
.
I work really hard to give women what they actually need. In reality, this looks like:
👆 Nutrition Education - stop with food guilt, stop with binge and restrict cycle, eating foods they actually enjoy

👆 Resistance training - women think they need to burn more calories and HIIT style workouts are the only way to do this ✖ Resistance based training changes our body shape and increases our BMR.

👆 Accountability - we all need accountability. Myself included. It helps us stay on track but also it gives us a support line. When my clients are struggling is when I tell them to reach out more.

👆 Community - I've always worked better as a team. I can train alone easily but know I've people to report back to and a team I don't want to let down, this is very important to me. I'm not just creating an online programme here but a community of women supporting one another ❤🙌
.
.
If any of the above sounds like something you'd like and  you're interested in Online Coaching. Dm me 'Coach'. I've a few spaces opening up in August 🤗

𝐌𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐚𝐥 𝐇𝐞𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐡 𝐢𝐬 𝐧𝐨𝐭 𝐣𝐮𝐬𝐭 𝐚𝐧𝐱𝐢𝐞𝐭𝐲 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐝𝐞𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐬𝐢𝐨𝐧 ✖✖✖
.
.
Sometimes it doesn't need a name. And what about bipolar and schizophrenia? Mental Health encompasses a huge variety of areas and sometimes it's just not as simple as a diagnosis 🤷‍♀️ I am not a mental healthcare provider so I'm not going to go down that route, I just know what I've been through and I'm happy to share 😘
.
.
I wouldn't ever say I was depressed or even suffered with anxiety (this phrase is too commonly misused btw). But that doesn't mean I never suffered. 
.
.
August 2018
This photo was taken during a time in my life when my mental was at it's WORST - you wouldn't think it would you 🤷‍♀️ I was having an absolute ball with my friends - drinking way too much to forget the fact that my life was in turmoil. 
.
.
The day after this photo was taken, I woke up to a call from a stranger to say my mother had been taken to hospital (physical injuries as a result of her mental health problems). 
At the time, I was running a gym, commuting, looking after my mother, and playing inter county football. 
.
.
This is not a pity party. It's not to say I've had life tougher than others. 
Thankfully, I'm well on the other side of that period of my life 🙏 
.
.
What I just want to do is raise awareness that it's not always black and white. And sometimes, you have NO CLUE what someone is going through 🙏
.
.
So firstly, BE KIND ALWAYS ❤ You literally have NO IDEA how much someone may need it.
Secondly, check in on your strong friends too.
.
.
People in Syndey, these are tough times. But look at our Irish counterparts, look at how they managed ❤ We got this. And never ever be afraid to reach out, even if it's just for a moan down the phone 🙏
I'm definitely always here ❤🙏

#mentalhealthawareness 
#mindyourmentalhealth

.
.
✅€30 = $46.17 AUD. But they are 2 totally different currencies.
✅1000 Tonnes Feathers = 1000 Tonnes Coal. But they are 2 totally different components. 
.
.
The same goes for food. 
.
.
100 Calories Apple = 100 Calorie Chocolate Bar (as a measure of calories). But you cannot compare them in composition. The lack of micronutrients, the high sugar and fat content in the chocolate bar cannot be easily compared to the vitamins, mineral, water and phytonutrients in the apple 🤦‍♀️
.
.
Since when was Maths ever that simple 😅 I am not saying Calories in versus calories out is non sense, because it isn't. It makes sense and is very important. All I'm saying is, it's not the ONLY thing that is important. Food quality matters for long term health benefits and body composition 🙌
.
.
Questions? 🤔

𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐢𝐬 𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐛𝐚𝐛𝐥𝐲 𝐨𝐧𝐞 𝐨𝐟 𝐦𝐲 𝐦𝐨𝐬𝐭 𝐡𝐨𝐧𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐩𝐨𝐬𝐭𝐬 𝐈'𝐯𝐞 𝐄𝐕𝐄𝐑 𝐰𝐫𝐨𝐭𝐞...

And that's saying something 🙈Because I'm pretty much an open book 📙
.
.
I lost my love of football about 3 years before I quit💔💔💔
.
.
When I first started, skill was priority. Which I had none of 😂 But I still had the craic. It was so much fun. Even though I never got a game, the sidelines were hopping when I was around 🎶🎶🎶
Between the ages of 18 and 25, fitness was priority 🏃‍♀️Finally my lucky break 🙌 I may not be able to kick a ball, but I was fit 🙋💪 I enjoyed football so much during these years ❤️ And thankfully, they were my best years performance wise and I had a few medals to show for it too 🏅🏅🏅
.
.
But the last 3 years the game changed. Or maybe it was just my mentality. I had sacrificed so much for so long, maybe I was just sick of doing that 🤔 Or maybe I just didn't have the same winning mentality others have. 🤷‍♀️ I cannot do 'whatever it takes' to win. Its just not in me 🚫 And as for sacrifice. It used to be a 2 week drinking ban which has now turned into: No holidays, no alcohol for months, no social life, strain on relationships/friendships.
.
.
So why did I still do it?
The girls ❤ I wanted the community. That community was part of me for so long and I loved it so much. But thankfully I found another little community that aligns very well with my goals and values.
.
.
And even MORE EXCITING I've created a community. Something that has helped me, motivated me, encouraged me. Now I want to share that community with you 👆 
.
.
Dm me 'Community' if you want to join my tribe 🥰

caption:
Eat the damn burger 🍔
.
.
✖ No guilt
.
.
✖ No burning it off
.
.
✖ No compensating with extra exercise
.
.
Fun fact: 
I've actually never eaten a burger 😅 (well unless you count a bunless Turkey burger). It doesn't appeal to me. But I do love me some Carbonara 🤤 Or chocolate 🤤 
.
.
I believe everything in moderation. I usually adhere to an 80/20 idea - 80% whole nutritious foods that fuel me, 20% foods I enjoy - for my soul 🍫
.
.
I encourage my clients to adhere to something similar. I rarely exclude foods from people's diets. And I definitely don't advocate restriction. I don't allow clients associate foods with 'good' or 'bad' labels. And I definitely don't promote 'burning foods off' 🚫
.
.
Food should be a source of energy and nutrients not just a calculation 👊

caption:
𝙇𝙖𝙪𝙧𝙖, 𝙦𝙪𝙞𝙘𝙠𝙡𝙮 𝙩𝙖𝙠𝙚 𝙖 𝙥𝙝𝙤𝙩𝙤 𝙬𝙝𝙞𝙡𝙚 𝙄'𝙢 𝙩𝙚𝙣𝙨𝙞𝙣𝙜 📸
.
.
Not words that come out of my mouth very often anymore 🤭
.
.
I used to be obsessed with the idea of abs. I thought I'd be happier in my body. Believed I'd like my body more if I 'liked' how it looked. I didn't understand that abs were never going to make me happy, because my appearance wasn't what I was fighting with, it was a much deeper self loathing 😫 
.
.
What did I do to turn this around (which took years btw):
1. I went to a counsellor and worked on my mental health
2. I started training for performance instead of aesthetics
3. I journalled and practiced gratitude 
4. I stopped talking negatively - not just about myself but others too
.
.
I have never been happier in my own skin - NOTHING to do with how it looks but how I feel 🙌 I feel strong, healthy and empowered. I'm  fit and extremely happy 😁
.
.
Please remember, no clothes size, scale number or body fat percentage will make you happy unless you deal with what's going on in your head. 🙏
.
.
P.s Its so empowering not caring how you look post workout 😅😍

#reallife #fitness #strongwomen #physicalhealth #mentalhealth

.
.

.

caption:
𝐋𝐞𝐭 𝐦𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐫𝐨𝐰 𝐬𝐨𝐦𝐞 𝐧𝐮𝐦𝐛𝐞𝐫𝐬 𝐚𝐭 𝐲𝐨𝐮...
.
.
20/193 
- The number of times I've drank this year. That averages at less than once a week.
(And this is why I won't be an athlete 😅)

140/193
- The number of times I've trained this year. That averages at 5 times a week.
(Just a side note - alcohol doesn't get in the way of my training. I won't drink until/unless my training is complete for the week. And Monday I go back training regardless of weekends antics.)

5/35 
- The number of meals I have weekly that aren't very nutritious (Usually have one meal out, one breakfast and chocolate twice, the last is just to make up for those crazy weekends😅) 

7.75
- The average number of hours sleep I get a night

3 
- The average amount of water I drink

15,000 
- My average step count
.
.
Consistency. That's what it all comes down to. Not over 6 weeks or 6 months but 6 years. Long term consistency. Playing the long game 👊🙌 
.
.
Just to be aware. This is me. This is my life and I live a life I love. I don't expect or want anyone else to sacrifice or make the changes I make.  But don't expect the results you want, with the work you didn't do 🙈👊

#realresults #sacrifice #fitness #fitliving #strongwomen #pullups #onlinecoach

caption:
𝐒𝐡𝐨𝐰 𝐦𝐞 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐡𝐚𝐛𝐢𝐭𝐬 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐈 𝐰𝐢𝐥𝐥 𝐬𝐡𝐨𝐰 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐟𝐮𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞 🔮
.
.
You are a sum of the things you do consistently 👊
.
.
✖ Not training regularly? Don't get annoyed with the results you didn't get by the work you didn't put in 🚫

✖ Snoozing your alarm and missing your morning walk - Don't get frustrated when you don't hit your step count 🤷‍♀️

✖ Weekends throwing you off? 🍷 You actually can still enjoy yourself but your binge restrict lifestyle is your main problem 👊
.
.
I keep non negotiables that I can stick to EVERY single day. This means Christmas, Holidays, Hangovers etc 😅 They are nothing crazy. But it works 👊 Consistency trumps any and all diets. 
Consistency in training is the only way to progress 💪

NOTHING trumps consistency, with regards what you can control - Name one thing - I dare you
⬇️⬇️⬇️

I am a strong woman 🙆‍♀️🙆‍♀️🙆‍♀️
.
.
Yes in the physical sense. I have worked for years to get stronger and build a body I feel confident in. I have consistently trained for the last 10 years. First at intercounty football which then led to my love of strength and resistance training😁 My body is a reflection of that.
.
.
But I am so much stronger than my physique. My mental strength is something you cannot see, but it's much stronger than any weight I could lift. Or any competition I'll do. 
I have gone through more than most will go through in a lifetime. I have had my own share of mental health issues. But I have come out the other side. A true reflection of my mental strength.
.
.
I have worked damn hard to be in the position I am in right now. I said to a client last year how lucky I am to have got a job during COVID and how amazing my job, clients and boss are. And she said 'Amanda, you are not lucky. You've worked for this.' She was right. This year as proved that 👊💪
.
.
It's an amazing feeling to feel like a strong woman. A strong woman can be intimidating. A strong woman can come off as bossy. A strong woman can get a hostile response especially from the opposite sex. And this is where I acknowledge the strong men in my life. Most notably my Dad was the strongest man I've ever known. Owen has the patience of a saint. And final shout out to the men I've worked with who were not immasculated taking orders from a woman and the bosses I've had who not only considered my opinion but actually valued it. 🙏
.
.
I am a strong woman. Are you?
