caption:
Grace's Experience: 

Thank you so much Amanda for everything I have learned in the past 12 weeks. The knowledge and confidence I now have will last a lifetime. 

I was diagnosed with PCOS nearly 4 years ago and the Doctor told me that I will just always struggle with my weight. He gave me no information about it. 

Then into a third lockdown, I was feeling unmotivated, lost, and had low self esstem. I turned to Amanda who offered a 12-week program that focused on building habits rather than an all-or-nothing approach. Amanda is so positive, enthusiastic but also really understanding that we are all juggling different things while trying to hit our fitness goals. Since joining Amanda I have lost 5 kg which I am so happy with. But I have also learned a lot about having a more positive outlook on life and on myself. Amanda's habit-building approach really does work without you restricting yourself. I have learned loads about my PCOS which makes me feel more in control. Getting my steps in, drinking 2 liters of water, exercise, 8 hours of sleep, and hitting nutrition goals are part of my day to day now. Amanda has taught me that every day does not have to be perfect, what is important is to try your best and consistency will prevail.

𝗜 𝗵𝗼𝗽𝗲... 
one day you feel so good in your body that you work with it rather than against it. You listen to it. Nourish it. And stop being at war with it ❤ 
.
.
𝗜 𝗵𝗼𝗽𝗲...
you become confident enough in your body that you can rock a bikini at any time of year. I hope you learn that 0 and 100 are not the numbers that you should be working toward. ❤ 
.
.
𝗜 𝗵𝗼𝗽𝗲...
you stop letting a number on a scales dictate your happiness. I hope you realise how beautiful you are regardless of your clothes size. ❤ 
.

𝗜 𝗵𝗼𝗽𝗲...
you stop abusing exercise and see it for what it truely is... an opportunity ❤

everyone finds something in their life that makes them as happy as training makes me. ❤

caption:
There are some very frustrated and homesick people in Austrailia at the moment 🤦‍♀️
.
.
But don't forget this too shall pass 🙏
.
.
Think of our friends and families at home. They've had MONTHS of this to endure 😢 If we just do the right thing, we have weeks 🙏🤞
.
.
Last lockdown, I started CrossFit 🥳 I got fit and lost my Sydney stone 😅 This year I'm using it to focus on my business. Why not use this lockdown to better yourself in some way?

💫 Improve your 5km time?
💫 Get better at push ups?
💫 Start an online course?
💫 Read a book? 
💫 Do something creative? 
💫 Invest in yourself 

Learn from the last lockdown.
Allow yourself the weekend for the pity party. But don't let bad habits become your new habits 👊🙌

#lockdownlife #useitwisely

How do people look good when training? 🤔

caption:
How many of you have looked in a mirror or seen a photo and thought 'Damn I look good? I look fit, healthy, and strong 💪'
.
.

.
.
I wish more people could be that happy in themselves that they don't criticise every photo. I wish people didn't hide their bodies because they are ashamed. I wish people could see true beauty is skin deep 🙏 
.
.
🎯 Try talking to yourself a little nicer
🎯 Try looking at yourself a little better
🎯 Try allowing yourself be happy in the body you're in
.
.
These are some of the strategies I work on with my ladies 🥰 You know it's perfectly ok to be happy in your body - contrary to what society tells us 🤦‍♀️
.
.

caption:
💫 𝐀𝐥𝐨𝐧𝐞 𝐰𝐞 𝐜𝐚𝐧 𝐝𝐨 𝐬𝐨 𝐥𝐢𝐭𝐭𝐥𝐞, 𝐭𝐨𝐠𝐞𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫 𝐰𝐞 𝐜𝐚𝐧 𝐝𝐨 𝐬𝐨 𝐦𝐮𝐜𝐡 💫
.
.
This is another part of my why 👊
.
.
I've always been a part of a team and a community. I've been so lucky to play football with so many teams over the years and gain so many friends and contacts through sport. 
.
.
𝐖𝐡𝐲 𝐂𝐫𝐨𝐬𝐬𝐅𝐢𝐭? 
CrossFit has nailed the element that a lot of gyms don't have - a community. A lot of commercial gyms have no idea of who comes in their doors, members are just another direct debit. CrossFit took the idea of a community and worked it 🙌 
.
.
But CrossFit is not the only place you can gain a community. I know plenty of other gyms @fullbodyworkhouse @strengthandmovementlab who have built the community aspect into their gyms. And @ownitfit we have a great community vibe 🙌 So if you're not into absolutely Killing yourself (which makes total sense 😅 - crossfit is NOT the only option)
.
.
One of my main goals of my Online coaching was to build a community. Because community has had such a massive impact on my goals and my motivation, I knew it would help others too. And the other day, one of my clients said 'Amanda you really need to emphasis the community element of this programme, because I think that's what sets it aside from other programmes. It's the game changer'. I honestly wanted to cry 😭 I am making all my ideas into real life actions. This is honestly the most excited I have been about my job ever (and for those of you who know me know this is a big statement because I love my job so much 😍)

Here's to building the community online 👊

#thecommunitycoach

caption:

💫 I am good enough

💫 I am worthy 

💫 I deserve this

💫 I am beautiful

💫 I am strong

💫 I am independent 

These are just SOME of the daily affirmations I tell myself. Self love is a journey I work on with all my clients. Its a difficult one.

We've been brought up in a society that frowns on women speaking like this. We've been brainwashed into thinking self confidence is a bad thing. People are genuinely intimidated by strong, independent women 🤦‍♀️

So let's break the mould together. Let's start working on that self love. 
But remember it's a process. It won't happen over night and you need to work on it 🙏

Let's tag some incredible ladies who need to hear this. Or share it to your story if you believe it 🙋‍♀️

caption:
💫 ꜰɪɴᴅ ʏᴏᴜʀ ᴡʜʏ 💫
.
.
When people ask me how am I always so motivated. I laugh it off 😅🤦‍♀️ How can you think I'm motivated all the time 🤷‍♀️ I can assure you I'm not. 
.
.
But my goals are more important to me than any excuses 👊 
.
.
Here's some of my goals. Some of which I've never shared with people.

1. Health - health is my number 1 priority. 
👉 Ever since my Dad died at such a young age, I've made it my mission to become healthier. Most people would say I've been healthy since before my Dad died. I would not agree. I may have exercised and ate well but my stress levels were abnormally high and I was WAY too busy. In recent years, I've learned to take a step back and my health has noticed ❤🙏

2. I want to be the fittest person I know (this is one I've never really shared). 
👉 It's a personal goal I've had for quite awhile. What determines fitness to me? Well a multitude of things - Strong, Powerful and having a good engine. I may not be the best individually at any one of them but I'm good at all of them. This is why I think Crossfit suits me because it's being a jack of all trades but master of none 😅🤩

✔ These goals are to live a long, healthy, fulfilling life. I want to succeed in a lot of areas of my life. I always have. I want my just rewards for the effort I put in 🙏 I want to say I am proud of myself and my efforts, always!  This is my why! 

Most people never TRUELY think about their WHY! I have people all the time saying they want to lose weight or tone up but WHY? Ask yourself why? And ask yourself again? Because no weight, no clothes size, no inches lost will ever make you truely happy unless you ask WHY!

With my clients, I always ask why! Sometimes it's difficult for people. Sometimes they've bottled up feelings and emotions they thought they'd never have to open up to.
But honestly, I've changed people's lives by asking this simple question 👊🙌

If you want to work with me and find out 'WHY'. DM me 'Coach' 🙋‍♀️

caption:
✖ 𝐌𝐞𝐚𝐥 𝐩𝐥𝐚𝐧𝐬 𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐚 𝐰𝐚𝐬𝐭𝐞 𝐨𝐟 𝐭𝐢𝐦𝐞 ✖
.
.
Disclaimer: I actually used to do them 🙈 When I first started out I gave people what they wanted 🤦‍♀️ (not what they needed). But I quickly learned it was not the right approach.
.
.
Meal plans are a band aid 🩹 Let's be honest, we all know what's healthy and what lacks nutrients 🤷‍♀️ We're not all nutritionists but we've a fair grasp that we should be eating more colour and less packaged crap. We should be drinking more water and reducing alcohol intake. 
.
.
Meal plans are essentially a menu of options. This can actually help a very small percentage of people.
.
.
But from my experience, meal plans are NOT enough. Most people need education. Guidance for when things are not going perfectly and support for getting started. People need to introduce small incremental changes that lead to new habits. And people have lives they want to live. Meal plans don't account for this. They are strict rigid plans that focus solely on main meals and don't allow for life's pleasures 🍫🍷
.
.
Comment Below if a Meal Plan Changed your life 
⬇️⬇️⬇️

Amanda, I’m so sorry this took so long but I didn’t know how to express my gratitude. I still don’t think I will do you justice but I just wanted to say thank you so much for your help and support over the last 8 months. I started this message so many times over the past few weeks and I always ended up getting emotional 🙈 I cannot thank you enough for everything! So much has changed since our initial phone call! When I started I was stuck in a rut, lacked motivation and had got in bad habits, I was not in a great mindset! I don’t even know how to explain how much things have changed, but you already know that! I feel like a new woman with a new perspective of all things health! When I signed up I was looking for help getting back exercising and to create a new routine, I had no specific goals but just to feel good again and by god I feel like a new woman! But it’s not just the physical transformation, what I lost in inches I gained multiple times over in knowledge, confidence and mental strength! I know you will say that I did all the work but I couldn’t have done it without your support and encouragement, not to mention all the girls in the group call 🥰 I feel absolutely fantastic Amanda! I know I’ll be back for a refresher course at some stage so until then thank you 😊

.
.
One of the main reasons I started online coaching was to get the opportunity to work with more people. I love the idea that no where is off limits and I can extend my coaching guidance to anywhere in the world.
.
.
In the last year, I am so proud of the community I have built within my coaching business ❤🙏 The ladies I work with on a daily basis literally make my job feel like it's not a job. They are the most incredible women with all very different goals but very similar personalities and values 🙏
Unfortunately, they are not all based in one place so its hard to organise getting them all to catch up. But today,  a group of them met up 💕
.
.
And it's the perfect opportunity to welcome the newest member to the Coach Mc Loone team. I am so excited to have @lisacuddyfitness on my team. I started working with Lisa as her trainer (so she really learned from the best 😜lol). She has all the same morals and values as I do and she is such a great addition to my team 💕 
.

caption:
𝓒𝓸𝓶𝓹𝓪𝓻𝓲𝓼𝓸𝓷 𝓲𝓼 𝓽𝓱𝓮 𝓽𝓱𝓲𝓮𝓯 𝓸𝓯 𝓳𝓸𝔂 🤦‍♀️
.
.
I see this one a lot.
.
.
You are individual. You are not like anyone else, so why would you compare yourself to anyone else? 🤷‍♀️
.
.
Most of the time the circumstances aren't  even comparable. Let's give you some examples
❎ Comparing your image to celebrities 
❎ Comparing your performance to athletes
❎ Comparing your body to fitness influencers
.
.
If you are not where you want to be, being honest it is probably something you are or are not doing. BUT you are making life a hell of a lot more difficult for yourself by setting unrealistic goals and targets 🎯
.
.
✔ Start by setting some realistic goals
✔ Progression over perfection 
✔ Be consistent - stop giving it a short term tag. Look at the long term. Look at your future self.
✔ Find something you enjoy - you are more likely to stick to it
.
.
Stop blaming other people and start looking at what you need to do to get where you want to be 👊 
.
.
And remember no number on the scales will make you happy unless you deal with the shit in your head 🧠
.
.
I am currently taking on new clients. If you're interested in cutting the excuses and want to really make a lifestyle change - DM me 'Coach'.

.
.
Females comparing themselves to other females is like comparing two different types of spreads? 🤔
ℍ𝕠𝕨 𝕪𝕠𝕦 𝕤𝕒𝕪?
Well although you are similar in some ways (being female, being a spread) you are so different in other ways 🙈 
.
.
Although these spreads serve the same purpose and people use them similarly, they contain very different ingredients 🧈 
As females, we may have the same features but we are so different in other ways. 
.
.
Who has that friend who no matter what she eats, never gains weight 🙋‍♀️🙈 Or the teammate who is fitter than everyone else? 🙋‍♀️🙈
.
.
❎We cannot control what others do.
❎ We have no power over other people's lives
.
.
💥Even if we all did the exact same thing we would look different💥
.
.
So STOP comparing yourself. STOP trying to be/look like someone else 🖐 
.
.
💫YOU ARE THE KERRYGOLD💫

caption:
𝐏𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐨𝐝 𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐛𝐮𝐭 𝐤𝐧𝐨𝐰 𝐲𝐨𝐮'𝐫𝐞 𝐧𝐨𝐭 𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐠𝐧𝐚𝐧𝐭? 𝐑𝐞𝐚𝐝 𝐨𝐧... 🔴🔴🔴
.
.
Firstly, do you track your period? Do you even know when your period is due? If not, why not?
Cycles are a very important part of a woman's life and a lot of elements can be affected at different phases of our cycle and not just our hormones 🙀 💥Have you ever noticed you're more productive at certain times? 
💥 Noticed you're stronger at certain times?
💥 Is your sleep affected at certain times? 
What gets measured gets managed 👊👊👊
.
.
OK, so you've started tracking...
And you notice, ok my cycle length is a lot longer than normal (21-35 days). You know you're not pregnant (immaculate conception 😇). So what could it be?
.
.
There are many factors that may contribute to your irregular cycle. 
.
🔴𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐯𝐞𝐥
🔴𝐈𝐥𝐥𝐧𝐞𝐬𝐬
🔴𝐒𝐭𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐬
🔴𝐎𝐯𝐞𝐫 𝐞𝐱𝐞𝐫𝐜𝐢𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐠 
🔴𝐔𝐧𝐝𝐞𝐫 𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠
🔴𝐇𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐨𝐧𝐚𝐥 𝐈𝐦𝐛𝐚𝐥𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐞
🔴𝐀𝐥𝐜𝐨𝐡𝐨𝐥
.
.
Tracking will help you realise what your irregular cycle may be linked to.
I personally know travel and alcohol really disrupt mine but I never would have realised if I didn't track 👊
.
.
Ladies start getting to know and understand your body 🙌

#irregularcycles

Who remembers or knows a coach who always suprised you with 'one last rep/run?' 😅😅😅

#squatsnatches

caption:
ℍ𝕒𝕓𝕚𝕥𝕤 𝕒𝕣𝕖 𝕒 𝕘𝕚𝕣𝕝'𝕤 𝕓𝕖𝕤𝕥 𝕗𝕣𝕚𝕖𝕟𝕕 💥
(Or a Guys 👊)
.
.
You're daily habits are what defines everything about you 🙋‍♀️
.
.
- 𝐖𝐚𝐧𝐭 𝐭𝐨 𝐥𝐨𝐬𝐞 𝐰𝐞𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭?
What are your daily habits like? Do you try to change everything and fail because you try to go from 0-100? Small changes to habits over time equate to much greater results, just ask my girls 💃
.
.
- 𝐖𝐚𝐧𝐭 𝐭𝐨 𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐯𝐞 𝐢𝐧 𝐬𝐩𝐨𝐫𝐭?
Do your current habits align with improving? Or are you doing the same thing and expecting a different result? Are you recovering as hard as you're training? The key lies in your daily habits. ⛹‍♂️
.
.
- 𝐖𝐚𝐧𝐭 𝐭𝐨 𝐛𝐞𝐜𝐨𝐦𝐞 𝐚 𝐛𝐮𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐞𝐬𝐬 𝐨𝐰𝐧𝐞𝐫?
Are you 9-5er? Or are you willing to put in time and effort while everyone else is living the easy life? The answer lies in your daily habits. 👩‍💻
.
.
This is in EVERYTHING. Health, Lifestyle, Work, Relationships, Money... the list goes on. 
.
.
And you know what. Rome wasn't built in a day so think of that if you are looking to change your habits 🤔 Slow changes over time are a lot more sustainable and yield much better results in the long term 👊
.
.
𝐓𝐨𝐩 𝐓𝐢𝐩:
✅ Surround yourself with similar people who align with your goals. It makes it a hell of a lot easier with a hype squad 🥳

#habits #dailyhabits #habitbasedcoaching

I've always been very open minded.
.
.
I pride myself on it actually. I've alway been a pro choice kinda girl in all aspects of life (not just health and fitness related). You'll never hear me boast about one type of diet or slate any either. You won't hear me downgrade any form of exercise, although I do openly talk about the huge benefits of resistance training 💪 I'll never tell any of my client's 'You have to do this type of exercise' or 'you cannot eat this for weight loss'. So you see I'm very open minded. If someone who loves yoga comes to me, I'm not going to force them to lift weights. And if someone who is vegan comes to me, I would not force them to eat animal products. My problem with any of these things lies in the misinformation. .
.
.
Did you know that vegan fast food production has sky rocketed in recent years? 🤔 Similarly, a few years ago, gluten free products were a huge trend? And before that, sugar free was the hype? This I have a problem with.
.
.
Veganism is a lifestyle choice. I have huge respect for anyone's lifestyle choices, whether they conform to my own is irrelevant. What actually annoys me is actual vegans are getting a terrible name due to all these people jumping on the bandwagon, thinking veganism is the healthiest lifestyle going. People are going into this lifestyle, uneducated and naive. 😒 It was the same a few years ago when gluten free was the buzzword. Did you know you can have a totally adequate, balanced, healthy diet without adding one gluten free product? And thats for ACTUAL coeliacs out there, because they are the ONLY people that need to be eating gluten free toast 😂
.
.
What my very long winded post is trying to say is stop jumping on bandwagons. If you are and always have been vegan, that's fine. Continue with your choices. If you are coeliac, continue with your gluten free bread 🙈 
.
For the rest of you, stop following trends by the latest celebrity diet.
❎ Stop conforming to social norms ✊ 
❎Stop basing your beliefs on a bloody stupid documentary 😒 
✅Get some advice from a professional. 🙏
✅ Follow said advice 🌈 
✅ And unfollow anyone giving terrible, uneducated advice 
.
.
#propaganda #foodfear

caption: Here's what Sinead had to say 👉

Let's clear something up... 
.
.
There is no perfect form of coaching ❎
Or perfect form of exercise ❎
.
.
Each style has it's pros and cons 😈
.
.
But it is the form that you can consistently work with and that give you long term sustainable results - that works for you. That does not mean it works for everyone 🤔
.
.
Let me give you some scenarios.
.
.
One of my online clients first approached me for in person PT. She didn't know I lived in Austrailia 🙈🤣 She wasn't interested in online coaching due to wasting money on previous online programmes. This lady works 2 jobs and barely has time for herself let alone fitting into a PT schedule. Online coaching was a great option for her. She lost 18lbs and felt amazing in her wedding dress 🥳
.
.
I have a friend who tried online coaching...twice. First time went well, second time not as well. Nothing wrong with the programme, she just responds better to in person accountability. She is now doing in person PT and loving it 🥳
.
.
There's nothing special about Crossfit. It's more the community and the vibe than the exercise prescription people enjoy. 
.
.
Running may be an excellent form of exercise for an introvert but an extrovert might find it very isolating...
.
.
My point?
1. Just because Sharon got results from a PT does not mean that PT has extraordinary powers. This form of coaching got Sharon results because it was something she CONSISTENTLY did and could stick to.
2. There is no right or wrong coaching style - just what works for you. 
3. Please find something you enjoy and can see yourself doing for the next 50 years 🙏 As opposed to hating exercise, see it as a blessing 👏
.
.
📸 @marceauphotography

I'd love to hear some of your experiences

caption:
I've been there too 🙋‍♀️

I think the impression I portray on social media is of a strong, independent female who has her shit together. Most of the time, this is me. But I haven't always been this way. 

I had issues...
Serious ones...
Ones I struggled with for years...
Ones I didn't even realise I had until I look back... 

💥I was an attention seeker.
I wore skimpy clothes. I was the loudest, most outspoken person in every group. Most people would mistake me for confident.
But I was craving people's attention. I wanted people to like me, wanted people to care because I didn't always get that recognition growing up. 

💥I was a perfectionist.
The control of being the best in every situation. I'm not going to lie this is still one I struggle with to a degree but compared to where I was, they are miles apart 🙏 

💥I drank to forget.
A lot of my late teens, early 20s I would pass out before I could even make it to a club. We all laughed at the time, I was known for 'Never making it out' but honestly this was yet another cry for help. 

Look I'm not going to say I had the worst upbringing in the world because that is just not true. But that doesn't mean that parts of your childhood/life don't form who you become years later. I never had problems with weight or issues with weight loss but that doesn't mean I haven't faced my own demons. 

I deal with women on a daily basis who have terrible relationships with food because of 
1. Their home life (control often leading to eating disorders or disordered eating)
2. Family figures - Parents who excessively dieted or commented on appearance regularly
3. Fad diets - I actually had a woman just this morning who I'm trying to convince there is no such thing as a 'bad' food but her years of WW has told her to stay away from fats 🤦‍♀️ 

I'm not a psychologist. I don't try to be. I am a  nutritionist so I don't veer outside the scope of my practice but I do want to help. I want to help women heal their relationship with food. I want to help them realise their worth is not based on a number or a figure. I want them to see food as fuel and not be afraid of it. 

If any of the above sounds like you DM me ❤

caption:
Why Protein? 
.
.
Quite often I hear people recommending high protein diets without having a clue why they are recommending it 🤷‍♀️
.
.
My clients know why I recommend up to 2g Protein/KG BW/day 🙌 Why? Because I educate them why 👊
.
.
1. TEF - Our total daily energy expenditure (TDEE) is made up for 4 components - BMR, NEAT, Purposeful Activity and TEF. It accounts for up to 10% of our TDEE. Protein rich foods have a higher thermic effect from food than any other macro nutrient.
.
2. Satiety - Protein is super filling. It's difficult to eat large quantities without feeling full. This is a good complaint 😜
.
3. Recovery - Protein is required for so many processes in our body. Regardless of your goals - weight loss, weight gain, performance - everyone will benefit from a high protein diet.
.
.
So now you understand 👆👆👆

caption:
What are you willing to sacrifice? 🤔
.
.
Can you believe that I RARELY tell clients they 'Can't' have something.
.
.
I think people expect a nutritionist to give you a short list of foods you can eat to achieve your goals 🤦‍♀️ This could NOT be further from the truth.
.
.
Majority of the time I'm adding foods to their diet: Water, Colour, Protein, Wine (lol I don't add this but I don't exclude it either).
.
.
You see most of the time - unless your  goals are REALLY specific, you can actually include a little of the foods and drinks you like. If you look at health as a long term thing and not just a 6 week challenge, you can actually have your cake and eat it too 🍰
.
.
All I will say is don't lose sight of the goal. I may be having a glass of wine in this photo but I also have water in front of me too. I may eat chocolate but I eat a lot of colour too. I choose not to drink on Fridays so I can train Saturday mornings. 
.
.
Have your non negotiables. But remember there is a thing called life that I encourage you all to live 🙌

.
.
Diet is defined as the kinds of food a person habitually eats. No diet will ever be successful if someone cannot successfully stick to it and be consistent with it. And for this reason, it is my bread and butter. It is the most important element when it comes to nutrition.
.
.
I am a nutritionist so Food Quality is my next most important element. I know in terms of energy balance it is as simple as calories in versus calories out but I just cannot educate people and say that
Food quality doesn't matter. If I didn't care about my clients and I just cared about transformation photos I could give someone a calorie calculator and say 'Here once it's within your calories it doesn't matter what the meals include'. Maybe not for body composition (questionable) but certainly for long term health 🤦‍♀️
.
.
Then, I put calories. Calories do matter but to me food quality matters more. As I've said, this is opinion. At the end of the day, it is an energy balance equation so I can't disregard them but just be aware of how inaccurate logging and tracking can be. Just be informed 👊
.
.
Technically that should be macronutrients but I'm putting protein as the king 🤴 Although I do feel very strongly about good balance so please don't disregard carbs and fats 😬
.
.
Lastly, comes supplements. Supplements should always be an addition.
.
.
Did I miss anything 🤔
.
.
Interested in opinions too 😇

Do I coach guys too???
.
.
Of course 🙌
.
.
While it's probably very obvious my clientele is mainly female based i still train guys 👊

.

I used to be so hard on myself and so frustrated when I wasn’t seeing immediate results mainly because I was following all the wrong people and lost in a sea of online content and not knowing what to believe! I know feel empowered and feel confident with what I’m doing and the biggest take away being that progress isn’t linear and you have to be a support to yourself! Balance is key and working out should done for mental and physical well being rather than wanting to have disco muscles! Honestly Amanda, thanks so much for being a guiding light, I really appreciate it and am happy and excited to carry on by myself! 😁😁
.
.
If you want results like Niall, DM me 'Coach' 😁

ℍ𝕖𝕒𝕝𝕥𝕙 ℙ𝕪𝕣𝕒𝕞𝕚𝕕 🔺️
.
.
The fitness industry is becoming saturated. There is so much conflicting information it's overwhelming to even know where to start. I want to stand out and not fade into the same mould.
.
.
I'm pretty safe though because:

❎ I won't be that 'hot' fitness model - although leave some 🔥 if you love the posts of my sweaty red head
❎ I won't be posing in lingerie to get thousands followers - although I do look good in Lingerie 😜
❎ I won't be putting videos up of myself doing 10 variations of crunches or booty band workouts.
.
.
I actually struggle to find time to put up content these days because I am so busy with my clients. All my time, effort and education goes into helping everyone of them. They have invested their time and money in me and I'm so proud of the work we do together ❤
.
.
Anyway, I'm going to be different to a lot of other fitness accounts - I'm not going to say its just as simple as 'Eat Less, Move More✌'. 
Sorry unfortunately I just don't think it is.
.
.
My hierarchy begins with stress reduction - why?
.
.
Well because stress in all shapes and sizes leads to incredible problems in the body. 
Example: Stress of too little calories - Can lead to hormonal disruptions which can lead to amenorrhoea which can lead to infertility. Too little calories and poor food quality can lead to micronutrient deficiencies and injury. 
Stress can be as simple as drinking too much caffeine or as severe as overwhelm. Add up all the daily stresses in your life and see how many there are😱
.
.
Sleep should be AS IMPORTANT as exercise and nutrition combined - end of story😴
.
.
Nutrition and food quality come next.🥦
.
.
Exercise in general should technically come next but this is my pyramid so I'm going to do what I believe is most important - irrespective of goals! 🏋‍♀️
.
.
Lastly, individual variance. Have a condition or a goal? Follow all the below first and foremost and the individuality should come last 
.
.
Interested to see your views 🤔

caption:
Health and Fitness goals in a nutshell 👊👊👊
.
.
✅ Training average twice a week for 52 weeks is better than 7 days a week for 4 weeks (every time you 'restart' your fitness journey)
✅ Drinking 1.5L water daily is better than yoyo extremes of 3L and 500ml
✅ Eating Whole Nutritious food 50% of the time 52 weeks a year is better than your 'starting Monday' almost every week
.
.
Remember, you and your body is a representation of what you do most of the time, not some of the time. 
🎯If you are going over your calorie deficit 4 days a week - you're not in a calorie deficit anymore.
🎯 If you're making more time for socialising than you are for the gym, expect your results to reflect that
🎯If you have more alcohol units a week than Green vegetables - don't be annoyed when you're not where you want to be 👊
.
.
Now how are you going to spend your time? 🤔

Cauliflower Rice vs Brown Rice
.
.
Which is best?
.
.
Answer is.
.
.
Neither are better, neither are worse.
.
.
I eat both. But why you are eating it depends on your goals 👊👊👊
.
.
✅ Weight loss a goal? Cauliflower rice is low in calories and high in volume so may be a great option
✅Alternatively, portion control of brown rice can also work.
✅ Performance a goal? You will not get the same complex carbs from caulifower rice as you will from brown rice. 
✅ Both have different nutritional compositions when it comes to vitamins and minerals.
✅ Taste? Force feeding yourself cauliflower rice because your favourite fitness influencer recommended it? YOU ARE JUST BEING STUPID!!!! 
.
.
There is no right or wrong answer to comparing these. As always, it is dependent on your individual goals and anyone that gives you a clear defined answer is a fruad 😅🚫
.
.
#eatforperformance #eatforhealth #nutrition #nutritionist #fitness #irishfitness #irishinoz #irishinsydney #fitlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

You won't be happy in any weight, clothes size or body shape unless you deal with what's going on in your head first 👊👊👊
.
.
In my experience, people thinknthey want to be smaller, leaner versions of themselves when truth is the y just want to be happier ❤
.
.
Some tips to change this mindset:
1. Stop focusing on the number on the scales - start focusing on the weight you are lifting
2. Stop seeing food as calories - start seeing food as fuel and nutrients
3. Stop trying to look like someone else - start trying to look like the best version of you
.
.
If you are unsure of the next steps, please please reach out for help. If not to me, to someone else you trust 🙏 This is our job. I want to help ❤
.
.
Dm me 'Coach' if you are interested in my approach to health and fitness x

A high protein diet is optimal no matter what your goals are. Why?
.
.
✅ Protein is essential for recovery especially from exercise, illness or injury
✅ Protein saties you. It gives you a 'fuller' feeling. No matter what your goals, feeling more satisfied is a good thing right?
✅ The Thermic Effect of Protein is high. So it actually contributes to our overall TDEE. Food type and nutrient composition is important 😁 A calorie is just a calorie but the sources those calories come from matters.
.
.
I recommend 2g/kg BW/day. People find this hard to hit especially without supplements. So here is an idea of what 150g of protein looks like in a day 😊
(P.s I would not recommend tuna everyday due to heavy metals.)
.
.

caption:
Variety is the spice of life 🌶🌶🌶

.

.

So one of the things I harp on about constantly as a nutritionist is trying to get more vegetables in my client's diet 🥦🥒🍄

.

.

But did you know how you cook your veggies can have an impact on it's nutritional status? For example: when boiling vegetables you may lose a lot of the vitamins in the water. Roasting vegetables can actually change the glycaemic index of a food. And any cooking method  can cause loss of fibre from the vegetables.

. 

.

What does this mean?

Get a variety of vegetables in your diet. And a variety of different cooking methods 

E.g A salad for lunch and roast veggies for dinner

Or Raw Spinach for breakfast and a stirfy for lunch

👉👉👉Tag someone who eats the same food constantly 🙈

.
.
This is something I encourage highly with all my clients. We are all busy being employees, mothers, wives, grandmothers, friends, bosses etc. We all do so much for everyone else, sometimes we forget about ourselves 😢
.
.
Ever heard the saying you can't pour from an empty cup? Actually that saying makes no sense surely it should be pot? 🤔 Anyway same theory applies....
.
.
Some of my selfcare advice:
✅ Find something you enjoy and do it EVERY single day. It might be 5 or 50 minutes but make the time for it
✅ Stop putting everyone else's needs ahead of your own
.
.
Some options if you can't think:
✅ Meditate - I use an App called Bloom and I have a discount code of BLOOMERS 🙌
✅ Jigsaws/Wordsearches/Crossword Puzzles
✅ Exercise - I've always used this one. But lately I've found I need something to help me unwind after CrossFit. I've started Yoga.
✅ Read a book
✅ Listen to a podcast/music
✅ Have a chat with a friend
✅ Have a cup of tea in peace
✅ Sit Outdoors
.
.
These are just some of my favourites. But do something for you EVERY.SINGLE.DAY ❤
.
.
Tag a boss lady who needs to see this 
⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️

P.s If you're interested in getting my advice and help. Dm Coach 🥰

I like to blow people's minds every once in awhile 😅🙈
.
.
🎯There are micro nutrient differences like white potatoes contain more potassium. Sweet potatoes have a lot more vitamin A. 
🎯Their Glycaemic Index is also quite different - white potatoes are High GI while sweet potato is lower GI.
🎯But macro nutrient wise there's very little difference 👊
.
.
P.s If you are still buying sweet potato fries in restaurants because they are the 'healthier' option - just stop 🤦‍♀️

caption:
Some of my favourite things about Austrailia:

✅Early Mornings - I've always been an early riser (like my Dad). But in Ireland it's not normal, I love that I'm the majority here when my alarm goes off for 5am 

✅ Breakfast - Any day but especially the weekends. Saturday mornings are made for the CrossFit followed by Breakfast. Honestly, it's one of my absolute favourite things to do down by the beach 🥰 

✅ Health and Fitness are a priority- do we have a recurring theme here 🤣 If I stay in my Grannys house in Donegal, there isn't a gym within a 30 mile radius 🙈 Over here almost every second building is a gym 

✅ Weekends are for Fun - whether you want to include alcohol or not, every weekend there is something new to do and in the 60 weeks I've been here I've done something new almost every weekend. Apart from CrossFit and Breakfast - that's a constant. 

✅ Tan - I haven't wore fake tan since September 🥰 Dont worry I wear SPF everyday 

✅ Friends are like Family - I saved the best for last. Friendships are intensified by the fact that we're so far away from home together. I love this though, I've made friends for life in such a short period of time ❤🙏

#happinessis

caption:
Thai Curry anyone? 🙋‍♀️
.
.
Simples, delicious and more nutritious than your local takeaway 🙈
.
.
Ingredients:
🎯 200g Prawns 
🎯 Frozen Peas
🎯 Frozen Spinach
🎯 Coconut Milk (if you're dieting just use half a tin and water as opposed to low fat)
🎯Thai Red Paste (decent quality - very little additives)
.
.
I dry fried all these. Added the coconut milk and 2 tbsp. Paste. Simmer for about 20 mins and Voila 👆
.
.
P.S Did you know shellfish has more iron than red meat. 

P.p.s You need Vitamin C to absorb iron

P.p.p.s Tannins in tea, coffee, red wine inhibit iron absorption. Be mindful if you suffer with low iron.

caption: I know what I'm choosing 🎯

I remember 7 years ago when I started strength training. 

I remember saying I wish I'd started sooner... 

7 years on and other people now say that same thing to me. 

It's never too late to start. I know people who start it in their teens and I also know people who start it in their 40s. 

Never use it's too late as an excuse. The time passes anyway.

It is never too late to make an improvement to your health. 

Stop waiting. There will never be a good time. Just do it! 

Not sure what to do? Why not use the next 90 days to make that long awaited start? 🙋‍♀️

𝐖𝐡𝐲 𝐝𝐨 𝐰𝐞 𝐰𝐚𝐢𝐭 𝐮𝐧𝐭𝐢𝐥 𝐰𝐞 𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐛𝐫𝐨𝐤𝐞𝐧 𝐭𝐨 𝐛𝐞 𝐟𝐢𝐱𝐞𝐝 🤦‍♀️
.
.
We all do it. 
.
.
I asked on my story the other day do you only wait UNTIL you are injured to go to the physio. Only 1 person said they go regularly 🙈
.
.
Ok, I understand maybe you're not going to go until maybe there is a little ache or pain or tweak etc. But please stop waiting until that festers into an actual problem. I'd say physios most common thing to hear is 'Oh ya I've had that for years'. It's not 'normal' to be in pain constantly 🤦‍♀️ 
.
.
Same goes for a coach. I feel people think you need to be overweight to invest in a coach. This couldn't be further from the truth ❎❎ 
.
.
Some of the reasons I suggest to invest in a coach:
1. You are not happy in your body - inside and/or outside
2. You don't know what to do to achieve your goals
3. You have tried every diet in the book and failed
4. You lack motivation
.
.
Don't keep holding it off. You don't need to be broken to be fixed ❎
.
.
If you are interested in hearing more about my online programme - DM COACH 🙌

#onlinecoaching #strongwomen

caption:
𝐓𝐨𝐩 𝟏𝟎% 𝐢𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐰𝐨𝐫𝐥𝐝 𝐁𝐚𝐛𝐲 👆👆👆
.
.
This was never even in my thoughts or goals but I'll take it. After just one year doing CrossFit competively, I'm beyond excited to see where the next few years takes me 🙌
.
.
I can honestly say there were no low lights to my second Open experience. 
.
.
🎯21.1 - I was happy with an exercise no one was prepared for and my double unders have come on 10 fold since my last Open
🎯21.2 - My Fav 🥰 (a past footballers dream)
🎯21.3 - 11 (fugly) Muscle Ups - I WILL TAKE THAT
🎯21.4 - Hang Cleans are my limiting factor 
.
.
I am Terrfied for what the next stage brings but just getting to this stage is the win for me. Special thanks to @crossfitcoogee and the team. I would not be where I am without your help 👊
.
.
Proud of myself is an understatement ❤🙌 
.
. 
#crossfitopen #crossfitopen2021 #crossfitgirls #quarterfinalsherewecome

caption:
𝕆𝕟𝕖 𝕠𝕗 𝕥𝕙𝕖 𝕓𝕚𝕘𝕘𝕖𝕤𝕥 𝕞𝕚𝕤𝕥𝕒𝕜𝕖𝕤 𝕀 𝕞𝕒𝕕𝕖 𝕨𝕙𝕖𝕟 𝕀 𝕤𝕥𝕒𝕣𝕥𝕖𝕕 𝕠𝕦𝕥 𝕚𝕟 𝕥𝕙𝕖 𝔽𝕚𝕥𝕟𝕖𝕤𝕤 𝕀𝕟𝕕𝕦𝕤𝕥𝕣𝕪 𝕨𝕒𝕤 𝕥𝕙𝕚𝕟𝕜𝕚𝕟𝕘 𝕡𝕖𝕠𝕡𝕝𝕖 𝕨𝕒𝕟𝕥𝕖𝕕 𝕥𝕠 𝕓𝕖 𝕝𝕚𝕜𝕖 𝕞𝕖 🙈
.
.
There I said it. I can admit when I'm wrong.
.
.
🎯I thought people would want to eat like me - and I got frustrated when people wouldn't. I would remove foods from their diets and limit their treats. I couldn't understand when people couldn't sustain it?
'What did you think Susan this was going to be easy?'

✅ I thought people would prioritise sleep like me - I neglected the fact I was working with mothers and shift workers. I painted everyone with the one brush.

👊I thought everyone's goals were the same as me. I thought everyone was willing to make huge sacrifices. 

🙈 Honestly, I just considered people moany or whingy when they couldn't do what I asked them.
.
.
I do these things. Why can't they?
.
.
Because Amanda - their goals are completely different to yours 🤦‍♀️.
.
.
Years of experience made me realise what a fool I was. People want something sustainable and what people are willing to commit and sacrifice are totally different for everyone 🤦‍♀️
.
.
What I've realised:
💫 People need to change habits slowly
💫 Quick fixes don't work
💫 People need to enjoy the exercise they're doing - not necessarily the exercise you want them to do - 80% of what they like, 20% of what they need
💫 People need accountability 
💫 People need to be able to talk to their coach/trainer/nutritionist 
💫 People who really care will invest in themselves
💫 The journey is so much easier with a community spirit
.
.
So yet again. I was wrong. I made mistakes and now I'm making up for them. 🙋‍♀️
.
.
But thankfully my clients are getting the Amanda 2.0. If you're interested, DM me 'Coach' 🙋‍♀️

📸@marceauphotography

caption:
Do or say something special to/for another person every single day. 
.
.
✅It might be as simple as telling your mother you love her.
✅Why not compliment a friend?
✅Or what about holding a door for a stranger! 
.
.
It is such a simple thing to do, it will make someone else happy and it'll bring you joy. Win win 🙌

#beagoodperson

No words can describe this group of women ❤
.
.
But seeing as I'm a talker I'll try to explain it 🤣
.
.
I've played sport my whole life but I've never been part of a community that care more about one another. The beauty (and the downfall) of most sports is competition. CrossFit is competition to improve yourself, never at the expense of someone else. Watching these girls take on RX workouts is honestly as thrilling as doing it myself. I am so proud of every single person in this picture ❤
.
.
Thank you @crossfitgames @crossfitcoogee @aldoalduccio not only for finding my sport but for finding some of the best friends 👭

caption:
What you see:
👆 A relatively lean, healthy looking person
👆 Someone happy enough to put a half naked picture on social media
👆 Not much difference between pictures
👆 Some new tattoos and a tan 
.
.
What I see:
🎯 A totally different person
🎯 A physically and mentally stronger person
🎯 A girl who is finally happy in her own skin
🎯 A girl who doesn't care what the scales says
🎯 Someone who has learned a lot.
🎯 Someone who has made mistakes 
🎯 A fighter
🎯 No dress size dictates her happiness
🎯 Has a good relationship with food
🎯 Eats to fuel herself and her performance
🎯 Has found balance 
.
.
I know so many women unhappy in their bodies. I see so many women wasting money on diet plans and gym memberships 😭
.
.
I can promise you all - no number on the scales, no clothes size, no diet plan will make you happy unless you deal with your 'why'. 👊
.
.
I had all the knowledge in the world re nutrition. I trained. And none of it mattered until I realised why I was so unhappy in my body. (I was looking through old photos and I literally used to take photos every SINGLE day to see if my body changed 😭). Once I understood my why - everything changed.
.
.
P.s it required outside help. I seen a counsellor and life coach #therapyiscool
If you need help reach out 👆 I am currently taking on new Online Clients. I want to help you reach your full potential. I want you to become stronger inside and out 💪🙌

caption:
✳ 🎀  𝒮𝑒𝓁𝒻 𝒞𝒶𝓇𝑒 🎀 ✳
.
.
I hope each and everyone of you leave some time for you every day. I don't mean hours, it can be minutes. But every day you need to find some 'you time'. 
.
.
Everyone has something different. Meditate, read a book, listen to a podcast, drink a cup of tea - just find what works for you. And do it daily. 
.
.
Now, find something you need to do for yourself every so often. For me up until recently It was go on 2 big holidays a year and a couple of weekend breaks. I understand that is not something everyone can do at the moment but why not make a plan for when it is? Or save or invest in something for you - it may be a new car, a new couch, some home gym equipment? 
.
.
In recent years I've realised the importance of self care. I invest in holidays and my health. 
.
.
🎯It never ceases to amaze me how people can spend $100's on handbags but a physio appointment is too expensive? 🤦‍♀️
🎯 I still can't comprehend how a facial or a massage is seen as a luxury but 3 uber eats a week is normal?
🎯 Coaching is a waste of money but alcohol and drugs are 'worth it' 

I know it all comes down to priorities, I understand that. Not everyone sees the benefit of investing in your physical and mental health right now. I get that. But don't think these things are 'expensive' or a 'luxury' if you are literally throwing away your money 🙈❎
.
.
What is your go to for self care? 
⬇️⬇️⬇️

caption:
Stop comparing foods as like with like 🤦‍♀️
.
.
✅€30 = $46.17 AUD. But they are 2 totally different currencies.
✅1000 Tonnes Feathers = 1000 Tonnes Coal. But they are 2 totally different components. 
.
.
The same goes for food. 
.
.
100 Calories Apple = 100 Calorie Chocolate Bar (as a measure of calories). But you cannot compare them in composition. The lack of micronutrients, the high sugar and fat content in the chocolate bar cannot be easily compared to the vitamins, mineral, water and phytonutrients in the apple 🤦‍♀️
.
.
Since when was Maths ever that simple 😅 I am not saying Calories in versus calories out is non sense, because it isn't. It makes sense and is very important. All I'm saying is, it's not the ONLY thing that is important. Food quality matters for long term health benefits and body composition 🙌
.
.
Questions? 🤔

caption:
𝐀𝐫𝐞 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐧𝐤𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐚𝐛𝐨𝐮𝐭 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐟𝐮𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞 𝐬𝐞𝐥𝐟? 👆👆👆
.
.
I hear so much talk about having a good job, financial security, engagements, weddings, starting a family etc. Etc. These are normal topics of conversation. 
.
.
Who's talking about reducing your risk of heart disease and cancer? Increasing you likelihood of conception? Limiting your risk of bone density related issues? Do you know what sarcopenia is?
.
.
Why don't we talk about these things? 🤔 
.
.
I'm not trying to be a negative Nancy here. But you are your own most important asset. 🙏
❎What good is all the money in the world if you're not around to spend it?
❎ Having a baby is NOT a given. I work with women constantly who have difficulty trying to conceive.
❎ Do you want to be able to play with your kids and grandkids? 
.
.
Every decision you make now contributes towards your future self. Are you happy with your decisions? 🤔👆

caption:
𝓝𝓾𝓽𝓻𝓲𝓽𝓲𝓸𝓷 𝓪𝓻𝓸𝓾𝓷𝓭 𝔂𝓸𝓾𝓻 𝓬𝔂𝓬𝓵𝓮
.
.
There is nothing too mind blowing here. There's a very recurring theme. .
.
.
✅Eat a good balanced of carbohydrates, fats and proteins.
The luteal phase is a time that cravings are high so try to stabilise blood sugars.
✅Increase calories during certain phases if needs be. And possible reduction during other phases. It's your body's requirements!
✅Eat anti inflammatory foods - wholefoods with colour. 
✅Sufficient magnesium in your diet - seeds, dark chocolate, nuts 
✅Green Leafy, Cruciferous Vegetables - This will help the liver reduce any excess estrogen.
✅ Reduce alcohol, caffeine and salt to avoid fluid retention
.
.
Nutrition around your cycle is important. But if you're like me and have a great diet, full of colour, high in all macronutrients and don't drink alcohol to often then you're doing pretty darn well 🙌 Anything extra is a bonus 🙌
.
.
Save for later and maybe tag a friend ⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️
.
.

caption:
𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐭𝐢𝐦𝐞 𝐥𝐚𝐬𝐭 𝐲𝐞𝐚𝐫 𝐈 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐭𝐨 𝐛𝐚𝐜𝐤 𝐬𝐪𝐮𝐚𝐭 𝐚𝐠𝐚𝐢𝐧 🏋‍♀️
.
.
After I did my ACL, I started to do box squats. I felt comfortable with box squats. I didn't feel pain and I had a bigger ego (I.e I could lift heavier). Thankfully, box squats were transferable to my sport so I didn't even think about full depth squats. I was hitting 1RM 135kg comfortably. I was pretty happy 👌 Until I had to go back to below parallel squats (CrossFit). Where was my strength? I was struggling with 40kg. I was hiding behind this half depth strength and when it came to a full squat my body hadn't a clue what was happening 🙈
.
.
Why am I telling you this?
.
.
𝘉𝘦𝘤𝘢𝘶𝘴𝘦 𝘐'𝘮 𝘯𝘰𝘵 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘰𝘯𝘭𝘺 𝘱𝘦𝘳𝘴𝘰𝘯 𝘮𝘢𝘴𝘬𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘢 𝘸𝘦𝘢𝘬𝘯𝘦𝘴𝘴. 𝘐'𝘮 𝘯𝘰𝘵 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘰𝘯𝘭𝘺 𝘱𝘦𝘳𝘴𝘰𝘯 𝘶𝘴𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘢 𝘣𝘢𝘯𝘥 𝘢𝘪𝘥 𝘵𝘰 𝘧𝘪𝘹 𝘱𝘳𝘰𝘣𝘭𝘦𝘮𝘴.
.
.
🎯 If something isn't right stop ignoring the problem - health, happiness, weight, self esteem, job... the list goes on
❎ Stop waiting until we are broken to be fixed
.
.
I help people every day overcome their fears. Their issues with self confidence. Their poor relationships with food. Their association of exercise with just burning calories. This is my job. I'm here to help. If you are interested in coaching DM me 'Interested' ❤🙏 

@marceauphotography

caption:
𝕀 𝕙𝕒𝕕 𝕒 𝕤𝕔𝕒𝕣𝕖 𝕕𝕦𝕣𝕚𝕟𝕘 𝕥𝕙𝕖 𝕨𝕖𝕖𝕜 
.
.
My period was 14 days late. 
.
.
It wasn't a fear of pregnancy. Quite the opposite actually. Don't forget our menstrual cycle is a sign of health 🙏 
.
.
10 years ago if you had said to me, give me a once off tablet to never have my period again, I would have taken it. Why? Because I considered it 'disgusting' or 'an inconvenience'. I was so uneducated. But being totally honest I just didn't care about my health enough either 😬
.
.
I have been so in tune with my body the last 5 months that it honestly came as a huge shock to me to have such an irregular cycle 😢 I harp on to all my clients about it's importance and here I was with a 42 day cycle. 
.
.
The thing about the menstrual cycle is, it's sensitive. It can't deal with too much stress. But remember stress looks different on everyone 🤷‍♀️ For me last month I travelled time zones (this ALWAYS puts my cycle off) and I had my 30th Birthday weekend (the most alcohol I've drank in months - another stress). 
.
.
One long cycle like that due to stress is ok. But if it's a continuing problem, it is really worth seeking medical advice or help from a professional.
.
.
You may not be thinking about it now. But amenorrhoea or irregular menstrual cycles can have a profound effect on your future health.
.
.
My advice:
✅Start tracking 
✅ Understand the different phases in your cycle
✅ Monitor symptoms, emotions, feelings, productivity, energy.
.
.
Work with your body, not against 🙏❤

caption:
Fitness to me shows consistency, hard work and determination ✌
.
.
I will never tire of people calling me fit. I loved when people didn't want to mark me. I am so proud anytime someone calls me a 'tank' or a 'machine' 😅 

.
Why?
Because of where I started and where I came from ❤
.
.
I was not always fit. I was definitely not skilful. But my God find someone who was a harder worker than me.
.
.
Hard Work 
✅I went from the girl who had to give her football boots to another player to making the county team.
✅I went from the scrawny midfielder to the strong full back. 
✅I made the bloody Connacht panel. And rest assured I was not the most talented defender in the province.
✅ Weddings, 21st Birthdays, social occassions, holidays, j1s - all missed
.
.
Consistency
✅ I was back on the pitch with Roscommon 8 months after my ACL reconstruction
✅ I was in the gym 2 days after surgery on my wrist
✅ 8 weeks after dislocating my knee I took part in a Crossfit Competition and achieved my top 10 goal.
.
.
Determination
✅ After being told I'd never be the same footballer after my ACL injury - I came back stronger and fitter than ever. Ill never forget winning my first sprint the day I went back to full training or scoring the winning point the day of my return to play
✅ I won a CrossFit competition on a Saturday, played in a county semi final on a Wednesday - did great in both
✅ At 28 with Achilles Tendonopathy, I played 2 games - 1 county, 1 club - I actually HIGHLY do not recommend this 😬🤦‍♀️
.
.
This is not intended to be a boast post 😅 Although I'm pretty bloody proud of all of the above - apart from the 2 games in 1 day, that was pure stupidity ❎ 
.
.
This is almost 20 years of time and effort. 20 years of commitment. 20 years of sacrifice. (I've sacrificed a lot less in recent times, priorities shifted).
So before you think about quitting because you haven't seen results in 6 weeks. Think about the commitment you're giving. Think about the sacrifice you're making. 
.
.
Think about where you can be in 20 years time 👊

#heresto20more

Happy International Women's Day ❤
.
.
I am so blessed to have so many incredible women in my life - my friends, my family & my clients 🙏
.
.
We deserve a day to be celebrated and each and every one of us should take this day to be thankful and grateful for all our achievements 🌟

#happyinternationalwomensday

𝔹𝕦𝕥 𝕨𝕙𝕒𝕥 𝕒𝕓𝕠𝕦𝕥 𝕤𝕖𝕝𝕗 𝕝𝕠𝕧𝕖?
.
.
Yesterday in Austrailia we celebrated Mardi Gras. I am, have been and always will be a 'love is love' advocate ❤🙏
.
.
I do however, see a little problem within our society 😢 We focus so much on finding love with another person that we forget to love ourselves 😔
.
.
A few years ago I would have found this talk 'absolutely ridiculous' 🤦‍♀️ The same person would self sabotage with alcohol 🤷‍♀️ It's a very individual belief and idea. It doesn't look the same on everyone so here's my two cents.
.
.
What self love means to me:
❎ Not seeking other people's approval - doing things for myself, not others
❎ Not being jealous - it's a terrible trait to compare yourself, your possessions or your life to others. Find happiness within what you have or within what you do - if you're not happy, change it. This was a MAJOR turning point for me
✔ Be content with the person you are - your traits, your characteristics - what makes you you ❤ And again, if there is something you are not happy with - remember you have the power to change it.
✔ Be happy in your own company - another game changer. I am beyond blessed with Owen, the very large group of friends I have, the work I do and the training I do. I am a social butterfly and I love that. But I am very comfortable being in my own company and alone also.
.
.
I was so lucky to have found Owen at a period in my life where I really didn't love myself and I needed his attention so much. That puts pressure on a relationship. Insecurity is difficult. But in the time we've been together he's seen a change to me, a welcome change. (He actually said to me just last night how proud he is of me 🥰😭)
.
.
I am so happy within myself. I'm confident in my work. I love my body - not for how it looks but for what it can do. I love my soul - I am a good person and the friends I have are proof of that. 
.
.
It's MORE than ok to give yourself a pat on the back. Its more than ok to say how proud you are of yourself.
.
.
LOVE YOSELF🌈

caption:
𝐍𝐞𝐯𝐞𝐫 𝐮𝐧𝐝𝐞𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐢𝐦𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐬 🤯
.
.
𝘋𝘪𝘥 𝘺𝘰𝘶 𝘬𝘯𝘰𝘸?
.
.
Stress is not just 'feeling stressed'. I always ask my clients about stress levels. Most people respond with either 'yes I'm stressed or no I'm not stressed'. Stress is a lot more complex than 'feeling stressed'.
.
.
Stress can present itself from so many things,some which I'm sure you're aware of, some which you won't realise 🙈 (the above is just a handful)
.
.
When you're stressed body switches on fight or flight mode - releases Adrenaline, Nora adrenaline, Cortisol.
.
🎯Adrenaline increases heart rate, breath faster and tenses muscles.
🎯Noradrenaline diverts blood from (unessential areas during fight or flight) reproductive system, digestive and skin.
🎯Cortisol raises blood pressure and blood sugar levels.
.
We need stress hormones in our body, but the problem arises when they are imbalanced.
.
𝐈𝐦𝐩𝐥𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐬 𝐨𝐟 𝐢𝐧𝐜𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐬𝐞𝐝 𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐬 𝐡𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐨𝐧𝐞𝐬
✔Suppress other hormones - sex
✔Suppressing immune system & libido
✔Increased blood pressure
✔Having impact on digestion
✔Increasing acne and obesity risk
.
𝘞𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘤𝘢𝘯 𝘺𝘰𝘶 𝘥𝘰?
⭐ Reduce controllable stresses
⭐ Take so me time every day
⭐ Meditate
⭐ Rest and Relax more
⭐ Talk to people more - about issues etc.
⭐ Seek medical attention if necessary
.
.
#howstressedareyou

𝐘𝐨𝐮 𝐧𝐞𝐞𝐝 𝐭𝐨 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐭 𝐥𝐨𝐨𝐤𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐭𝐨𝐰𝐚𝐫𝐝𝐬 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐟𝐮𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞 🔮
.
.

𝘖𝘒 𝘨𝘶𝘺𝘴 𝘐'𝘮 𝘢𝘣𝘰𝘶𝘵 𝘵𝘰 𝘴𝘵𝘢𝘳𝘵 𝘵𝘢𝘭𝘬𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘴𝘰𝘮𝘦 𝘴𝘦𝘳𝘪𝘰𝘶𝘴 𝘴𝘩𝘪𝘵 𝘩𝘦𝘳𝘦
.
.
✔It is great to exercise. 
✔It is great to eat healthy. 
✔It is great to have a healthy mindset... 
.
.
❎ It is not ok to let any of these overconsume your life
❎ It is not ok to let your health take a back-seat for an aesthetic goal
❎ It is not ok to lose your period (because of your lifestyle)
.
.
𝐀𝐫𝐞 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐧𝐤𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐚𝐛𝐨𝐮𝐭 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐟𝐮𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞?
.
.
𝘋𝘪𝘥 𝘺𝘰𝘶 𝘬𝘯𝘰𝘸?
🎯 Extreme dieting can affect your fertility
🎯 Hormonal imbalances can have an affect on bone density
🎯 Too much exercise causes stress on the body
🎯 Nutrient deficiencies can have detrimental consequences on people's health
🎯 The knock on affect of dieting or exercise obsession can have an impact on social occassions
🎯 Obsession with food can lead to disordered eating
.
.
The above literally scratch the surface of the negatives of too much exercise or dieting.
.
.
I need women to realise you are NOT just looking at the here and now. What you do now impacts you in the years to come. As a mother maybe? Or a grandmother? Please please please think of that next time you decide to embark on your fitness journey 🙈
.
.

𝐈𝐟 𝐲𝐨𝐮'𝐝 𝐥𝐢𝐤𝐞 𝐭𝐨 𝐛𝐞𝐜𝐨𝐦𝐞 𝐚 𝐡𝐞𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐞𝐫, 𝐟𝐢𝐭𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐬𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐨𝐟 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐬𝐞𝐥𝐟. 𝐈'𝐦 𝐭𝐚𝐤𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐨𝐧 𝟑 𝐧𝐞𝐰 𝐜𝐥𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐌𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡. 𝐃𝐦 𝐦𝐞 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐝𝐞𝐭𝐚𝐢𝐥𝐬 🥳

caption: BE THE WOMAN WHO FIXES ANOTHER WOMAN's CROWN,WITHOUT TELLING THE WORLD IT WAS CROOKED ❤

ℍ𝕠𝕨 𝕨𝕖𝕝𝕝 𝕒𝕣𝕖 𝕪𝕠𝕦 𝕣𝕖𝕔𝕠𝕧𝕖𝕣𝕚𝕟𝕘?
.
.
Quite often people think you need to do more to achieve your goals. And in a lot of cases that is true - more exercise, more water, better nutrition. But for some actually less is more. 
.
.
Everyone has their problem areas. Some people nail nutrition and exercise and can't understand why they can't lose weight - while their bodies are in chronic sleep deprivation 🤦‍♀️ Others weigh in the week before their period and can't understand why their weight fluctuates. Others would rather take a supplement than eat real food 🙈
.
.
These are some of the elements to think about when it comes to your goals - in no particular order 👊
.
.
My own Experience 
- I'm excellent with training and drinking water, I'm very good with nutrition and my sleep is decent. Performance is my goal. I felt like I wasn't fully recovering right - so instead of doing more - I've been training with my body. I'm back on creatine and I'm managing my stress 👊👌
.
.
Nutrition and exercise are not the only 2 elements you can control. If you have those nailed why not look at other areas? 🤔

Greatness happens outside our comfort zone ❤🙏

#soproudofmyself

caption:
𝕀 𝕨𝕒𝕤𝕟'𝕥 𝕒𝕝𝕨𝕒𝕪𝕤 𝕔𝕠𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕕𝕖𝕟𝕥 ❎
.
.
This will come as a shock to people.
.
.
Even when I was younger, I gave off the appearance of a confident person but deep down I suffered from really low self worth 😢
.
.
I was the exact replica of the majority of my clients and women in general:
.
✔ I put myself under too much pressure
✔ I tried to please everyone but myself 
✔ I based my self worth on my appearance
✔ I wanted to be perfect at everything
.
.
My game changed when my mental game changed.
.
🎯 I realised I was putting myself under huge unnecessary pressure. It was self inflicted and I needed to realise that
🎯 I stopped trying to please everyone else and put myself first
🎯 I don't base my self worth on how I look but what kind of person I am ❤
🎯 Perfection doesn't exist but I'm doing a damn good job at life
.
.
If your mental game is not strong, I can Promise you - no clothes size, weight target or 'ideal body' will feel good ❤ Start working on both your physical and mental health. Seek the help you need. Find something you can stick to long term 🙏 And enjoy life - we only get one 🙌
.
.
#liveyourlife #createthelifeyouwant #mentalhealth #physicalhealth #onlinecoach

caption:
𝓦𝓪𝓷𝓷𝓪 𝓴𝓷𝓸𝔀 𝓶𝔂 𝓼𝓮𝓬𝓻𝓮𝓽?
.
.
Consistency 👊
.
.
✔ I tried cheap products 
✔ I tried expensive products 
✔ I quit on it 
✔ I blamed all the products
✔ I blamed my hormones
✔ I blamed my diet
.
.
Then one day I decided to take it serious. I booked in for a consult with @advancedrejuvenationbondi. I started getting regular facials. I started listening to my body - training with it rather than against it. I reduced my stress levels. I reduced dairy from my diet. This was a process. It didn't all happen in one day. I took it step by step day by day. I was patient 🙈 (for once in my life). And now 6 months on, I'm reaping the rewards 🙏😍
.
.
Why am I telling you this?
I always compare my skin journey to others fitness journey.
Why?
❎ Most people try 10 different programmes but never stick to one
❎ Most people blame everyone and everything else for not achieveing their goals
❎ Most people are impatient 
.
.
If you need help achieving your goals just reach out. Pm me.There is no shame in asking for help. You'll save yourself a lot of time in the long run 👊
.
.
And lets be honest if you knew what to do you'd have the results already? 
🤷‍♀️🤷‍♀️🤷‍♀️

caption:

.
.
I don't mean happiness from a material thing or a place or other. I mean true internal happiness. 🙏 
.
.
Realising your absolute worth and how incredible you are. Understanding your beauty is skin deep ❤ Surrounding yourself with positivity and incredible people. 😍 Removing any negativity or toxic environment from your life. 
.
.
I practice gratitude daily. I always find the good in even the most awful situations. But honestly, the only way I can describe how I feel at the moment is whole. I wish I could bottle up this feeling and give it to people. ❤
.
.
I practice self love and preach it to all my clients. If I could help everyone with it I would. But if you honestly want to make a change and become more confident and happy in your own skin - dm me - 'whole'

🙅‍♀️𝐖𝐡𝐲 𝐬𝐡𝐨𝐮𝐥𝐝 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐧𝐨𝐭 𝐜𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐭 𝐜𝐚𝐥𝐨𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐬 𝐛𝐮𝐫𝐧𝐞𝐝 𝐨𝐧 𝐚 𝐅𝐢𝐭𝐛𝐢𝐭, 𝐚𝐩𝐩𝐥𝐞 𝐰𝐚𝐭𝐜𝐡 𝐞𝐭𝐜?🙅‍♀️
.
.
1. You were not born to just consume and burn calories - you and your body are worth more than that
2. Instead of checking what calories you burned why not instead enjoy your training?
3. If reason 1 & 2 weren't enough, These trackers are so inaccurate 🤦‍♀️ So even if you do it just to see calories burned it's more than likely wrong.
4. Journalling the weights you are lifting and the reps and sets you are doing is so much more beneficial to your goals - no matter what they are 🤷‍♀️ 
.
.
If we all actually started becoming as obsessed with what weights we're lifting, we would actually start seeing so much better results 🤦‍♀️
Do yourself a favour. Stop focusing on calories burned and scale weights and start focusing on weight lifted and enjoy your exercise. Amen 🙏

caption:
🎯 Values and Goals 🎯
.
.
People set their goals too high - it's a natural thing.
.
.
From an aesthetic perspective, we have all been raised with unrealistic expectations of what the 'perfect body' is. So of course people set their limits towards that. In most cases:
1. The person we want to look like doesn't actually look like their photoshopped photo
2. The measures they went to, to look like that are unhealthy and unattainable
.
.
From a fitness perspective, we go in all guns blazing expecting to train every day. Expecting an RPE of 8-10 on every session. Expecting to hit pbs everyday. Expecting training sessions to be fun and exciting and different and enjoyable.
1. If you are a person who doesn't exercise, commit to NO MORE than 3 sessions a week - 40 mins. Anything extra should be a bonus.
2. If body composition change is a goal, lift bloody weights - I'm sick of explaining all the reasons why.
3. Boring can be progressed. Progression = improvement. Stop trying to make it fancy.
.
.
From a nutrition perspective, we want to change our whole diet in a week which leads to.... Falling off the wagon altogether, saying fuck it  and starting that cycle 7 million times. What you should do:
1. Start small. Build habits. Imagine 1 habit a week over 12 weeks. No crazy changes just small incremental changes.
2. Instead of eliminating foods - add foods. Add colour, add protein, add water. 
3. 80/20 rule is and will always be my go to. 80% of the food your body needs, 20% of the food your body wants.
.
.
Support - Stop trying to do this all unassisted. If you're like me and love the support from your girls ❤ Find a gym buddy. If you need help with your goals invest in a coach 🙏

I used to hate my small boobies....
I used to hate my teeth...
I used to hate my curly hair...
I always wanted to be smaller...
I wanted to be prettier...
I wanted to be smarter...
I wanted to be fitter...
I wanted to be lighter..
I wanted abs... 

I always wanted something more. I was never happy. But the problem wasn't in my appearance. The problem lay deep inside. I wasn't happy within myself. I didn't love myself or my body 😢 And this is something I see in 90% of women, a feeling of self loathing 😭 

I made changes. I changed how I viewed myself and my body. It took time. A long time. But finally I am at a place in my life that my exterior does not define me. I am living in a country where aesthetics is priority and most people have injected at least 1 part of their body 🙈😅 And here I am - delighted with my frizzy hair, my crooked teeth and my muscular legs 👊 

This is something I work on my clients with constantly. Stop trying to look for happiness in a clothes size, the bottom of a make up bottle, or the newest beauty trend. I can promise you no amount of beauty products fitness regimes or shopping can make you feel like self confidence feels 🙏 

P.s Who knew having no boobies at 30 would be the absolute dream 🤷‍♀️

.
.
This age seems to freak some people out 😵 I know it freaked me out 5 years ago 🙄
.
.
At 30 I thought...
✔ I would be married
✔ Have at least 1 child
✔ Have my own business
✔ Have bought a house
✔ Settled in Donegal
.
.
Reality turning 30...
👆 In a 10 year relationship with no plans - sorry Mom 😆
👆 I don't even have a pet currently 😢
👆 Employed 🙏
👆 Still renting - and paying way too much for a 'sea view' 😆
👆 Living in Oz
.
.
And I COULD NOT BE HAPPIER ❤ Everyones journey is different 🙌 Don't compare journeys ❎ I'm fitter, healthier, happier and have better skin turning 30 than I ever have before 😜
.
.
❤ Getting older is a privilege denied to many. So be grateful ❤

caption:
Why Protein? 
.
.
Quite often I hear people recommending high protein diets without having a clue why they are recommending it 🤷‍♀️
.
.
My clients know why I recommend up to 2g Protein/KG BW/day 🙌 Why? Because I educate them why 👊
.
.
1. TEF - Our total daily energy expenditure (TDEE) is made up for 4 components - BMR, NEAT, Purposeful Activity and TEF. It accounts for up to 10% of our TDEE. Protein rich foods have a higher thermic effect from food than any other macro nutrient.
.
2. Satiety - Protein is super filling. It's difficult to eat large quantities without feeling full. This is a good complaint 😜
.
3. Recovery - Protein is required for so many processes in our body. Regardless of your goals - weight loss, weight gain, performance - everyone will benefit from a high protein diet.
.
.
So now you understand 👆👆👆

caption:
Collette's Experience:

I have spent the last few days thinking about how I can put into words what the past 12 weeks have down for me. I started off with a particular goal in mind, it definitely hasn't ended up with that same goal!!! I wanted weight loss along with other things and I have lost very little but amazingly the weight loss is irrelevant to me. I haven't even looked at the scales in past 2 weeks. It's the journey that has happened internally that is my biggest achievement and I can honestly say i have never felt better, as Amanda has said so many times it doesn't matter what you look like on the outside if you're not happy on the inside you'll never be happy with how you look. I have achieved so many small personal goals, swimming in the sea on probably the coldest day of the year without worrying about how I looked to others, walking 10 Kms without even thinking about it and loving every single step. I have a very sedentary job and before I started there was days I didn't even get 2000 steps in, most definitely a thing of the past. But THE most important part of my 12 week journey is the fact that I am off all my medication for my mental health, no more anti depressants or anxiety tablets. 💪💪💪 This journey has taught me to make time for me, just me and as a result I'm a better mother, partner and work colleague because I am happier in me . My journey has just started and I can't wait to see where the next 12 weeks will bring me. From the bottom of my heart Amanda, Brian and all the girls on the coaching calls thank you for the wonderful support along the way 
💗💗💗

caption:
Comparison is the thief of joy 🤦‍♀️
.
.
I see this one a lot.
.
.
You are individual. You are not like anyone else, so why would you compare yourself to anyone else? 🤷‍♀️
.
.
Most of the time the circumstances aren't  even comparable. Let's give you some examples
❎ Comparing your image to celebrities 
❎ Comparing your performance to athletes
❎ Comparing your body to fitness influencers
.
.
If you are not where you want to be, being honest it is probably something you are or are not doing. BUT you are making life a hell of a lot more difficult for yourself by setting unrealistic goals and targets 🎯
.
.
✔ Start by setting some realistic goals
✔ Progression over perfection 
✔ Be consistent - stop giving it a short term tag. Look at the long term. Look at your future self.
✔ Find something you enjoy - you are more likely to stick to it
.
.
Stop blaming other people and start looking at what you need to do to get where you want to be 👊 And remember no number on the scales will make you happy unless you deal with the shit in your head 🧠

caption:
Training and Nutrition
Aesthetics vs Performance 
.
.
Some of the differences include:
1. Calorie requirements may be different. 
Performance goals usually require maintenance calories or even a surplus depending on how active you are. Aesthetic goals usually require being in a calorie deficit.
.
.
2. Training looks different. 
Training for aesthetics is usually some bodybuilding format with some form of light cardio. Training for performance is usually sport specific like pitch training, strength sessions or even high volume sessions like CrossFit.
.
.
3. Nutrient profiles may be different.
Firstly, weight loss requires you to be in a calorific deficit. Technically, you could eat 1 Mars bar a day and lose weight. I wouldn't recommend it, but you'd achieve your goals. Where as if you tried to perform at your best for a sport on 1 Mars bar a day, I cannot imagine you'd be performing very well.
Nutrition for aesthetics can be as simple as calories in versus calories out. Nutrition for performance is much more intricate - do you have enough fuel? Are you recovering ok? Do you have a full nutrient profile? Are you consuming good fats for hormonal balance and recovery? 
.
.
These are some of the main differences in nutrition and training when you have different goals. Can you think of more? 🤔

📸@marceauphotography

caption:
The meaning behind my Lotus Flower Tattoo 🌺
.
.
I went through a really hard period of my life after my Dad died. As the oldest of his daughters I felt a responsibility to keep my shit together, look after my mother and sister and keep up appearances. It was a struggle. I tried to do this while managing a gym, commuting, playing with 2 football teams, studying, trying to maintain friendships and a relationship. I felt like I was just surviving as opposed to living 😢
.
.
And then I took control of my life. I started to look after myself first and everybody else's needs and wants came second. 
.
.
The meaning of the tattoo is that even the most beautiful things can come from the ugliest of places. 🙏
.
.
I'm not alone. I know we've all had struggles and strifes in our lives. I'm not saying mine has been harder than anyone else's. But I decided to take control of mine. I asked for help. I seeked the help I needed. And I made life changing decisions 💔❤
.
.
My first Austrailia day in Sydney ❤ I honestly am so proud of my choices and decisions in the last few years 🙏 And I could not have spent it with anyone better @o_boyce ❤❤❤

caption:
I am fully aware things are crap in Ireland at the moment 😢 90% of my clients are in Ireland, my friends are in Ireland, my family are in Ireland ❤ I am genuinely heartbroken for them 💔
.
.
When lockdown occurred in Austrailia, one of the biggest habits people developed was daily alcohol drinking. And openly admitted when working from home, the time would get earlier and earlier 🙈
.
.
I am not anti alcohol. Actually I am the polar opposite. I encourage clients to have a glass of wine at weekends if that is what truely makes them happy. It's important to have balance in your life 🙏
.
.
I do believe though that alcohol is a little too readily available and can be 'too easy' to use as an escape. 
.
.
I implore people to find other things to pass their time. Exercise, walk, bake, knit, zoom call, cook, spring clean, learn a new skill ... the list goes on. But please don't let alcohol be the ONLY thing you look forward to daily 🙏🙏🙏

caption:
Being, feeling and looking stronger is the most empowered I have ever felt 🙌💪
.
.
I can't explain it. But the feeling is like no other 🙌🤩 It is euphoric. Even as I sit writing this my hands are ripped open, I've rope burn on my legs and my calves feel every km I put in yesterday 😅 People think I'm crazy, I do understand why 😅🙈
.
.
But honestly I don't think I'd be me without this strength now. 
.
.
For years, my identity included football. People in my locality knew me as the footballer. But moving country helped remove that association 😅 Nobody I know over here even associates me with the sport 😅 But no one associates me with CrossFit. Last year I thought I wanted to get really serious about Crossfit. It was the competitive mindset 🙈 Going from one sport to another. 
.
.
But now, I'm just Amanda who trains. I like that ❤ No pressures. No stresses. No giving up a social 11am
life. Training when I want to. Working to better myself everyday.
.
.
And MOST IMPORTANTLY I train for performance as opposed to aesthetics. This was game changer for me. Its not everyone's goals I understand that but it certainly shifted my mindset towards myself and my body ❤
.
.
I am still taking on clients who want to get stronger improve performance, and become more confident. DM me for more details. 

📸 @marceauphotography

✅ Fruit with or without nut butter
✅ Nuts and Seeds

caption:
Hello New Followers 🙋‍♀️
.
.
I wanted to give you a little bitta background about me. Who I am and what this page is about 🙏
.
.
💫 Amanda
💫 29 
💫 From Roscommon 
📍 Living in Sydney
🎓 BSc. Human Nutrition, Level 3&4 Certs in Fitness, Pre and Post Natal Coach, Precision Nutrition Coach
.
.
💫I work with a company called @ownitfit. I do in person Bootcamps and I am the  nutritionist, but most of my time is spent on my Online Coaching clients all around the world 🌍 I also work as a nutritionist in @strengthandmovementlab 🙏
.
.
💫 I have been involved in Sports from a very young age. My career as an inter county footballer Ceased in 2019 and I haven't looked back since 😅Beach Sundays are pretty decent 🥰 My Dad was my no.1 supporter of my sporting career. After he passed, health and living my life became my priority 🙏
.
.
💫 My ethos:
The only thing I love more than health and fitness is women supporting women ❤ Thankfully I get to do that every single day in my job ❤🙏 I want to help educate women about health and wellness. I want to help them become super confident and strong females 🙌 
.
.

caption:
Training with my cycle is amazing 💥💥
.
.
It means I can push my body hard when I need to and take my foot off the gas when my body needs it.🙏
.
.
This week is the week after my period (follicular phase). I feel like a bloody machine this week. And next week is always a good training week too. Then I know to reduce intensity and frequency during my luteal phase.😵
.
.
I have tuned into my body so much more and I'm getting the most out of my sessions. Most importantly, I'm not beating myself up when I can't train as hard 🙌
.
.
If you have not already, you NEED to start tuning into your body 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️

caption:
Mindset Matters 🧠
.
.
Exercise and Nutrition are key to achieving your goals ✅
.
.
But so is mindset and it is an  element very often overlooked 🤔
.
.
For some people mindset is engrained. For me it was. I grew up as an athlete so exercise was a ready made component of my life. I didn't 'decide' when to exercise, it was decided for me. If I didn't eat right, I didn't perform well, I didn't make the team - the main goal. I trained with like minded people. So you could say things were easier for me. 🤷‍♀️
.
.
Easier than say:
- An overweight lady struggling her whole life to lose weight. Uncomfortable with her body but too uncomfortable to start exercising. Feeling tired and lethargic and her only support network is people in a similar situation who shame her into saying this is ok and normal.

- A skinny man who wants to add some muscle. He drinks a lot and dabbles in drugs. His friends are all the same and think he would be wasting money going to a pt. 
.
.
Without the right mindset and the right support network exercise and nutrition may just be too hard to sustain 🤷‍♀️
.
.
I work with athletes. But I also work with mothers who have never put themselves first. I work with women who have struggled their whole life with weight. I work with girls who are desperately anxious about how they look. Giving them a nutrition and exercise plan would be USELESS without educating them or helping them with the real WHY!!! 
.
.
I am so overwhelmingly happy to have so many amazing people on board at the moment. People who truely want to change their health for the better ❤
.
.
If you are one of these people DM me interested and we'll organise a call 😊🙌

📸 @marceauphotography

caption:
Now look I totally understand some people simply cannot afford non essentials...
.
.
But honestly, a lot of the time it does come down to priorities. 🙏
.
.
I spent over $200 yesterday and I know there are others out there that do the same on a weekly basis 🤔 But yet they think an investment into their health is too expensive? 🤔
.
.
I heard another person say their friends don't understand why they 'waste' money on a life coach? 😔 
.
.
Your health and wellness should never be seen as an expense but an investment 🙏

Did you know I'm actually a pre and post partum Coach?
.
.
Emma reaped the rewards from my knowledge. Maybe you could too 🤔

January Diet as difficult as the Assault Bike? 🙈😭
.
.
Why put yourself through that torture YET AGAIN? 
.
.
Another year, another failed new you 😵
.
.
My clients were back on coaching calls with me on Monday to talk about their plans going into January. They laid down markers over Christmas which makes January a hell of a lot easier and guess what every one of them enjoyed Christmas 🌲🍷🎅🥳
Me too 🙋‍♀️
.
.
You see what my clients and I have in common is a lifestyle choice. One that makes Christmas, holidays and social events PART of our routine. We can enjoy occasions - without guilt. We also don't severly restrict ourselves getting back into normality. We don't do hours of endless cardio to burn extra calories. We simply get back to reality and pick up where we left off ☄☄☄
.
.
Why don't you do yourself a favour this year? Why not make 2021 the year you truely decide to put yourself first? Invest in your health and stop starting over 🙌
.
.
It'll be the best decision you've ever made 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️

📸 @marceauphotography

I absolutely hate comparisons...they are the absolute thief of joy 😞
.
.
I used to compare myself all the time. Still do at times, it's only natural 🤷‍♀️
.
.
But I always assess my comparison. It's always fitness related 🙈 If I see someone fitter or stronger than me, I question how? It's an internal conversation....
.
.
More often than not it's one of 2 options.
1. They train more than me.
2. They have been training longer than me.
.
.
This is what it comes down to.
.
. 
NOT:
❌They take supplements I need
❌They eat a specific diet I need to eat
❌They do any fancy training I need to do
.
.
No they have simply been doing it longer or do it more often ✔ 
Basic and simple consistency ✔
.
.
Start falling in love with boring because guess what? That's what gets results ✅

.
.

2020 was the year I: 
.
.

✅Travelled - So lucky I had the chance to see Asia and Western Austrailia.
✅Moved to Austrailia - the best decision of my life 🙏
✅Raised over 15,000 Aud for charity - 2 fundraisers accumulated to this amazing amount for 2 very worthy charities 🙏
✅Joined Crossfit - It's been in the pipeline for 2 years but I finally did it 🤣
✅ Overcame my fear of driving in a city 🤠
✅ Met new friends - thank you to every new person I have met and has made my experience in Austrailia so incredible.
✅ Became Coach Mc Loone 🤣🤣🤣
- So thankful for the job I am in and the opportunities I have been given especially in the middle of a pandemic.
.
.
Thank you to every single person I have met on route to where I am now. I feel so lucky with where I am in my life 🥰🙏 (Even if I have been a moody bitch the past few days😅). 
.
.
Happy Christmas to everyone 🌲🎅
.
.
Don't forget to check in on everyone. Some people may be seriously struggling, even the ones you think are strong.
.
.
Here's to making 2021 the best one yet 🤞🥳
