caption:
Training with your cycle 🥵💪
.
.
Firstly, I have not added in weeks so you can go get researching yourself 😜 If you don't already know.
.
Secondly, please be aware all cycles are different and the advice I give is general. 
.
.
I had a story up the other day about my own experience. And so many of you wanted to know more. Now luckily I am in a position where I have control over my training. I can reduce frequency and intensity when I need to. If you are an athlete, you may find this more difficult. But I cannot recommend enough to train with your body as opposed to against it. You should be able to speak to a coach or trainer about training intensity at different times. 
.
.
This really could be a game changer for your training and your overall body composition. 💪💪💪
.
.
#knowyourcycle

caption:
Not drinking IS COOL!!!! 😍
.
.
So is drinking, if that's what you choose to do 🍻 (as long as it's not negatively affecting your health)
.
.
I was so disappointed by how many people replied to my story saying they feel pressure to drink 😢
.
.
So what I have to say to this:
.
1. If you decide to not drink, don't mind other people's opinions. It has absolutely NO impact on them if you don't drink but it could negatively impact you (for whatever reason you have decided). 
.
2. Your goals will not always be the same as everyone else's. It's not that those people are trying to be rude, they just don't understand so don't take it too personally.
.
3. If you are one of the people saying 'Ah sure one won't hurt' - just think before you say it. I definitely was one of these in the past. But I've learned that sometimes we don't know or need to know why people chose not to drink.
.
.
Whatever you do just be kind. Be respectful of people's wishes. You have no right to question people on their reasoning - they deserve to have a choice. And same goes for sober Sallys - no judgement as long as people are consuming alcohol in a healthy manner 🙏
.
.
Opinions and experiences welcome 
⬇️⬇️⬇️

caption:
These people are why I love Crossfit ❤
.
.
#crossfitchristmasparty #swipeleftforlevelsofdrunk

Let's clear something up... 
.
.
There is no perfect form of coaching ❎
Or perfect form of exercise ❎
.
.
Each style has it's pros and cons 😈
.
.
But it is the form that you can consistently work with and that give you long term sustainable results - that works for you. That does not mean it works for everyone 🤔
.
.
Let me give you some scenarios.
.
.
One of my current online clients first approached me for in person PT. She didn't know I lived in Austrailia 🙈🤣 She wasn't interested in online coaching due to wasting money on previous online programmes. This lady works 2 jobs and barely has time for herself let alone fitting into a PT schedule. Online coaching was a great option for her. She is currently at her goal weight 11 weeks into the programme 🥳
.
.
I have a friend who tried online coaching...twice. First time went well, second time not as well. Nothing wrong with the programme, she just responds better to in person accountability. She is now doing in person PT and loving it 🥳
.
.
There's nothing special about Crossfit. It's more the community and the vibe than the exercise prescription people enjoy. 
.
.
Running may be an excellent form of exercise for an introvert but an extrovert might find it very isolating...
.
.
My point?
1. Just because Sharon got results from a PT does not mean that PT has extraordinary powers. This form of coaching got Sharon results because it was something she CONSISTENTLY did and could stick to.
2. There is no right or wrong coaching style - just what works for you. 
3. Please find something you enjoy and can see yourself doing for the next 50 years 🙏 As opposed to hating exercise, see it as a blessing 👏
.
.
I'd love to hear some of your experiences
⬇️⬇️⬇️

caption:
❤𝓛𝓸𝓿𝓲𝓷𝓰 𝓽𝓱𝓮 𝓼𝓴𝓲𝓷 𝔂𝓸𝓾'𝓻𝓮 𝓲𝓷 ❤
.
.
A client said to me the other day.
'I'm really happy with how things are going. I don't think I'll ever love everything about myself but I'm in a much better place about my body'. I also don't feel guilty about food anymore.'
.
.
Same client in October (direct quote):
'I just feel ugly and probably compare myself too much to other people.'
.
.
2 months of healing. 2 months of working on her relationship with food. 2 months of enjoying the process. 
.
.
Imagine where she will be in 2 years? 🤔🤔🤔
.
.
I can tell you where because that client of mine was me. And I didn't have help. I didn't have guidance. It took me a hell of a lot longer because I did it alone.
.
.
I feel like sometimes being confident is mistaken for being cocky. Being happy in the skin you're in is not about thinking you are better or more beautiful than anyone else. 
.
.
👉 It's smiling - not because you have perfect teeth but because you have teeth
👉 It's about having a photo taken of yourself - not for the bloody gram 😔
👉 It's about knowing your body will never be perfect - because perfection does not exist
👉 It's understanding food is fuel 
👉 It's finding that exercise you love and enjoying it
👉 It's about comparing you to you - nobody else 🚫
.
.
It's a journey and a process but the final destination is an amazing one 🙏❤ 
.
.
If you want help in finding that inner confidence and finally achieving internal happiness. Dm me 'Get Started'.

#confidenceisbeautiful

caption:
***Soppy Post Alert*** 
.
.
I signed up to do @thetribalthrowdown in August and was so excited to do my first ever intermediate comp 🥳
.
.
The very next day I dislocated my left knee cap.
.
.
The first day I went to physio, I asked him would I be able to compete. He said: 'We'll use it as a goal'. I wasn't too optimistic 😢🙈
.
.
12 weeks later. There was a change to the structure due to lockdown but Ryan and the gang handled it brilliantly. I completed every wod and minus a terrible wod 1, I am absolutely delighted with how it went. Beyond proud to have achieved my initial goal of top 10 😭
.
.
As proud as I am of myself, I'm even prouder of the AMAZING ladies who did this comp with me. And massive congrats @szczygielklimska outright winning the comp 💪Solidifying my love for Crossfit and the people involved in it.
.
.
Thank you @thetribalthrowdown. I'm sure this has helped people over the last 4 weeks more than youll even know.
.
.
Bring on the next one ❤

#postinjury #crossfitcompetition #onlinecompetition

caption:

.
.
Try and stick to something for longer than a week. 🤦‍♀️ 
.
.
There is no magic potion. There is no perfect training plan. 
.
.
You can spend all the money and time in the world but unless you are consistent, you're wasting your time 🙊

Is the environment you are in or the people in your life helping towards your goals? 🤔
.
.
This is often an element people overlook when it comes to forming habits 😬🙊 And it can have a huge impact on your results. 
.
.
Here's some examples:
.
👉 You're trying to reduce your alcohol consumption for your health but all your friends drink every night. They consider it normal and you are ABNORMAL for trying to limit it. YOLO 😜
.
👉 You're trying to cut down on takeaways in a bid to lose weight but your partner is constantly ordering them. YOLO 🙊
.
👉 You're trying to exercise more and have started working with a coach. Your parents call you obsessed 😑
.
👉 You're trying to reduce sugary snacks but the kids treats are calling to you from the kitchen cupboards 🤦‍♀️
.
.
This is where you need to start thinking about YOUR goals. How important they are to YOU. You may even need to have a talk with friends and family about how important this is and that you'd appreciate their support ❤🙏
.
.
I have been very lucky that my environment always suited my goals. My Dad, sister and friends were involved in sport and understood the importance of it to me. They understood social occasions were harder for me and they were supportive of my choices. My friends and family initially found it strange that I brought Tupperware with me everywhere 😅 But it soon became the new norm 🙏 I am a result of my environment. The people I chose to associate with. The actions I choose on a daily basis. I want them to support my lifestyle not take away from it 👍
.
.
If you feel your environment is not supporting your goals, you need to take action 💥 It's hard enough to create new habits without everything working against you 🤦‍♀️😅

caption:
What is the key to results? 
CONSISTENCY 🔑
.
.
How do we stay consistent?
Finding something we enjoy and can sustain 🙏
.
.
If you don't see yourself doing it a year from now. It's not sustainable or something you enjoy 🚫
.
.
If you are someone who hates running but your friend Mary lost 2 stone from pounding the pavements so you plan on starting....
Find something else. Please 😑
.
If you love carbs but everyone tells you keto is the best weight loss diet. Keto may not be the best option for you. 🥩
.
If you've never cycled over 5km in your life but you 'want to challenge yourself' and sign up to a triathlon without training. You my friend are a lunatic. 🚴‍♀️
.
.
I'm going to give you a success story. Not a client of mine. But my boyfriend. Owen has been training for years and years. He's dipped in and out. Trained hard 5 days a week for weeks, then nothing. He's never been consistent. During lockdown in March, Owen started coaching with @komplexfitness. Owen is now approximately 7-8 months consistently training (he missed 1 session - due to a severe hangover 😅).
.
Owen is the strongest he's ever been and he looks great. Why?
- He enjoys his training. 
- He can fit it into his lifestyle. 
- Kevin is obviously an alright coach 😜😅
.
.
Be like Owen. Find something you like. Something you can sustain. And something that helps get you to your goals 💪

caption:
How big is your glass? 🤔
.
.
People can't believe it when I tell them I've only consistently been doing Crossfit since March. 
.
.
What they don't see is the 6 years of CONSISTENT strength training. The 18 years of football training. My capacity is big. I've been training for a long time. 
.
.
I wouldn't say I'm a keg now but I've a pretty big glass. The bigger the glass, the easier everything becomes. It's the reason a balanced lifestyle is easier for me than Mary who needs to lose a stone. My glass is bigger. Therefore, my lean muscle mass is bigger. Therefore, this has a positive impact on my BMR. Hence, I can eat chocolate and get away with it while Mary just needs to look at Chocolate and she has gained 2lbs. 
.
.
Work on making the glass bigger. Everything else will come 🙏
.
.
#strengthtraining #resistancetraining #howbigisyourglass

caption:
If scales is the only measure of progress you're using, you are are going down a slippery slope. ⛰
.
.
What happens if you don't lose weight one week? Does it undo all the hard work you've done? All the consistent effort you've made. All the new habits you've built. Or what if your weight plateaus? Does this mean you quit and give up? 🤷‍♀️
.
.
We are all impatient humans. And we want to be rewarded for our hard work. And that's fair. But success does not happen overnight in any industry so why would weight loss be different. 🚫
.
.
Consistency is key. Finding a method that works for your goals but that you also enjoy - making it sustainable. And don't forget about all the good habits you are making. If you made one good habits each week for a year, that'd be 52 good habits. ✅ Keep up the great work 🥳

#slowprogressisbetterthannoprogress

Start Taking Responsibility for your actions 👈👈👈
.
.
If you are not where you want to be, it is NO One else's fault but yours.
.
.
🚫Stop blaming friends and family members 
🚫Stop blaming gyms and exercise methods
🚫Stop blaming diet approaches 
🚫Stop blaming coaches
🚫Stop blaming time restrictions
🚫Stop blaming money limitations
.
.
You are ultimately the problem. You HAVE to take part in your own rescue 🛶
.
.
🔊Before trying yet another diet or another exercise method or another trainer. Why not stick with something? Not for 6 weeks or 6 months. Why not try 6 years?
.
.
💥💥💥
I am not where I want to be. But I am a hell of a lot closer than I was 2 years ago. If you want to compare yourself to me, why not compare these stats:
👉 I have been playing intercounty football for over 10 years
👉 I have on average been in the gym 4 days a week for over 6 years. That is 1300 gym sessions. 
👉 I have drank 2L water at least 95% of the time for the last 10 years.
👉 I have a healthy balanced diet - no extremes of diet and binge - for about 6 years (not including the picky years 😅)
👉 Up until this year, I have drank very IRREGULARLY.
💥💥💥
.
.
So unless thats comparable to you. Stop comparing yourself. I was considered a semi professional athlete. I made HUGE sacrifice to get to the fitness level I am at right now (and I still want to be a hell of a lot fitter).
.
.
Comparison is the thief of joy. Stay in your own lane. Be patient. And bloody stick to something long term 😅🙈

caption:
🌟Let's talk periods and training 🌟
.
.
Firstly, I am so happy with how normal it now is to talk about periods 🙏 Secondly, having a period is such a good thing and I think until you've lost it, you'll never realise how good it is to have it. (P.s I've never lost mine. Just through client's experiences)
.
.
I'm going to start off with the fact that until this week I have never ever followed the information I'm about to give you. But after my nightmare training week last week, I promise my body I will now train WITH my cycle and not against 🙌 I'm pretty happy I have an excuse as to why my performance was so poor last week 😅🙈
.
.
So here are just some of the things going on within your body:

Follicular Phase

● Increase in estrogen = increase in strength
● Increase in pain threshold
● Increase in insulin sensitivity = increased efficiency in burning carbs
● Muscle recovers well = get training

Ovulation Phase

● Increase in all hormones including testosterone
● Up to 11% increase in strength
● Increase in estrogen
● Increase in metabolism = increase in appetite 
● Water retention & bloating can occur

Luteal Phase

● Decrease in estrogen & progesterone
● Decrease in serotonin = PMS starts to kick in
● Increase in water retention
● Increase in body temperature
● Decreased quality in sleep
● Craving sugar
● Not a good time to do measurements
● Best to avoid max training / PB’S

Menstrual Phase

● PMS starts to subside
● Experience cramping
● Reduction in body temperature
● Increase in energy
● Insulin sensitivity starts to increase
.
.
Taper your training to your cycle. It doesn't mean you have to lie in bed for 2 out of 4 weeks. Sometimes it's hard to talk to a coach or trainer about these things but you HAVE to listen to your body.
.
.
I have tried for too long to think I am invincible. That I can train hard 365 days a years. It's BS. And at almost 30 I am finally starting to realise I need to listen to my body and my cycle. Thankfully I copped on before losing it 🙏❤
.
.
#trainingaroundyourcycle

.

Let's stop buying into fads 🚫
.
.
You do not need Apple Cider Vinegar, Laxative Teas or Waist trainers. Please spend and invest your money in good wholesome food and a trainer. ⚠️
.
.

.
.
If you enjoy HIIT training, do it. If you are doing it solely to lose weight and hate it, there are a lot easier ways ⛔
.
.
We overcomplicate weight loss. 
Majority of it is down to self control, mindframe and consistency. 🙏
.
.
If you can't do it alone, invest in someone who can help. But please stop waiting your time with the above in hope that you achieve miracle results 🙈
.
.
Dm me if I can help 🙏🌟

First Austrailian CrossFit Comp 🌟
.
.
This wasn't my first rodeo. I was more excited about seeing everyone else's wins than I was about seeing my own 😅 Like @orlac_fit 36 Pull ups mid wod 🥳🥳🥳 Or people thrusting 20kg more than they expected. The max cal row was outstanding and the encouragement and vibe this morning was exactly everything I could have expected and hoped for ❤ Well done to each and everyone involved especially those who were pushed WAY outside comfort zones today 💪
.
.
I'm also pretty proud of my knee 🦵 8 weeks post dislocation, currently training 7 days a week and about to start a 4 week comp. 💪 .
.
.
Body thank you every single day for pushing beyond boundaries I never even knew exsisted 🙏
.
.
P.s Outfits were totally accidental 😅

caption:
💥 Name Change 💥
.
.
Old news I know 🤣
.
.
I got so many people asking why? 
.
.
So here it is. 
.
.
When I started in the fitness industry, I was a footballer. I actually wanted it to be cleanandleangaagirl but a friend veered me away from it saying it'd narrow my audience. 7 years ago I ate super clean. I still believe in natural wholefoods, I am still a huge advocate but I don't eat clean full time 🤣 I'm much more about that balanced lifestyle. Finally, being lean is NOT important to me anymore. It's not a goal, it's not something I work towards and it's not a word I want associated with me.
.
.
Where do I see myself now?
I see myself as a coach. I truely believe I have helped a lot of people over the last 7 years. I've helped people in A LOT of ways. I don't call myself a pt or a nutritionist but a combo of both. I've changed people's lifestyles which to me is a lot more important than any meal plan or training programme I can prescribe. I absolutely love my job. I love helping people and I'm so happy to call this my job. 
.
.
In short, I no longer play sport, I don't eat clean 100% of the time and I'm not worried about being lean 🤣 I am however a coach. A good one at that, and thats what I want to be recognised as 😁
.
.
#thanksforthesupport

caption:
But that doesnt mean they are unhealthy either.
.
.
I know plenty of very healthy men and women with abs.
.
.
I also know people with abs who would be breathless after walking up 2 flights of stairs 
.
.
My point is you cannot judge a book by it's cover.
.
.
There are so many layers to health and fitness, it cannot just be based on how somebody looks.
.
.
Personally, I'd rather 'be fit' than 'look fit' (or what people THINK fitness looks like)
.
.
What do you think? 🤔

💥Consistent at 80% is better than inconsistent at 100%
.
.
💥Progress over perfection
.
.
💥Stop focusing on the 1% and do the 99% consistently
.
.
Honestly, why do we feel the need to over complicate nutrition so much 🤯
.
.
👉 Please realise everyone is different. What works for you may not work for someone else.
👉 Instead of REMOVING everything (gluten, dairy, etc. Etc.) Start adding in
Water, colour, protein
👉 Counting calories is not essential to weight loss but being in a calorie deficit is.
👉 Food is fuel. Load up on the good stuff, reduce the processed stuff and never deem foods as good or bad.
.
.
It can be as simple as that 🙏🙌
.
.
Tag someone who needs to see this 🙈🙈🙈

caption:
Building Habits 👊👊👊

.

.

This approach has been game changer with my clients. It's slower but so much more sustainable.

.

.

I do it in relation to nutrition,training and mindset.

.

.

Without a doubt, its impact on nutrition is invaluable. It teaches people to slow down when it comes to nutrition. Making them realise its not all about 0 to 100. There are ALOT of numbers in between there 😅 It's simple and relatively easy. 

.

.

Examples include: Drinking 2L water consistently EVERY DAY. Eating vegetables with lunch. Treat every second day. 

.

.

It also works for movement. 10,000 steps daily is a habit. I have clients who nail this daily. And clients who STRUGGLE!!! But having that target helps them move more than without a target. Quite often if I have someone hitting 1000 Steps a day, I won't throw an unrealistic target of 10,000 on their back. Ill start with 2-3k. Hit that for a week great. Increase to 4,000. Hit that EVERY day. Great. Increase again. And so on. NEW HABIT BUILT! You need wins along the way. Otherwise you will quit. Make things achievable.

.

.

Same goes for mindset. Journaling, meditation and reading Are all great habits to work on with clients. 

.

.

Here are some of my habits I'm planning over the next 6 weeks. I've  already nailed the basics so that's why I'm jumping. Please don't jump until youve the basics nailed 😅

.

.

Week 1 - No alcohol ✅

Week 2 - Intermittent Fasting 

Week 3 - Fruit or veggies at every meal

Week 4 -No bread or chocolate

Week 5 - Fizzy drinks only at weekends

Week 6 - Full clean week - No processed food

.
.
#habits #habitsforlife #nutrition #realresults #realnutrition #fitness #eatforhealth #eatforperformance

Pre Deadlift Exercises ✌
.
.
1. Single Leg RDL
2. Banded Good Morning
3. Knight Stretch 
4. Inchworm
. 
.
Preparing my hamstrings and  working on that hinge position are 2 things I focus on pre Deadlift. I also do some sort of upper body activation to get my back muscles ready for the lift, usually some sort of scapula Hang and banded row 👌
.
.
Save if this is something you're interested in 💥💥💥
.
.
#mobility #movementismagic #movebetter #livewell #getstronger #strengthtraining #crossfit #fitness #fitliving #fitfam #irishfitfam

I compare my skin journey with most people's fitness journeys..

I've spent so much time trying to improve it...

Years and years...

I've bought hundreds of cheap products essentially WASTING money...

I've even bought expensive products that were not the right fit for my skin...

I told myself I cared. But really I didn't. I wasn't committed to a regime. When I didn't see results after 6 weeks I would try something different 🙈

I'm 29 and have finally invested in a routine that suits my skin 🙏 But Admittedly i have wasted YEARS of my life trying to rectify this situation myself...

I couldnt do it by myself.. I tried...

For years...

Sound familiar to your fitness journey? 
❌Trying for years and STILL not where you want to be?❌

Speaking from experience, it's not necessarily the most expensive product but the product that works for you. You NEED to give it time. Doing it alone without knowledge WILL NOT work... I am speaking from experience.

I spent years hating my skin. Uncomfortable in it. But doing NOTHING about it. Stop doing that in your body 🚫

Dm Me for help ❤

caption: Opinions? 🤔

Sometimes the world scares me 😔
.
.
Nothing to do with this pandemic. But just our day to day lives 😔
.
.
On Saturday I got Owen to take a picture of me with a white light on me just to look better 😢 Turned out I actually looked even nicer with no bright light (the above photo). This is common for people, I know. But not for me. I pride myself on NOT being like that. I believe in loving yourself warts and all. I've never used editing apps (I can barely use a filter 😅). But I did this. Why? To get a few extra likes? Maybe a few extra followers? 
THAT IS NOT ME 😭
.
.
Also on Saturday, someone tried to sabotage an event @acountydownunder was organising. Let me explain the nature of the event.
Bringing people together in Sydney from all parts of the world, to be united during these tough times. Can you believe someone could do that? I was appauled😢
.
.
Finally, on Saturday. I met the most incredible bunch of ladies who I would have never met, if it weren't for Facebook and Instagram 🙏
.
.
The point to this post... ?
A lot happened on Saturday 😅
.
.
No.
.
.
Social media and the world today can be an amazing platform for meeting new people, sharing likeminded opinions and general positive messages.
.
.
But there is a nasty side. One that is jealous of other people's success. One that changes you to be someone you are not 😢
.
.
You do have a choice.
.
.
If social media is negatively impacting you. Delete it. If you follow someone who impacts how you feel about yourself, unfollow them.
.
.
I plan on reducing my screen time as I think it's negatively impacting me a little. It doesn't mean I'm leaving - far from it. I just plan on occupying my time with things I've been neglecting like Mobility, Podcasts and reading 🙏
.
.
Use social media for good ❤
.
.
What is your opinion?

caption:
Confidence is sexy ❣

.

.

I can be almost certain if you go on a date with a guy, he doesn't ask what you weigh 🤭 If he does, I dunno if a second date should be on the cards 😅🙈

.

.

Sexiness and body confidence is not:

✖ A number on a scales

✖ A dress size

✖ A certain body fat percentage

✖ Free from cellulite or stretch marks

✖ Filters

✖ Super fit or unfit

✖The loudest or quietest person in the room

✖With make up or without

.

.

Confidence is how you perceive yourself. It's a smile. It's being happy in the clothes your wearing. Happy in the company of others. Comfortable in your relationship. It's being happy in your own skin with and without beauty products. It's exercising and eating well because you want to not becauae you have to.

.

.

Confidence is beautiful ❣
.

.
Confidence is something I really work on with my clients in all elements of their life 👌 It can be a battle and with most it takes weeks to months to instill in them but tthat feeling of self worth and improved self esteem IS LIKE NO OTHER ❤
.
.

caption: Walk slowly but never backward 🙏

Cauliflower Rice vs Brown Rice
.
.
Which is best?
.
.
Answer is.
.
.
Neither are better, neither are worse.
.
.
I eat both. But why you are eating it depends on your goals 👊👊👊
.
.
✅ Weight loss a goal? Cauliflower rice is low in calories and high in volume so may be a great option
✅Alternatively, portion control of brown rice can also work.
✅ Performance a goal? You will not get the same complex carbs from caulifower rice as you will from brown rice. 
✅ Both have different nutritional compositions when it comes to vitamins and minerals.
✅ Taste? Force feeding yourself cauliflower rice because your favourite fitness influencer recommended it? YOU ARE JUST BEING STUPID!!!! 
.
.
There is no right or wrong answer to comparing these. As always, it is dependent on your individual goals and anyone that gives you a clear defined answer is a fruad 😅🚫
.
.
#eatforperformance #eatforhealth #nutrition #nutritionist #fitness #irishfitness #irishinoz #irishinsydney #fitlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Hangover Hacks 🤢🤢🤢
.
.
I've had a fair few of them over here 🙈 I'm a social butterfly at the moment🦋 😅 These are some of my ways to combat them, so you can still stay social and not ruin all your progress 🙋‍♀️
.
.
1. Pre plan your food. THIS IS 90% OF PEOPLE'S downfall....
They order takeaway or uber eats. Or both...twice. That craving can be satisfied with a homemade pizza
Or taco chips or even a ready made my muscle chef meal 🤗 Stop ruining your progress because you're eating like an asshole after alcohol.
.
.
2. Sleep as much as you can that night. Enough said. 😴
.
.
3. Drink 2L water. Seems very obvious. But how many of us actually do it? Add an electrolyte. Add cordial if you don't like water. Make it a soda water? I don't care just get 2L in 💦
.
.
4. If you do want a fizzy drink, please for the love of God don't waste your calories on the sugary options. At least have sense to go for a 0 Cal alternative 🤦‍♀️
.
.
5. Move. It doesn't have to be a gym session. It doesn't need to be intense. Aim for your 10,000 steps or a little ocean swim. Your body will thank  you  for it 🙏
.
.
If all else fails, just go on the rollover...
.
.
Lol, jk 😜🤭

#hangoverhacks #socialbutterfly #dontwasteallyourhardworkattheweekend #balance #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitness #irishfitness #irishfitfam

caption:
Training with an injury?
.
.
I had a poll on this a few weeks ago and a majority of people voted they agree with it.
.
.
Lets be totally clear on the context. It was training WITH an injury. Not training THROUGH an injury. Very different. 
.
.
However, it is not uncommon to train through an injury either. I want to be clear here. I am NOT telling you to train with an injury. This is very individual dependent and requires advice from a professional I.e Doctor, physio etc.
.
.
✅Training with an injury

👉 Anyone who knows me, knows how much of an advocate I am of this. When I injure lower body, upper body is still very much manageable, however, I am careful not to put too much pressure on affected area

👉 Mental Health - I don't know about the rest of you but mental health is one of my main reasons for training so if I had to sit still I'd cry 😩

👉 Socialising - It can be a tough time going through an injury. If you are a sports player it can be so isolating 😢 Being able to do something in th gym, in a class or with your team can have a huge impact on your mindframe ❤

➡️ Training through an injury

🚫 Only do under advice from your healthcare professional (But a little bit of important info is there actually is evidence to suggest you can)

✅ Nutrition with an injury
⛔ Most overlooked aspect of recovery in my opinion

👉 Fats are anti inflammatory and a vital part of the healing process 

👉 Protein as ALWAYS is King 🤴

👉 Calories will need to be adjusted for activity levels

➡️Remember Recovery does not just mean 'rest

Would love to hear your experiences?

caption:
❤I love feeling fit and strong
.
.
❤I love that I can bench with the boys 
.
.
❤I love when randomers say to me 'You're a beast'😅
.
.
❤I love when people are kind of afraid of your training level 😅
.
.
❤I love the feeling of pushing yourself to be better every single day.
.
.
❤As annoying as it can be, I love that my body doesn't have a clear size anymore. I can range from a 6 to a 12, a small to a large 😅 It feels so good to not let a number define me.

But I also love:

💕To dress up at the weekend

💕To go out for dinner with Owen

💕To enjoy drinks with friends

It doesn't HAVE to be one or the other.

It doesn't HAVE to be so hard.

You can have your cake and eat it.

But maybe you just need help? Maybe you need to be nicer to yourself? Maybe you need to be educated? Maybe you need support. Maybe you need to train less? Maybe you need to train more?
.
.
Why keep playing the guessing game? 
Decide now to take control of your life
👊👊👊

caption:
My non negotiables the day after drinking:
.
👊 10,000 Steps. You don't need to make a workout. You don't have to move fast. Just move.
👊 2L water - minimum 
👊 No sugar filled drinks - if I want something fizzy I go for a sugar free alternative
👊 Don't eat like an asshole. You don't NEED 10,000 calories the next day. Try get back to a normal routine. It doesn't have to be kale smoothies but get your  normal rotuine back. Decent breakfast, protein in every meal and lots of micros.
.
.
The day after drinking doesn't have to be perfect. But just stay consistent. A lot of my clients love to socialise and want to be able to incorporate it into their lifestyle. It doesn't have to be totally detrimental to your goals. But do be aware it will have an impact. It's your choice, own it 😜 

#hangovers #howtogetbackontrack #dontwasteyourwholeweekend #bankholidayweekend #tips #fitness #fitfam #irishfitfam #irishinoz #irishinsydney

I scream, you scream, we all scream for Ice cream 🍨🍦
.
.
Especially ice cream that aligns with our goals 😍
.
.
Remember, it's not about eliminating everything you like out of your diet. Instead why not make smarter choices 🙌 This way you have a less likelihood of binging 🙏 
.
.
I always encourage my clients to have treats but just choose wisely. I educate them on calories and how to work treats into their life. I help heal their relationship with food and the guilt associated with 'bad foods'. 
.
.
If you are interested in becoming more educated. Pm me SAS. ❤
.
.
#smartchoices #healthylifestyle #healthybodyhealthymind #balance #nutrition #nutritionist #nutritioneducation #irishinoz #irishinsydney

caption:
Expressing gratitude 🙏

.

.

Mindset is more than half the battle when it comes to our goals. Ever hear the saying 'the body achieves what the mind believes '.

.

.

I firmly believe a positive attitude helps the body and mind in more ways than you can even imagine 🙏

.

.

Begin each day with something positive. This sets your body and mind up for the whole day

.

.

My morning Ritual:

💥 NOT snoozing my alarm - when my phone buzzes at 5am. I am up with bells on. (Yes I am an annoying morning person)

💥I have my  bag packed and breakfast made from the night before - so I am organised and not rushing and racing

💥My morning coffee - unfortunately I dont get the time to sit on social media and reflect on my morning coffee thoughts 😅 (but i still have them)

💥Morning bootcamps or client coaching calls start my day the right way

.

.

I find things i am grateful for EVERY SINGLE DAY. I may not jot them down but I have them. (If it's not already obvious this man is certainly one of them 💕)

.

.

Something I get my clients to do is physically write them down. 3 a day. It can be something as simple as morning coffee to being proud you've overcome cancer. Its relative to you. No one else.

.

.

Try it for a week and see the difference in your attitude.

.

.

If you are not willing to work on your mind, good luck working on your overall health 🚫

#overallhealth #healthybodyhealthymind #mentalhealth 
#attitudeiseverything 
#pma 
#positivity
#positivementalattitude
#gratitude

caption:

This is nothing new. In fact, at least 90% of my clients initially come to me with poor self esteem and distorted visions of themselves 😢😩
.
.
When I first got into the health and fitness industry 7 years ago, I had the same issues. It has taken years of self talk, mindfulness and even therapy to help me 🙋‍♀️ When I first started in the industry, I handed people nutrition plans and training plans with no follow up or contact ever again. I wasn't being lazy or greedy but I lacked knowledge and experience. 
.
.
7 years on and I can safely say coaching to me is actually a lot more mental than physical. Yes, I provide nutrition advice and training plans but I work very hard with my clients to improve their mental attitude and mindset 🤗
.

👉👉👉I have been you ladies out there who struggle with self esteem

.
👉👉👉I have spent years and a lot of money investing in my mental health and mindset

💥But now I feel how empowering it is to be comfortable in your own skin. I feel how incredible it is to not feel guilty about eating food. I now look in the mirror and instead of picking out every fault, I feel strong💥

caption:
Variety is the spice of life 🌶🌶🌶

.

.

So one of the things I harp on about constantly as a nutritionist is trying to get more vegetables in my client's diet 🥦🥒🍄

.

.

But did you know how you cook your veggies can have an impact on it's nutritional status? For example: when boiling vegetables you may lose a lot of the vitamins in the water. Roasting vegetables can actually change the glycaemic index of a food. And any cooking method  can cause loss of fibre from the vegetables.

. 

.

What does this mean?

Get a variety of vegetables in your diet. And a variety of different cooking methods 

E.g A salad for lunch and roast veggies for dinner

Or Raw Spinach for breakfast and a stirfy for lunch

👉👉👉Tag someone who eats the same food constantly 🙈

#eatforhealth
#eatforperformance 
#health 
#fitfood
#eatyourveggies
#fitness
#fitliving
#fitfam 
#irishinoz 
#irishfitfam

Sunday thoughts 💭💭💭
.
.
Why do we only think about everything in the short term?

- Body Appearance

- Health  

- Alcohol and diet

- Drugs

- Having the latest brands

- Photos for the gram

What do all of the above have in common? We focus on the short term and not long term. 

Examples:

The long term effects of yo yo dieting on the body. 
.
Alcohol/Drugs/Poor food choices all evoke a short term satisfaction that long term can lead to serious health implications. 
.
Living beyond your means and 'having the latest trends' can have you in serious debt long term.
.
I actually know of people with the perfect Instagram account who are suffering from Depression
.
Does the future ever enter your mind?

#wellness #shortterm #letsstartthinkingmorelongterm 
#fitness #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #irishfitfam

Physical Results are great 💯👌
.
.
But it's the changes you can't see that really makes me love my job ❤❤❤
.
.
When this lady said to me:
 'She started being nicer to herself' I almost cried. I cannot explain what a breakthrough that was.
.
.
Then, she said 'She was proud of herself' 😢 I nearly lost my shit. 
.
.
14 weeks later she is still learning to love herself, enjoy the process and be the strongest, sassiest version of herself 👏🤗
.
.
Proud is an understatement 💯💯💯

#onlinecoach #onlineclients #strongandsassy #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #realresults #realnutrition #fitness #fitliving #balancedlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

It's ok to want to lose weight. It's ok to want to lose body fat. 
.
.
It's not ok to think it's a necessity 🚫

#healthylifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #goals #fitness #fitliving #balance #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
💣The gym shark controversy validated what I have been saying for the last few years.
.
.
💥Fitness is no longer about being fit but rather 'looking fit'💥
.
.
💯When I became a trainer, I too was obsessed with the quest for the perfect body. Small waist, big bum, abs..
.
.
💢Not necessarily because I actually wanted these things but because thats what i thought being 'fit' was. I associated fitness with aesthetics and beauty. And let's call a spade a spade, most fitness influencers look flawless at all times. 
I could have easily ended up going down this route. On the constant search for beauty and perfection.
.
.
💢But I enjoyed 'being fit' too much. Being fit includes: inappropriate sweat patches, a red face and HARD WORK!!! While others focused on their booty poses and dieted until they see 'perfect abs' , I got fitter. And Fitter. And now, im the fittest Ive ever been (injury and all)
.
.
🚫Im very disappointed at how 'fitness' has turned into a beauty contest because that is NOT what it is. Fitness comes in all shapes and sizes with varying different levels. 
.
.
⚠️I remember a time when I was a teenager where fitness was just associated with how aerobically fit you were? How strong you were? How fast you were? How much you've progressed and improved?
I'd like to go back to this.⚠️
.
.
Can we please make fitness normal again❓❓❓

caption:
Yesterday's breakfast was next level delicious 😍🤩
.
.
What I see:
👉 Carbs - sourdough bread
👉 Fats - avocado, goats cheese, haloumi
👉 Protein - goats cheese, haloumi
👉 Vitamins and minerals
.
.
What someone else may see:
👆 Healthy Breakfast
. 
.
What someone doing weight watchers may see:
👆 A lot of 'syns'
.
.
What someone counting macros and calories may see:
💣 A lot of calories 
.
.
Remember, food is different for everyone. Everyone's goals are different. What's 'right' for one person may be 'detrimental' to another person. Not everybody has a good relationship with food. Actually from my experience, most people have a terrible relationship with food. 
.
.
So I suggest, unless someone asks for help or advise; refrain from commenting on people's food habits. You have no idea what can of worms you may be opening up.
.
.
If you want to heal your relationship with food and understand nutrition better pm me 😁

caption:
#balance
'𝐓𝐨 𝐠𝐢𝐯𝐞 𝐬𝐞𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐚𝐥 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐬 𝐞𝐪𝐮𝐚𝐥 𝐚𝐦𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐭𝐬 𝐨𝐟 𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐨𝐫𝐭𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐞, 𝐭𝐢𝐦𝐞 𝐨𝐫 𝐦𝐨𝐧𝐞𝐲 𝐒𝐨 𝐭𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐚 𝐬𝐢𝐭𝐮𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐢𝐬 𝐬𝐮𝐜𝐜𝐞𝐬𝐬𝐟𝐮𝐥'
.
.
Balance isn't always about an 80/20 rule. Balance isn't the same for every one. 
.
.
Sometimes balance is bloody hard. It took me years to find balance. And now I still question if I have it. Instead of being too strict, am I now being to lenient?

.
.
Balance can cause anxiety for people. 
.
.
How are some people able to eat pizza and still remain lean? I eat 100% clean and still can't see changes? 😢 Do I have enough protein in my diet? Do I drink too much? Is low calorie Ice cream or no ice cream the best option? How many steps should I be taking? What exercise is best? Is rest important?
.
.
My opinion: If it works towards your goals, do it. If not, don't!!!
.
.
There is no right or wrong. Just what's right for you 👆 

#fitness #fitliving #health #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
And in the red corner... Weighing in at 71kg... Amanda Mc Loone 🥊🥊🥊
.
.
Currently sitting at my heaviest EVER weight. I don't actually normally weigh myself but I had to get it done for something.
.
.
If I used scale weight to objectify my progress I think it's safe to say I'd be pretty darn disappointed 😂 But I don't.
.
.
A scale weight does not determine my worth. It doesn't signify how fit I am. It doesn't show how strong I am (it does however make it harder to do pull ups 🙈). It doesn't have any relevance to how hard I work or my job. So why would I let one number determine my happiness?
.
.
Those extra few kilos are the memories I've made. Those extra few kilos are the weekends that I've enjoyed more than ever before. Those extra few kilos are able to lift some extra weight.
.
.
So please, before you let a scale number determine your happiness, think about what that number actually means. To me, it means freedom. 🙌

#weightisjustanumber
#healthisyourwealth
#healthyishappy
#balance
#strong
#strongwomen

caption:
Attitude is everything 👊👊👊
.
.
It’s not about being positive and motivated constantly. It’s about turning up and being consistent even when you don’t want to be 🤕
.
.
Last week was a nightmare for me. Honestly, I am probably the fittest I’ve ever been. I had signed up for City to Surf and an online CrossFit comp at the end of October and what happens!? I dislocate my bloody knee 😩🙈 
.
.
Damage done on the Wednesday. Balled crying Wednesday night. DID NOT emotionally eat. Stuck to the plan. And I was back in the gym Thursday 💪🤟🏼 
.
.
My nutrition is absolutely key 🔑 I am a firm believer the reason I have bounced back from injuries previously is due to my nutrition ✅ 
.
.
Where did I get this attitude from?! I got it from my Daddy ❤️ My poor Dad suffered for the last 18 months of his life and you would never know it, because he never complained ❤️🥺 His attitude showed me important the right attitude can be 🤗🥰
.
.
So for now, I’m goblet squatting 10kg to a ball. But soon, I’ll be back where I was. And further 😉 
.
.
I hope this motivates someone else today 🙏🏻

#thecomebackwillbegreaterthanthesetback 
#injuries
#crossfit
#squats
#fitness
#attitudeiseverything

Upper Body 'Bro' session ✌
.
.
Just so thankful I can still train. Gonna use it as an opportunity to work on my weaknesses like strict Pull Ups and Hspus. 🙏
.
.
30 min Bike
.
.
Goblet Squats 3 x 10
.
A1. Pull Ups 3 x 5

B1. Inverted Row 3 x 8
B2. Bent Over Row 3 x 10

C1. Hammer Curls 3 x 12
C2. Tricep Pulldowns 3 x 10

D1. Leg Raises 3 x 10
D2. Russian Twist 3 x 40
.
.
10 min Bike
.
.
Save if your looking for some inspo. But be aware doing random unstructured sessions are probably NOT the best option for progression. Thats why I don't post them very often 🙈😅
.
.
Happy Friday 🥳🥳🥳

.
.
Don't knock it till you've tried it 👊
.
.
I've been hit with obstacles this week and many reasons to emotional eat but I've stayed strong. I feel better when I eat better so I decided to even improve my sweet treats 😊
.
.
Carob tastes similar to chocolate but is naturally caffeine free with low amounts of fat and sugar. It also contains fibre and antioxidants. It has twice the amount of calcium than cocoa and contains potassium, magnesium and B group vitamins 😊 
.
.
A lot of you may have tried choc shot before. Thats made from carob. You probably won't find it innthe supermarkets but may need to head to a health food shop 😝 
.
.
What are your favourite healthier alternatives? 🤔
.
.
#carob #sweettreats #balance #health #fitness #eatforperformance #eatforhealth #nutrition #nutritionist #fitfam #irishfitfam #irishinsydney

caption:
💥Mobility💥
.
.
👉Don't use it, you lose it.
.
.
I don't talk about mobility much. I don't post about it. It's not very visually appealing. It definitely won't get as many likes or shares as me in a bikini or a swim suit for that matter 😅🤪
.
.
But it bloody matters... 
.
.
❎ Can't touch your toes? Keep trying.
❎ Can't go below parallel in a squat? Keep squatting.
❎ Working at a desk with aches and pains. It takes 10 minutes.
❎ Lower back issues or hip problems? Have you tried this. 
❎ Guess what running in NOT bad for your knees. The WAY you are running is bad for your knees.
❎ Ever tried to do physio rehab. It's BLOODY HARD!!! 
.
.
My new goal is to get back to my previous 30 minute sessions daily. Its pretty manageable 10 mins in the am, 10 mins pre gym and 10 mins in the evening. I just have to stop making excuses. I use the @gowod_mobilityfirst app👌😁

caption:
💫You are NOT super human💫
.
.
And that's ok
.
.
This week has been crap. 
.
.
I don't know if it's post holiday blues? PMS? Lack of recovery? Too much crappy food or alcohol at the weekend? Homesick?
.
.
All I know is I'm sitting here on Friday evening, knee deep in chocolate, crying at soppy programmes. I've taken more rest days than trained. And my skin is currently in the worst condition I've seen it in a long time 😑
.
.
It has been a crap week. 
.
.
My mood may improve tomorrow. It may take until Monday. But it will improve. And I will get back to normality. 
.
.
We all have bad weeks. We all struggle. None of us are perfect.
.
.
So here's to non perfection.🙋‍♀️ And allowing ourselves a break. Physically and mentally. 💓
.
.
#practicewhatyoupreach

caption:
A high protein diet is optimal no matter what your goals are. Why?
.
.
✅ Protein is essential for recovery especially from exercise, illness or injury
✅ Protein saties you. It gives you a 'fuller' feeling. No matter what your goals, feeling more satisfied is a good thing right?
✅ The Thermic Effect of Protein is high. So it actually contributes to our overall TDEE. This is why a calorie is not just a calorie. Food type and nutrient composition is important 😁
.
.
I recommend 2g/kg BW/day. People find this hard to hit especially without supplements. So here is an idea of what 150g of protein looks like in a day 😊
(P.s I would not recommend tuna everyday due to heavy metals.)
.
.
Tag someone who needs to see this 🤪

#protein #highproteindiet #fitness #goals #fitness #balance #fitliving #fitfam #irishfitfam

Right time to set myself some new goals 🙈🙈🙈
.
.
I'm pretty consistent with my daily routine.
✅ I eat mostly whole, nutritious foods
✅ I train 5-6 days a week
✅ I average 17,000 Steps daily
✅ I drink 3L water (at least)
.
.
My weekends are becoming too enjoyable these days 🤪😅 So while I definitely want some leniancy at weekends, I don't want all my hard work to go to waste to wake up Monday feeling groggy and bloated 😵😵😵 
.
.
My New Habitual Goals:
1. Alcohol once every 3 weeks 
2. Treats every 3-4 days (not daily)
3. Fizzy drinks at weekends only
4. 1 Uber Eats a month
P.s I also think I've signed up for a run 🙈 
. 
My first one and it's 14km 🤪😵 
.
.
To be totally honest, this shouldn't be hard for me. I did this all the time when I lived Ireland. But over here it's very easy to let bad habits creep in 🙈 There's definitely a YOLO approach to life in Sydney 😅 And while I'm constantly striving for 'balance' It's important to me to not tip the scales in the other direction and end up over indulging all the time 🚫🚫🚫
.
.
New Week, new goals, let's do this 💪

#weekendvibes #newgoals #fitness #balance #balancedlifestyle #citytosurf #irishinoz #irishinsydney

caption:
I am a strong woman 🙆‍♀️🙆‍♀️🙆‍♀️
.
.
Yes in the physical sense. I have worked for years to get stronger and build a body I feel confident in. I have consistently trained for the last 10 years. First at intercounty football which then led to my love of strength and resistance training😁 My body is a reflection of that.
.
.
But I am so much stronger than my physique. My mental strength is something you cannot see, but it's much stronger than any weight I could lift. Or any competition I'll do. 
I have gone through more than most will go through in a lifetime. I have had my own share of mental health issues. But I have come out the other side. A true reflection of my mental strength.
.
.
I have worked damn hard to be in the position I am in right now. I said to a client yesterday how lucky I am to have got a job during COVID and how amazing my job, clients and boss are. And she said 'Amanda, you are not lucky. You've worked for this.' She was right. 
.
.
It's an amazing feeling to feel like a strong woman. A strong woman can be intimidating. A strong woman can come off as bossy. A strong woman can get a hostile response especially from the opposite sex. And this is where I acknowledge the strong men in my life. Most notably my Dad was the strongest man I've ever known. Owen has the patience of a saint. And final shout out to the men I've worked with who were not immasculated taking orders from a woman and the bosses I've had who not only considered my opinion but actually valued it. 🙏
.
.
I am a strong woman. Are you?

caption:
It took my Dad dying 5 years ago for me to finally find true happiness...
.
.
Not that I wasn't happy before that. But his death made me question everything. I really went on a journey of self discovery 🙏
.
.
Just because you are living doesn't mean you're truely alive ❤
.
.
So what changed when my Dad died:
1. I appreciated life so much more ❤ Life is precious and a gift.
. 
2. I discovered travel - I always thought I didn't want to travel. I believed I was a home bird and I didn't need it. My trip to Thailand with the girls was a game changer. I cannot thank my friends enough for helping me find travel.
.
3. Fell in love with myself - I was ridiculously self conscious. I don't have good skin so I always covered it up. I don't like my teeth so I wouldn't smile properly in pictures. I stopped focusing on all the negative aspects of my appearance.
.
4. I stopped caring about what people think of me. I remember years ago saying to my sister: how will you cover up those tattoos on your wedding day? And she replied: She loved them and she'll want them to be seen. I had this perception in my head that tattoos were 'unattractive' and should be covered up. I now see them as self expression and see my body as a canvas 🙏
.
5. I stopped working towards what I considered success to be. I remember after college I was so embarrassed that I worked in a restaurant. I was a fully qualified nutritionist working in a restaurant. I believed I was too good to work in that restaurant. Why? Because my peers and societal norms led me to believe I was better than that. I worked so hard for a good Leaving Cert to be top 10 in my school. Why? Because that's what everyone else did. The last few years I have been so content in my work, not because of how much money I earn but because I truely love my job. I don't put pressure on myself to be something I'm not.
.
6. I quit looking for a perfect body - When I was a teenager, I thought skinny was the perfect body type. My early 20s - lean was 'IN'. I now realise there is no such thing as a perfect body. But I'm happy in the one I'm in.
.
7. I stopped comparing myself to people - comparison truely is the thief of joy.
.
Continued in comments

caption:
It's Friday 💥💥💥
.
.
It's the weekend 🎉🎉🎉
.
.
My body and I are very excited to have a weekend off socialising 😅 
My plans:
🤩 Work
🤩 Train
🤩 Yoga 
🤩 New Ink 
🤩 Recouperate 
.
.
What are your plans? Do they align with your goals? Are they getting you closer to where you want to be? Or are they forcing you to take a step back!? 🤔
.
.
Let's think about this. 
.
.
💣If your goal is to get leaner or lose body fat. Are you:
🤥 Eating protein based meals at the weekend
🤥 Drinking 2L+ water daily
🤥 Getting 70,000+ Steps weekly
❓❓❓❓❓❓❓❓❓❓❓❓
.
.
If the answer is no. Don't forget that  the weekend is a NOT a free for all. 
.
.
If you have been tracking calories and have banked some for the weekend. Well done ✅ But if you are just Good Monday to Friday - you are fighting a losing battle. Stop STARTING all over again on Monday. Stop being at war with food, exercise and your body 🚫🚫
.
.
It IS possible to eat chocolate, drink  alcohol and eat food in a nice Restaurant. But you need education. You need to improve your relationship with food. You need to change your mindset.
.
.
I CAN HELP 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️
DM me for details 🤗🤗🤗

caption:
100 Double Unders Baby 🎉🎉🎉
.
.
(They may or may not have all made the cut, damn insta having to make me shorten videos 🐒)
.
.
More importantly swipe left and see where I started. It literally took blood, sweat and tears to get where I am now with my Double Unders 😅 And it took months. Not days or weeks. Months. And I still believe I've a long way to go. But I'm a lot closer than I was this time last year 💪💪💪
.
.
Think of this in relation to your own fitness goals. Think of how much further you could be this time next year? How much stronger? Fitter? Leaner? There's never a perfect time to start!!! But the Main thing I will say is just stay consistent. Initially, you'll be hitting PBs, running faster or being able to move better. There WILL be plateaus. You will get bored at times 🤪🙈Or frustrated or both 🙉
.
.
💥💥But the only way to become excellent is to be endlessly fascinated by doing the same thing over and over again.Fall in love with boredom 💥💥

caption:
Insta vs Reality 🧞‍♀️🧞‍♀️🧞‍♀️
.
.
I think I'm pretty open and honest. Always have been. I might put the odd filter on to make me look more tanned but I actually don't know how to use Photoshop Or Change my appearance to look good for an Insta post 😅🤪 I am not the type of person who dresses in lingerie and poses to make her butt look good. I know I could get 10 times the followers if I sexualised my content. But that is not me, nor the role model I want to be 🙏 
.
.
But even without filters or Photoshop. People look different, in different positions and in different clothes 😬
.
.
Stop killing yourself to look like people on Instagram. People on Instagram don't even look like that in real life 😏 I've seen it first hand. People who are barely recognisable in real life after seeing them on Instagram 😬 Who wants that 🤷‍♀️
.
.
🚫Stop trying to look like someone else. 🚫Stop trying to be someone else.
✅ Be upapologetically you 
✅ There isn't another you. That is your most amazing attribute 
.
.
👋 Hi I'm Amanda. I train hard but also like chocolate. These are the only high waisted shorts that fit me 😅 
.
.
Yes I am red Post workout 🍅😅

caption:
The body is much more complex than comparing it to a bloody scales or seesaw 🙄😑
.
.
This one does really grind my gears. 
'Oh well you're just not in a calorie deficit'
Well you know Sharon it's not always that simple 🤨
.
.
What can also have an impact on total daily energy expenditure:
💥 The type of food you eat - the thermic effect of food has an impact on our TDEE
💥 Endocrine System - hormones and hormonal imbalances can have a huge impact on our TDEE
💥 Chronic Inflammation - due to a number of different things: stress, illness,  poor diet etc
💥 Lack of sleep - Sleep is as important for weight loss as exercise and nutrition - look up the scientific literature
.
.
This does NOT mean calories don't matter. They do. But they're not the only things that matter. This post is to inform you that your body is complex. Much more complex than we think. That's why as a nutritionist my LAST question is actually about nutrition and food. I get a full insight into people's whole lives. It's not always as simple as a calculation unfortunately.
.
.
⛔ This post does not give your lazy ass a license to use hormones or 'adrenal fatigue' as an excuse. ⛔

#understandnutrition #understandyourbody #itsprobablynotyourhormones
#butitcouldbe
#nutritionist
#nutrition
#fitliving 
#strongwomen

.

A lot of people start with me because of my sporting background and nutrition knowledge. Niamh was one of my longest clients.. Listen to her experience

Missing once is an accident ...
Missing twice is start of a new habit 👊👊👊
.
.
Nobody is looking for perfection. Do the small things consistently. Show up, even when the motivation is not there. 
.
.
Lost days hurt you more than successful days help you!!!
.
.
💥 Drink 2L water
💥 Sleep 7-9 hours a night
💥Resistance train at least 3 times a week
💥 Eat protein with every meal
💥 Eat lots of veggies 
💥 80/20 Approach
💥 Limit Alcohol
.
.
If everyone could just do this CONSISTENTLY there would be a lot happier people out there 😬
.
.
BE PATIENT AND ENJOY THE PROCESS 🥰🥰🥰

caption:
You are not weak if you ask for help ❌❌❌
In Fact if anything I think you're a little more courageous 
🤩🤩🤩
.
.
You are not expected to know everything. That's why people have occupations with the relevant knowledge and skills to help 👌
.
.
💥 If you are a student, unsure of your path. Please talk to a career guidance teacher.
💥 If you are unsure of your career and thinking about changing everything for a different route. Maybe you could see a life coach.
💥 If you are sick. See a doctor.
💥 If you are having mental health issues, a counsellor may be an option
💥 If you're having car troubles, go to a mechanic.
💥 If your phone isn't working, bring it to a phone shop.
.
.
See the trend???
.
.
Once upon a time I thought I was totally independent. I didn't want to ask for help from anyone!!! But then I realised, I can't do it all alone and actually support and guidance is the best thing I could get. NOW, I ask for help all the time. From family, friends, and colleagues. I have a coach. If my mental health is affecting me I call someone for help. One of the best things I ever did was see a life coach ❤
.
.
Why is it so hard for people to see the same applies to training and nutrition? 🥴🥴🥴 You could be spending weeks, months or even years trying to do it alone? 🙈 Wasting your time and money in the process. If you aren't qualified in the area. YOU CAN ALWAYS ASK FOR HELP 🙏 Please please stop making poor nutrition choices based on what Google told you. Stop wasting time trying to 'shred belly fat' based on a free workout Susan gave you.
.
Ask for help. Stop wasting your time. I'm literally just a phone call away. 
.
.
Pm me with 'Get Started' to organise a phonecall 😁

caption:
6 months in the land down under 🦘
.
.
A few new followers since I moved abroad so here's 10 Things you may not know about me 🤪
.
.
1. I was born in Donegal (all you will know me as a Rossie but I've been a true Donegal wannabe my whole life 💚💛) I did well to find a Donegal man too 😆
.
2. I'm actually a dab hand at Karaoke. Some of you will know me from 'My Happy Ending' days and my most recent power ballad is D.I.V.O.R.C.E. @o_boyce doesn't allow me to sing it anymore as I once cleared a bar out in Albuferia.
.
3. I have one sister @lauramcloone. She is my best friend 🥰
.
4. I have played football my whole life. I was useless when I was younger. Persistance and my singing skills paid off when I was asked to play with Roscommon intermediate Ladies back in 2009. I had 10 years played with Roscommon and 2 Connacht interpro jerseys under my belt before I announced my retirement last year.
.
5. Andy Moran overshadowed my retirement in 2019. (No harsh feelings Andy)
.
6. I can't drink for shite. I continue to try though 💪
.
7. I have the same amount of medals from Scaled Crossfit comps last year as I have for playing with Roscommon 🙈 (still the best days of my life but I want younger people to see it's not all about winning)
.
8. I ruptured my ACL, broke my wrist in 2 places and badly dislocated my finger all within 15 months. Previous to that, I never had an injury.
.
9. My Dad died of Pancreatic Cancer in 2015. Since then, I have been an advocate for health and happiness. I do everything in my power to be the healthiest version of myself. I also like to do fundraisers and my most recent one raised over $10,000 aud for May Roscommon Hospice.
.
10. I've only been in the fitness industry 6 years but I honestly feel like it's my whole life. It's not just a job, but a passion and I adore it 💖

caption:
Priorities
.
.
What are yours?
 
- Karen wants to be super lean <20% BF. But Karen enjoys socialising at the weekend and religiously has a takeaway to cure herself Sunday. Karen doesn't want to put in the commitment to get to her goal. And that's ok, because it's not 'easy' to get visible abs. It requires sacrifice. It requires hard work. And not everyone is willing to do that. 

- John wants to become a 6 figure coach. John works 9-5 Monday to Friday. John trains himself twice a day. John competes in bodybuilding competitions (he's in GREAT SHAPE). But he won't sacrifice his training for his client's timetables. John is not making sacrifices. John is unlikely to become a 6 figure coach with his current attitude.

When I played football....

I lived, slept and breathed football.

My whole life revolved around football - social occassions, relationships, friendships, family events, work. I honestly mean MY WHOLE LIFE. Some would have called me obsessed. But I truely believe this is the level you need to prioritise Inter County football. I was never the best player in the world but find someone who worked harder than me, not just on the pitch but in every element of my life. I am an athlete. I still consider myself an athlete but my priorities have definitely shifted. 

Instead of Sunday morning matches, I have swapped it for Sunday morning breakfast. Instead of Friday night training, I'm enjoying Friday morning training in the gym. Instead of a very lean physique, it's obvious I train but enjoy chocolate too ;) 

Priorities change and that's ok. 

If you are someone who's willing to put in minimal effort but expecting huge results, it's not going to happen (unless you are genetically gifted). If you are someone that enjoys socialising every weekend, you're probably not going to make an Inter county team.

'But just don't be disappointed in the results you didn't get for the effort you didn't put in.'

caption:
'Walk slowly but never backwards'
. 
.
A healthy lifestyle is relatively simple. It is we who over complicate it. That doesn't mean it's easy. Easy and simple are very different words. There are many barriers in our way of health, some we have no control over like socio economic status, but there are many we can control 🙏 So let's try and control the controllables..
.
.
I really enjoyed this post as it focuses on habits. Even before I started reading Atomic Habits I was a big believer in habits. Now, I am even more so 😋
.
.
Of the above habits. I do:
At least 7-8 daily (depending on the weather in Sydney 😆🤪).
.
.
How many do you do????
⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️

Ever thought about signing up for coaching with me? Still unsure what i do? Worried I only work with athlete
es? 

Here's Elaine's Journey

I'm a little obsessed with the book Atomic Habits at the moment. I cannot recommend it enough 🙏 I wish my 18 year old self would have read it. Even my 23 year old self. I feel like the book now is just reiterating that I am doing things right for me at this stage in my life ❣🙏
.
.
But not all my habits are good. Some of my bad habits include:
👉 Stressing over small things (I'm getting better but not perfect)
👉 Over working (I love my job but that doesn't mean every waking minute should revolve around it)
👉 Over training 
👉 Being on my phone too much (part of it is due to work but I need to get away from this one)
.
.
And with that. It's Friday evening. I am finished work. (If you have any queries you'll need to wait until Monday 🙈). My training is DONE for the weekend (Full weekend off in God knows how long 🙈). And Me and Owen have a little trip away which I plan on being more present 🙏 
.
.
P.s I will announce the winner of the 1 on 1 coaching in the morning 🙌🙌🙌
.
.
Happy Friday 💥💥💥

caption:
I wish I had time for 'Morning Coffee thoughts' 😅😅😅
.
.
👉 Reality is my days are long. I don't get time to brush my hair in the am let alone sit down and think with my coffee 😆😆😆
.
.
💥I love my job but it can be tiring. 
💥I love training but I'm not always motivated.
💥I love early mornings but sometimes I'd like to stay in bed a half an hour longer
💥 I love healthy food but some days i just want chocolate and crisps
.
.
Weekends are my 'rest' and 'reset' time. For so long I was in 'constant go go go mode'. At home I worked Monday to Friday (long days), Saturday was study and Sunday was football. I NEVER switched off, unless I took a holiday. I'm never going to be a laze in bed until 11 on a Saturday morning kinda gal 😅 But it's nice to know sometimes I can just sit and be present with my coffee and a good breakfast at weekends 🥰
.
.
Anyone else the same? Living for that chilled weekend vibes 🤘

caption:
Saturday spent educating 🤘🤘🤘
.
.
When I was younger I wanted to be a teacher...
.
After work experience, I knew I didn't have the patience to be a primary or secondary school teacher. But turns out I still went down that path.📚
.
.
My education and teachings don't have a syllabus. They are constantly changing. There is no one size fits all approach.
.
.
I love this though. I love helping others. I love practicising what I preach. This is not just my job. This is my passion and lifestyle 🥰
.
.
What better way to spend a Saturday morning than with like minded people. Training. Drinking coffee. And talking sense 👊 @strengthandmovementlab so happy to be part of this great community 😊😊😊

caption:
It would be so hard to be a teenager right now 🤦‍♀️🙈
.
.
I thought my teenage years were tough. I can definitely say it was the peak of my self loathing. I hated my body. I drank too much. I self harmed. I worked too hard. I put too much pressure on myself.
.
.
And I didn't have social media or drugs in that era 🥺😞
.
.
1. Social Media
The ideal of perfection is damaging. The 'perfect body'. The 'perfect make up'. The 'perfect picture'. The 'perfect life'. It's ALL FAKE NEWS!!!!!! Please please please stop following people who make you feel inferior. Stop trying to look like influencers. Stop trying to seek a perfection that doesn't exsist 🚫🚫🚫
.
.
2. Drugs
Since when are drugs the norm? 🤷‍♀️ Yes I am going to address the elephant in the room 🐘 I actually cannot get my head around this... It's like teenagers are now fully grown adults 😔 Making choices like this probably won't affect you now. But NO ONE IS THINKING ABOUT THE FUTURE!!! 😟 
.
.
I feel like I am old (maybe not wise) beyond my years. Everyone is looking for the quick fix. The easy option. The momentary high. No one is thinking about the long term. Their health? Long term health 😶 Physical and Mental Health 😞😣
.
.
Can we please protect this group of young adults? Can we please do our best to be good role models? Can we show them that perfection DOESN'T exsist? Can we encourage them to act their age and stop trying to be and look like adults? 
.
.
Make mistakes. 🔞
Take silly photos.📸 
School is important but so is life.📚 Travel (when we get out of this). 🏖
.
.
Rant over ⚠️⚠️⚠️

caption:
Fajitas 🌶🌶🌶
.
.
Super Simple, Nutritious and delicious
.
.
Ingredients (makes 3-4 portions)
500g Chikcen 
Green and Red Pepper
Onion 
Tomato Paste
Chilli Powder 
Garlic Powder
Salt
Pepper
Tbsp Olive oil
.
.
Optional:
Low Fat Cheese
Wraps
.
.
Fry peppers,onions and chicken in Olive oil until golden brown. Add 5 tbsp tomato paste, garlic, chilli, salt and pepper and simmer for 10 mins
.
.
I have about 2600 calories to play about with so I added low fat cheese to a whole grain wrap. If weight loss is a goal why not add the mixture to a low calorie wrap alternative or a lettuce boat? 

#fajitas #mexican #balance #dinnertreats #fitlife #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam #sydneyfitfam

How do you calculate calories? 
.
.
1 Calculate BMR 

Weight in kg x 24 = BMR

2 BMR x Activity Level
1.2 Sedentary
1.4 Lightly Active
1.6 Moderately Active
1.8 Very Active 
2.0 Athlete 

3. Adjust for goal

caption:
SMART GOALS 🚀🚀🚀
.
.
DO YOU REALLY NEED THEM? Well if you're looking to make progress, yes!!!
.
.
How long have you been wanting to get a pull up for? How long have you wanted to lose that extra kg? How long have you wanted to improve your speed? 
.
.
Well then you need to make smart goals. You also need to take action  in the steps to achieving these goals. What are SMART GOALS?
.
.
S - Specific - Weight loss is too general. You need a specific target in mind and a path to get you to that goal.
.
M - Mesurable - 60m dash speed is measurable - 'getting faster' Isn't 
.
A - Achievable - this one is a BIG one. Please don't set yourself up for failure. If you have just started resistance training and you want to compete in a bikini competitions in 8 weeks with no coach you are setting yourself up for a fail 🙈
.
R - Realistic - If you are playing high level football and want to sign up for a Crossfit competition just don't 😅 (unless you are me. I know Pot Kettle Black - I still wouldn't advise it)
.
T - Time Specific - Instead of 'I want to be able to do 10 Chin ups (btw this is a very hard goal) - why not say ' I want to be able to do 1 chin up in 8 weeks and maybe 5 Chin ups in 6 months'
.
.
Now you have your goals decided make a plan to make it to your destination. If your goal is to master chin ups and your constantly doing hiit classes (unless the classes have this in it) you're probably never going to achieve that goal. If your goal is weight loss but you're not interested in changing your diet, you're probably never going to achieve that goal. Be SMART about your planning too 🙃 
.
.
Some of my goals to share with you:
💫 I want to be able to do All Rx exercises by the end of 2020
💫 I want top 100 in Ireland in 2021 Open
💫 I want a 50kg Snatch by September 
💫 I want an 80kg C&J by the end of 2020

caption:
My own journey 👸👸👸
.
.
I truely believe people think. Ah ya, she's always been fit it's easy for her. Sure what would I know I've never had to lose weight 🤷‍♀️
.
.
Not every battle can be seen 🚫🚫🚫
.
.
I struggled with my image from a young age. People will think I was always confident, always the life and soul of the party. But it wasn't until I seen a counsellor that I realised I was masking my unhappiness. I had issues I didn't even know exsisted. When I was in school I was so self conscious. I had mental health problems I didn't know exsisted. These continued on into my early 20s. I was obsessed with my body image. EVERY single time I walked past a mirror I checked for abs. I took photos of myself every single day on the quest for a 6 pack 😔 My relationship with food and exercise was poor 😰 I honestly thought I was not lean in the first photo 😬
.
.
Fast forward to being 29 🥰 I cannot believe the journey I've been on to get here but I am in love with the process 🤩 I am so proud of what my body can do. I fuel it right. I'm good to it (most of the time, unless I do too much 🤪😶). It's not all about the physical. Physically I'm probably the fittest I've ever been but MENTALLY I'm 100% the best I've ever been 💘 
.
.
So please don't think I don't know what it's like. That because my journey is not weight loss, that it doesn't matter or count. EVERY journey to better health matters. EVERY conscious effort to improve mental and physical health matters. You matter 😘

caption:
As a nutritionist, my answer of 'it depends ' is unappreciated and unappealing 😅 But it's the honest one. 
.
.
But this one I can safely say applies to the VAST majority of the population 👆👆
.
.
If I could give my top pieces of advice, they would be:
.
1. Base your diet on one ingredient foods - Meat, Fruit, Vegetables, Nuts, Eggs, Grains etc. 
.
2. Get 2L of water in daily
.
3. Sleep 7-9 hours a night
.
4. Get 10,000 Steps in daily 
.
5. Eat protein with each meal
.
6. Self care daily - whatever it is that destresses you, do it
.
7. Resistance train 3 times a week 
.
Focus on the 99%, Stop worrying about the 1% 🙈 Do the basics right consistently. It's relatively simple. Stop overthinking it 😚

caption:
Back to the gym this week or in the coming weeks? 🤔
.
.
LEAVE YOUR EGO AT THE DOOR. 🦧
.
.
Similar to the football post I put up a couple of weeks ago. There are a lot of considerations when going back to exercise in a gym setting 🙃
.
.
As per usual, this is very individual based but I'll try make this advice as generic as possible 😊
.
.
1. Don't expect to lift what you lifted pre Covid (unless you've had a home gym setting and have been training consistently during isolation)
2. Ease yourself in. 3 days of training will be MORE than enough. You WILL be sore. You don't need to make up for lost time. You don't need to punish yourself for the extra half stone you gained. Just ease yourself back in.
3. Get back into a routine. Sleep, hydration and training. Make these a priority.
4. Recovery is KEY!!!!! Nutrition will be more important than ever. Protein is our principal recovery food. Eat it in abundance. Carbs are our main energy source. Don't neglect them. Essentials fats have anti inflammatory properties. Eat them 🥑 And let's make sure our immune system is in tip top shape. Keep lots of colour and fibre in there too 🍆🍎🍌🥒🍄
.
.
It's pretty simple really
.
.
If you want to avoid monstrous doms and increasing risk of injury. Take this advice.
.
.
If not, enjoy sitting on the toilet seat 🚽🚽🚽

#backtothegym 
#besmart 
#avoidinjury 
#fitliving 
#fitness

☠ ☠You train so hard, how do you not have Abs? ☠☠
.
.
Contrary to popular belief not everyone trains to have abs 🤫
.
.
🙋‍♀️I used to. And I didn't enjoy my training. Actually scrap that I didn't enjoy life 🤐🤨 I ate so clean, I did not have 'cheat food' and I was tired and moody constantly. Since then, I've learned to love my training and what my body is capable of 🥰🤭 I also like to socialise 🐷🥂 .
.
For me, happiness is not linked to a body part or looking a certain way. It's being confident in your body. Eating to nourish and fuel your body. Training to be fitter and stronger not to look like a fitness model. .
.
So no, I don't have visible abs. Not constantly anyway. And I don't care.
.
.
P.s Are legs not the new abs anyway? 🦵🦵🦵 #trainforstrength 
#trainsmart
#eatforhealth
#eatforperformance
#fitliving 
#fitlifestyle

What I ate Yesterday 🍽🍽🍽
.
.
Firstly, I actually don't like posts like this. I feel people think if they eat it, they will look or perform like the person who's diet it is. And that's not necessarily the case.
.
.
What I'm trying to do is educate you and make you understand that you CAN and SHOULD eat lots of nutritious food ☺ And there can also be some room for the odd treat 😉 You don't need to have that: Restrict/Binge cycle that so many of you subject yourselves to 😭 As I've mentioned before I don't count calories. But I'm Fairly in tune with my body and know what my body needs.
.
.
I eat lots of protein (varying my sources - Whey Protein, Greek Yogurt Salmon, Chicken), change my veggie cooking methods (raw and Stirfried), I eat fresh and frozen fruit and have good fats in there too (feta cheese and nuts). .
.
My nutrition is based on my weight, activity level and training. Please don't eat these exact foods, thinking they are 'the best' foods to eat 🤦‍♀️ Instead educate yourself. Maybe even invest in someone who specialises in the area 😁 .
.
Happy Hump day 🐪🐪🐪 #eatgoodfood #realnutrition #realresults #instafood #instanutrition #stopthebingerestrictcycle
Any experiences or opinions welcomed! 😁

caption:
Lets talk fruit 🍑🍊🍌🍍🍓🍎🥝🍇
.
.
I 'prescribed' a client to eat more fruit during the week. And she questioned the idea 'does too much fruit not store as fat?'. Too much anything will result in excess calories which will result in weight gain. Too much Fruit will not solely 'turn to fat'. .
.
The difficult thing with nutrition and understanding nutrition is there is so much crap on the internet. And then even the science changes regularly so it really is a minefield 🤯🤯🤯
.
.
This guide is great to show that you can get a lot more bang for your buck with fruits like berries and watermelon. More quantity leaves a greater satiety which avoids over eating. As opposed to a simple banana that is convenient.
.
.
I have had people over consume fruit. It's not totally false. And if you are bodybuilding or prepping fpr something that requires a very low body fat, you may need to be careful with fruit. Fruits are simple sugars and are classified as carbohydrates. But they are full of vitamins, minerals, water and fibre. And believe me, with majority of population, fruit is the least of your worries 🙃😉 #fruitforthewin #deliciousandnutritious

Want a strong core? 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♂️
.
.
As most of you already know I was allergic to core work 😅 I did it through my strength training and that was it. I have no desire to have a 6 pack so it just seemed irrelevant to do isolation exercises 😅🙈
.
.
Since starting my Crossfit Programme my core strength has been seriously tested. I thought (and still believe) I don't have a weak core. But there are so many levels our core strength can get to. Gymnastics is a new ball game to me and my God has my core has been tested 🤪😬 I'm now very happy I've been doing this extra core work because it's helped a lot.
.
.
1. Toes to Bar
2. L Sit
3. Hollow Rocks
4. Half Get Up
5. Palloff Press with Squat
6. Side Plank rotations
.
.
These are just some of the exercises I'm doing regularly. Again, they are a little more advanced. And don't expect miracles when it comes to training your core. I'm not promising a six pack but I certainly believe I'm getting stronger doing it 💪

#corework #strongwomen #strong #strongcore #crossfit #fitness

caption:
And just like that...
3 months are gone 💭💭💭
.
.
Did you spend the last 3 months doing anything productive? Did you procrastinate? Did you work towards your goals? We are into the 6th month of the year!!!!🥴 Yes, the circumstances are different but that doesn't mean we have no control 🚫🚫🚫 You can choose to stay active. You can choose to eat well. It's a choice to drink every weekend 🤐
.
.
I decided I wanted to work harder on Crossfit. Having never giving it my full attention I decided what better time to start into a Crossfit programme than during isolation. Sure I had no access to a lot of equipment but that doesn't mean I wanted to sit about doing nothing. That wasnt going to get me to where I wanted to be. I started isolation with a KB, a skipping rope and attempted some met cons. I hadn't been following a programme since before December. 6 weeks ago I got on board with @estevolveprogramming and i haven't looked back 😍🤩 I'm still not where i want to be BUT I'm a hell of a lot closer than I was 🙌🙌🙌 My 2020 goals:
👉 By the end of 2020 I want to be able to do everything rx
👉 I want to improve my Open position
.
.
The time is going to pass. Why don't you stop talking about it and take action? Why not stop starting over and stick with something consistently. Its 6 months into the year. Prioritise your health. Prioritise you!!!! #endofisolationinaustrailia
#gymsreopen
#crossfittraining
#fitliving 
#workingonmyself
#fitness
#stronggirls

Health versus Calories....Round 2 🥊🥊🥊
.
.
This breakfast is super nutritious. It hits a good quality protein source, healthy fats, micros and it tastes absolutely delish 🤩
It would be something I'd regularly get when eating out 😍
.
.
This breakfast however probably knocks you back 600-700 Calories. So if weight loss is your goal, this breakfast may not be for you 🙈
.
.
Health is my goal. I don't track calories. I train hard and I'm pretty good at guestimating what I need to fuel me 🙌 So therefore this breakfast is perfect for me. And if it's your goals, enjoy it 💥💥 However, if weight loss is your goal, it's not enough to just 'be eating healthy'. You need to be in a caloric deficit 🙏
.
