caption:
Footballers BEWARE!!!! 🚫🚫🚫
.
.
It's fantastic to see football is back on the cards for 2020 😍🤩 But don't forget or lose sight of what a crazy year it has been. .
.
👉 Your body has not been training as normal (NO MATTER WHAT TYPE OF TRAINING YOU'VE BEEN DOING)
👉 Do not overload your body as you increase your risk of injury.
👉 Nutrition is so overlooked. It will be your best friend during this period. High Protein, complex carbs, good fats and lots of micronutrients (fruit and veggies)
👉 At least 2L water daily.
👉 Fix your sleep routine which is probably all out of whack 😵
.
.
Basic principles but I can PROMISE not everyone will adhere to them. Talk to your S&C coach. Talk to your trainer. Talk to a physio. Talk to someone who knows what they are doing.
.
.
Mind yourself and enjoy 💗💗💗 #football #gaa #gaanews #injuryprevention #lgfa
I talk about nutrition in terms of health and calories a lot but sometimes it's more than that. We socialise, we eat out, we are not always in control of our food. What happens then?

10 Days into June and I'm on 39,400kg 🙌🙌🙌 (as you can see from the videos the 60kg Front Squats almost killd me today 😅) I need to take this opportunity to thank everyone who has donated so far. 💟
.
.
Mayo Roscommon Hospice was chosen because of the AMAZING work they have been doing and continue to do. Unfortunately, due to covid, a lot of their fundraising went with it. So when Laura and I decided to do a fundraiser, it was the obvious choice 💕
.
.
For those of you who dont know. @lauramcloone and I lost our Dad to pancreatic cancer 5 years ago. This June we wil have our 5th Fathers day without Daddy 💔 I am honoured that we can help this charity. Especially because they helped us so much in Daddy's final days 💔 Please please give whatever you can and share this amazing charity 😇 (I promise we are putting in the work begind the scenes🤪) Link in my Bio

💟 Do you want a healthy relationship with food? No 'bad' or 'good' foods. .
.
💟 Do you want a nutrition education? As opposed to throwing calories and macros at you and giving you Myfitnesspal.
.
.
💟Do you want accountability? Not just a generic cheap plan. That you won't get results from.
.
.
I believe women need to be educated. I believe we need to improve our relationship with food and exercise. I believe we can all benefit from accountability. I believe we need balance in our life but we also have to make small sacrifices.
.
.
This lady's results are 3 weeks into an online programme with me. She exercised regularly but not excessively. She improved her protein intake. She did not use Myfitnesspal. She did not fully abstain from alcohol but she didn't drink as much as normal. She was accountable to me each week. .
.
This lady took control of her health and lifestyle. She INVESTED in a coach. And she didn't waste time and money on a generic plan.🚫🚫🚫 Are you going to take control?
Are you going to invest in your health?
.
.
If so, pm me 🤳🤳🤳 #onlinecoach #realresults #realnutrition

💕Imagine loving your body? .
.
💕Imagine having such a good relationship with food that you don't feel guilty after a 'bad' weekend
.
.
💕Imagine loving exercise and not using it as punishment
.
.
💕Imagine such a balanced lifestyle that you can incorporate your favourite foods and still achieve your goals!!!!! .
.
🚫 I was not always like this. 🚫 It takes a lot more than healthy eating and training to fix your relationship with food and exercise. It takes time and patience. It's definitely easier with support. .
.
❌ You won't find it in a clothes size
❌ You won't find it with abs
❌ You won't find it with certain or specific exercise
❌ You won't find it with a specific diet
.
.
🎀 You need to want this. Stop chasing an aesthetic goal. Stop chasing a perfect body. Stop looking for the ideal diet. Stop copying what influencers are doing.
.
.
💘 Invest in yourself. Invest in your health. Work on yourself EVERY SINGLE DAY ❣ Stay consistent. And be patient. Enjoy the process and fall in love with your body...warts and all 🤩
.
.
Here I am.. At my heaviest, strongest and happiest ❤
.
.
Pm me if you need help‼ Don't let another week go by of you hating your body. Take control. Take action ❣ Stop waiting for it to happen and MAKE it happen ‼

caption:
I'm so unbelievably proud of how this fundraiser is going so far 🥰 Thank you to all you incredible people supporting such an amazing cause. I'm a big believer in Karma and doing a good deed will be repaid. ❤
.
.
To anyone who has had to use hospice services and sees first hand the AMAZING work they do, you'll understand why this means so much to me ❤🙌
.
.
@lauramcloone and I have been killing it behind the scenes and are currently on 38,000kg between us. 💪💪💪
.
.
Sharing the fundraiser and getting more coverage is so important so I appreciate if you could ❤🥰
.
.
#fundraiser #amandaandlauralift200tonnes
#mayoroscommonhospice

Hi Guys,

So with the month of June being @lauramcloone birth month and the month Ireland celebrates Father's Day I thought it'd be a great month to do a fundraiser 🙌

As most of you already know, Laura and I lost our dad Denis to pancreatic cancer in 2015. This will be our 5th Father's day and Laura's birthday without him 💔 During the time leading up to his untimely death, the Mayo Roscommon Hospice and Palliative Care were incredible so we have decided to donate all proceeds to this amazing cause 🤩

What are we doing: 🏋️‍♀️Laura and I plan on lifting 200 tonnes over the month of June between us 🤪 Yes you heard right - 200,000kg!!!
To give you an idea of what this looks like - 40 x 80kg Deadlifts daily for the month of June. Sound manageable? 
Why not join in? 💪 We will be giving daily updates on our progress but the more the merrier 🥳 
I think Daddy would have been in total shock if I said this to him 🙈But then again I'd doubt he would be too suprised with his 2 super competitive daughters 🤣🥰 Whether you decide to join in or not, please donate to this fantastic cause and help other families like us going through a tough time ❣

Thank you so much to everyone who has already donated.❤🙏 https://www.facebook.com/donate/250894555982640/?fundraiser_source=external_url

#mayoroscommonhospice

𝗠𝘆 𝗴𝗼𝗮𝗹𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗱𝗶𝗳𝗳𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘁𝗼 𝗺𝗼𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗳 𝗺𝘆 𝗳𝗼𝗹𝗹𝗼𝘄𝗲𝗿𝘀. 𝗦𝗼 𝗱𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝘁𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗸 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗻𝗲𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗼 𝗯𝗲 𝗱𝗼𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘄𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗜'𝗺 𝗱𝗼𝗶𝗻𝗴. 𝗠𝗼𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗳 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝘄𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗻𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿 𝗻𝗲𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗼 𝗽𝗯 𝗮 𝗰𝗹𝗲𝗮𝗻 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗝𝗲𝗿𝗸 𝗼𝗿 𝗺𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗿 𝗮 𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗺𝘂𝘀𝗰𝗹𝗲 𝘂𝗽. 𝗕𝘂𝘁 𝘁𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝗢𝗞 𝗯𝗲𝗰𝗮𝘂𝘀𝗲 𝗮𝗹𝗹 𝗴𝗼𝗮𝗹𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗶𝗻𝗱𝗶𝘃𝗶𝗱𝘂𝗮𝗹. 
𝗡𝗼 𝗺𝗮𝘁𝘁𝗲𝗿 𝘄𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗴𝗼𝗮𝗹𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝘀𝘁𝗿𝗲𝗻𝗴𝘁𝗵 𝘁𝗿𝗮𝗶𝗻𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗰𝗮𝗻 𝗳𝗶𝘁 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗴𝗼𝗮𝗹𝘀 💥💥💥

caption:
A friend said to me last night 'Amanda I can't believe how much counselling helped you. You're so much better at dealing with stressful situations now' 🙌
.
.
It honestly was one of the nicest things to hear ❤️ I have always been an open book. I never say life is perfect when it's not. Life is far from perfect but I try to see the best in all situations 🙏
.
.
Once upon a time I didn't look after myself. I looked after everyone and everything else. I gave everything to helping my family, working and playing football. I had nothing left for me 🤷‍♀️
.
.
I made the decision last year to come to Australia for me and Owen. So for once, we came first ❤️🙏So many years of putting everything else first very nearly burnt me out 😳But we're here. Living our best lives ❤️🙌
.
.
Honestly, I can say that getting a coach (Alan you know who you are) and seeing a counsellor were the best things I have ever done in my entire life. They changed my outlook on life. They made me focus on myself and looking after no. 1. They helped me deal with my constant need to help everyone. And they helped me overcome a lot of anxiety and stress related problems I've had ❤️
.
.
We all have bad days. That's normal. I do too. But I'm now in control of my life 🙏

#itsoktonotbeok

caption:
ɪꜱ ʏᴏᴜʀ ᴄᴏᴀᴄʜ ᴘʀᴏɢʀᴀᴍᴍɪɴɢ ᴛᴏ ʏᴏᴜʀ ɢᴏᴀʟꜱ ᴏʀ ᴛʜᴇʀᴇꜱ? 🤔
.
.
Is your coach programming to your lifestyle or are you changing your lifestyle to suit the programme? 🤔
.
.
Coaching should add to your life. Not take away from it ❌❌❌
.
.
I feel that people think I only coach athletes 🤦‍♀️ Or that I will make you do what I do 😩 Honestly, I've only had 1 Client I have progressed to a really high level. And she has been with me for over a year 🤣 Most of my clients are: Hot mommas trying to get back into fitness, lovely ladies trying to get into a routine, teenage girls who want to start strength & conditioning and women just wanting to build better relationships with themselves and food 🙌🙌🙌
.
.
A handful of my clients have done some of the training I do. Most of them start as beginners or intermediate ✔️✔️✔️
.
.
There is honestly nothing to worry about when training with me. I progress and regress all my programmes based on the individual. I work my programmes around the client, not the client around the programme 🚫🚫🚫 I love coaching. Coaching is about the clients, not me. I provide the tools, they do the work ❤️🙌
.
.
If you are up for a challenge though:
50-40-30-20-10
KB Snatch
Jump Squats
Hollow Rocks

caption:
💥🄷🄾🅆 🄼🄰🄽🅈 🅃🄸🄼🄴🅂 🄰 🅆🄴🄴🄺 🅂🄷🄾🅄🄻🄳 🄸 🄱🄴 🄴🅇🄴🅁🄲🄸🅂🄸🄽🄶?
.
. 💥🅆🄷🄸🄲🄷 🄸🅂 🄱🄴🅃🅃🄴🅁 🄲🄰🅁🄳🄸🄾 🄾🅁 🅆🄴🄸🄶🄷🅃🅂?
.
. 💥🄼🅈 🄵🅁🄸🄴🄽🄳 🄳🄾🄴🅂🄽'🅃 🄲🄾🄽🅂🄸🄳🄴🅁 🅆🄰🄻🄺🄸🄽🄶 🄴🅇🄴🅁🄲🄸🅂🄴?
.
. 💥🄷🄾🅆 🄻🄾🄽🄶 🅂🄷🄾🅄🄻🄳 🄸 🄱🄴 🄴🅇🄴🅁🄲🄸🅂🄸🄽🄶?
.
.
These are just some of the questions I am asked on a regular basis 🙈 The list really does go on.....
.
.
Please realise, like food there is NO one size fits all. Everybody is different. Has different goals. Has different commitments. Has different preferences. Everyone is at different fitness levels
🚫🚫🚫
.
.
My answer is normally: Do 70% of the exercise you like and 30% of the exercise you need. How often can you commit to exercise? I wouldn't be telling a 6 Week post partum mother to exercise for 90 Mins everyday at 5pm because that is just unrealistic. There is no specific time or regularity you need to follow. But you do need to find something that suits you and your schedule. Just because Susan doesn't consider walking exercise doesn't mean you can't 🤦‍♀️
.
.
Stop comparing yourself to people on instagram 🤦‍♀️ Stop feeling 'guilty' that you're not exercising twice a day 🚫 Stop thinking if you do what you're favorite influencer is doing, you'll look like her ❌
.
.
Do what you can ✔️
Do it to the best of YOUR ability ✅
Enjoy it ❤️ #fitness #fitlifestyle #stoplisteningtocelebrities #stopcomparing
#fitliving #fitfam #irishfitfam

💥𝕋𝕙𝕖𝕪 𝕤𝕒𝕪 𝕚𝕟𝕤𝕒𝕟𝕚𝕥𝕪 𝕚𝕤 𝕕𝕠𝕚𝕟𝕘 𝕥𝕙𝕖 𝕤𝕒𝕞𝕖 𝕥𝕙𝕚𝕟𝕘 𝕖𝕧𝕖𝕣𝕪𝕕𝕒𝕪 𝕒𝕟𝕕 𝕖𝕩𝕡𝕖𝕔𝕥𝕚𝕟𝕘 𝕒 𝕕𝕚𝕗𝕗𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕟𝕥 𝕠𝕦𝕥𝕔𝕠𝕞𝕖💥
.
.
Think about that one 🙈🤔 Are you doing the same thing everyday and expecting a different result 🙄😱
.
.
This can relate to all areas of your life 💥💥💥 Be it in a relationship? Or a job? But it most certainly can be used when it comes to health and fitness 🙈
.
.
A little information about me:
👆 I am HIGHLY self motivated. I work outrageously hard at what I do in all areas of my life. Not everyone is. That's fine (And also where investing in a coach is a very good idea). 👆 I am really positive. Not always but I try to keep a good outlook on life. I have not had an easy ride. I have probably been through more in a couple of years than most go through in their lifetime. But I don't let it define me and I don't whinge and complain about it (all the time anyway 🙈).
👆 I know what I'm good at but I also know where my weak points are. I'm constantly learning and I believe that we can all benefit from other knowledge and expertise.
👆 I belive in giving compliments. People should know what a good job they are doing. Jealousy is natural but is usually a reflection of you and not the person or thing you are jealous of. Jealousy can actually have a postive effect on us if treated right, it can motivate us to get to where we WANT to be 🙌
.
.
Long winded point of this post. Are you doing what you need to do, to get where you want to be?
💥For me, I'm working when other people are drinking. I'm awake when others are asleep. I'm training in the rain when other people are making excuses. 💥
.
.
I don't wait for things to happen. I MAKE THEM HAPPEN 🎉🎉🎉 What do you do? 🤔

#makehealthapriority #noexcuses
#makeachangetoday
#hwpo

caption:
. 🎀  𝑅🍬𝓁𝑒 𝑀💍𝒹𝑒𝓁𝓈 🎀 .
.
.
When I was growing up. I had role models. They were usually female Footballers. @valeriemulcahy @emercaseyross were 2 big ones for me. They excelled in their sport and showed a level of professionalism and work ethic I had never seen before 🙌💯 .
.
These days though there are female role models everywhere 😍 There are women in relationships earning more than their male partners. There are women bossing the business industry. There are strong women. Female Gaa players these days are considered celebrities. Women commentators on sports shows. Body confident women. The list is ENDLESS 🙌🙌🙌
.
.
The word role model has been thrown at me a few times. And honestly, I turn into a shy kid when it does. It is genuinely one of the greatest compliments I've ever gotten. Why? Because I know what it means ❤️
.
.
What do I try to bring to the table:
💥My work ethic - in everything I do. Hard work gets you places. It may be the extra hours work I put in to build a future business. It may be the extra work I put in off the field. It may be the hour earlier I get up to get my steps in. These extras will all add up some day.
"Hard Work beats talent, when talent doesn't work hard" ❤️
.
💥I try to portray a stong, resilient personality - Life is not always easy, but you have a choice in how you react.
.
💥My relationship with food and exercise - I love exercise. I love what my body can do and how strong I've become. I love being able to lift the same weights as @o_boyce 😜 But I love to show women it is important to nourish your body. I love educating people 🙌
.
💥Body confidence - This is not a size or a weight on a scales. This is not something gained overnight and it can take ALOT of work.
.
.
My Advice:
Stop looking at celebrities and their bodies and start looking at Real women. Real women with their cellulite and their imperfect skin. Real women who work 40 hours a week. Real women who have families and have dinner on the table every evening. .
Tag your role models below ⬇️⬇️⬇️ #rolemodels

caption:
Let's talk sports injuries 🤔🤔🤔
.
.
You know what I'm talking about here. That person who constantly has 'tight hamstrings'. Or the full forward who repeatedly strains their calves. What about the goalie with the shoulder impingement?  Or the corner back who has tore their quad on more than one occasion 🙈
.
.
I've had my fair share of serious injuries. I've had my ACL reconstructed. Broke the 2 bones in my wrist and had wires inserted. Dislocated fingers badly 🙈I Attribute it to the fact that I put my body on the line and never pulled out of a tackle. My years and years of running the pitch ragged caught up on me when I developed tendonopathy in my Achilles but I've never had a muscular injury 🤔🤔🤔
.
.
Why? Especially after ACL reconstruction. People normally have issues. Why didn't I?
💥Firstly, I am not a physio or a doctor. What I'm about to say is my opinion💥
.
🌟 Consistency - This is a major problem in the world of GAA. Players spend a month or 2 in pre season and that's their gym work for the year done ❌❌❌ Strength based training should be done year long for athletes. A good coach will periodise it and tailor it to the individual and their workload. But it should not be neglected mid season
.
. 🌟Knowledge - It's not enough to be doing a few Squats and Pull ups. If you are 'doing your own thing' or 'copying other people' it won't suffice. Pitch athletes require good exercise prescription, relevant to them and their sport. Basic, generic plans could lead to injury.
.
.
🌟Nutrition - High protein diet with carbohydrates for fuel, good fats for recovery and micro nutrients for immune function. Again, not just in season but off season too. Please do not under estimate the importance of good nutrition year round ❤️🙌
.
.
I was lucky enough to have a solid career on the pitch. Even when I had serious injuries I bounced back from them. I wasn't the player constantly on the side line with recurring injuries 🙋‍♀️And that wasn't down to luck. That was down to looking after myself.
.
.
Continued in comments

caption:
It can be this simple 💥💥💥
.
.
1. Fill up your plate with nutrient dense, low calorie vegetables.
2. Add a decent protein source - opt for oily fish regularly 3-4 times a week. White meat/fish is lower calorie if weight loss is the goal. 
3. You don't need to eliminate carbohydrates. Our body wants them. Our brain needs them. Just reduce your portion size and choose the right type of carbs.
4. P. S Fats are also vitally important but I've used this as a typical 'Irish dinner' (meat, veg and spuds type🇮🇪) .
.
❌Most of you don't need to worry about nutrient timing
❌Most of you don't need to cycle carbs
❌Most of you don't need to intermittent fast
❌It doesn't matter if you do your cardio fasted or fed
❌Stop worrying about supplements if your diet isn't perfect .
.
✔️ Most of you just need to eat less
✔️ Most of you just need to move more
✔️ Most of you need to drink more water

caption:
Let's make salad tasty and enjoyable 😍
Rather than using the term 'rabbit food' 🐰
.
.
💥5 Steps to a tasty, nutritious Salad💥
. 
1. Choose your base - I usually go spinach, you could go iceberg lettuce, kale, whatever you fancy
.
.
2. Add in some extra colour - I usually go beetroot, maybe carrot or peppers - I know tomatoes are a staple or maybe you'd like to add some olives 🍸
.
.
3. Add in some fats and/or Carbs - I tend to add a cheese - Feta, Goats, Halloumi. I sometimes add carbs to my salads but I rather fats. You could add cous cous or quinoa.
.
.
4. Add dressing - this is my go to. Low cál and the tastiest there is. The odd time I might use pesto but I never waste my calories on dressings 🐷
.
.
5. Add a protein and I like to add some fruit to colour ❤️💜💙 I tend to be a salmon, chicken or turkey burger gal 🙋‍♀️
.
.
Don't think for a single second just because you eat salads you'll lose weight 🙄 Salads have the potential to have higher calories than you think. Overdoing it on fat based foods like cheese or nuts or calorie laden dressings are the 2 main culprits 😏 There's also the fact that because they don't 'fill you' you may over eat after it 😕
.
.
Salads are amazing and should be a staple in most people's diets but don't think eating them automatically means you Lose weight 😅👆 #deliciousandnutritious

This was just as tasty but with almost half of the calories 😍

Makes 6 Portions
- 400g Dry Pasta
- Pasata
- Tomato puree
- Peppers
- Onion
- 500g Turkey mince
- Drizzle olive oil
- Salt
- Pepper
- Chilli Powder
- Garlic
- Low fat cheese

Fry mince in a little oil. Add vegetables. Cook in Pasata and tomato puree. Add seasoning. Cook pasta separately. When pasta is cooked add into the mince mix.
Place in oven proof dish and top with cheese 🤤 For 30 Mins or until cheese is brown. 💥Great Post training meal for athletes💥

#delicious #nutritous #simplemealideas #healthymealideas #fitness #consistency #fitlifestyle #fitfam #fitfood #irishfitfam

Who's Struggling with serial snacking
🙈🙈🙈
.
.
Real Time. My 3 main meals are full of nutrients, wholesome and enjoyable food. But the last 3 weeks I cannot stop snacking because of working from home. Sound familiar? 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️ I have fallen into this vicious trap. But this week, I'm taking action. Who's with me?
.
.
How do I plan on doing it?

1. Plan my meals and snacks. Knowing exactly what I plan on having for each meal or snack and not going 'outside the plan'.
.
2. Protein rich snacks - to keep you fuller for longer. I always recommend this to clients but recently have not been practicing what I preach.

3. Fruit is still a great snack 🙋‍♀️
.
4. Make sure I'm not just bored or thirsty. If I feel I want to go for a snack, I'll drink some water and re assess in 30 Mins. If you're still hungry. Pick up your snack from your meal plan.

5. Find a structure that works for you. I allow clients have treats. People need rewards. ❤️ I however, need to stop rewarding myself so much 😂 I always called treats and irregular thing. But they've become too regular and now can't be called a treat 🙈 So I'm pulling back on that too 👌

Lastly guys, if you are mindlessly snacking and don't care, that's fine. We are in such a crazy time, it might seem like the least of your priorities right now for you. My priority is to get into a structure and routine so I need to do this 🤷‍♀️
.
.

caption:
Complex Fun 🌟🌟🌟
.
.
A complex is any series of movements performed back-to-back with the same piece of equipment in which the set number of reps is completed for each movement before moving on to the next. It is also nice to create a flow for the exercises. You can do this with a Barbell, Kettlebell, Dumbells, a Sandbag or a Deadball. It is a another great way to increase difficulty of exercises with limited equipment during quarantine. 🙌
.
.
My Complex This morning was 20 sets of:
- 1 Deadlift
- 1 Hang Clean
- 1 Split Jerk
(The ideal weight should be determined by the most difficult exercise. So for example this deadlift was relatively easy for me but the split Jerk was harder.)
.
.
An idea of a double DB Complex Could be:
- 10 Renegade Row
- 10 RDL
- 10 Cleans
- 10 Front Squat
- 10 Push Press
.
.
These are a great way to get more bang for your buck with very little equipment 🙌

#complexes #barbellcomplex

caption:
Unilateral Movement 🙌🙌🙌
.
.
This means single arm, single leg movements. Ever noticed in a Bench Press  one arm is more dominant than the other?🤔 Or do you play sport and notice that balance is better on one leg over the other 🤔 Unilateral movements should be in all good programme design. They should be implemented to help improve weaknesses and imbalances. 👌 They are also a great method of varying difficulty of home based training at the moment 💪
👉 A basic air squat vs a pistol squat 😯
👉 BW Glute bridges vs SL elevated bridges 🍑 👉 Push ups vs single arm push ups 😂
.
.
Unilateral Movement is an important accessorie tool for all strength based training. If you haven't started implementing it, start now 💪

#homebasedtraining #workhard #strength #strongwomen #fitlifestyle #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
👉For years we were told you NEED to eat Breakfast...
👉Then we were told to fast...
.
.
So what's the deal? Is breakfast really the most important meal of the day? 🤔
.
.
So I'm not going talk from a scientific perspective right now. Even though a lot of the science that is thrown around this topic is all horse crap anyway 🙈 From a personal perspective.
.
.
👉 If you absolutely detest eating a breakfast. I say don't eat a breakfast. I'm not going to force feed someone a breakfast 'so they don't go into starvation mode' 🙈. But if they're general wake up call is a cigarette and a coffee, I'd recommend something a little more substantial of course. But forcing and scare mongoring is not something I recommend.
👉On the opposite scale of things, fasting is not for everyone. It is not some miracle weight loss programme. It is simply, consuming fewer calories in a smaller space of time. It works for some people it doesn't for others. I personally like to push my breakfast out to 9 or 10am because my days are long. If I start eating when I get up, I'd eat too much calories, simply because I'm eating too many times 😂
.
.
We over complicate everything 🙈😂 Please don't listen to celebrities or unqualified people about these topics🤔
.
.
It's (for the most part - not all cases I.e someone who's diabetic etc) this simple. If you want to eat breakfast eat it. If you don't, don't.
💥Fasted cardio is useless unless you are in a calorie deficit.
💥Your body will not 'eat itself' if you skip breakfast.

T. U. T (Time under Tension) or Tempo 💥
.
.
This is not something I discuss regularly because this is normally an advance on normal gym training. I tend to keep things simple for people because people over complicate everything 🙄 Basics first always 😂
.
.
But as most people are probably struggling with equipment this may be a handy tool 👌
.
.
TUT or Tempo refers to how long or how much time a muscle is under strain. The longer time your muscle is under stress the greater muscle fiber recruitment it will have. You will usually load the muscle in the eccentric phase (downward portion of the exercise). So as you are lowering yourself in a Squat or lowering yourself down from a pull up. In the videos, I am slowly controlling my movements. The weight is light but because I am using TUT and adding more reps I am getting more bang for my buck 💶💶💶
.
.
Hope this helps with getting Lean in Quarantine 💥💥💥 #tut #tempo #pausesquats #getmorebangforyourbuck #homeworkouts #trainingalone #imissthegym #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitfood #fitfam #irishinsydney #irishfitfam

👉 We need to eat protein 🍗 We need loads of colour in our diet 🥭🍓🥦 We need fibre 🍚 And we need to keep active 🏃‍♀️ We need good immune systems to get through this time ❤️ Don't think 'you are healthy and young'. ☢️ Nobody is immune ❌
.
.

The last 2 weeks has just been absolutely Crazy. In every sense of the word.
.
.
I know we've all had it tough but I can promise you my friends have had it tougher. And not being there to comfort them has been so hard 😢 I've had tough times in my life but this is different. I've never felt this way. I know nobody has. But I needed time to reflect. Time to be present.  Social media takes up a lot of my time. And I'm glad I took a little time away. I needed it.
.
.
I was however keeping an eye on all the amazing work people are doing in Ireland ❤️ I've never been so proud to be Irish. I'm also so proud of all the gyms have been doing to keep there members ❤️ @fullbodyworkhouse And while physical health during this time is Absolutely vital. Please do not take for granted your mental health ❤️ It's very easy at a time like this with financial worries and future uncertainty for mental health to deteriorate. Please please please look after yourselves and anyone vulnerable (not just to physical problems but also sufferers of depression and/or anxiety) ❤️
.
.
I will be jumping on the home workouts bandwagon 😁🙌 Let's help get each other through these tough times ❤️🙌 Love to you all from Oz 😘
.
P.s this photo was one of the first times all week I relaxed, smiled and laughed😂 I promise to take care of myself more for the next few weeks X

Let's talk labelling ✨✨✨ .
.
I'm a big fan of this type of labelling in Australia 👌👌👌
.
.
In Ireland, we have a traffic light system which in my opinion is very flawed. Foods receive green, amber and red lights. It is based solely on calories. Fats contain 9kcal per gram. So technically they are high in calories. But certain foods like nuts, nut butters and avocados while high in calories are full of other nutrients. But fats themselves are essential for fat soluble vitamin absorption, reducing inflammation and it's also an energy source. So should these high calorie foods receive a red light? 🤔 Foods are not just calories. ❌❌❌
.
.
This labelling gives a foodstuff a health indicator rather than a colour. I think it's a much more accurate and truer representation of the food rather than just based on calories alone 👌
.
.
This being said calories are important and you can't just disregard them. Just be mindful and reduce portion size 🤗
.
.
@nathalielennon_ I reckon you'll like this one 🤗🙌 #irishinoz #healthyfood #healthyoptions #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitness #fitlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

Plant Based is defined as a diet consisting mostly of foods derived from plants, including vegetables, grains, nuts, seeds, legumes and fruits. 🤔
.
.
I base most if not all of my meals around plant based foods so... 🤔 So yes I would consider my diet plant based 🥬🥑 And I am in no way vegan. .
.
Veganism is a way of life. I have the height of respect of anyone choosing to do something for health purposes, whether I believe in it or not is irrelevant. But I don't agree with people changing their views or opinions after watching a TV show. I also don't believe anybody should scare monger anyone else into their choices 😔And this goes for anything. Not just food choices. But please don't think by choosing a diet (any diet not just plant based) that automatically makes you exempt from disease. I genuinely know people who take drugs but they adhere to a vegan diet so ya know.... Health 😏
.
.
Anyway the basis of this post is education. Plant based diets don't have to be meat free diets. Natural whole foods like mentioned above should make up a large part of your diet, if health is a priority.  A herbivore is plant based. An omnivore can also be plant based. 🌱

#fitlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #nutrition #nutritionist #realnutrition #fitfam #fitfood #irishfitfam

.
.
Anywho yesterday's programming went something like this:
A1 Squats 3 X 10 @55,55,57.5kg

B1 Hip Thrusters 4 X 10 @85kg (last set dropset)

Finished with some core and DUs 
#training #consistency #onlinecoach #fitliving #strength #strengthtraining #strongwomen #irishinoz #irishinsydney🇮🇪

Pregnancy was once considered a reason to stop all exercise and eat for two. Which often led to excessive weight gain, gestational diabetes, pre eclampsia, difficult births and difficulty with weight loss post partum. Now, obviously pregnancy is massively different for everyone. Unfortunately there is no one size fits all. But the information I'm giving is general recommendations. If you have any further questions. It is probably worth talking it over with your doctor or other medical professional ☺️
.
.
Exercise:
-Studies have shown that exercise during pregnancy can actually lead to easier birthing and healthy weight gain during pregnancy.
-It is also thought to be beneficial for post partum weight loss.
-Guidelines for exercise encourage women to stick with similar exercises prior to pregnancy. Light Resistance based training is highly recommended.
- Adaptations may be needed through different trimesters such as: Not lying on your back for too long or overhead extension exercises may need to be removed. This is very dependent on individuals
- Hiit training may not be recommended after trimester 1 - again very dependent on the individual and their training history but it will become a lot harder
- Light exercise like walking can possibly be done the whole way up until due date
- The main take home point from this is: Exercise during pregnancy is encouraged. Everyone's levels, capabilities and pregnancies are different so go with how you're feeling. Don't over exert yourself. And talk with your coach and doctor 🙏
.
.
Nutrition
- This idea of eating double for two is non sense 🙈
- Calories shouldn't even be increased in first trimester. Daily calories should be increased by about 300Cals in 2nd trimester and 500Cals in 3rd Trimester.
- There may be food aversions or food cravings during pregnancy - this is totally normal.
- Try to stick with whole nutritious foods
- Supplements include: Folic Acid, Vitamin D, Iron and Omega 3 Fatty acids. But talk to your doctor or health are consultant before taking any of these
.
.
Something to be very aware of during pregnancy is labelling. Some food labels distinctly say 'not suitable for pregnancy' so just be aware 💯

caption:
Can you put a price on your health? 🤔🤔
.
.
This is one that I'm a firm believer in.
.
.
€50 a week to be trained in a top quality facility. Are you serious? No way can I afford that. Yet, you're able to afford to go on the piss every weekend 🤔
.
.
€100 a week on food. That's out of my budget. Yet, you spend €150 ón cigarettes every week 🤔
.
.
€50 for a Sports massage? That's ridiculous. Yet, you spend €70 on lunches out every week 🤔
.
.
2 litres of water is impossible. But 8 coffees a day is manageable?
.
.
Supplements are too expensive but 10 weekly fizzy drinks are cheap?
.
.
Sometimes you need to start prioritising what is important to you irrelevant of price 🤔🙈 I moved over to Australia with no job after travelling for 5 weeks. I had no full time job since the 20th December until 9th March 😵😵😵 I still managed to eat decently and train. Why? Because that is my priority. I had to make budget so supplements did take a hit but nutritious food and exercise never left my budget. If I had to stay in a night I did. If I couldn't afford a day trip that was fine. But health is priority to me so even with a lack of money I MADE IT WORK.!!!!! You can too. You just need to prioritise ❤️🙏 #fitness #health #healthylifestyle #priorities #makehealthapriority #fittravel #fitlifestyle #fitfam #irishinsydney #irishinoz #irishfitfam

caption:
I can't say I wasn't a little annoyed at myself when I saw a video of me with a few extra pounds on 😔 I can't say I didn't notice that I now have cellulite 🙈 But do these things define me? 🤔
.
.
Absolutely not. I can change both of these things if I want to. It's 100% in my control. 💯💯💯 BUT I'm choosing not to (for now anyway). My weekends are important to me 🙏 For at least the last decade, I have stayed in weekends. I have been going to bed before 12 on a Saturday night. I've been up early on a Sunday morning. I've been the fresh 🌼. That was a great time in my life and I have no regrets but I'm ready to let my hair down a little. At the moment, I'm not an athlete (never thought I'd say that 🙈). I eat well. I train hard. But I'm not making the sacrifices I did to have the body I had. I accept that. .
.
I'm very happy😁 yes I have an extra few pounds but as a friend pointed out to me, they suit me ❤️ #happiness #health #healthylifestyle #balance #fitlifestyle #fitliving #fitfam #irishfitfam #irishinsydney

caption:
New followers here's a brief synopsis of this page and what I'm about:
.
.
1. Health is number 1 priority to me. Not aesthetics. Not calories or macros. Performance is 2nd most important. This was particularly important when I played football and when I was doing Crossfit competitions. Right now, it's not priority because I have just moved to Australia and I was all over the place with training and a schedule etc. But now that I will have one resuming soon, performance will come back big time 👏
.
.
2. I love food. I love educating people on food and nutrition. I love helping build good relationships with food ♥️ I just love what I do. .
.
3. I am so blessed to have the people in my life that I do. I post soppy things about my boyfriend and sister. I definitely don't give my AMAZING friends enough credit. They have been there during good times and bad and I cannot express in words how much I love them.
.
.
4. I am one of these annoying, motivating, smiling at 6am people. But I haven't always been like that. No more than anyone else I've had tough times in my life so don't let that happy exterior fool you 😔
.
.
5. This page was started as a motivator to help me. It's probably done a 360 in recent times. I no longer need motivation as this is now my lifestyle. I eat well, I train hard and I socialise. I'm a normal person. I eat ice cream and drink just not all the time. I don't have abs, but I have strong legs. I sweat in the gym profusely 😂 I'm not some beautiful flawless influencer. I'm real 💯
.
.

caption:
Nail the basics first...🙏🙏🙏
.
.
Today I started a new programme. I'm not gonna lie, I've been slacking on the programme front for quite awhile now🤷 I suppose I didn't really have any set goals for awhile, but there is no mistaking the obvious, programmes work 🙊 They've worked for my clients so why wouldn't I use my own programme 😂 Now I have goals 🤗 So I need to keep a structure. ☑️
If you are doing random workouts without any structure, are you seeing results? 🤔 Are you copying fitness bloggers and expecting results? 🤔 Are you trying to out train a bad diet? 🤔
.
.
Do you really need to be doing the 45 degree Single Arm Lateral Raise with a 4010 tempo? 🤔 Oh but I seen a fitness blogger doing it 💩
.
.
All my fitspos are doing Crossfit now. I'm gonna try to do a Handstand Push Up...🤕🤕🤕
.
.
My favourite online coach says to eat avocados so now I'm force feeding myself avocados 🥑🤦
.
.
Please keep it simple. Most people will never need to do gymnastics so why would you copy me doing this🤦 Get a coach, get accountable, do the basics and eat well. The rest will look after itself 🥰
.
.
P.s yes I did tangle myself in the ropes 😂

#gymnastics #dothesimplethingsright #fitness #fitliving #fitaustrailia #trainer #onlinecoach

Sydney so far...
.
.
👉 I am absolutely loving the aray of healthy food options over here. It makes eating well so easy🙏 That being said I haven't been 100% healthy 😅🙈 The unhealthy options are tempting too 😂
👉 There are gyms and fitness centres everywhere 😍🙏 Gone be the days of Asia where I had to trek kms just to get to a gym 😂 Again, the lifestyle is so geared towards health 🤗
👉 Water is readily available. This is a great incentive to refill water at these stations which are located all over the place. Also, there are water taps on bars which has been an absolute life saver for me the last 2 nights out 🙈😂
👉 Last night I got sniffed by a dog for drugs 😳 It was an experience to say the least
👉 On Sundays, all public transport is $2.80. What a great incentive to get out and get exploring.
👉 Coffee is great 😍☕
.
.
So far, so good 🙏🤗 #austrailia #travelling #irishinsydney #happy #happinessis #fitlifestyle #fitaustralia

💥💥💥Fun fact 💥💥💥
.
.
I didn't eat fruit or vegetables until I went to college (studying to be a nutritionist🙈). And at that it was VERY limited. Maybe the odd orange and carrots with dinner. 🙈 @len_tils was my saviour when I moved to Sheffield with her. She had me eating food I would never ever eat 😂Even if I did make her chop vegetables into the tiniest pieces 😂 My point is I changed a habit. Not only did I change it, I absolutely did a 360 🤗 (I don't do things by halves 😝)
.
.
When people come to me with: I don't eat this or I don't like that or I don't eat any vegetables etc. I see that as a choice. Its absolutely fine if you are one of these people and choose to 'be picky'. No one is expected to like everything 😂 I still cannot eat Cauliflower and I'm not a fan of asparagus but I am much more open to trying new things. And not once, because that is not enough. They say if you still cannot stand something after the 3rd try, there's a good chance you like it. 🤷‍♀️
.
.
💥💥💥Another fun fact 💥💥💥
I only started eating salads about 4 years ago. After years of telling myself I don't like iceberg lettuce and tomatoes (still don't) I realised that's not the only salad that exists 😑😳 If you think you don't like salad, don't make it with items you don't like 😅😜 I base most of mine on rocket or spinach, add as much colour Usually Beetroot, carrot, Cucumber, sun-dried tomato, a cheese and finish it with fruit 😍 I love fruit in salad. And salads shouldn't just be a summer thing🚫🚫🚫Add a warm meat, fish or meat alternative, add a warm grain like cous cous, quinoa or pasta and voila ☑️☑️☑️
.
.
Stop holding yourself back from the healthiest version of you 🤗

#fitfood #nutriton #nutritionist #fitlifestyle #fitliving #fitfam #fitaustralia #irishfitfam

What defines health? 🤔
.
.
Let me tell you what I think it is...
.
.
❌Health is not a low body fat
❌Health is not training excessively
❌Health is not clean eating
❌Health is not being mindful
❌Health is not sleeping 8 hours a day
❌Health is not 1 thing
.
.
Health is different to everyone. Health has a physical aspect but it has a huge mental aspect too. Obsessing about calories is not healthy, YOLOing isn't either. A measure on a scales is certainly not a definition of health. Eating whole nutritious foods is amazing but if you are constantly thinking about all the foods 'you can't have', that's not healthy. Sleeping 8 hours a day but stressing for the other 16 is not healthy. And training is important but if it's consuming you, affecting relationships, affecting your physical or mental health that obviously is not healthy.
.
.
I want to help people. I want to help them develop a healthy relationship with food and exercise. I want to help them stop being so hard on themselves and celebrate little victories. I want to cut this idea that exercise is just a way to burn calories. I want people to stop obsessing over calories. I want to help ❤️ if you want my help. Pm me.

#happiness #goodrelationships #healthyrelationships #behappy #behealthy #fitlifestyle #fitliving #fitaustralia

What is my main aim of coaching clients? 🤔🤔🤔
.
.
❌ It's not weight loss ❌ It's not getting stronger
❌ It's not getting fitter
❌ It's not even improving your body shape.
.
.
⬆️⬆️⬆️⬆️⬆️⬆️⬆️⬆️⬆️
All of the above are by products.
My main aim is to find a lifestyle that is healthy and sustainable. Healthy doesn't always mean 'eating healthy foods' sometimes showing people they can have 'treats' actually makes people healthier. I deal with all my clients individually and help them create a healthy relationship with food and exercise.
.
.
I would say at least 90% of my clients have disordered eating in some form. Some know it, some don't. I have had it. And I've found a light at the end of a tunnel. So this is my main aim. Yes, I give nutrition plans. Yes, I provide training plans. But my programmes are more than that.
.
.
Previous or current clients are more than welcome to comment ⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️ #onlinecoach #changinglifestyles #changingopinions #nutrition #realresults

caption:
I am so excited to finally become an actual Crossfit member in Australia 🙈

I started Crossfit about a year ago but due to Inter County football I could never give it full commitment. In season (January - October) I was probably only doing it once or twice a week. As soon as Championship started I actually had to give it up as training intensity was just too high and I'm no spring chicken anymore😂
In season I competed in 2 competitions, which I took podium at both🥇🥉
As soon as football was finished I had time to give it my full commitment. I did my first Open which was the biggest learning experience🙏 And I did my first competition with training🏆

Why Crossfit?
I have been training consistently at a high level for at least 14 years. I have played Intercounty football since I was 12 and anyone that knows me as a player, knows my (probably only) strength is my engine. So I have a very good capacity. I have also been consistently weight training for 5 years so my strength is decent too. I have a huge competitive nature so pushing myself outside my comfort zone is something that I thoroughly enjoy. Crossfit seemed like a perfect match and so far it's ticking all the right boxes☑️☑️☑️ I also absolutely love the incredible sense of achievement and community spirit within it 😊

Do I recommend Crossfit to everyone?
Like with any high intensity sport, injuries happen. Up until now, I have trained for Crossfit alone. Something I would not recommend to people. I am a fully Qualified trainer (not crossfit coach) but I'm competent in in my exercise execution. If you are a beginner, I would recommend getting a baseline before starting crossfit. And get a good trainer. Unfortunately, Crossfit gets a bad rap for under Qualified coaches but this is actually minimal. I have yet to come across a bad one, but they exist (and not just in Crossfit may I add, i have seen worse in the GAA). To answer the above question, no I do not Recommend RX Crossfit to everyone. But that doesn't mean that everyone cannot enjoy it to a certain level. Most gyms do some sort of cross training🤷‍♀️ I do not endorse Crossfit. I do not recommend it for everyone. But right now, I'm loving it ❤️🙏

caption:
Tips on travelling and how to maintain a  good lifestyle while away:
.
.
1. Don't drink your calories.
 If you are going to go on the lash every day chances are you will gain weight 😒 Also, if you're adding a lot of extra calories through drinks (even healthy ones) you may put on weight. Let's take a smoothie for breakfast with breakfast, a milkshake with lunch, sipping on Fanta throughout the day and 2 cocktails at night. That will probably clock up an extra 500-1000 cals a day. 🙊 Stick to water. Or a coke zero is an absolute life saver if you're craving a little sweetness 🙏
.
.
2. You don't need to be in the gym to stay active.
 Did you know your NEAT contributes more to your metabolic rate than Purposeful exercise? I may not be training much but I'm getting between 15-30k steps every day. So get swimming, walking, hiking or kayaking. If you want to laze by the pool, that's fine but don't be suprised if your body feels tired and sluggish 😬
.
.
3. Get at least one decent meal in.
 I try to opt for eggs and fruit for breakfast. This way I can leave a little lenancy for dinner 😜 You should enjoy yourself at the end of the day but you want to feel good at the same time. Try opt to snack on fruit and nuts instead of ice cream and crisps the whole time 🙊
.
.
4. I'm weird about salads in developing countries. The water is so dirty over here so if that's what they use to clean it, I try to veer away. I do get veggies cooked, normally in a curry or stir fry 👌
.
.
5. That leads me onto my next point. Be weary of meat. I tend to go pescatarian when away as the meat quality just isn't  the same 🙈
.
.
6. A few things to have handy: Bug Spray, tissues, plasters, iodine, after sun, antibacterial gel, wipes and a fan 😂😂😂
.
.
7. Invest in a Go Pro. They are worth it.
.
.
Travel is amazing and should be enjoyed but if you want to stay comfortable and not self conscious maybe points 1-3 may help. 4 to 7 are just some of my tips and to be honest I probably have a million more I've forgotten 🙊
.
.
#tipsandtricks #travel #instatravel #fitliving #fitlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #irishfitfam

New year, New me 🙌
.
.
Each year since my Dad died I have vowed to put myself first. I'm not great at it tbh. I let work come first, football, looking after others and my needs and wants came after all those things 🙈
.
.
If my friends or family, hear the word organised they will probably think of me. I organise my organisation 😂😂😂 So when I decided to leave my job and head to the other side of the world at (almost) 29, I'd say people couldn't believe it 🙈 But it's something I had to do. ❤️
.
.
I genuinely thought I'd be married and have a child before 30. I thought I'd have my career sorted. But dya know what... I couldn't be happier. I am currently travelling with the love of my life @o_boyce and with no job organised we hope to start up a new adventure in Sydney.
.
.
It's OK to be almost 30 and not have a certain plan. It's OK to not have a mortgage. It's OK to be single. It's OK to not have a career. .
.
Life is what you make it. You are a product of your environment. I believe good things are coming my way so here's to a positive outlook on 2020❤️🙌 I hope you all have the same YOLO attitude 🙋
.
.
P. S Beach pics will cease for awhile as I am currently in Kuala Lumpur and it is raining 🤣🤣🤣

caption:
How incredible does @imeldascally look 😍🙌
.
.
I took part in Amanda's 6 week programme and it was honestly one of the best things I've ever done for myself! After just moving jobs my routine and head was all over the place, I always loved the gym but looking for a new job took over and I didn't have any motivation for working out. I decided to do this programme to get me back into the right mindset which it did, I wanted a food plan that I could maintain and wasn't impossible to stick too (ie I could have amazing chocolate bars FibreOne will forever be my favourite treat lol😂) and I also wanted a gym plan that was sustainable which it is! Amanda was always at the end of the phone to answer any questions, the online Facebook group had plenty of demos to help and her phone calls and Voice tags were always so encouraging! She really knows what she is talking about and you can tell she truly passionate about her clients. I have never felt better and i am going to carry on with my new lifestyle 😍❤️ I started at 71.1kg and I'm down to 69.9kg (I did want to get back in the 60 zone) I have toned up and feel super healthy all thanks to a wonderful programme by Amanda 😘 Xxx
.
.
New Clients starting up soon 🙏⭐ I am currently full but will let people know if anything becomes available 👌

caption:
As you can see from my feed I have began to love Crossfit 💋
.
.
I didn't always love it and actually I was a huge skeptic. My friends know this as some of them have questioned me on it 🤔 But my views and opinions on so many things over the years have changed. I also believed that a restrictive 'clean' diet was the healthiest diet there could be, forgetting the impact that restriction has on your mental health 🤷‍♀️🤷‍♀️
.
.
I have made so many mistakes over the years I've been in the health and fitness industry. I've called foods 'good' and 'bad', and I've shunned certain exercise routines. But from experience comes knowledge and wisdom. 🙏 And I am a lot more open minded to things now 👌
.
.
I don't think Crossfit is for everyone. It's a seriously stringent training regime which requires a huge level of mobility, strength and conditioning. Even at a regressed level, it can be overwhelming and injury levels can be high due to poor training technique or poor coaching (this is obviously not all coaches). But I also don't think everyone should be running. Poor running technique can contribute to any number of problems with joints, ligaments, tendons or muscle strains.
.
.
I am a firm believer in anyone starting out on a fitness journey, to look around. Find what works for you. There's not a one size fits all. I would normally say to get a coach to steer you in the right direction and then you'll find a lifestyle you can enjoy ❤️ Because exercise should not be a punishment 🙏

#fitliving #ineedtopostthiscauseiwontbetrainingforawhile
#fitlifestyle

I actually love Cardio 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️(except rowingit's the devil's exercise 😂) .
.
Coming from a football background, cardio was my first love fitness wise 👌I'm not gonna lie, I love that breathlessness feeling. I feel it always shows me I've pushed myself 😉 And being honest, running is the highest my heart rate goes to (even when I don't think it and some of the other sessions I do feel way worse 🙈)
And I'm one of the very few Assault Bike fans.
. .
But let me tell you something, if you think you're going to change your body shape by doing cardio alone. You're so wrong 🙈
.
.
Sweat should not be a determinant of a 'good session'. Again, I love the feeling of a good sweaty session. But quite often my weights sessions barely work a pore, does this mean they are not as beneficial? ABSOLUTELY NOT!!! Resistance training is and should be priority. No matter what your goals?
👉 Weight loss, gain or maintenence (along with calorie manipulation)
👉 Reduce injury risk
👉 Stronger bones, joints, ligaments, tendons
👉 General strength and fitness
.
.
If you have not already realised how important resistance training is, make it a goal and priority for 2020 💪

#cardio #cardiobunnyatheart #weightlifting #resistancetraining #fitliving #fitness #fitlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
You're telling me, you can actually enjoy Christmas? 😳😳😳
.
.
Every other year I've given tips on 'how to not lose all your hard work over Christmas'. This year I'm taking a different approach.
.
.
I plan to train less over Christmas. Before, I would panic about this. Oh but 'Will I lose all my strength?'. 'What about all the chocolate I've eaten'😭 I now have a good relationship with exercise. I don't plan on sitting on my arse all Christmas but my normal 6 day training week will probably reduce to 3. Why? To facilitate for spending time with friends and family ❤️ This Christmas is even more important than others that I spend valuable time with friends and family as I'm moving in 2.5 weeks 😱 But training is a part of my lifestyle so I won't be going cold turkey on it (Christmas pun or what🤪)
.
.
As always I will enjoy myself. But as usual, good nutritious food makes me feel best so I will stick mostly to what I know and enjoy the treats too ✌️ I won't take the p#*s. 🐷🚫
.
.
Lastly and most importantly, when the 5th of January rocks up and I'm about to get into a bikini I will not be hard on myself. I will cherish the weeks over Christmas. I will be grateful for the food I CAN eat. I won't be resentful of the extra few pounds I will probably gain. And I will rock that bikini 👙🌟
.
.
Christmas starts for me today 🎊🌟🎉Haha although I know for most it started 2 weeks ago 🍹🍸🍬🍴 #christmasisaroundthecorner #holidaysarecoming #behappy #begrateful #happinessis #fitliving #fitlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Travelling Workout 🏖️🌍
.
.
A lot of you had asked will I be training on holidays 🤔 The plan is to definitely keep up a minimum level of training while travelling while including a lot of hiking and extra steps 👣👣👣
.
.
I'm not gonna lie, a good gym is what motivates me 💪 I don't have much interest in a Hiit Bodyweight session 🙈 But if there is no option for a good gym in some of the places I am here are some of the exercises I will keep up 🤞
.
.
1. Skipping - This is definitely one I will be keeping up. Since I bought my new rope I'm going to use this as an opportunity to improve my DUs
2. Squats - BW air Squats are pretty easy for me so I've progressed them to pulse Squats here
3. Lunges - Again, normal Lunges are pretty regressed for me so I've added an OH Walking Lunge option
4. Push Ups - Still one of the hardest exercises to perfect
5. Core Work - Being honest I probably won't do these as I hate doing isolated core work but I've added it in for any of you thinking about home workouts 😜
.
.
I will probably add Burpees as I love a good Burpee but not everyone can or should do them so I haven't added them. Hope this helps some of you 😁 I hope to do most of my training in gyms but this is an option for when there are no gyms to avail of 🤷‍♀️ #fullbodyworkout #fitliving #fitlife #fitlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #exercise #fitfam #irishfitfam

It's easy to assume I've always been confident 🤔
.
.
I've always been the loudest in the room
.
I've never been afraid to show a little skin
.
Attention seeker was my middle name
.
.
Delve a little deeper and you'd have seen a very vulnerable girl, terrified to show how insecure she truely was 😢
I was the girl who couldn't be seen without make up. The girl who was more than uncomfortable in her own skin 😩 I conformed to norms & standards that I thought I 'had to'. I was being someone I wasn't. And I'm well aware this is a vast majority of women unfortunately 😭
.
.
But I'm at a stage in my life where I am now so happy and confident in myself ❤️
A girl who once thought I had to have life sorted by 30 is off to Austrailia next year.✈️ A girl who was obsessed with having a 'perfect body' is thriving in her strong body 💪 Instead of designer handbags and expensive jewellery, I'm more interested in what tattoo I'm going to get next 😂 And did I mention I got a nose piercing at 28 😜
.
.
So don't make assumptions. Yes I'm at a place in my life where I'm happy, but I haven't always been there. It can take a long time. It takes a lot of self care. But it's worth it. And don't be afraid to be who you are 💕

#confidence #confident #travel #movingaway #getmesomesun #3weekstoday #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitlife #fitfam #irishfitfam

Absolutely BURSTING with Pride right now 🌟🌟🌟
.
.
It's not our first time to host a charity event in @fullbodyworkhouse. We've actually held a lot in the 3 years I've been working there ❤️ The support seems to get better every time 🙏
.
.
This is NOT just a gym. This isn't even just a community. This is a family.
.
.
Encouragement is one thing. What I saw some of these people do for their team mates today, you can only compare that to what you'd do for your family ❤️
.
.
I know I'm leaving in 3 weeks but I honestly don't think I've been prouder of anything in my life than I am of this gym and the people in it 💕💕👆👆

caption:
A rare find... A Good Avocado 🥑🥑🥑
.
.
I'm a big avo fan 😻 Smashed, in Guacamole, sliced... The list goes on 💗
.
.
Sure its high in calories but that's due to the fat content. Did you know that we need Good Fats in our diet for Hormone balance, insulation, absorption of fat soluble vitamins and energy? And that's just a few of it's benefits 🙏 It's also a good source of fibre, is a source of potassium and B group vitamins. It's a health food gold mine in my opinion 👌
If weight loss is a goal, eat less of it. If health is a goal, eat more. 🤗 OH AND PLEASE FOR THE LOVE OF GOD, DON'T CALL IT A SYN 😩
.
.
Hands up if ya love some avo🥑

#goodfats #antiinflammatory #healthylifestyle #healthfood #fitliving #avocado #healthiswealth #fitlife #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
I've always been very open minded. I pride myself on it actually. I've alway been a pro choice kinda girl in all aspects of life (not just health and fitness related). You'll never hear me boast about one type of diet or slate any either. You won't hear me downgrade any form of exercise, although I do openly talk about the huge benefits of resistance training 💪 I'll never tell any of my client's 'You have to do this type of exercise' or 'you cannot eat this for weight loss'. So you see I'm very open minded. If someone who loves yoga comes to me, I'm not going to force them to lift weights. And if someone who is vegan comes to me, I would not force them to eat animal products. My problem with any of these things lies in the misinformation. .
.
Did you know that vegan fast food production has sky rocketed in recent years? 🤔 Similarly, a few years ago, gluten free products were a huge trend? And before that, sugar free was the hype? This I have a problem with.
.
.
Veganism is a lifestyle choice. I have huge respect for anyone's lifestyle choices, whether they conform to my own is irrelevant. What actually annoys me is actual vegans are getting a terrible name due to all these people jumping on the bandwagon, thinking veganism is the healthiest lifestyle going. People are going into this lifestyle, uneducated and naive. 😒 It was the same a few years ago when gluten free was the buzzword. Did you know you can have a totally adequate, balanced, healthy diet without adding one gluten free product? And thats for ACTUAL coeliacs out there, because they are the ONLY people that need to be eating gluten free toast 😂
.
.
What my very long winded post is trying to say is stop jumping on bandwagons. If you are and always have been vegan, that's fine. Continue with your choices. If you are coeliac, continue with your gluten free bread 🙈 For the rest of you, stop following trends by the latest celebrity diet. Stop conforming to social norms ✊ Stop basing your beliefs on a bloody stupid documentary 😒 Get some advice from a professional. 🙏 Follow said advice 🌈 And stop eating Vegan Fast Food, surely it tastes revolting? Anyone care to let me know 🤔🤔🤔

#hspus #cleanandjerk #olympicweightlifting #progressnotperfection #littlebylittle #keepworking #fitliving #fitlife #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #healthylifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

Health and Travel
.
.
These are my 2 of my biggest priorities at the moment ❤️✈️
.
.
But let me tell you this. One is much more important than the other. Because without one, we would be seriously limited 🤔
.
.
Health should be EVERYONES number 1 priority. Health is different to everyone. It's not necessarily eating clean or training. But it involves a physical and mental component. Without good health, we restrict ourselves in so many ways. It should be a priority over every single other goal/task in your life ❤️
.
.
For me prioritising my health involves:
🙏 Eating a diet with wholesome, nutritious food but not depriving myself if I want some chocolate
🙏 Exercising daily - because I love my body, not hate it
🙏 Social interactions - I thrive on talking to people. Always have. My job helps me with this. If I'm not working, I'm meeting friends and family
🙏 Organisation - sounds silly but not being organised would spark anxiety problems. I don't want that therefore, I am highly organised
🙏 Sleep - no explanation needed
🙏 Being selfish from time to time - I've always been selfless. I've always put everyone else first. These days I have a healthy balance ❤️
🙏 Reading - whether it's light reading or learning
.
.
If you are not prioritising your health you need to. You need to start doing things for yourself. You need to start looking after your body because believe me, we won't be here forever 😔

I'm all about that balanced life 💯💯💯
.
.
But choose wisely 🤔
.
.
Not all foods are equal.
.
.
So take the humble sausage. A staple in a good 'Irish Breakfast'. There are different types of sausages: Veggie or meat. Then meat can be broken down into: pork, turkey, chicken, beef... But even a meat sausage can be 50% meat (50% God knows what) or it can be 85%. It can be 80 calories or 280 calories. It can be grilled or it can be fried 🤷‍♀️🤷‍♀️🤷‍♀️ So is a sausage really just a sausage? 🤔
.
.
What I recommend:
👉 A sausage is no harm in moderation. And I mean moderation. It is still processed even the highest quality ones.
👉 Check calorie content - huge differences between products
👉 Grill don't fry

Self Praise is No Praise ❌❌❌
.
.
Wrong 🔴🔴🔴
.
.
It's absolutely perfectly normal and appropriate to give yourself a pat on the back. I used to be of the opinion that only 'cocky' people praise themselves. This couldn't be further from the truth. We should all be doing it. It's actually so important 🙈 You wouldn't say the things you say about yourself about anyone else 😔😔😔 In the words of Jess Glynne 'Don't be so hard on yourself'.
.
.
I've become very self aware the last year or so thanks to some great advice I got. I've started looking out for myself. Working on myself. And it's given me a new lease of life ❤️
.
.
👉I'm proud of all the adversities I've overcome 💯
👉 I'm proud of the work I do on a daily basis. 💯
👉 I'm proud of the commitment and effort I give into everything I do. 💯
👉 I'm proud of becoming a little more selfish and putting myself first 💯
.
.
Think of 3 things you could praise yourself for❤️🙌🤔 #selfpraise #bekindtoyourself

caption:
First ever Crossfit Open.. OVER AND OUT 👏👏👏
.
.
EXPECTATIONS before the Competition :
👉 Compete in Scaled and try to finish all Wods.
.
.
REALITY:
👉 Surpassed every expectation possible 🙆🙆🙆
.
.
20.1 - Learnt me to NEVER EVER do an Open Workout hungover - this is the only workout I can say I'm a little disappointed with as I know I could have done better had I not went on the tear the night before 😂
.
.
20.2 - Learnt me Double Unders are my ARCH NEMISIS... 😭 I absolutely hate them but will continue to try and improve
.
.
20.3 - Made me realise doing elevated HSPUs has not helped 😔😂 From the ground is sooo much harder. Huge improvements in these. Not the most neck friendly exercise 😏
.
.
20.4 - My favourite ❤️ I pushed past all expectations in this one. Learning to do split jerks and realising I can actually do pistols 😜
.
.
20.5 - Made me realise I still have a LONG way to go 👆👆👆
.
.
This was one of the most amazing experiences ever. I know I sound dramatic but I actually mean it. I came into this Open having very little experience and even less knowledge. I have been a part time Crossfitter at best so to be able to compete in all RX wods was beyond any expectation I ever had. Each week I pushed outside every boundary I have ever built. And believe me, its something we can all do. In any area of life 💕
.
.
To top it all off I achieved my goal of top 20% in the country. (I was actually even close to my TOTALLY unrealistic goal of top 100). To my amazement I even placed in the top 20% in the World 😍💪 This sport is not for everyone but it is DEFINITELY FOR ME 🙏Watch this space 💪😜
.
.
Massive thanks to @fusion_mma_crossfit_cuchulainn and @craughwell17_ who helped me every week. Honestly, without their encouragement this could have been a totally different post 🙏

#crossfitgirls #crossfitopen #intheopen #open2020 #crossfitopen2020 #rx #fitliving #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #irishfitfam

The weekend is almost over... Are you really trying to achieve your goals or are you just kidding yourself 😬🤔
.
.
If you are like my clients and making a conscious effort everyday to create new, better habits. Then well done 👏👏👏
.
.
It's not about perfection. It's about consistency. It's about 'trying'. If a client says to me, 'Amanda I had a meal out for my sister' s birthday, I stuck to a decent dinner but I did have dessert'😬. I count this as a win. Before, this client would have a starter, main and dessert without even a thought about the nutrition content of the food. Now, they are making a conscious decision to have a healthier dinner but still enjoy dessert. They didn't overdo it by having 3 courses. It's about progress, not perfection 👏👏👏
.
.
On the other hand, if someone told me, they went out of their way to order a takeaway 'because they had a bad week at work'. I'd be a little less impressed 🤐 I try to help my clients with emotional eating. And not using food as a coping mechanism. Again, it's about progress. If this happened once, mistakes happen. If it was a continuous cycle, I would express my disappointment. 😏
.
.
I said last week I was going to try and 'treat myself' less frequently. Which to be fair, I actually did. But then I visited family over the weekend and they were all about treating me 😂 I enjoyed myself but I didn't take the absolute piss either 😒 My goals are not aesthetic based and are more based on energy and performance levels so I want to keep my diet as nutritious as possible as that's the food that makes me feel the best 💪
.
.
If you want to change, I mean really WANT to change, make small changes. If you don't, that's fine too, but stop wasting your time, your money and your energy 🙄
.
.
Ready for Monday after a relaxing weekend and a belly full of spuds 🤣

#makingchanges #smallchanges #fitliving #fitlife #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #healthylifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
I've been called: 'too skinny' 'too tiny' 'too healthy' 'too muscely' 'too lean' 'too obsessed'....
.
.
Why do we have to be 'too' anything??🤐
.
.
🚫I am healthy yes but what makes me 'too healthy'? Just because I don't want to get a takeaway. Or don't need a donut for lunch. Or because I've never had a breakfast roll 😬
🚫 Maybe I am obsessed. Maybe I do want to be the best version of myself. I love pushing myself to boundaries. I always have. If that's obsessed, then yes I'm guilty. But there's a lot worse I could be obsessed with 🤦‍♀️
🚫 And as for how I look. That should never be commented on. Its no one's business. And why do we have to be 'too' anything? 🙄
.

❓❓❓Did you know that Whey is a by product of cheese production? Yes you heard right. Its a simple dairy bi product that is dried and may have lactose or fats removed during production 🙈❓❓❓
.
.
So if you are on the bandwagon of thinking whey protein has some sort of steroid included or has some sort of extra powers, I'm afraid your both wrong.
.
.
It's not needed in everyone's diets. But if you are someone who:
👉 Does not get enough protein in their diet its a good source of protein and is convenient and easily absorbed.
👉 Trains a lot and finds it hard to get in the amount of protein you need. It's a great addition. Remember it is a supplement do that's exactly what it should do. Supplement the diet.
.
.
🚫 It will not make you bulky
🚫 It is not only for athletes
🚫 It is not only required after the gym
.
.
I'm not going to compare it nutritionally to milk. But if you're a person who would drink a glass of milk, but wouldn't drink a protein shake, maybe think twice 🤔

#wheyprotein #beinformed #nutrition #fitliving #eatforhealth #eatforperformance
#goodchoices #healthylifestyle #healthyliving #healthiswealth #fitfam #irishfitfam

I wish I could help more women 💕💕💕
.
.
If I had my way, I would start women on a journey of self love from their early teens. This is an age they can be thought to love themselves and their bodies ♥️ Its an age they start to learn, develop and mould their personalities. The older we get and the longer we hate our bodies the harder it is to get away from that idea 😪 And I'm saying this from experience. I had so many body confidence issues😭
.
.
But it starts with you 👆👆👆
.
.
👉 Start Loving what your body CAN do not what it can't
👉 Appreciate your strengths - we all have them. Stop focusing on your weaknesses
👉 Take more time for yourself
👉 Stop using exercise as a tool to punish yourself for what you've eaten
👉 Look at food as energy and nutrients not focusing solely on calories 👉 Surround yourself with incredible people who lift you up, not put you down
👉 Remove toxicity - relationships, friends, feelings
👉 Pay someone a compliment - saying something nice to someone actually has a positive effect on the giver, not just the receiver. And what comes around goes around 🙏
👉 STOP COMPARING YOURSELF TO OTHERS - THIS IS THE THIEF OF ALL JOY. YOU ARE NOT SOMEONE ELSE. STOP TRYING TO BE LIKE SOMEONE ELSE 🚫
.
.
Let's share some love 💕
.
.
P. S Yes this is a picture of me sweaty and red faced. But I literally couldn't be happier, doing something I absolutely love with one of my favourite humans in the world @lauramcloone ❤️❤️❤️ #selflove #selfcare #loveyourself #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitlife #fitfam #irishfitfam

One thing that grinds my gears is people overconsuming liquid calories 🙈🙈🙈
.
.
I actually understand how hard it is to reduce or eliminate foods we all enjoy like chocolate 🤤 Or Crisps, maybe even Bread or Takeaways. These foods usually require a lot of make you full (satiation). But there does come a point where you will feel full. Liquid calories however will never leave you feeling sated. 🤷‍♀️🤷‍♀️🤷‍♀️
.
.
1. Liquid calories include juices we consider 'just a drink', they may be a healthier option but they contain calories too. This is a very easy way to cut calories by eliminating these juices and replacing with water.
.
.
2. Fizzy drinks. This one still baffles me. I'm not a fizzy drink fan but the odd time I get a little craving 😜 But there are 'zero' options in EVERY drink these days 🤷‍♀️Why would you even consider the sugar alternative!? 😏
.
.
3. Alcohol contains calories. Quite often a lot of them. Drinking is fine. But be aware it doesn't go unaccounted for. But 'banking calories' for drinking can have dangerous consequences. Firstly, drunkoxeria is a very real thing. People starving themselves the day of a drinking binge 'to save calories'. Can we please stop saying things are 'bad' and 'good'. Go out every so often. Drink a sensible amount. Be aware it's not calorie free. The end.
.
.
4. Hot drinks. Tis the season and all that🥶 Hot chocolates and festive coffees are a sure way to boost your daily calorie consumption without a second thought. And I can tell you those 400 cals will not leave you as full as a nice chicken salad would 🥗😏 We all love a good hazelnut latte but let's just keep it as a treat, not a daily lunchtime special 😜 You'll save yourself some cash too for Christmas 😝
.
.
Tag someone who needs to see this 😂

#liquidcalories #liquidscontaincalories #festivetreats #fizzydrinks #alcohol #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitliving #fitlife #fitfam #irishfitfam

I'm a little bit of a fraud 😳😳😳
.
.
I'm always telling people to get out of a comfort zone... And I have to admit I don't think I come out of my own enough 🤔
.
.
I've always worked on what I'm good at. And I've pushed myself to limits I didn't think even exist. But I have to admit I've had a tendency along the way to neglect what I'm not good at 🙈
.
.
I did it in school. I was good at science and Home Ec so I worked really hard at these subjects and excelled. But English (my dreaded subject) never got the same attention 😮
.
.
I did it in football. I was always fit. But I constantly worked to be fitter instead of working on weaknesses like kicking and shooting 🙈 Oh what could have been 😂
.
.
I've done it in the gym. I've worked hard on improving my strengths while some very obvious weaknesses were left by the wayside. 😮😳
.
.
In the last 3 weeks I have pushed myself harder than I've ever pushed myself... MENTALLY!!!! First with those damn double unders and this weekend with hspus. Before Friday I could only do elevated hspus. Then Friday I miraculously hit 13 reps 😂 Yesterday, I finished the 21 reps. 🥳🥳🥳 Proud is an understatement. 👏👏👏 From now on, I promise to try and work on weaknesses a lot more, In all aspects of my life 🙏
.
.
Are u challenging yourself enough? 🤔

Do you understand what the body is composed of?🤔
.
.
Do you understand the optimal body composition? 🤔
.
.
So as we know we are made up of bone, ligaments, tendons, organs, muscle and fat. 🙈 Yes we all have it. And we all need a certain amount, especially women.
.
Our optimal body composition is to have a lower body fat mass (in healthy proroption s 18 - 28% woman and 8 - 18% man) and a higher lean muscle mass. We also would like a good bone density with strong joints. Strong, healthy, functioning organs would really top it off 👌
.
.
What if I told you with a good, balanced diet and some consistency you could achieve this 🙈😮
.
.
Yes, resistance training ticks all of the above boxes ☑️ Now it's pretty useless information alone because we cannot out train a bad diet but to make a start, try out some bands or body weight exercises. I personally recommend a trainer. Invest in one even just to learn the Ropes and keep you accountable initially.
.
.
And nó you don't have to become an Olympic weightlifter or Crossfitter. Just start with the basics. Learn how to Squat, Bench and Deadlift. Do some assistance exercises. Throw in a little cardio for your heart and lungs ♥️ It doesn't have to be over complicated.

Thank me later 💋
P. S Can I have some sun on my bones again please 🙏

Let's talk portion size 🍽️
.
.
Firstly, this is just a generic reference. It doesn't take into account body weight or goals but it's a good guide all the same 👌
.
.
Protein - palm size portion with every meal. Meat, fish, eggs, Yogurt, cottage cheese
.
Vegetables (not fruit, fruit is a cárb) - fistful with every meal.
.
Carbs - cupped handful with most meals. Grains, peas, fruit, rice, pasta, bread etc
.
Fats - thumbful with most meals. Opt for healthy options like avocado, oils, nuts, nut butter
.
.
Portion size is often a problem.
Other ways to avoid over eating:
🍽️ Try reducing plate size.
🍞 Avoid trigger foods. Contrary to popular belief bread does NOT make you fat. However, if you are having 6 slices of bread a day and you over eat it causing you to be in a calorie surplus you will gain weight 😑 If you feel there are foods like this in your diet that you cannot stop eating, I do recommend eliminating. At least for awhile until you can gain control back on them. It does tend to be carbohydrate dense foods like bread, and pasta. Personally, I keep these as a 'treat' rather than a dietary staple 👌
.
.
Hope thís helps. Happy Weekend ✌️ #portionsize #portioncontrol #fitliving #healthyliving #healthylifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #fitlife #irishfitfam

caption:
Hands up if you love burpees🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️
.
.
I often get asked some of the following:
⚡ How many days a week SHOULD you train?
Answer: How many time a week CAN you train? There is absolutely no point committing to a 5 day programme if all you can fit in is 3/4. You're already setting yourself up for a fail. There is no Right amount of days to train but there is what's right for you
.
⚡ Is rest not important?
Answer: Recovery is vital. Recovery is done through nutrition, hydration, sleep and reducing intensity/volume. Recovery does not necessarily mean sitting on your arse for the day 🤔 I prefer an active recovery with some light movement. You don't need to be totally sedentary.
.
⚡ Is Crossfit not dangerous?
Answer: If you have the capacity, you can increase the load. I'm a huge advocate of the sport but as with ALL sports of course there is a level of risk involved. The problem often lies in the person or trainer rather than the exercise prescription. If you have never done an Olympic lift before and try Snatch 50kg of course it's dangerous 🙄 But I put the problem down to you more than the sport. It may be benificial for any newbies to either start off with some level if weight training or invest in a really good coach ✌️
.
⚡What exercise is Best?
Answer: The one you enjoy and can adhere to ✌️ But if you want the most bang for your buck and are willing to try anything, it doesn't get more beneficial than resistance training 💪
. ⚡How do you keep motivated all the time? You never stop!
Answer: This one is simple. I love it❤️ I love training. I love fuelling my body right. I love that my body is capable of training so hard. We should be so grateful for all we CAN do 😍
.
