Not every transformation is about weight loss 👉👉👉
.
.
After years of doing my own thing in the gym with little or no results I decided to undertake Amanda's 8 week challenge. For me my aim at the end of this challenge was far more about mobility and strength rather then aesthetics. I had experienced so much difficulty from a cartilage issue in my knee that I felt I was so limited in what I could do. In general I'm quiet petite and have never had any issue with my weight however I wanted to see if I could tone up and get stronger while working through the problem with my knee. The program that amanda gave me was absolutely unbelievable.she knew exactly what I was looking for and tailored my plan to include strength exercises that would build up all the muscles around my knee allowing me to lift heavier weights and incorporate more cardio into my routine, something that I had been so afraid of in case I damaged my knee more. The 8 weeks with Amanda is worth so much more then any amount of sessions with a physio. I can now walk around pain free and have mobility back in my knee. My whole body has toned up and I am so much stronger. This program has made me enjoy the gym again and amanda herself is worth her weight in gold both professionally and as a personal friend. I would recommend this program to anyone who wants to change things up a bit or try something different you will not regret it.

Client Testimonial🌟🌟🌟
Having a busy lifestyle with 3 kids and a full time job, I found I was finding it very difficult to fit in classes as you had to make certain times.  Amanda devised a plan around my busy life style,  giving me 4 different  workouts of different durations.  This meant that I could get my gym sessions in when it suited me, I could pick and choose from the longer or shorter workouts depending on the circumstances of the day.  The workouts were switched up a number of times to continue challenging my body and she even managed to give me fantastic, challenging, realistic workouts minus the dreaded burpees!!
The nutritional plan is absolutely fantastic, I never found myself hungry nor did I ever feel I was depriving  myself or “on a diet”. Amanda checked in by phone on a regular basis to see if I needed any information or indeed inspiration and was happy to answer any questions I had for her. 
My results after the 8 weeks have been fantastic, I am so proud of what I have achieved but more importantly what I have learned.  Having spent years dieting and thinking I knew lots about nutrition, I have found that I finally have found a sustainable, healthy way of living and eating. 
Fitness and health are about more than being the perfect size or hitting certain targets in the gym, it’s about training your mind and learning to think differently.  Amanda has given me the tools to do this and I look forward to continuing my journey to a fitter, stronger me and working with Amanda again in the future.  I wouldn’t hesitate to recommend Amanda to anyone.

My top tips to holidays and how to be a little healthier 💯💯💯
.
.
Firstly, this is down to you and your goals and how much you want to achieve them. To me, personally, holidays are holidays. I enjoy them and am totally out of routine. Sometimes I train, sometimes I don't. But these are some tips to help with your goals.
👉 Walk everywhere. I clock up way more steps away than in Ireland. 20,000 plus per day.
👉 Enjoy your food, but don't take the piss. I always opt for a healthier breakfast and got to town on either lunch or dinner 🐷
👉 Keep hydrated. Especially if you are having mimosas at breakfast😂
👉 Skip the snacks. When I'm at home I'm constantly grazing but when I'm away I try to go for 3 main meals.
.
.
Hope thís helps. P. S Budapest had the most amazing Brunch places 😍 Enjoyed it a lot 😊

#howtobehealthieronholidays #brunch #breakfast #weekendaway #citybreaks #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
If you're like me and calorie counting is not your thing. All is not lost. Yes calories matter but so does your life and if you absolutely hate the thought of entering everything you eat into my fitness pal, as a trainer I would never force you 😉Most if not all of my clients have achieved their incredible results from never having entered a calorie or macro into myfitnesspal 👏👏👏
.
.
I am not slating it. It obviously works for people. And whoever uses it and enjoys tracking, go you 👍 There are some reasons why the calories on our food labels don't actually correlate to real life though 🙈So it's not a 100% fool proof method.
👉 Fibre and resistant starches are often overestimated
👉 Some of the data is outdated or the analysis of it was imprecises
👉 Only one product is tested so it doesn't take into account product variety
👉 Soil composition and animals diets are not taken into account
👉 Ripeness at time of harvest. Ever taste in season Irish strawberries vs imported out of season😏
👉 Storage, preparation and cooking of food can change nutritional composition of food
.
.
Some of my top tips if you're not interested in tracking:
💥 Protein at each meal (approx 2g per Kg BW)
💥 Load up on veggies (full of micros and volume, low in calories)
💥 Portion size (use a smaller plate and watch those cárb and fat portions)
💥 Fibre rich foods (fruit, veggies, legumes, some complex carbs)
💥 Drink plenty of water. A lot of the time we're actually thirsty not hungry
.
.
And just keep active. Technically, you don't have to if you're nutrition is on point. But come on, we are so lucky to be able to exercise. Enjoy it 😍

#fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitliving #balance #balancedlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Pancake Tuesday🥞🥞🥞
.
.
There's no right or wrong way to do it. If you want to have your Mam's pancakes lathered in butter, enjoy it. If you want to opt for the healthier option, enjoy it. If you don't want pancakes, don't have them. There's no hard rule. Just whatever you do own it. Don't winge or complain that you've went over your calories. Or don't give out about how boring your banana pancakes with berries were😏😏😏
.
.
I always opt for a little indulgence. I eat well enough of the time, I like to indulge on Pancake Tuesday. But this year I have even more reason to indulge as I am taking on lent tomorrow. 😑😑😑
I'm not religious. I've never pretended to be. But I do love a good challenge 😜 So from tomorrow I am off chocolate and crisps (I'm also scoffing some tayto ripples😂). I don't eat crap like this often so one would think this isn't a big deal for me. But oh on the contrary, I don't eat chocolate often but it is my absolute vice. I will struggle a lot to go without it 😭 But I wanna try💪 I usually take something on at Lent but I think I have more than enough on 😂😂😂😂
.
.
Would love to know if anyone else Is doing anything 👆👆👆 #pancaketuesday #chocoholic #lent #makingsacrifices #fitliving #fitlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance  #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Are you a pitch athlete? GAA, Camogie, Hurling, Soccer, Rugby or Hockey🤔
.
.
Do you resistance train throughout the year? Do you strength train pre season? Are you watching your nutrition? Are you recovering properly?
.
.
These are all factors athletes now need to take into account. It's not as simple as pitch sessions anymore, especially if you're at a higher level 👌👆
.
.
4.5 Years ago I tore my ACL. I was back on the pitch within 6 months and I haven't had any issues since 🤞🤞🤞 For the last 4.5 years I have kept up the strength work I did for rehab. I didn't do it sporadically. I've don't it consistently. I've eaten well. I've maintained a good body composition. Injuries are crap but they are something that cannot be neglected. You need to work on them long after they have 'healed'.
Or you need to prevent them. Either way, resistance training should be a part of every athlete's routine 😎

#singlelegdeadlift #gaa #gaaplayer #gaagirls #fitliving #fitlifestyle  #balancedlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
A little bit of info on calories and how sometimes less is not always best😑
***Disclaimer: This will not be relevant to a lot of people. Take into account my training schedule etc.***
.
.
Last week for possibly the first time ever I tracked calories 🙈 And I was shocked to see how much lower my calories were than they should be for maintenance. I kinda knew I was in a deficit but thought ah sure losing a little body fat would do no harm 😜🙈
.
.
You see when you drop your calories and your exercise activity is still high, your Resting Metabolic Rate (RMR) drops. Because you are eating less your Thermic Effect from food(TEF) drops. Being in a deficit also means energy can suffer. 🤷‍♀️ .
.
So I decided to up my cals and carbs. And I've never felt so good or more lean 👌😁 I trained 6 times this week and still had energy for a game today. My sleep has been great. My mood is incredible 😍
.
.
This mostly relates to athletes especially women. Less is not always best. You need to fuel your body. You need to recover well. You need your hormones, enzymes and antibodies to function properly. If you need help or advice seek it 👌

#eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitlife #fitlifestyle #balance #eatwell #sleepwell #fitgirls #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Walk before you can run 🏃🏃🏃
.
.
So the reason most people fail at their health and fitness routine is because they go from zero to 100 in a week 😔 It's a  sure recipe for success😞
.
.
You need to make much smaller steps. And make a new one weekly. All these small steps will make your fitness journey so much easier 👌
.
.
Let's take a breakfast for an example. If you're used to a big breakfast roll with a bottle of coke on your way to work, chances are you're not going to get up at 6am before work to make some 'Smashed avocado on sourdough topped with poached eggs' 😂🥑 Why not pick up a breakfast wrap minus the butter and ketchup and a coke zero. Maybe after a couple of weeks you might bring some Overnight oats with you 👌
.
.
If you've never exercised before in your life, 5 days of Hiit is never going to be sustainable🙈 Why not do 3 days of resistance training with 2 long walks?
.
.
If your regular water consumption is less than 500ml, forcing 2L down your throat is torture.
.
. 
I think you get the picture. Stop trying to be perfect. Perfection doesn't exist. Don't try a lifestyle overhaul. Make small changes. Be more conscious when shopping. This is something I try to instill in all my clients. It should work into your lifestyle👍 And some of you may never ever have salmon for breakfast 😂

#eatforhealth #eatforperformance #progressnotperfection #fitlife #fitliving #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

Why are we always so negative and pessimistic? 😩😩😩
.
.
Most common things I hear working in a gym:
-I can't
- I won't be able
- I'm too unfit
- I'm too heavy
- I'm not strong enough
- I'd never be able to do that
- I'll fail
🚫🚫🚫🚫🚫🚫🚫
.
.
Well you'll never know unless you try 💯💯 No one Jumps out of the womb super fit. Everybody struggles with nutrition to a degree. Everyone is on their own journey👌💪
.
.
Firstly, stop doubting yourself and start trying. I can assure you, you definitely will fail if you don't try. When starting to learn to drive and it's hard do you suddenly give up? No, because driving a car is important. We'll guess what your health is even more important ❤️💯 Secondly, stop bloody comparing yourself. Comparison is the thief of joy. You are never going to be somebody else, so stop trying to be. Instead focus on being a better version of you ❤️ I used to do this all the time, I'd watch other girls on Instagram lifting heavier weights than me and I'd be so jealous😒 Now, I focus on my own goals because I'm happy with where I'm at ❤️
.
.
This weekend I had clients say to me they were happy and proud of themselves. This was absolute music to my ears🎼🎶Finally, a bit of self assurance and confidence 👌 We could all do with more of it. ❤️ #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitliving #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #balance #stopbeingsonegative #stopbeingsohardonyourself  #fitfam #irishfitfam

Did you know that nothing changes, if nothing changes??? 🤔🤔🤔
.
.
If you're still stuck in the same routine, doing the same thing, you'll get the same results you always got. 🙄🙄🙄
.
.
Unless you make a change, you won't see a change👈👈
.
.
Start off small. Remove one 'chocolate bar' a day. Or save money and cut out the 3 daily mochas. What about trying to have protein with every meal? Get 10,000 steps a day. Start resistance training.
.
.
Be smart invest in a coach and/or a nutritionist. If you think you can do it alone and have been trying for the past 3 years, it's definitely worth the money. If you were sick you wouldn't wait 3 years to go to a doctor. Your health is your wealth ❤️ #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitlifestyle #fitlife #fitliving #balance #balancedlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

Hip Hinge Movement 👈👈👈
.
.
RDL, Good Morning, Rack Pull, Bent Over Row etc. All require this movement. From training people the last 5 years, I know people struggle with it for various reasons: tight hips, lack of flexibility or lower back issues
.
.
If you cannot get into this position, you have no business lifting weights.
👉 Work on movement with a stick and progress onto a band
👉 Improve flexibility
👉 Get a trainer to help you with exercises and watch your technique
.
.
Quality over Quantity every day 👌👌👌 #hiphinge #movement #hellohamstrings #gymproblems #fitlifestyle #fitlife #fitliving #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Never a truer word 😢
.
.
I heard it on the radio the other day and we are an 'extremes' country. It's all or nothing there's nothing in between. We're constantly 'grinding' I remember a point a few years ago and it was literally like a competition to see who got less sleep 🙄😑 We're either in health and fitness 100% or we binge eat and sit on our arses. 🤔
We're either drinking every weekend or we go cold turkey for a month (#dryjanuary).
.
.
These extremes are so hard to withstand. They put us under pressure, our bodies and our mind.
.
.
Lets try break away from extremes. Incorporate parts into daily life. Don't punish yourself for 'falling off the wagon' and a lie in is OK 🤣😱 Find a lifestyle that's sustainable. TAKE THAT HOLIDAY 🏖️🏜️
.
.
'We're here for a good time, not a long time' ⌚⌚⌚ #healthyliving #healthylifestyle #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitliving #balance #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Should you go all out when out for a meal or drinks??? 🤔🤔🤔
.
.
I made a confession last night that I'm an all out kinda gal when it comes to meals out, drinks too 🤤 The way I see it. I go out for dinner on average once a month. That is one meal out of approx 30 days, approx 150 meals. Its one 'bad' one. I also only drink on holidays. Its a very rare occasion. And super infrequent. Now my goals are not aesthetic. I could certainly be leaner, but my body doesn't function well on super lean. My body functions best at my current shape and performance is my goal 👌👌Therefore I'm at calorie maintenence so I don't need to overly worry about that one meal or that very infrequent drink 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️
.
.
But if your goals change this can change. Also if the frequency changes this can change. What about the other meals are they mainly healthy? You have to realise not all goals are the same. Just because I do it doesn't mean you have to 🤣And it may be affecting your goals?
.
.
It's what you do 'consistently' that matters not what you do once every so often. Achieving goals is all about Consistency and patience 👌👍 #canigobacktovegas #slushiesandjellyshots #consistency #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitliving #balance #fitfam #irishfitfam

This week was all about recovery for me ✌️
.
.
Since I came home from holidays at start of January I have been training really hard. First for a competition and then for football. I was doing a seriously demanding strength programme with 1/2 wods a week plus pitch sessions🙈
. .
So this week, I pulled it all back. No hard training. 2 strength sessions (maintenance is now my goal though rather than increasing weights every week), 1 WOD (not a hard one this week) and 1 ball skills session.
.
.
I also had a chiropractor session and a great recovery package @acepandr. Today is Foam rolling and stretching ✌️
.
.
Remember, you don't have to be constantly 'grinding'. It's OK to reduce volume, take a Deload week, take a week off etc. Your body NEEDS rest and recovery. Since my recovery session in ACE my sleep has been incredible 😍 And the cold I had at start of the week is more or less gone 👌
.
.
P. S First Ice Bath in months 🤣Hence my facial experssions

#lookafteryourself #recovery #rest #deloadweek #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitlife #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Know your treats 👉👉👉
.
.
So as I've said before here I'm a big fan of treats. I think we all deserve them (maybe not daily) but I think it's an important part of our enjoyment of food 👌👌👌
.
.
When it comes to macro nutrients these 2 products are not comparable. The protein bar is way higher in protein and the milkybar contains a lot of sugar. But both still contain calories. I'm not telling you to eat either or both. I just want you to understand that just because it's labeled as 'healthier' does not mean it doesn't contain calories 🙈 People could have 2 or 3 of these bars a day on top of their meals. So while you think you're eating well (and you probably are) you could be over consuming calories due to the nature of the foods your eating. This is obviously depending on goals. If goals are weight loss, calories are king. If goals are performance based, content of product becomes more important 👌
.
.
Take home point. Just because it's labelled as 'healthier' version doesn't mean it doesn't contain calories. Healthy foods contain calories too and we can over consume 🤔🤔🤔 Goals are too important. If you are an athlete looking to get the best from your body and looking to fuel yourself for your sport, it's different to you're average person just looking to lose afew pounds. Know your goals🎉🎉🎉 #healthyfoodcontainscaloriestoo

caption:
So I think this picture deserves its own post. It's not a progress pic. It's not a 'hey look at my body picture'. 🙄
.
.
The purpose it serves is to show 2 things:
1. The importance of pictures as a measure of progress
2. To show that scale numbers are not king 👑🚫
.
.
When I see these photos I see very little physical difference. On closer inspection, maybe a little thicker waist and thighs. And a damn good tan 😜 But the difference in weight is a whopping 12lbs 🆘🆘🆘🆘🆘🆘🆘🆘🆘🆘
.
.
Some things that can mess a scale number:
👉 Weighing yourself at a different time
👉 Different clothes
👉 Have you gone to the toilet 🚽
👉 Hydration Status
👉 Muscle mass - at the moment I am taking creatine
👉 Menstrual cycle
.
.
There are SO many factors that can change a scale number so please stop getting so hung up on scales 🛑🛑🛑 #fitliving #fitlifestyle #balance #balancedlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Can you be doing more to achieve your goals??? 🤔🤔🤔
.
.
OK so yes calorie deficit is king. And yes resistance training with some cardio is a great combination. But if you are sitting on your arse all day, every day you are doing yourself no favours 🙄🙄🙄
.
.
Neat activity is your non exercise activity thermogenesis. This is our activity levels  outside of training. It includes housework, walking, labour job, being a trainer etc.
.
.
Sleep is a MASSIVE factor. So many studies have Been done on this one. Make sleep a priority 😴😴😴
.
.
Stress levels can have a huge impact on goals. We need to learn how to switch off and relax a little. 📴
.
.
So please stop blaming your metabolism or your hormones until you have addressed every other aspect ✋✋✋ #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitliving #fitchick #balance #balancedlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

28 next week 😱😱😱
.
.
I joke about getting older. I say every year I'm gonna quit football because of my age 🙈 I've been involved in it for 20 years now after all 😏 I've been involved with the Roscommon Intermediate team for the last 10 years 🙋‍♀️ Do the math imagine all the games? 😜
.
.
But truth is I'm fitter than I've ever been👌💯 And I just love the athlete lifestyle. I was planning on hanging up my boots this year. Commitment is the part that people find the hardest. They love the sport but not the commitment. I actually like the commitment. When I do something its 100% or nothing. I live my life as an athlete. I eat like one, train like one, (try) sleep like one. I'd be doing it anyway so why not give it one last year 😅😅😅😅 #athlete #notinthisweatherthough #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitlife #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #balance #balancedlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
I am no different to anyone else 🚫🚫🚫
.
.
I'm not constantly positive. I'm not constantly body confident. Life isn't always peachy 🍑🍑🍑
.
.
Just last week I complained to my boyfriend that I actually think I'm getting too muscular 🙄 And a tough family life would be an understatement 😒
.
.
Sometimes you need to relax. We went away for a night. I put my phone on airplane mode for almost 24 hours. I felt relaxed physically and mentally. No comparisons. No feelings of guilt for the amount of chocolate consumed. No dwelling on not playin my football game that day.
.
.
Just down time. To relax. To enjoy. To forget. 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️
.
.
We all need it. How do you down time?

caption:
Hands up if you were on Mí Wadi this weekend 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️
.
.
This is NOT an alcohol bashing post. I drink myself and Love a good night out 🍻🍷💃 BUT I do think the idea of dry January and people's struggles with it is a pile of 💩
.
.
OK so firstly, it's 31 days. Is it really that hard? As soon as February 1st comes do you REALLY NEED that gin and tonic??? 😏 If you really, really do then why did you bother doing it in the first place? To prove a point? To put it on social media? To tell friends? 🤔🤔🤔
.
.
The last few years I have cut down on my drinking. I actually rarely drink unless on holidays or special occassions. But when I do it, I do it because I enjoy it and the occassion involved in it👌 I don't drink at home and I don't go to the local for one or two. I don't drink for January or February most years as football season has started back and as hard as pre season is its so much harder with a week long hangover 😂 I am far from a pioneer but I'm certainly not dependent on alcohol 🚫🚫🚫
.
.
I am not saying people need to be like me. I'm not saying my method is the right one. I just think the deal made out of no alcohol for the month of January is just silliness and the fact that as soon as Feb 1st comes people NEED to drink is a little worrying 🤔🤔Just something to think about??? #dryjanuary #soberlife #soberjanuary #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitness #balance #balancedlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:

.

.
Makes 8:
- 2 and half cups of oats
- 2 Scoops Whey Protein
- 2 tbsp. Dessicated coconut
- 3 tbsp. Seeds (I used pumpkin, sunflower and Chia)
- 30g Nuts (I used cashews)
- 3 tbsp Maple Syrup
- Protein milk to bind
Mix Altogether. Add small dashes of milk as you don't want the mixture too sticky or too dry. I didn't measure the milk 😩🙈 #healthylifestyle #healthyalternatives #fitlifestyle #fitliving #balance #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Calling all weights newbies or people dying to try it but too scared 👆👆👆
.
.
 I was once where you are too. Actually so was everyone. Nobody is born with weights in their hands 🤣 And nobody is born super strong. Strength comes from effort day in, day out. Any fitness for that matter comes from the sum of all your daily efforts, week in week out. It's about consistency 👌👌
.
.
I always hated when people said to me 'you're naturally fit'. Eh sorry Susan, I didn't see you up doing extra sprints on Christmas day. My whole life I've worked super hard to be fit. When I was younger it was aerobically fit. I ran so much (now I can't even do a 5k 🤣). Now I focus on strength and conditioning 💪🙋‍♀️ And no I have not always been strong. When I trained in @elitefpa I was weak as p*#s. I used a 7kg bar for overhead press. 4.5 years later I'm in a competition where 25kg is easy 🙋‍♀️👆 But again consistency. Last year I trained 50 out of 52 weeks (average 4/5 times a week). I took a week off the week after Connacht final and a week at Christmas. So no I am not naturally strong, I'm not naturally fit. It's not 'easier' for me. I'm an athlete. I train hard and reap the rewards ☝️☝️
.
.
Side note: I do have muscle but I don't look this pumped all the time 😂 💪

Healthier, Happier and Fitter than I've ever been 💕💕💕
.
.
Things I would have told me 18 year old self:
1. Health is so much more important than weight (2 stone difference between pics)
2. Stop trying to be perfect. Perfection doesn't exsist
3. Relax a little. Don't stress so much. Good things come to people who work but remember there's a thing called life that needs to be enjoyed
4. Problems aren't solved at the bottom of a vodka bottle (only have learned this one in recent years 😣)
5. Fitness is NOT about being skinny. I would tell my 18 year old self to start lifting weights ❤️
6. Eat your bloody vegetables and stop being so damn picky. It feels so much better on your body and you'd have so much more energy
7. Make up isn't life. You are beautiful, stop hiding yourself with layers of foundation and baggy hoodies.
8. Appreciate everyone in your life. You think they will always be around. Unfortunately that's not the case 💔

So much has changed, yet so much has stayed the same. 💕💕💕 #10yearchallenge #mentalnotphysical

Pre season Nutrition🍏🍏 A question I get asked quite often is should nutrition be different pre-season and during season. The answer is yes. You should not be consuming the same calories in pre-season as you do during championship.
.
. 
Think about it though. Preseason is usually gym based with maybe one pitch session so activity levels are not as high. Compare that to full on championship mode, you may be on the pitch 3 times a week with one gym session. And this only takes one sport into consideration. You may have multiple sports.
If activity levels increase so too should calories and vice versa. If we are in a period of lowered activity, calories should therefore be lower. Overall calories are determined by gender, weight, activity level and goals.
.
. 
Macronutrient requirements will also be different. Protein requirements will be high in both cases as the need for recovery will be high i.e post gym session or post-match both require high protein. Protein targets are usually 1.8-2.2g per kg BW.
.
. 
Fats are also important for recovery and to reduce inflammation. These should be approximately 20% of our overall calorie intake.
.
. 
Carbohydrate is our main energy source during sport. Pre season however, requires less carbohydrate intake. We are focused on more short bursts of energy like Gym work or sprints which use a different energy system to matches. We don’t need to consume carbohydrate with every meal during pre-season and while our calorie requirements are also lower here might be a good place to start. We could substitute our complex carbohydrate rice with a lower calorie cauliflower rice or breakfast could focus more on a larger omelette with extra veggies rather than 2 slices of bread? These are just options of how to reduce calories but keep bulk and not feel like you are depriving yourself. .
. 
It is important to understand that these are two different periods of an athlete’s schedule. Just like we cycle training, we should also cycle our nutrition 👌
.
.
This is what my pre season looked like thanks to @keelafarnon & @komplexfitness for pushing me to my limits the last few months training for this comp. Bring on Saturday 💪💪💪

caption:
My 2019 'Resolutions' 💕💕💕
.
.
2018 was my most mentally challenging year. From January until mid October I suffered with problem after problem. They accumulated. Stress accumulated. My mental health deteriorated. Excess stress lead to niggly injuries. I wouldn't rest or couldn't recover because I was putting myself under too much pressure. My football performance suffered. My work suffered. With the help of @womensgpa I decided to seek counselling services and it was the best decision I've ever made. I'm not quiet about problems and issues. I've always talked about them. But sometimes you need more than just the ear of a sibling, partner or friends. Sometimes you need to seek professional help ❤️
.
.
So therefore, 2019 is for me. For the first time in my life I'm putting 'my' needs and wants first. Not those of others. It's for prioritising myself.
.
.
'How can you help others if you are not looking after yourself? ' 💕

-Avocado

Christmas Drinks 🍻🍷🍹
.
.
If you're like me, you don't drink very often and enjoy a tipple over the festive season. Remember you didn't get it all in a few days, so you won't lose it in a few days. Alcohol will however, cause water retention, possible bloating depending on drinks and probably cravings the following day 🙈 90% of the time, I don't give into these and go back to normal eating habits. And that's probably why I can drink as part of a balanced lifestyle 👌
.
.
If you've been drinking since 1st December and use the whole of December as 'Christmas' things are gonna be a little harder for you 🙈But here's some of my tips:
1. Try a lower calorie option. Select from the above and try to stick with that. Pints and festive cocktails are laden with calories so beware.
2. Drink water between alcoholic drinks. You'll thank me the next morning 👌
3. Drink more water in general over the festive period. It will help flush you out💦
4. Eat a decent protein rich meal before heading out. And have a homemade snack ready when you get home to avoid chipper afterwards 🙈Once in a blue moon is OK but if you're out 4 times a week, it's a little excessive don't you think? My personal fav is toast with real butter🤤
5. Don't give into cravings the next day. Your body is dehydrated, tired and sore. It doesn't need more crap it needs nourishment. Again as I said, once in a blue moon is fine but if you are eating more 'hungover food' than normal food, then we have a problem 🙈
.
.
I will be enjoying my Gin and Slim tomorrow. Its my first of the holiday season and it won't be my last. But be mindful. Enjoy yourself but don't take the p*#s 😊

#alcohol #liquidcaloriescount #bemindful #enjoyyourself #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitgirls #healthylifestyle #healthyliving #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Let's talk stress 🙈 The whole world is taking about calorie deficits and training hard, did you know that maybe you're 'grinding' too much 🤔
.
.
What do I mean?
👉 We're always told, be in a calorie deficit to lose weight and exercise more? Right. But what if you're body is under chronic stress and you are not sleeping right? Will this affect you? Yes!!! Chronic and acute stress release hormones and neuro transmitters that tell our body to go into 'fight or flight' mode. These hormones and neurotransmitters especially norepinephrine switch off digestion and the GI tract making it very difficult to absorb nutrients 🚫🚫🚫
.
.
My own experience with stress. And how I learned to cope🤔🤔🤔
I have been a worry wart from day dot. And a control freak. I used to stress out so badly. I remember the tell tale signs would be on my skin if I was going through a really bad period of stress 😩 During my leaving cert I lost loads of weight and my hair started falling out due to stress 😔Before my Dad died, he asked me to try and relax and something triggered in me. I knew I needed to put things in place or I would end up running myself into the ground. And I had improved so much until this year🙄 This year tested me. A roller-coaster doesn't do it justice, so I realised I needed help. I started seeing a  counsellor and I have been seeing her for the past month 😊 (My issues are not as simple as I'm stressed they go way back so that's what I needed help with).
.
.
What can you do?
So while you may not need to go to the extreme I did. You need to manage your stress levels. The body does NOT want to be in fight or flight mode. It wants to be in 'rest and digest' mode. So you need to sort your stress out acute or chronic 🚫🚫
.
.
Self care is vitally important. I have only really started learning that since my Dad died. This year with the help of my counsellor I've realised that who's going to look after me if I'm trying to look after everyone else🤔 It's absolutely necessary to put yourself first sometimes. Don't ever forget that ❤️ #stress #hormonemonstress #fightorflight #fitliving #fitlife #fitlifestyle #balance #healthylifestyle #healthyliving #fitchick #irishfitfam

caption:
Why do you train? What are your reasons?
.
.
I remember YEARS ago seeing a skinny girl running and I thought to myself. Why does she run, sure she doesn't need to lose weight? I also remember a time in college where my friend was getting healthy food and I thought to myself, why is she bothering, sure she doesn't have weight to lose? 😔😔😔 A member told me recently that someone asked her why was she eating a salad for lunch (her normal lunch) sure she doesn't need to diet 😒
.
.
My head was just filled with social norms. So many of us have this perception. You only need to exercise and eat healthy to fix something? Well no you actually don't 🚫🚫🚫
.
.
I want to live a long healthy life. I want to hopefully have kids. I want to be able to play with kids and hopefully even grandkids in the far distant future 😂🔮 I want to try my best to live the healthiest life possible. Not just now while my body fat is low. But in the future during different periods of my life like during pregnancy or in my elder years. I am making an investment in myself now for the future ❤️ #health #healthyliving #healthylifestyle #fitliving #fitlife #fitchick #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
🎄Will you train over the holidays🎄
.
.
If yes, what way will you train? You may have to reduce volume or frequency? Rather than train 5 days you may need to reduce to 2 or 3. Or maybe you'll just go out for a walk, run or cycle?
.
.
If no, take responsibility for your choice. Don't moan or whinge after Christmas. Just own it and get back on it after Christmas 👍
.
.
Everyone is different. There is no right or wrong answer. You shouldn't feel guilty about your decision but you do have to own your decision. 👌😬
.
.
My recommendation would be to keep up exercise. You can reduce frequency but don't let months of training go to waste 🙄 The Doms afterwards from the lack of exercise are just awful too 🙈😂 But whatever you chose to do.... Own it ❤️ #healthylifestyle #healthyliving #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitlife #fitgirls #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

P. S My faces 😛😵

🎅How to stay on track over Christmas 🎅
.
.
Firstly, let me start by saying I'm not a grinch 😂 I love Christmas as much as the next person and I enjoy myself too 👌 But I don't take the absolute p*#s either 😙 Here's my top tips on how to not ruin your progress over the holidays 🎄
.
.
1. Relax. It's not Christmas yet. I'm all for YOLO and all that but there's no need for the celebrations to be out on 1st December 🙄 If you take the whole month of December to celebrate one day, you WILL ruin your progress 😬
.
.
2. Keep active 🏃‍♀️🏃‍♂️Get out in the fresh air, bring the dog for a walk, take part in a charity swim, go for a cycle or even a home workout 👍 Being 100% sedentary will do you no favours 🙏
.
.
3. Stay hydrated 💧💧💧 Simple tip but one of the most important 👌
.
.
4. Try stick to one 'bad meal' a day. If you want a fry in the morning, stick with a healthy lunch and a wholesome dinner. If you are going out for dinner, opt for a protein rich breakfast and maybe a salad for lunch.
Top tips for eating out:
- Stick with 2 courses or a main meal with a couple of drinks
- For a main meal, try a high protein/high cárb/low fat option or high protein/high fat/low cárb
.
.
5. Be cautious of drinking your calories. Check out my last post on how calorific festive hot drinks are 🙈 With Alcohol, stick to clear drinks with a diet mixer or water. Steer away from creamy cocktails or baileys 🤷‍♀️
.
.
6. The most important part is ENJOY yourself. It's a time of year to spend with family and friends and appreciate what you have ❤️ You don't need to be the prude sitting in the corner with fish and greens but you also don't need to do a 10,000 calorie challenge every day 😂 Find a balance that means you'll enjoy yourself but you'll also keep an eye on your goals 😊
.
.
P. S if you decide to eat like an asshole. Own it and don't come whinging in January. 🙄🙈 Nobody wants to hear it 😅
.
. 
#christmasiscoming #christmas #enjoyyourself #happyholidays #fitliving #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #balance #fitgirls #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

☕ DON'T DRINK YOUR CALORIES☕
.
.
So this time of year its very tempting to exchange your regular americano for a blackforest mocha 🤤 And while one every once in awhile is a perfect treat if you change this to a daily routine while keeping your normal diet you may be adding a serious amount of extra calories to your overall weekly intake 🙈 Just because it's liquid don't think it doesn't count 🙈😢
.
.
If you buy one 400 Cál drink a day until Christmas that's an extra 10,800 Cals on top of your normal diet. And that won't even take into account the odd treat you'll have here and there 😭
.
.
Be mindful 👆👆👆 I love a good hazelnut hot chocolate 🤤 But it's been about 2 years since I've had one (maybe this year I'll break out for one again 😂). Just understand. Be more educated. Be more mindful of what you do with your calories. It's NOT about deprivation but about being sensible. I know I'd rather use my calories towards something that will fill me more 👌👍 #liquidcaloriescount #bemindful #dailyhabits #dailyritual #healthyliving #healthylifestyle #balance #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitgirls #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
One of the biggest problems with our society is we wait until we are broken before we fix ourselves😢
.
.
This goes for everything. We let our mental health deteriorate before we decide to do anything about it. We only work on our stress levels when we've had a breakdown. We only start looking after our diet when we've been diagnosed with an illness. We don't exercise until we have weight to lose. We don't sort injuries until they stop us from working. We take shortcuts, tablets, pills, shakes all to avoid  reality, which is actually so much easier. .
.
Move a little everyday. Nourish your body. Sleep. And stress less ❤️ #fitliving #fitlife #balancedlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitgirls #fitfam #irishfitfam

Let's talk healthy eating 👆👆👆
.
.
 I put up a poll the other day and was disappointed to see over 30% of people found it restrictive. I didn't ask reasons why but here's my thoughts on the whole matter. 💭💭💭
.
.
What even does 'Healthy eating' mean?
That's a very subjective statement but here's my opinion.
👉 Food that nourishes your body
👉 Food that fuels your body
👉 Food for body and mind
👉 Non restrictive
.
.
I believe healthy eating is eating 80% of the food that the body needs and 20% of the food the body wants 😉❤️
.
.
That being said there are healthier versions of everything these days. As above 😍👆🤤
.
.
☑️And I also think as you get older you realise health is important.
☑️It's becoming realitively inexpensive. ☑️You feel better, look better, sleep better. The list is endless
.
.
If you find it restrictive you're doing it wrong. ❌❌❌ You need to grow up a little. Yes vegetables are important and you should be eating them with most meals. Health should be more important than a bowl of coco pops in the morning. Water should make up 50-60% of your body, if it's not, your body doesn't function properly🚫
.
.
If anyone has any objections or comments. I'd love to hear them and argue against them 😂👆 #healthylifestyle #healthyeating #healthyliving #fitliving #fitlifestyle #balancedlifestyle #fitfam #fitgirls #irishfitfam

caption: 'I don't do it because I have to, I do it because I can' 🙏🙏🙏 #healthylifestyle #healthyliving #fitliving #fitlifestyle #strongwomen #strongirls #fitchick #fitgirls #fitfam #irishfitfam

'A lot of people won't relate to you because you never had weight to lose'
.
.
You know this is as insulting as calling someone obese.
.
.
Firstly, everyone has a different reason for getting into fitness. Not everyone's journey is weight loss. Mine certainly wasn't as you know. For me, fitness has been a release. It's my way of dealing with stress and always has been. Stress affects people in different ways. Some overeat, some undereat, and  some do nothing. I exercise. Like everyone, I have loads going on outside of what you see on this. So what better way to relieve any excess stress than exercise ❤️
Strength was my other reason for getting involved in fitness. I was tiny and so weak. I initially did it to get stronger for football. But now I just absolutely LOVE the feeling of seeing what my body is capable of 😍 Exercise should not be about punishing yourself. It should be a celebration of what your body can do 🙌🙌🙌
.
.
Secondly, how I look should never come into it. If I was overweight would you say 'you're not a good role model'. It doesn't matter what size or shape you are. If you are good at what you do and want to help people for the better who cares if you've been fit all your life or if you just under went your own transformation 🤷‍♀️
.
.
Stop being so damn judgemental people 🚫🚫🚫 You do you. Find a lifestyle you enjoy 💯 And that is sustainable to you 👌 And enjoy every single day ❤️

caption:
How to get back on track after weekend of bad food and alcohol??? 😥😥😥
.
.
Remember it is what you do MOST of the time that will be a reflection of your health and body composition. 🙌 NOT what you do SOME of the time.
.
.
So if this weekend was the first weekend in weeks/months that you went out then chances are you won't do huge damage to progress. But if it's a regular occurrence and you're complaining that you're not seeing results. Remember the weekend is 35% of your week, so if it's consistently a problem this will have an impact on results 🙈🙈🙈
.
.
What to do?
👉 A wise woman once said to me, when you make a mistake think of the 3 f's. Forget about it. F*#k it. You didn't kill anyone did you 🙈 And fix it. The way you fix it is not by overdoing the cardio or living on fish and leaves for the week. Instead go back to normal eating habits
👉 Drink plenty of water.
👉 Catch up on sleep. Sleep is one that is undermined.
👉 Get back to exercise. Even if you need to wean your way in with a walk or something light. You'll always feel better afterwards

Hope everyone enjoyed their Bank Holiday 🙌🙌🙌 #healthyliving #healthylifestyle #health #fitliving #fitlife #fitlifestyle #balancedlifestyle #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Contrary to popular belief⚠️⚠️⚠️ 👉 You can miss a Monday with a valid excuse
👉 It's OK to listen to your body and not train because you are tired (🙋‍♀️ Me today along with feeling sore from the chiropractor)
👉 You don't have to be motivated every single day
👉 You can mess up your diet and get back to normality the next day 👌 We are all human. We all do it. But make it a lifestyle you can sustain. Treats here and there are essential #balance
👉 You don't need to blast it at the gym to make up for drinking the night before. This can actually be more detrimental than beneficial sometimes
👉 Being sick IS a valid excuse
👉 Just because you are busy all the time, doesn't mean you are productive 🙄
👉 Most people on instagram look nothing like their photos 🙈😂 👌The odd occasion I do dress up and look like a girl. Heres photographic evidence 😂 And I plan on looking like one agaín after I tackle Carauntohil Saturday. Wish me luck 🍀

caption:
⁉️Did you know that we have 11 systems in our body?? 🤔
.
.
⁉️Did you know that they work in conjunction with one another?? 🤔
.
.
⛔ If you have an issue with one system you could be putting other systems at risk.
.
.
➡️ Take your digestive system for example. If you are not absorbing nutrients properly it can have an impact on your skeletal system (in the case of calcium)
➡️ If your stress hormones are imbalanced it can have an impact on your integumentary system (hair loss)
➡️ When your nervous system is out of whack, you may have a weakened immune system

The list goes on. The point is. Look after all parts of your body. No part is more important than the other. Looking healthy externally means nothing if you aren't healthy on the inside 👌 This doesnt just mean exercise and nutrition. It goes for every part of your health ❤️ And don't forget to enjoy life while you live your healthiest life 💋

#healthyliving #healthylifestyle #fitliving
#fitlifestyle #balancedlifestyle #fitchick #fitgirls #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
New lease of life ❤️🙌
.
.
The last 3 months have just been so hard as I've has a lot to deal with in my personal life. I haven't been myself. Stress levels have been through the roof. I lost weight for the wrong reasons. My hair is falling out. I lost motivation for my normal long days. I wasn't food prepping which led to poorer food choices. I wasn't my normal social self.
.
.
But the last week I've found a spark back in me 👌 My sister coming home helped that. I started really enjoying food and training again 🙌 I started studying again. I started working with clients again. The competition at the weekend helped 😊 I'm feeling back in the game 👊👊👊
.
.
It's OK not to have your shit together 100% of the time. It's OK to say you weren't feeling yourself. It's OK to be a trainer and not be motivated. It's OK not to be OK ❤️ #feelingmotivated #backinthegame #stillneedtogetmyinjuriessorted #happiness #healthylifestyle #healthyliving #fitliving #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitgirl #fitfam #irishfitfam

First but certainly not my last competition 💪💪💪
.
.
This is exactly why I train. Not to have abs or a booty pop 🙄 It's the incredible feeling of achievement that you get when you have given absolutely everything 😱
.
.
Thanks @aislingquinnmeldrum and @meldrumvincent 🙌

caption:
Why do you exercise???
.
.
Exercise has so many unbelievable benefits. The list is so long🗒️
💭 Mental Health
❤️ Heart Health
🧠 Brain Functioning
💪 Strong Bones and Muscle Function
💤 Helps improve sleep
☺️ Mood booster
🙌 Hormone regulator
The list really goes on and on...
.
.
Yet recently aesthetics seems to be the primary goal for most 😩 Now, a healthy body composition will occur with regular exercise it's not the ONLY reason to exercise 😒 Recently, some of my clients have started saying they 'want to gain knowledge' or they 'want to be healthier' or 'they want a healthy relationship with food and exercise'. These are the sort of goals I want to hear 😍 These people are in it for the right reasons. ❤️
.
.
Exercise is not a punishment. We are so blessed and lucky to be able to exercise. Please start seeing that and stop treating your body poorly.
.
.
'You are your own most expensive asset'

Priorities 🤔🤔🤔
.
.
I always talk about goals and how important they are. Well priorities link in with your goals. There is no right or wrong answer to this. We all have priorities. Some of us have them without even realising. 🙄
.
.
What do I mean?
👉 I prioritise my health. Therefore, I eat well. I exercise. And I try my very best to reduce my stress levels and sleep well 👉 I prioritise holidays. Therefore, I don't go out very often so I can save money to go on holidays. 👉 I prioritise my family, friends and boyfriend. Even with a very busy schedule. I make time to see them. It may not be very often but I still make them a priority. 👉 I prioritise my job. The hours I work are often very unsocial but I make it work, because its a priority.
.
.
I often hear people say they 'care' about their health but are not willing to pay for healthy food. 🙄Others who 'care' about their friends but never see them😵. Those who want to build businesses but are only willing to work 9-5🙈🤔 People wanting to save for a house but are out every weekend 😔Then, there's the ones who want to lose weight🤯. They may care. But caring and prioritising are 2 very different things. Again, I am not giving out. Nobody needs to have the same priorities as me. But remember, for you to achieve your goals in life, no matter what they may be you need to prioritise. ✋✋✋ #priorities #ineverythingyoudo #healthyliving #healthylifestyle #healthyalternative #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

Buzzword = Protein 👈👈👈
.
.
These bars are virtually identical🙈 But If it has protein on it surely it's healthy?? 🙄
Wrong 😱😱😱
.
.
Are you buying protein bars because they are the 'healthier' option? What is the context? Why are they healthier? Because they contain protein? Because they have 'less sugar? Or maybe you are eating them to hit your protein target? Do you understand the term food quality? Anyway you should really understand 'why' you are eating what you are eating and if it will help towards your goals? .
.
I haven't tried them because
1. They are a rip off
2. I like the original
3. Protein bars don't agree with me
.
.
If it were me and I wanted a boost bar. I'd buy the bar (as long as I could stop at 1 bar and it's not a multipack). I would have it as a treat.
.
.
If you are eating protein bars as your treat, just understand why? P. S I am NOT anti protein bars but I am anti miseducation. 
#healthyliving #healthylifestyle #education #healthyalternative #orisit #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitlife #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Last week was a bad week and came with it poor choices and what I consider poor health. 😔
.
.
👉Monday - Normal Diet and Gym session
👉Tuesday - Starting to feel tired and sick but still normal diet
👉Wednesday - Head cold, ate twice, stress levels sky high
👉Thursday - Still dosed, very high stress levels, ate twice
👉Friday - Terrible sleep, stress levels through the roof, forced myself to eat, ate rubbish
👉Saturday - Played a match (didn't have my normal energy), felt sick after, still ate pizza (first takeaway in MONTHS)
👉Sunday - Ate twice - both poor choices
.
.
Monday morning I've woken up, feeling hungover 😩 Without a drop of alcohol. A cycle like this is really really unusual for me. But it's almost though I eat crap, feel like crap but do it again. It has been years since this has happened before. Normally, I feel good so I keep eating good. My energy levels were low, my mood was low. I felt terrible. It really had a huge impact on how I felt. But it's Monday. It's time to start a fresh. This week is under my control and I've a super important game Saturday which all of my focus is on 🙏 Bring it on 🙌🙌🙌 #honestyisthebestpolicy #poorfoodchoices #leaveyoufeelingterrible #healthylifestyle #healthyliving #healthyalternative #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

I am honest on this. Always have been, always will be. People who know me describe me as 'positive' which I am. But there's only so much positive someone can be 💔 I've never discussed this aspect of my life before because I felt I didn't need to... But since I'm a talker and talking usually works for me I feel I need to.
.
.
Those who know me know my Dad died 3 years ago. I was super close to him. I was devastated. That left a family of me, my sister and my mother. I'm not close to my mother and have an amazing relationship with my sister ❤️ My mother suffers from many mental health issues. Did before my Dad died and definitely has since. I've been in as many hospitals with her as I have with my Dad. It's hard. Like really hárd and a lot of the time she doesn't help herself (not gonna get too in depth). I am now a next of kin and at 27 you'd think you'd be able for that but it's actually a massive responsibility.
.
.
I am beyond lúcky that I have my boyfriend, friends and family ❤️ Anyway long story short, while I myself have never had mental health issues. I have been affected by them. And believe me I know I'm just one in a million of us. But #itsoknottobeok ♥️ It's OK to ask for help and to talk ❤️ There are so many out there. So many support lines, not just for those with mental heath issues but others affected too ❤️ #yourmentalhealth #lookafteryourself

caption:
I am so glad I grew up when social media wasn't as big. There was no Facebook, Instagram or Snapchat until I was in college.
.
.
There is so much pressure on people to look picture perfect these days 😱 If I could show you pics of my teens 😂😂😂 Nobody cared. There was no such thing as likes on a photo or filtering. And my God there was no such thing as photoshop 🤔
.
.
Teenagers these days need to understand and love their bodies. They need to see exercise and food as health and nourishment for their bodies, not a way to abuse it♥️ We are so lucky we have the opportunities we do. Don't neglect them. And if you want that slice of cake, have it 🍰 I did on Saturday night 😉

#socialmediainfluence #behappy #behealthy #healthylifestyle #healthylife #fitliving #fitlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitgirl #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

I'm a big believer in enjoying your food😍
.
.
When people 'diet' they often HATE the food they eat. How do you ever expect to stick to something you absolutely detest??? 🙈🙈🙈 You should always enjoy your food no matter your goals ✋
.
.
Now people will take that out of context and start eating pizza and chips for lunch 🙄 At the end of the day, you can't be an ass*#le about it either 🙄 I love pizza and cookies just as much as the rest of you AND I still eat them. Just not daily ❌❌❌Bitta cop on please here 🙏 But I enjoy my food. I love the food I eat 🍲It's not boring 🙈 This prawn, kale and spinach pasta was delish and so quick to make 👌
.
.
Fuel your body right, results will follow. 80% of what you NEED (healthy, nutritious food) 20% of that stuff you WANT (pizza, chocolate🤤).
.
.
Who agrees?? #healthyliving #healthylifestyle #healthyalternative #fitliving #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitgirls #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Consistency 💯💯💯
.
.
I had said my page was not going to focus as much on aesthetics and its the truth but sometimes people (myself included) need a reminder about what consistency actually is 🙈
.
.
I'm gonna relate this to fitness but of course it can be related to anything. Consistency is sticking with something, through the good and the bad 👌 I am consistent. Even when I think I'm not I am (no Amanda that chocolate bar at the weekend will not kill you) 😂 If I take a break, it's a short one and I'm 100% back to normality after it. I loooove my lifestyle because its one I can adhere to. Its not restrictive (this is my version of non restrictive but others would probably find it restrictive). I have my treats if I want them. I drink occasionally. But I am consistent. I train regularly and 80% of the food I eat is healthy ❤️
.
.
Anything short of consistency will end in failure. I'll give an example:
- You train 3 - 5 times a week = 3 - 5 hours a week. You eat relatively well during the week but all hell breaks lose at the weekend (probably because you are so restrictive during the week). 1 drink turns into 10 on Saturday and Sunday = takeaway to cure the hangover 😭. ALL OF THE ABOVE IS INCONSISTENT. From training times to eating patterns to number of alcohol units. But now let's really throw a spanner in the works. You decide to take 2-6 weeks off training/diet to 'enjoy your summer' or 'holidays' 😩😩😩 And you wonder why you don't get results 😭
.
.
Unless you can find something that you can stick with, something you enjoy, something that is not a chore and are consistent with it, you're really not going anywhere 🙈😩
.
.
P. S I'm not saying you have to have the same lifestyle as me. But please stop complaining if you're not getting results for putting in minimal effort 🙄✋ #consistencyiskey #consistency #healthylifestyle #healthyliving #balancedlifestyle #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitgirls #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

Some tips for shopping on a Budget

✔️ Shop early morning or late in the evening (there is often discounted foods with short best before dates)

Are sauces and flavourings denying you results??? 🍶🍶🍶
.
.
It's very easy to think marinades or sauces don't count. But unfortunately they do 🙈 And they can be a big downfall for people. Take for example this marinade, the first ingredient is sugar 😱😱😱 When we compare it to natural flavourings like chilli powder or paprika which have minimal calories and very little processing 🤔
.
.
Another example of this is salad dressings. Salads can go from diet hero to zero in a matter of seconds. A lot of salad dressings are very calorific so be cautious 👹
.
.
The same goes for ordering food when you're out. Theres no point ordering the hake when you get the creamy sauce, creamed potatoes and vegetables lathered in butter. Believe me I'm all for 'treat yoself' but is it really helping you towards your goals? 🤔🤔🤔
.
.

Do you think you need supplements??? 🤔
.
.
Do you think your diet is sufficient??? 🤔
.
.
Unfortunately many of us need supplements, even those of u who have a balanced diet🤷‍♀️ Why?
👉 Food quality can be poor even 'organic' and 'wholefoods'
👉 Our lifestyle - high intensity exercise, high pressure jobs, long days, poor food choices etc
👉 Lack of availability of certain nutrients
.
.
These are the supplements I take and why
💊 Probiotics
Gut health is vital. Your gut sends signals to all the systems in our body and works in conjunction with them all. Day to day, we damage the bacteria in our gut. Not to mention what medication and illness can do to it. I recommend taking a 30 day course of Probiotics every once in awhile
.
.
💊Fish oils
It is recommended to eat fish 2-3 times a week. But did you know that white fish does not contain the same fats that oily fish do? So if you are only eating white fish you are not getting sufficient omega 3 fats. And furthermore, because our food quality has gone to s*#t, oily fish doesn't even contain enough omega 3 fats. So majority of people, even those with a good diet are not getting adequate omega 3 fats. I recommend a fish oil supplement for overall health. When looking for a fish oil supplement look for EPA and DHÁ content
.
.
💊 Vitamin D
Also known as the sunshine vitamin. Ireland does not have enough sunlight to produce adequate amounts of vitamin D in the body. We can obtain Vit D in our diet but the preferred form is sunlight. Vitamin D is required to absorb calcium as well as many other functions.
.
.
💊 Magnesium
Did you know that magnesium is needed for over 300 chemical reactions in the body? And we only absorb 20-50% of our dietary magnesium. I started taking this for muscle cramps. Magnesium Chloride is the most easily absorbed form. I get mine through magnesium oil. Epsom salts are another good form

What supplements if any do you take and why?
Comment below

Chocolate Comparison 🍫🍫🍫
.
. 
So this one is probably gonna be a little shocker to some. And as with everything, this is all very goal dependent👌But sometimes the 'healthier' option is not the best option to suit your goals. But let me put that into a little more context 🤔
.
.
So I'm sure most of you have been lead to believe dark chocolate is 'better' for you. It is full of antioxidants, good fats and has been linked to many health benefits. But if you ABSOLUTELY hate it and are forcing yourself to eat it so you can have a treat, is it really healthy? To an extent, we should be eating foods that are more nutritious but your treats should also feel like a treat? Who's with me on that one? 🙋‍♀️
.
.
So the above photo shows a milkybar wowsome which has less calories, less sugar, less fat and practically identical protein to dark chocolate. So if your goal is weight loss the milkybar is actually probably the better option. Now if your goal is healthy eating, the dark chocolate definitely wins 🎉
.
.
Again it all is really goal dependent. I eat both. I like both. But my goals may not be the same as yours. I am not saying one is better for you than the other I am simply saying, make an informed choice when picking a 'treat' and please don't force feed yourself dark chocolate just because its 'healthier'. 🙈🙈🙈
P. S please don't take this out of context and start eating crap food because it is lower calorie😕

caption:
🦄Have a slow metabolism? What are you doing about it?
.
.
🐒So first things first, unless you have a hormonal imbalance which has been diagnosed chances are you don't have a anything wrong with your Basal Metabolic Rate. If you THINK you have a 'slow' metabolism it's probably because you don't look after your dietary intake and you have a sedentary lifestyle!!! 🙈🙈🙈
.
.
🦁People want to use excuses🤦‍♀️Some people genuinely have difficult circumstances to overcome and others are just full óf BS 😑😑😑
.
.
🐰I often get asked how do I have such a 'fast' metabolism, especially because I eat so much. Well my BMR is based on the fact that I have ALWAYS been active and in the last 5 years I have dramatically improved my eating habits. But it took 5 years, not 5 days or 5 weeks, 5 years👆👆
.
.
🦄Don't think after 6 weeks of exercise you are going to dramatically overhaul the years of lack of exercise. Changing from a takeaway at lunch to a salad for a week, will not correct all the damage to your hormonal system. It takes time to correct the damage you have done to your body. And unfortunately that is what it is. Lack of exercise and immobility is damage. Excessive body fat and lack of muscle mass is damage. In a lot of cases, it is also malnourishment.
.
.
🐒But you CAN change it. It won't happen in a week. It won't happen in a month. It may even take longer than a year. But you can improve it. Step by step. Day by day. Working on a lifestyle that is sustainable. A way of living that is healthy but not too restrictive. Looking after yourself inside and out 😊👌 #slowmetabolism #isitreally #excuses #horomonalimbalances #healthylifestyle #healthylife #healthyliving #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitgirl #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Will lifting weights make women bulky 🙈🙈
.
.
Bulky? No. Add muscle? Yes.
Adding muscle does not mean getting bulky 🚫🚫🚫
.
.
To gain muscle in very large quantities you need
👉 Steroids
👉 Weight training multiple times a day
👉 A lot of VOLUME
.
.
This is all very hard to do. So don't worry by picking up a couple of dumbbells you are not going to turn into a bodybuilder. You are not a powerlifter when you pop a Barbell on your back. And you CERTAINLY won't turn into a Crossfit Games athlete by doing some wall balls 😂
.
.
You will however:
👉 Increase lean muscle mass
👉 Reduce Body Fat Mass
👉 Increase BMR - Basal Metabolic Rate
👉 Reduce Risk of Injury
👉 Improve bone mass density
👉 Get Stronger
👉 Feel more confident
.
.
Unfortunately I still deal with this stigma on a daily basis more with older clientele. 🙈 #notions This is something I recommend everyone doing in some form or another no matter what your goals are 👌 If it's not something you love, fair enough, but it is something you NEED so you should be at least getting it in once a week 🙈

caption:
Check out my Insta Story on Championship Preparation 👆👆👆
.
.
For me, recovery is most important.
🍏 Eating really well - fueling my body
💧 Hydration
😴 Sleeping as much as I can
🤪 Reduce volume of training
❄️ 3 Ice Baths a week
Having picked up a few minor injuries this year, that won't heal until I can rest fully, I need to make sure I'm looking after myself. Priority number 1 is being ready for each game so whatever I have to do I'm doing it 👌
.
.
This time of year is about fueling your body, playing hard and recovering 😜 Make sure you are looking after yourself. Injuries are most likely to happen when you are not minding yourself👎 And Good Luck to all 🤞

#eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitliving #fitlife #fitlifestyle #gaaseason #championship #rosladies #fitgirl #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

Lovely little find in @aldi_ireland 😊😊😊 .
.
I've said it before and I'll say it again, eating healthy does not have to be boring🚫🚫🚫. If you hate plain rice, don't eat it. Opt for the more interesting style and get some veggies in while you're at it 👌 Now I actually like plain rice and this is a rare treat to me (because I rarely get a chance to eat warm food and this is a steam pack 😭).
.
.
The best diet out there is the one YOU can stick to. If you can't stick to it, you're going nowhere. Now sometimes you may go hell for leather with an event coming up like holidays or a wedding etc (that's different). If you are constantly eating clean for 6 weeks and binging for the other 46 you have not found a sustainable way of living 😑😑😑
.
.
If you are unsure of what you should be doing to achieve your goals. Speak to a nutritionist or dietician 👍

#healthylifestyle #healthyliving #healthyalternative #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitliving #balancedlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitchick #fitgirls #fitfam #irishfitfam

Are you the type of person that doesn't like a food before you've even tried it? Eating with your eyes rather than your mouth? You've a list of dislikes longer than your list of likes🙄🤔
.
.
I used to be you 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️ Genuinely I was the pickiest person going. Now I'm still a bit weird with some things touching each other on a plate and I'm never going to be a cauliflower fan but I've changed DRAMATICALLY. Why? Well to be totally honest I just grew up. I know it's hard for some to hear but that's exactly what it is. 🙈 Now obviously intolerances are a totally different kettle of fish 🤪 But if you are just choosing to eat broccoli as your only veg, fish doesn't exist in your diet and potatoes are your only starch and it's purely down to not trying other foods, you really need to broaden your horizons👊
.
.
You are missing out on so much nutrients and whole foods by keeping your diet so limited. You won't like them all. That's understandable but at least try 👍
.
.
P. S up until recently I couldn't stand Goats cheese but because I eat very little meat I had to start finding higher protein alternatives. After a few tries I'm a fan 👆

#healthylifestyle #healthyliving #healthyalternative #fitliving #fitlifestyle #balancedlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
So as you can see, those who have been following me for awhile my page has changed A LOT through the last year. All the photos of food and exercise have changed to nights out and experiences. It's not that I'm not still eating well or exercising, it's just that lately it hasn't been the priority in my life. I don't know if that makes me a fake or just human. 🤷‍♀️ What I do know is, it has made me extremely happy 😍❤️🙏 Last year I made a bucket list and I made a pact with myself to put me first ✔️ This year has been the most action packed fulfilling year in my life 👌💯 I will get back to more food posts and sharing exercise tips as it's my passion but I've realised it's not the only part of my life. Some of this years antics 😜 📍 Las Vegas
📍 Florida
📍 New Car
📍 Donegal with the girlos
📍 Galway with the college crew
📍 Ed Sheeran
📍 Connacht Title
📍 Benidorm with the Rossies
📍 Rock Wertcher

To be able to have these experiences with the most incredible people in my life is what makes me happy most. That being said, football is my no. 1 for the foreseeable future so my pics will defo be more food and exercise 😂 #balance

#healthylifestyle #balancedlifestyle #selfish #sometimesyouhavetobe #lifeisforliving #happiness #fitness #dowhatmakesyouhappy

caption:
What a bloody weekend 💯💯💯
.
.
Now, pass me all of the vegetables, I'd like my body back 😂😜 #rockwerchter #belgium #whataweekend #brokenwoman #glitterbabes #tinnies #smiles #happiness #

Truth the whole truth and nothing but the truth 🙈🙈🙈 1. I drank waaaay too much on this holiday
2. I didn't eat near enough
3. I didn't have a micro in the 3 days
4. I didn't want a bikini pic because I was too embarassed (the swell was real) 
5. My sleep was terrible
6. The most exercise I did was jumping in and out of the pool
.
. 
Day to day none of the above happen (bar maybe no. 5🙈 due to lack of time). From time to time, we all change our habits. I needed a break. Now I probably didn't need all the alcohol 😱But otherwise the break was pretty darn necessary because I'm ready to get back into the gym today 👌💪
.
.
Some tips to get back on track after a few days like this
👉 Get back to normal eating habits,as soon as possible (I go straight back to it but if you find that hard start with a good breakfast and dinner and work your way to normality)
👉 Get water into you. In this weather 3-4L
👉 Get moving - yesterday I got about 10km walked. Today I'm back in the gym
.
.
I know some people won't think this is #fitfam, others will appreciate normality either way I'm just being honest 😁👆👆 #honestyisthebestpolicy #bereal #connachtchamps #doesnthappentoooften #stillnotright #worthit #balancedlifestyle #balance #fitness #fitliving #fitchick #fitlifestyle

caption: Since I started following a Pescatarian diet I have Tuna every single day 🐟🐟 It may be as a snack or in a salad. This week I put it in an egg bake for breakfast🍳🍳 Protein is an essential part of all diets no matter your goals 💪👌But I especially need it this week for recovery in the run up to our Connacht Final 💙💛 Thanks @johnwestire for hitting me up 🙋‍♀️😁 #NaturalProteinPitstop #GetTheBestOutOfJohnWest

Health versus Calorie Control explained 🙄

This is a big topic for me. As a nutritionist, health is priority. Whatever nourishes your body will be what I advise. Food is fuel ⛽

Counting calories is constantly thrown all over my news feed. Flexible dieting and IIFYM. The list goes on.... 😑😑😑 1. So firstly, yes a calorie is a calorie. But the problem with some of these posts is, people see calorie for calorie comparisons, substitute foods based on these calorie comparisons but don't understand anything about their own caloric intake. I've seen doughnuts compared to wholefood bars, Alcohol compared to smoothies etc. People see 'fitness people' eating these foods so eat them themselves, uneducated to the fact that they may be in a calorie surplus while the said educator was probably eating this in a calorie deficit. Understand it is overall calories that count and each individual is different. Calorie intake is based on weight, height, age, gender, activity level, etc.
.
. 
2. While a calorie is a calorie. Micros count!!!!!! Eating a Mc Donald's every morning may 'Fit your macros' but my god are you missing out on the fibre, magnesium, Iron, Zinc, and B Group Vitamins that a big bowl of oats provide 🥣🥣🥣
.
. 
3. Gastrointestinal discomfort. I have a sensitive stomach so this MAY be just me but my God do I feel like crap after a takeaway/chocolate binge. Its fine every once in awhile but consistently is just hard 😱 Even if the calories were the same, I'd take my fish and greens any day🙋‍♀️
.
. 
4. From my experience and experience with other athletes, wholefoods improve performance. If you asked me to go play a game tomorrow under 2 different conditions 1. 2000 Cals of wholefoods, lots of complex carbs, healthy fats, protein and water versus 2. 2000 Cals of Chips, pizza and diet coke. I can tell you now which one I'd feel better on 🤪🤪🤪
.
.
So yes, a calorie is a calorie and calorie wise there is no difference between water and diet coke. And with regards Aspartame do your research. Again, it all comes back to goals. I certainly wouldn't be able to fuel my body with crap and perform well, another may be able but at least be educated next time 🤟

caption:
'Elephants never forget' 🐘🐘🐘 To all the people out there spending Father's Day with their Dad's, spoil them 💜 To those who have lost theirs but are lucky enough to have made memories, treasure them 💜

#happyfathersday #thebestmemories #daddysgirl

But #balance 😋😋😋 I use this hash tag a lot and I'm a true believer in it. But it is all very relative. People throw it around A LOT and the problem is it ends up becoming an imbalance 🙈

Remember to never lose sight of your goals 👆They are key. They are drivers. 👆If your goal is weight loss and you are 'treating' yo self after every good thing you do, chances are you may be 'balanced' but only on the scales because you have cancelled out any deficit you were previously in 😫 But its not all about weight loss. I consider balance being able to go out with friends on social occasions for a meal or a few drinks. But I would not be able to do this every weekend with my lifestyle 🙄😴 That to me would be an imbalance ❌❌❌ I am not saying its all about deprivation. Far from it 🤟 Treating yourself is NECESSARY. But is it really a treat when it's happening regularly. I'm all for the YOLO but binge drinking every weekend and expecting fat loss is difficult (not impossible but really f*cking hard🤪) Whatever you do, take ownership for it 👊Goals are not easy to achieve but it depends on the effort you put in too. Minimal effort = Minimal results 😱

#balancedlifestyle #copon #besensible #goals #fitlifestyle #fitliving #fitlife #fitchick #fitgirls #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Way to my heart... FOOD 😍😍😍 A client brought this humongous box of strawberries into me Saturday and I'm still not finished 🤣🤩 So what's so good about strawberries? 🍓Well apart from the fact that they taste amazing, kick that sweet tooth (that I suffer from badly)
👉 Strawberries are an excellent source of Vitamin C (even higher than oranges), Vitamin K and Folate
👉 They are high in fibre
👉 Jam packed full of antioxidants
👉 100g of Strawberries = 30KCal (so they are great for dieters)
👉 They are so versatile. I have them in Greek yogurt, with salad or as a snack 🤩

Tag a 🍓 Lover

caption:
Advanced Core Workout 🐾🐾🐾 I'm not a big fan of isolation core work, I get bored very easy 🙈🙈🙈 But a strong core is key to all elements of fitness especially when lifting weights or pitch stability ✌️ I try to do a little core activation before resistance training so this is usually how I train my core but recently I've tried to do a little isolation work and it's helped improve other elements of my fitness especially my strength 💪

I wouldn't recommend these exercises to beginners as you need quite a lot of upper body strength and need to understand how to use your core. If you are a beginner, I recommend planks (all forms) and other exercises directed by a trainer 🙌 Remember if you are really serious about fitness, always speak to someone qualified in the area before starting 😁 Let me know if you try any of them 😁

#corestrength #corestability #strongirls #strength #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitgirls #thunderthighs #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
March vs June 🧟‍♀️🧟‍♀️🧟‍♀️ The first 2 pics are me at my leanest all year, just before my hols in Merica 🇺🇸 The second 2 are today after a bank holiday 🐷🍟🍫🥂 Let's be honest as much I can knit pick, there really isnt a MASSIVE difference 😂😂😜 Sometimes I go through periods of not drinking for months (pic 1). I eat really really well and train 5-6 times a week (pic 1). There is a time and place for this in my life. But it's not the only part of my life 👆

Fast forward to pic 2. I'm just home from a weekend of 🥂 and 🍫. I've been carrying injuries so I haven't been as consistent with training but I still eat really well 👆

Life is not about being ripped 24/7. Life is about memories. Life is about experiences. Life is about spending time with loved ones. Life is not about guilt over a pizza slice or running miles to burn off a glass of wine.

That is not to say that I YOLO every weekend 😂🙈 I am back into a period of drinking bans and serious training😆😋 But just don't get sucked into thinking that being lean is the best thing in the world. Being lean and having a life don't go hand in hand 🤫🤫🤫 Life is for living 😁😁😁 #balance #balancedlifestyle #fitlife #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitchick #fitgirl #fitfam #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #irishfitfam

caption:
Pet Peave alert ⚠️⚠️⚠️
.
.
.
The odd person gives me the 'you don't know what it's like, you've never been overweight' OR 'sure you've always been fit, you wouldn't understand'. There are so many points I can make to this comment 😡😡😡
.
.
.
1. I may not have ever been over weight because health and fitness have always been a huge part of my life so no weight is something I never struggled with. And the reason I am fit is because I work for it. Not because I am NATURALLY fit. Not because fitness comes easy to me but because I push myself, every day 👊👊👊
.
.
.
2. Body Confidence is a whole different kettle of fish and this is something I can relate to. Being a certain clothes size or having a low body fat % does NOT equate to being happy. I have been 8 stone, a size 6 and seriously unhappy. Like most women I struggled with self image. I would not leave the house without make up. If I ever had to buy clothes in more than an 8 I considered myself fat 🙊😩😭 Do not think just because someone is slim that they are happy or confident because the 2 just do not go hand in hand 🙄🙄. .
.
.
3. And no I've never had to lose weight but dya know what I did have to gain weight. 2 stone to be precise. Mostly muscle, a little fat. Not everyone's journey is the same. Sometimes it's just as important to gain weight as it is to lose it. But truth be told I am the happiest I have ever been with my body 😍 I fuel it well. I eat LOADS, mostly nutritious wholefoods, the odd time junk food 🤗 I train hard, I am strong, I am fit and I am fast. I don't wear make up every day but I feel a million dollars when I do. I have crazy wild curls that I have finally learned to love. I have days that I think I'm fat, days I think I'm too muscly (it's called being a woman 😂) but all in all I'm happy 💖

Next time you think about saying something to someone think about what you are saying. Is it beneficial to the person? Is it a nice thing to say? Is it necessary?

Remember, if you have nothing nice to say. Don't say it at all 😑

#happybody #happymind #bodyconfidence #confidence #itsnicetobenice #fitliving #fitlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitgirls #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam
