caption:
2 and half years ago (crazy to think how fast time has went,😩) my life changed. I'm not the only one to experience it and unfortunately I won't be the last. The last 2 weeks have been hard. No particular reason, just missing an important person in your life is enough 😔

I think maybe because I've really started to look after myself, relax myself and do well for myself I'm even more sad because he can't experience that with me. But last week I found 2 white feathers. I'm not hugely superstitious but I truly believe it was his little way of communicating when I was down❤️❤️❤️ There is no right or wrong way to grieve. Your life has changed and will forever. But you can be sure as hell they are looking down on you smiling 💓

#daddysgirl #missingyou

Top tips for eating on the go 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️ Most days I'm gone from 5-22 so I understand how important it is to have good options on the go. I tend to bring all my food with me but sometimes I need to buy out 🙊

1. The best you will be prepared is when you make the food yourself. Knowing exactly what is going into your food. This is key but more often than not we end up having to buy out. Thankfully there are so many healthy options these days 😍👌 2. Structure your meal around protein. If it is from a salad counter pick a good quality meat/fish, tins of tuna are great, these tuna packs from @johnwestire taste AWESOME 😍 You may find a protein shake handy or even some Greek yogurt
Protein rich foods keep us fuller for longer and have a higher thermic effect from food. No matter what your goals are having a diet high in protein will be beneficial regardless 👌

3. Try not to go for seriously long periods without food as we tend to get over hungry and pick the worst options I. É takeaways and junk food

4. Be careful of certain 'health foods' as their sugar content is often through the roof 🙈 Choose snacks like nuts, seeds, yogurt, fruit and veggies 🙋‍♀️ There are now so many healthy convenience foods that there is really never any excuse to eat badly on the go 👌👌👌 #healthylifestyle #healthyeatingonthego #balancedlifestyle #healthyliving #fitliving #fitlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitgirl #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Missed my Dad big time this weekend.  Reason being before he died he told me to relax a little, stop being so busy and find a little me time. It made me emotional to think how much I've changed in the 2 and a half years he has been gone💔

While I can't say I'll ever be the person to relax 100% I'm certainly not the stressed out Sheila I used to be 🙈 I have learned to enjoy my time off. I have seen more places and made more memories in the last 2 and a half years than I have in my entire life (no joke) 😲😲😲 I have ticked bucket list adventures off. I have spent time with friends and family ❤️ And it's only May yet 😉😁🌞 Still lots more to come.

I've also changed my mindset. I used to want to be a certain body fat. Or hit a certain amount of pull ups. Chasing abs. My ideals have changed so much.
My mindset now: I have fat but not that much. I can do a pull up, go mé. I may not have a 6 pack but dya know what I've good legs. Confidence (not Cockiness) is the most amazing trait. Embrace it 💓

#fitliving #fitlife #fitlifestyle #donttakeadayforgranted #happiness #lifeisshort #liveit #liveyourbestlife #liveyourlife

Morning all 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️ Can't sleep due to excitement of Ed Sheeran today coupled with meeting my friends for a few bevvys and some lunch 🍸🍜🥑 So I decided a little education on this beautiful Saturday morning would go a long way 😁😍 Above are 3 different types of pasta and their nutritional composition. I reckon sometimes we see the 'healthier' option and over consume it. Remember, we can over consume 'healthier' foods too 🙈 And what would make it 'healthier'. Let's be honest, all the above products are processed. All the above products have carbohydrates, fats and protein in them?? Let's be clear on one thing. When buying foods, you need to take your goals into consideration. My goals will be a hell of a lot different to someone looking to lose weight so why would I eat the same foods? 🙄

Anyway long story short. These 3 products are not all that different. Per 100g their calories are pretty similar, their protein content virtually identical and carbohydrate content is similar. The main difference being fibre content of products.

I've heard people pick the 'Buckwheat pasta' because it's healthy. The same people will smother that 'healthy' pasta with cream and bacon 😩😩😳😳 P. S be more cautious of the sauces you are having with the pasta 😂😉 #healthylifestyle #healthyalternative #whichisbetter #dependsonyourgoals #healthyliving #fitliving #fitchick #balancedlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

Thursday thoughts 🤔🤔🤔 We are all so lucky. Just by being alive we are lucky. Having a roof over our heads. Being able to buy food. Being able to move.

Complaining about not being able to afford a designer bag, fancy holiday or new car are not important 👎 Having abs is not important and quite frankly is not worth it in my opinion. A size in clothes or a specific weight are absolutely irrelevant if you are healthy and happy. 
For me, carrying a few knocks has meant I have to rest ALOT 😭 I understand it is only temporary and I am lucky to be even able to exercise regularly. It makes me question why those who can chose not to 😭 Anyway that's my view on it. Everyone else's is different. 😑🤗 Just remember what is important in life. And more specifically what is important to you 🙋‍♀️ It's my Friday 🎊🎊🎊 #luckytobealive #behappy #begrateful #fitliving #happiness #happybody #happymind #fitlifestyle #healthylifestyle #healthyliving #fitfam #irishfitfam

Mushroom Stroganoff 🍄🍄🍄 I try to get more protein into my meals than just veg alone but this was a nice change. Beware, this does taste like a healthier version but it hit the spot 😁👌 Ingredients:
500g Chestnut mushrooms
250ml Greek Style Yogurt.
1 Onion
3 cloves Garlic
Tsp. Mustard
Tbsp. Paprika
Tsp. Olive oil

Fry garlic and onion in olive oil. Add mushrooms and fry until slightly brown. Add all other ingredients and allow to cook for a further 15-20mins. Serve up with some basmati rice and voila 😍

What is health??? Some will say a 'normal' BMI, others will say a good diet, exercise daily, don't smoke, no alcohol, being free from disease.

Others get more in depth. You need to see visible abs in order to be a healthy weight. Or you need to train until you feel like collapsing. High cárb/low fat or low cárb/high fat. Green tea. Green shakes. Kale. Chia seeds. More weights. More cardio.

My idea of health:
👉 THAT EAR TO EAR SMILE 😍😍😍
👉 Seeing my sister for the first time in 18 months and being ABLE to go to visit her and take the holiday of a lifetime because I am fit and able
👉 Having a beer in my hand because dya know what? I was on holidays and I bloody well deserved a beer
👉 Being happy and confident in my body. Not worrying that my bottoms were too small and I had rolls
👉 ENJOYING my life. Nourishing my body but eating out if I want it. Exercising because I love it and appreciate how lucky I am to be able ❤️ Everyone's idea of health is different. Health to me is not:
❌ Starving yourself to achieve the perfect body. Nobody is perfect. Embrace your flaws.
❌ Exercising as punishment
❌ Missing out on life
❌ Running down people's lifestyle choices. If you want to go out every weekend, your choice. If you don't want to drink or smoke, also your choice.

Happy Friday peeps❤️❤️❤️ #throwback #happiness #smiles #happy #dowhatmakesyouhappy #healthylifestyle #health #healthyliving #fitliving #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitgirls #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

Who needs aesthetics when you can have strength? 💪💪💪 No but for real though. Understand your goals. Know why you want them. How hard/easy it is to achieve them? Give yourself TIME to achieve them. And the most important part... Enjoy the process 😍😍😍 We are so lucky that we are ABLE to exercise. We should not view it as a punishment but more of a celebration of what our bodies CAN do ❤️ I had to take a lot more rest recently due to little niggles (old age will do that to you 😂). And although I needed it, I hate rest as I miss it so much 😭 But my lack of rest is what got me into that position in the first place 🙈🤐🙄 Vicious cycle😂 Long story short, treat your body well, exercise but don't over do it, nourish your body and keep your eyes on the prize 🙌🙌🙌 #strongirls #healthylifestyle #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitliving #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitgirls #fitfam #irishfitfam

I have been carrying a good few niggles recently. My opinion being down to lack of rest, sleep and maybe even lack of consisency (out some weekends, weekends being a free for all). It's been seriously bugging me so I've been trying to iron out my faults 🙌 I only trained 3 times last week and I have been feeding my body very well 🤩😍 Last night, rather than a chocolate binge I munched on these 😀

Energy bars (makes 9)
👉 2 and half cups oats
👉 1/3 cup desiccated coconut
👉 1/3 cup ground almonds
👉 2 Tbsp chia seeds
👉 5 Tbsp maple syrup
👉 2 Tbsp coconut oil melted
👉 3 Tbsp. Peanut butter
👉 3 squares dark chocolate melted

To make:
All dry ingredients in a large bowl. Mix with melted oil, peanut butter and maple syrup. Top with melted dark chocolate and refrigerate ❤️ Plus I didn't wake up with a sugar hangover this morning 🤗 Have an amazing Bank Holiday everyone 🙌❤️ #healthyliving #healthylifestyle

caption:
Morning guys 🤗

So here are some of the snacks I've had this week 😁 I just want to explain to you the difference between healthy foods and calorie control 👌

This is all very goal dependent but you CAN over consume healthy foods. Healthy foods contain calories too and if your calories in are higher than your calories out even though you are eating super healthy you can still gain weight 😬🙄 This picture is 2 different snacks I ate during the week. Both were scrumptious 🤩😍 But the 'healthier' option was double the calories of the alternative. Am I saying don't eat the raw bar? No, absolutely not but be mindful that just because its healthier doesn't mean its lower in calories. My goal is weight maintenance and health. So a little of the healthy stuff is perfect for me with a little fibre one bar here and there because.... Balance 👌❤️ Tag a friend 👌🙌 #healthylifestyle #health #healthyliving #balance #balancedlifestyle #beeducated #fitlife #fitliving #fitfam #fitgirls #irishfitfam

Weight loss or weight maintenance is relatively simple. Overall weekly calories in are less than calories out. 🤗😄 It is that simple. Unfortunately people like to overcomplicate situations 🙄🤐 So Monday to Friday you have cut out bread, dairy, refined sugars, processed foods. The worst thing to touch your lips is a protein bar or piece of fruit. Then the weekend comes and you're out on the lash, takeaway the following day washed down with a coke. Sound familiar?

Guys, you are kidding yourselves 😵😵I am not saying you can never go out or have takeaways but weekends count. They are not a free for all. They account for almost 30% of your week 🙈 
Stop over analysing it.
👉 Eat well Monday - Sunday
👉 Enjoy your treats but keep goals in mind
👉 Move daily
👉 Alcohol in moderation
👉 Drink at least 2 litres of water a day

It's not easy but it is simple. Find what suits you 😄

#weekendscount #healthyliving #healthylifestyle #fitliving #fitlifestyle #makeachange #fitlife #fitgirls #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

My motto... ALWAYS🙋‍♀️ I've never been a materialistic sort of person, it was just never something I cared/care for. I'd rather have more memories than items. But stop trying to be something you're no and especially not to please others 🙄👊 #material #nonmaterial #happiness #smiles #dowhatmakesyouhappy #healthyliving #fitliving #liveyourlife #liveyourbestlife #loveyourlife #makingmemories

Thinking of my Dad today and how his life was taken way to early. He was taken at 50 and still didn't get to do everything he wanted to do.

Life is too short. Smile😁Laugh😂 Forgive 🙋‍♀️ Make friends, not enemies. Do what makes you happy 🏐🍸👭👫 Spend time with people who make you happy ❤️ Take adventures ✈️ Make memories 📸

Before my Dad passed my life was eat, sleep, play football, stress out, repeat. Since his death, I've adapted a much more fun and selfish outlook on life that I needed 😍

Sunday thoughts 💭💭💭 As a week finishes and we start another week, think about how much you actually do for yourself. Not others but for yourself. We are constantly trying to please other people. At work we try to please bosses and colleagues. At home we keep a house going, mothers looking after their children, putting our partners happiness ahead of our own. The list goes on....😼😼😼 This week take time out for yourself. It is not selfish, it is necessary. It might be something small like sitting down with a cup of coffee for 10mins or it could be booking the trip of a lifetime. Whatever it is,do it for you💆‍♀️👆You are your own most important asset and you need to prioritise yourself sometimes 😍🤗 Happy Sunday xxx

caption:
👉How to improve pull ups

Firstly, understand pull ups/chin ups are hard. It is not a case of 'Oh I started going to the gym I should now be able to do a pull up' ❌❌❌ I am sharing a few tips that have helped me through the years. And notice that word 'years' because that is how long it took me 😱🙈 👉You need a strong back. Back and biceps are the primary muscles used in this exercise. A strong back is built through exercises like Deadlifts, Rack Pulls, Rows, Pull Downs etc. And go heavy (with correct form and technique of course). 👉 Your body weight and body fat will have an impact. The heavier you are, the heavier you have to lift. The more excess body fat you have, the harder you are to lift. But this does not mean the lighter you are the easier you are to lift. I was once 8 and half stone and could barely bend my elbows left alone pull myself up 😅😅😅You need to have a balance of both. Low body fat and strength 👌 👉Slow eccentrics - jump to the top of the bar and slowly lower yourself down. And repeat. Often. 👉 Ever heard practice makes perfect 👌It definitely applies here. Practice often. You want to get better at something? Once a week is not enough!!!! Happy to hear other tips if anyone wants to let us know how they improved? ❤️ #chinups #Rackpulls #strongback #strongirls #strongwomen #strong #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitgirl #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Lacking consistency = Lacking results 👊

Like it or not, it's the truth 🙈 Are you the type to work seriously hard for a week only to have a few drinks at the weekend which leads you to missing your Monday workout? Or maybe it's a month of hard work and expecting to see instant results!? Sound familiar 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️ If that's the way you want to live your life, setting yourself up for disappointment that's fine. But stop blaming everything else and start looking at the real reason you are not getting results ☝️☝️☝️ My own personal example. On holidays I drank A lot, ate totally off course and exercised once every 2/3 days. Lack of consistency lead to a very bloated, swelled Amanda. I came home, Ate really well, trained every day and then Easter weekend came = chocolate and gin. Result: Same bloated Amanda🐡🐡🐡 Finally the last 2 weeks I have been CONSISTENT. NO ALCOHOL. Back to training 5-6 times a week. Eating well and I eventually feel kinda back to normal 🙋‍♀️😍 Don't expect to see results for a half hearted effort. It just does not work that way 👎 ~ You have to make a change to see a change ~

caption:
I'm back 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️ This week I am trying to beat the holiday and bank holiday bloat 🐡🐡🐡 I'm sure I'm not the only one that over indulged but if you're like me you probably felt absolutely CRAP afterwards 🙈🙊So this week is beat the bloat week for me 👊👊 How am I trying to reduce the swell?
👉Drink 3-4L water daily
👉 Combo of field training and weights (just get moving daily)
👉 This week I've decided to take meat from my diet

Let me elaborate. I am not a plant based enthusiast and I am not a meat hater. I don't believe in extremism and this is my opinion so please for those of you who feel the need to go to town on this post, don't. I am simply voicing my opinion and giving my reasons. I don't believe meat causes cancer. Cancer is multi factorial and it is very easy to blame cancer on 1 thing. What about air pollution? What about the tap water we drink? Daily stresses in people's lives? Financial worries? Genetics? Similarly, I don't believe in veganism. I believe if you HAVE TO supplement a diet, it is not substantial. Again, OPINION!!! Why have I decided meat free this week?

1. Meat is hard tó digest. It requires a lot of work by enzymes and makes our gut work harder. My poor gut has had a tough time of it recently so I'm trying to give it a break ❤️
2. Due to mass production, the quality of all food has gone to 💩 (not just meat, plant based foods too,) Unfortunately, meat has been hit one of the worst. So for me, it is absolutely no harm taking a break from that.
3. I can increase micros. Although I don't believe in pure plant based, it is so important to get a good daily dose of fruits and veggies
4. Fish is an excellent source of protein, I feel satisfied and I don't feel I have taken anything away from my diet nutritionally🤗🤗🤗 Anybody else out there try something like this or is pescatarian? Would love your feedback 😍😍😍 #tryingoutsomethingnew #letsseewhathappens #pescatarian #health #healthyliving #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitgirls #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Real Talk 🤪🤪🤪 I have been really struggling to beat the bloat this week after holidays. I am back to regular eating habits, drinking at least 3 litres of water and today has been my first rest day. Yet, I feel sluggish and lethargic and it was really getting me down until today.

Today, I read a blog post from a young girl who was taken way before her time. The post really resignated with me. Here I am complaining that I can't see my abs anymore while others out there are dying. Life is way too short to be knit picking over silly little things. I know first hand how fast a life can be taken away and moaning about tiny insignificant details is absolutely absurd ❌❌❌❌ So I am going to make the most of my weekend❤️ I am catching up with friends, playing a match, enjoying a night out or 2😉 and coaching at my first ever championship game with the u14 team I am involved with. I will eat like normal with  a little Easter egg here and there😉 And I'll stop worrying about the silly stupid irrelevant things 🤗

I'm sure I'm not the only fool out there worrying over the silly stuff. Enjoy your weekend❤️❤️
P.s normality will resume next week. And I still have a video for you🤗

#vegas #throwback #twoweeksago #ohhowtimechanges #cold #needsun #needvitamind #willgobacktofitnessassoonaigetfitagain #lazybumbum #fitgirl #fitchick #fitfam

So accurate
😂😂😂😂 And not 2 f*#ks given. I'm 1/3 alcohol, 1/3 sugar and 1/3 water., cause ya know... Balance 😂 Pictures or words cannot describe the incredible holiday I've had. It was a mental and physical rest from everything in life and it was just amazing 😍Seeing my sister again was the icing on the 🎂but we literally should not be allowed let out together 😂🙈 Normality resumed yesterday when I returned to a training game after 36 hours of no sleep and just a couple of hours off the plane 🤣 I also weaned my way back into healthy eating and enjoyed a 15 hour sleep last night😴

I've said this before and I'll say it again. To me a holiday = a break from normality. Therefore I go all out I eat, I drink and I enjoy myself. I trained 5 times while away as I enjoy training but it was a huge difference to my 5 days a week. BUT not everyone is the same, some people take a total break, some eat really well and don't drink. DO WHAT WORKS FOR YOU!!!! Don't feel guilty because people you follow train while they are away. Don't eat salad if you WANT fries. And if you want the mojiito have it🍸But whatever you do, own it. Don't go feeling guilty about it. Don't give out if you gain weight or retain water. Don't go hiding away. Embrace it nd enjoy it 🧜‍♀️ P. S I have some new body art to show you once my swelling goes down and I look like a normal human again 🤣🤣🤣

caption:
I promised a workout and I will show it but it's very important to understand the necessity of a warm up before exercise 👌
.
.
You want to
👉 Mobilise joints
👉 Activate muscle groups
👉 Improve elasticity/flexibility
.
.
Your warm up should mimic your workout, using muscle groups you will be training. Today I trained fullbody so this was just a snippet of my warm up and it hit various muscle groups.
.
.
Warm up inclued:
👉 Inchworms with push up
👉 OH Squat
👉 Lunges
👉 Glute Bridges (Single and double leg)
👉 Deadbugs
👉 Bear Crawl (Forward and Reverse)
👉 Lateral Crawl

#fitliving
#fitnessislife 
#fitlifestyle 
#mobility 
#flexibility 
#warmup

caption:
Morning Guys 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️ So today I could stomach a little bit of food so what better way to wean my way back to food than some comfort food 💖

I got a lot of messages about my scones so I'll put up the recipe here. Very simple foods I always have lying around 👌

P.s I'm terrible with weighing ingredients out so this is in or around weights 👊

Ingredients -makes 4
👉 Cup and half of oats
👉 300g O% Greek yogurt/Natural yogurt
👉 Tbsp. Baking powder
👉 Seeds of your choice

Cook at 180 degrees for 20-30mins 👌

#healthyliving #comfortfood #healthyeating #healthylifestyle #fitliving #eatforhealth #fitlife #snowdays #baking #fitfam #irishfitfam

This can work on 2 opposite spectrums.

We have A. The group of quitters who as soon as they don't see results they quit. Or they eat something bad, so might aswell eat bad for the rest of the day. Or missed a training session so therefore quit on the rest of the week 🙈 Sound like you??
.
.
.
Or we have B. Those who take it to an extreme level. Give all for the first few weeks, hit a plateau with energy or don't hit a target weight and quit. .
.
.
And then we have me. Who will never ever learn that there is such a thing as too much 😣🙈 Sick on a snow day is CRAP!!!! 🤢🤢🤢 Enjoy the rest of you and be safe 💖

#learntorest #recovery #restisimportanttoo #restiskey #neverlearn #fitlifestyle #fitliving #fitchick #fitfam

caption:
So let's get one thing straight there's nothing 'lucky' to weight loss or a lean physique. ❌People don't lose 2 stone by chance.
❌People don't have visible abs through a poor lifestyle (apart from the minute few genetically gifted people)
.
.
Weight loss is hard. Weight maintenance is even harder.
⚠️ It requires discipline ⚠️ It requires HARD WORK
⚠️ It is NOT EASY - if it's easy you're A. Not doing it right or B. Not going to achieve your goals
⚠️ It takes time
⚠️ Patience is ESSENTIAL
⚠️ You need certain qualities ⚠️ You need to understand the harsh truth. ⚠️ You need to stop making excuses
.
.
If and when you give up on your excuses, you will start seeing results 🤘 And guess what you might even enjoy it👊👊👊
.
.
I'm not a big fan of scale numbers but here are some numbers I consider important
👉 1st January - Last time I had a takeaway
👉 8 weeks ago - Last time I drank (bar a Baileys coffee last week 🙈)
👉 5 days a week - frequency of my training
👉 110kg - my max Deadlift
👉 24/7 - My lifestyle
.
.
I don't feel deprived (apart from the start of the week when I tried to 'diet' and failed miserably 🤣🤣🤣 I LOVE my lifestyle. I do this for me. I do this for my health. I do this for my sport. I do this for energy. .
.
I understand it's not for everybody. Not everyone cares about themselves unfortunately. But I do. You only have one body, why not get the best out of it 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️ #fitliving #fitlifestyle #goodattitude #healthyliving #healthylifestyle #fitness #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitchick #fitfam #fitgirl #irishfitfam

caption:
This will be on my gravestone the amount of times I've said this and my friends are sick of hearing it. But if it helps one young person stay in sport I would be happy 💓
.
.
When I was younger I put my hand up for everything (quote from my Dad🤣). Athletics, Badminton, Cross country,  Draughts, Egg and spoon race I'd say I could do the alphabet of what I tried 🙈 And I was absolutely CRAP at every single one of them 🙈🤣 Like really crap. And to make matters worse, my sister was a little superstar. She had an all Ireland medal at 7, she played football with the boys she was just super talented 😍 Still is 💓 
I never started on any team, I was always picked last. One time, I actually had to give my football boots to another player because she forgot hers (this other player was no superstar either, I was just that poor). The one thing I did have was a good attitude, a great one actually. I never let it get me down. I always still kept with it, probably more for the social side to be honest 😂🙈 .
.
But I kept with it. Even though I was hopeless. I kept training. Then I trained harder. Then I trained harder than everyone else. Then I became fit, fitter than a lot of people. Then, I started going to the gym and I became stronger. Stronger than most. .
.
So now, with a good attitude and a decent level of fitness. I started to make All Ireland winning schools teams, Roscommon panels, UCD O Connor panels and last year made my first ever Connaught panel 🤗😁 I still have a fear of the goals and my overhead catch is crap but I'm an athlete. What I always wanted to be. Never give up on something because of the hard work it will take to get there, the time will pass anyway 👌
.
.
Hard Work beats talent, when talent doesn't work hard 👊👊👊
.
.
P.s I'm not chickening out on my video instas I will have one very soon 😉
.
.
 #athlete #workhard #playhard #gaagirls #stayinsport #trainhard #fitliving #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitgirl

caption:
Ok this week is Amanda is mean week 🙈

I'm going to hit you with a few home truths. 🙈🙈🙈 People take it easy on themselves. People use excuses. People take short cuts. People have no patience. People reward themselves far too easily ❌❌❌ If you want a change, you need to make a change. It will take sacrifice. Sacrifice isn't easy. 👊

Scenario 1: You want to lose weight. But you're not making any sacrifices = you will get nowhere. It doesn't have to something crazy like go gluten free or vegan. Something as simple as removing your 11 o clock chocolate break daily will lead to results 😁 You NEED to make a sacrifice to reap the rewards. If you keep doing qhat you've always done, you'll keep getting what you always got 🙈The truth hurts 👊

Scenario 2: You want to get fitter, stronger, leaner. But you're just not putting in the effort. It's not easy being fit. You don't just wake up lean (unless you are one of the lucky ones or are u18). Strength doesn't grow on trees. You need to work at it. You need to consistently fight for it. 
In anything you do, unless you make a sacrifice you will not see results 🙈

My own fitness story: I worked at it. I made myself sick once from training so hard. Then I decided to nourish my body. As soon as I did that I started to see results- performance and aesthetic wise. It wasn't easy. Ever. But I'm driven and I have goals to achieve. I'm not an excuse maker. I start most of my days at 5am and finish close to 10pm but I make it work. Because my health is my driver. Health is more important to me than excuses 👊👏😁 #sacrifice #hardwork #workhard #playhard #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitchick #fuelforperformance #fuelyourself #healthyliving #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Unflexed vs Flexed .
.
Same happy head 🤗🤗🤗
.
.
I've said it before, I'll say it again the whole 'fitness' world has gone crazy with unrealistic pictures of unrealistic bodies. People flexing is not realistic, they do not walk around like that 24/7 🙈Unless they are severly dehydrated which I certainly aint...EVER!!! And don't even get me started on photoshop 😠😠😠 Poor young girls these days, trying to be something that doesn't even exsist 😣
.
.
I am super happy and confident in my body. I eat well, really well. I train hard. I look after my body. I want to encourage all women to love their bodies, warts and all. The sooner you start to love your body, the more it will love you back ❤ Stop comparing yourself to others, it Never ever ends well. And PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE STOP basing your progress on God damn abs!!!!! 🚫🚫🚫
.
.
🥑Nourish your body
💪 Resistance Train
❤ Do a little cardio for your heart and lungs
😴 Sleep well
❌ Don't compare yourself to anyone
✔ Appreciate your body

Happy Saturday 🙆‍♀️🙆‍♀️🙆‍♀️ #fuelyourbody #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #livewell #healthymind #healthybody #fitlifestyle #fitliving #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Let's talk food consumption 🥝🥑
.
.
Ok, so this is a really important post and I need you all to listen up.
.
.
In order to understand what you need to eat and why, in order to eat for your goals, in order to get optimal body composition, in order to get the best from your body performance wise, you need to stop looking up the foods people eat and invest in a nutrition plan/nutritionist/coach etc.
.
.
Why?
- Firstly, every single one of you are different. So why would you all eat the same? Everyone has different schedules. Everyone has different training plans. You are all different weights and heights so why would you all eat the same. Social media is RIDICULOUS at times comparing whole nutritious foods to fast foods just because they are the same calories. People who are not as knowledgable will see this and think 'oh it's ok then to have fast food all the time because it's the same calories' 🙈🙈🙈 NO NO NO!! It is ok to eat these foods once in awhile with a balanced diet but you cannot just say 'It fits your macros, therefore you can have it'. People pick up these nuggets of information, use them and don't see results, why? Because they didn't use them properly and over induldged in these foods. It is essential to understand how you can have these things in moderation but you will only get that through a nutritionist. - Secondly, let's be straight here. If you are a normal person training 3 times a week, looking to lose weight and body fat, your diet DOES not need to be the same as an athletes training 5-6 times a week. For so many reasons. 1. Athletes require more carbs - it is essential fuel for sport. 2. Athletes body compositions are different so their BMR is higher and they need more food. 3. Their emphasis is on performance not aesthetics and the list goes on.

Obviously, I am both a nutritionist and an athlete so this area is hugely important to me. If you have any questions on this comment below or even drop me a DM I'm happy to help 🤗

caption:
Commitment 👊👊👊 👉You have goals. 👉You want to achieve them. 🙈But are you really commited to them? 
Now I don't mean dipping in and out. Some days giving all while others you slip up. I mean 100% commitment.

I mean eat, sleep and breath what you are doing. I mean long days just to get where you want to be. I mean not seeing your partner all weekend (or evenings for that matter). I mean missing out on social events. I mean saying no!!! Until you've done the above things. You are not fully commited. You are not truely sacrificing. And if you want something you've never had, you have to do something you've never done 👊

And there is no worse pain than doing everything you can possibly do, and still not come out on top. But that's just life. Nothing is linear. The road to success is hard, it's long and it's God damn bumpy. Sit back and enjoy the ride 👊

#football #youwinsomeyoulosemore #positivity #commitment #sacrifice #gaagirls

Training ✔
Nutrition ✔
Recovery ✔
Sleep ✔

Remember, training is important but it is only a TINY fraction of your time. While it's important to give it all while you're there the mjority of our time is spent recovering. Recovering includes nutrition and sleep 😪🥑🥝 It also includes foam rolling and for me Ice baths. It's all dependent on your goals, your training frequency and the intensity of your training. @komplexfitness wrote a great post on recovery. Check it out 🙆‍♀️ #recovery #icebaths #gaagirl #cryospas #fitlifestyle #fitliving #fitchick #trainhard #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
If you want to see a change you need to make a change 👊👊👊 In everything you do. Stop waiting around, hoping it will just happen.
👉 If you are not fit enough, you need to train harder
👉 If you have weight to lose and cannot seem to lose it, you need to change something. If you need help, ask someone qualified
👉 If you are not happy in your job, look for a new one
👉 If your relationship has more downs than ups, there are plenty more fish in the sea
👉 For me a big thing was learning to rest and relax more. My body is giving me a massive hug for reducing the stress load on it 💓

No matter what it is in life, the only way you will see that change is by making a change. 
This time last year I switched jobs which was the best decision I've ever made 😍 Since then, I've had to make some tough decisions but at the end of the day, if something is not working for you, you need to change it, no matter how hard it can be 💓

caption:
Heart Rate and Resting Heart Rate

I put up a poll about this and a lot of you wrote to me so I said I'd try explain a little more.

Heart Rate is the speed of the heartbeat measured by the number of contractions of the heart per minute. This can vary according to the body's physical needs including absorbing oxygen and excreting carbon dioxide. A great example is comparing at rest to during physical activity, the demand for oxygen is much higher during exercise than at rest.

Resting heart rate can be affected by exercise, sleep, illness, stress, anxiety and the use of drugs. Normal ranges of RHR are 50-90BPM. Normally, the more cardiovascularly fit you are the lower your RHR. It may be below 60. The lowest ever was achieved by Daniel Green in 2014 with a reading of 26BPM.

Specific heart rate zones are required for specific goals with regard exercise i.e fat burning, cardio and peak.  Your max HR is 220- Age.

I now use this as one of my goals. As I said before my goals are no longer aesthetic based but performance. One of my goals was to get my RHR below 50 ✔

caption:
The million dollar question I seem to be getting asked ALOT recently 🙈🙈🙈 👉Should women or kids be lifting weights?
There is a lot of crap out there on this topic. A lot of myths and some made up crap. You really would be suprised the amount of people I deal with on a daily basis who believe women 'should not be lifting weights' and 'lifting weights stunts your growth'. 👉 I'll deal with these 2 seperately. Kids/Teenagers can do resistance exercise. Bodyweight exercise is vitally important for gaining muscle mass, reducing body fat, mobility, bone strengthening. If you can successfully excute all bodyweight exercises, you're onto a winner. 👉 Is there an age you can start lifting weights? The research suggests that youths can lift weights as long as the reps are high and the weight is light. 👉 Resistance exercise is of VITAL importance to all ages and all genders. It can be in the form of bodyweight or weights but it is necessary for increasing fat free mass. The problem with anyone lifting weights is due to lack of information and incorrect technique. It WILL NOT make you masculine and if anything it emphasises your feminine features 🍑🍑🍑 But get proper knowledge from a trainer. If you care enough about it, invest in it 😍

Tag a skeptic 👌

#healthandfitnessisnotafad #healthybodyhealthymind #resistance #training #girlswhosquat #girlswholift #stronggirls #fitchick #fitgirl #fitfam #irishfitfam

Following my insta story of 5 things you didn't know, so many people have been questioning my 'I lived on mashed potato until I was 16'. So this is 100% true. I may have thrown in a few chicken nuggets and chips as a treat and a bowl of cornflakes here and there but as dinners go it was fairly simple. 💕So how did I become a nutritionist if I was so picky?
🤣🤣🤣 Great question. It was only about 3 years ago that I quit all my bad habits and started eating really well 🤣🤣🤣 💕 So what changed? I GREW UP!!!! I can accept a parent concerned about their child who doesn't eat any vegetables and who loves their chocolate and I CAN RELATE🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️ But as for a grown adult who is saying no to all foods, I'm sorry no sympathy. 🙈 Guys, it is habit. One that you have to cop on and break. It is down to you. No one can force you, no one can shove healthy foods down your throat. If you want it enough you will do it, if you don't you'll make excuses 🚫🚫🚫 💕 I used to be constantly sick and run down when I ate badly. I had every infection under the sun. Now the only way I get a sniffle is if I'm overdoing it. My lifestyle is hectic, my days are long and the only way I get through them is because I fuel my body so well 🤗

I know some of this is harsh but it's the reality of it, your health is priority. If you want to change it, you have to make a change 👊👊👊 #healthylifestyle #healthyeating #fitliving #eatforhealth
#eatforperformance #fuel #fuelyourbody #fitchick #fitgirl #fitfam #irishfitfam

At the end of the day, all weight gain, weight maintenance, weight loss comes down to this single concept.

Annoyingly, you can gain weight from eating too much healthy foods if the calories are high enough and similarly you can lose weight from eating crap if the calories are low enough 😣

But are all calories created equal?
👉 This is opinion, not fact.
👉 Whether you hit your macros, nail your calories or not, daily takeaways are not healthy in my eyes. Sure you may look good on the outside but the discomfort of digesting that food is not healthy and not good for you inside.
👉 People become so OBSESSED with how they look on the outside they totally forget, it's whats on the inside that counts. No point having a sparkly, shiny car and the engine about to blow up. Our bodies are the same.
👉 That being said. No one is saying you can never ever have treat foods. Approach food with the 80/20 rule and you are really onto a winner 👌🙋‍♀️ Tag a friend 😁

caption:
Morning all 🤗

So I'm going to try to increase my food posts as best as I can and my main aim is to educate you all on a healthier lifestyle 🤞👌 So I've said before that I don't count calories, never have probably never will 🙈 I don't count macros because I have a fair idea what is in food, what I need more of and what I can do better on. I'm not shredded but instead am a healthy weight and most importantly I'm healthy inside and out 👌👊 Remember health is not always about aesthetics 👎👎👎 But I do have a brain and I use it wisely 😋😆 Some of you will hate this, some of you will see the benefit. So I went to the cinema last night, and instead of getting cinema pop corn I opted for a lower calorie option. Propercorn is a fantastic substitute for cinema popcorn if weight loss is a goal. It comes in at just 88Cals compared to our 'SMALL' cinema popcorn at 200-300 Cals (and who ever buys small). I also brought water instead of a fizzy drink. 
Some of you will think for the love of God this is extreme. Others will understand. I don't always opt for the healthy option. I was the first one at Christmas head first in Celebrations but if you want to maintain a healthy lifestyle you need to make changes. Eating crap makes me feel like crap and so in turn I try not to do it. I try to find healthier alternatives that make me feel better but without restricting myself 🤗

Sunday vibes 👌

T minus 9 weeks until my hols. What approach am I taking to be bikini ready?
.
.
.
👉 Same thing I do day in, day out. Eat well. Move often. Sleep. Hydrate 🤗
.
.
.
There's no secret. It takes time. It takes patience. .
.
.
I've been training consistently for 4 years. I've over trained. I've tried low carb, no carb, gluten free, refined sugar free. I've made mistakes and learned from them. .
.
.
Find what is sustainable. Find exercise you enjoy. And be patient. It won't happen overnight, it may take a year or more. But when you are comfortable and confident year round, you know you have struck gold🎖Your body is your most important asset.
